(72, 'Captain America & The Falcon', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LspcDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marvel Comics', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LspcDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-LspcDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302484972', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-02-11', NULL, 'Collects Captain America (1968) #193-200. Captain America and the Falcon embark on a vast, desperate search for the most malignant conspirators in our history - and their insidious creation: the Madbomb! On the 200th anniversary of the United States, America will die - and only Cap and the Falcon can save it! Plus: Captain America stands alone against an army of underground killers! It\'s cataclysmic Kirby action in the mind-boggling Marvel manner!', NULL),
(73, 'Avengers', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fZrkSwE8-5wC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jason Surrell', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=fZrkSwE8-5wC&rdid=book-fZrkSwE8-5wC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178613', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Marvel Studios takes readers behind the scenes of one of the most eagerly anticipated films of all time in AVENGERS: THE ART OF MARVEL\'S THE AVENGERS. This keepsake volume is an experiential journey through the entire film from beginning to end - featuring stunning concept art; full-color photographs from the set, as well as the finished film; excerpts from the script; and exclusive interviews with the cast and crew, including writer/director Joss Whedon, producer Kevin Feige and, of course, the Avengers themselves. From costume and production design to visual effects and creature creation, AVENGERS: THE ART OF MARVEL\'S THE AVENGERS is a lavish showcase of all the artistry and creativity that brings the Marvel Cinematic Universe to life onscreen. Avengers Assemble!', 272),
(74, 'Spider-Man', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7_K1n7w6p9MC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marc Guggenheim', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=7_K1n7w6p9MC&rdid=book-7_K1n7w6p9MC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178637', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Amazing Spider-Man #584-588. Spidey\'s new world is rocked to its core! Who\'s been terrorizing people as Menace? Who\'s behind the Spider-Tracer Killings? Plus: Spidey teams up with the 44th president of the United States!', 184),
(75, 'Marvel Monograph', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jA-cDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Rhett Thomas', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=jA-cDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-jA-cDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302514624', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-08-14', NULL, 'Gaze in wonder on the art of modern masters - in the Marvel Monographs! Adi Granov\'s slick, polished work on Iron Man redefined the character for the modern era, helped set the look of the Marvel Cinematic Universe\'s first film and catapulted Granov\'s unique art style into a fan favorite! Now one of the most in-demand artists in the business, Granov\'s work has graced the covers of scores of Marvel books - including Iron Man, Spider-Man, Captain America, Black Widow, Thor, the X-Men and more! This volume presents a gorgeous gallery of many of the finest pages and covers Granov has ever drawn!', 112),
(76, 'Ms. Marvel Vol. 5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NzMKDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'G. Willow Wilson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NzMKDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-NzMKDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302488567', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-06-22', NULL, 'She\'s your new favorite. She\'s everyone\'s new favorite. And now she\'s joining the big leagues. Look out world, Kamala Khan is officially an Avenger! But will being one of Earth\'s Mightiest Heroes be everything she imagined? Or is life as a celebrity harder than she thought? But while saving the world is important, Jersey City still needs its protector too. A development company that co-opted Ms. Marvel\'s face for its project might well have more in mind for gentrification than just real estate. Can Kamala take down the evil suits destroying her home without ruining her personal life? Speaking of which, who exactly is that with Bruno? Get back on board and cling on, Kamala Korps, the ride is about to get wilder than ever! Collects Ms. Marvel #1-6.', 136),
(77, 'Spider-Man Noir', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vzsoDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marvel Comics', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=vzsoDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-vzsoDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302485979', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-04-14', NULL, 'Collects Spider-Man: Noir: Eyes Without A Face #1-4. The Goblin is gone. The Spider-Man saw to that. But then, along came the Crime Master, and now New York City\'s criminals have a new overlord - one who strikes terror in the hearts of the innocent and guilty alike. He must be stopped. And then there\'s Dr. Otto Octavius, a brilliant scientist working out of a U.S. Government lab on Ellis Island. What\'s he up to? What\'s the European connection? Robbie Robertson wanted to know. He never knew what he was getting himself into. Who is the Crime Master? What\'s going on in Octavius\' lab? Who\'s behind it all? Peter Parker has to find out, and fast. Before his friend Robbie is lost forever. Before more innocent people are killed. And before Spider-Man loses his greatest battle with the deadliest foes he\'s ever faced - enemies for whom the prize is not just control over the city, but over the world itself...', NULL),
(78, 'Amazing Spider-Man Vol. 4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9_-VDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marvel Comics', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=9_-VDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-9_-VDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302490386', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-07-21', NULL, 'Collects Amazing Spider-Man (1999) #46-50. Was the radioactive spider bite that granted Peter Parker his amazing abilities an accident...or something more? Now the mysterious Ezekiel offers him a shocking explanation: Peter may be the latest in an ancient line of humans gifted with supernatural spider powers. But Peter won\'t have much time to ponder his origins, as his existence has drawn the attention of Shathra, an otherworldly being who sees Spider-Man as her prey. Overpowered and on the run, the web-slinger has only his wits and his courage to keep him from becoming Shathra\'s next meal. The Life and Death of Spiders also features the long-awaited reunion of Mary Jane and Peter. With one last chance to be together, will this couple finally reconcile?', NULL),
(79, 'Spidey Strikes Back', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=27670pGH1RIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Todd Dezago', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '078511632X', NULL, 'Marvel Enterprises', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'A contemporary revisiting of some of Stan Lee and Steve Ditkos\'s classic Spider-Man tales, adapted for younger readers.', 96),
(80, 'Avengers Assemble Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4e2QM6QrepQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kurt Busiek', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4e2QM6QrepQC&rdid=book-4e2QM6QrepQC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170075', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2011-01-12', NULL, 'Fan-favorite creators Kurt Busiek and George PÃ©rez usher in a new era for Earth\'s Mightiest Heroes! Since the team\'s inception, the Avengers have always defended humanity against the forces of evil. When duty calls, these legendary champions answer, fighting valiantly until justice prevails. But what happens when their oldest foes strike directly at the team? On the eve of a huge Avengers gathering, an attack by the evil enchantress Morgan Le Fay sends these assembled heroes into a strange medieval reality where nothing is as it seems. Held under Le Fay\'s thrall, the Avengers have lost all memory of their true identities. Breaking free of Morgan\'s spell, Captain America and Hawkeye must fight to free their teammates before the Marvel Universe is altered forever! Plus: The Avengers take on the Squadron Supreme! Collects Avengers (1998) #1-11.', 408),
(81, 'Marvel Visionaries', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_WCgDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Martin Bursten', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=_WCgDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-_WCgDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302515621', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-09-11', NULL, 'Collects Avengers (1963) #4, Sgt. Fury #6, Fantastic Four (1961) #48-51, Captain America (1968) #200, Eternals (1976) #7, What If? (1977) #11; material from Red Raven Comics #1, Marvel Mystery Comics #13, Captain America Comics #1, Yellow Claw #3, Strange Tales (1951) #94, Amazing Adventures (1961) #1, Rawhide Kid (1955) #17, Incredible Hulk (1962) #3, Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #8, Fantastic Four Annual #5, Thor (1966) #134-136, Amazing Adventures (1970) #1-2. Celebrate the career of a true Marvel Visionary! Comicsâ€™ premier storyteller for over 40 years, Jack â€œKingâ€ Kirby brought new vitality and imagination to the medium, setting the standard for every artist to follow! This volume collects some of Kirbyâ€™s most monumental moments â€” including his earliest Marvel work, the debut of Captain America and the coming of Galactus! From the mystic fantasy of the Golden Age Vision to the Western world of the Two-Gun Kid, Kirbyâ€™s work spanned all genres and touched every corner of the Marvel Universe!', 352),
(82, 'Marvel Her-Oes', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KslnDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grace Randolph', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=KslnDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-KslnDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302506339', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-09-27', NULL, 'Collects Her-oes #1-4 And Savage She-Hulk #1. High school equals: bad cafeteria food, bullies, gym class and...people with secret super powers? As if!! Janet Van Dyne\'s no stranger to the pitfalls of teenage living, but it\'s about to get a whole lot trickier now that she has powers of her own. It\'s hard keeping a secret like that in high school, especially when it would be so easy to send some blasts in the direction of her nemesis and popular ice queen, Namora. Maybe Janet would get a break then. Too bad she\'s stuck pretending she\'s normal. Too bad she\'s in this all alone... or is she? Jenny Walters has some anger issues herself, causing her to Hulk out! Turns out the school theatre isn\'t the only place you\'ll find some drama this year!!', 208),
(83, 'Ms. Marvel By Saladin Ahmed Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=V4mmDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Saladin Ahmed', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=V4mmDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-V4mmDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302516390', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-10-16', NULL, 'Collects Magnificent Ms. Marvel (2019) #1-6. Ms. Marvel is back - and she\'s magnificent! But there\'s no such thing as business as usual in Jersey City. Aliens are wreaking havoc in Kamala\'s corner of the world, and they seem weirdly interested in Ms. Marvel...and her family! Kamala is about to face a devastating loss - but with an alien invasion ravaging her neighborhood, she won\'t have much time to grieve. Even if Kamala saves her hometown, will her life ever be the same? And what\'s all this business about a \"Chosen One\"? Eisner Award winner Saladin Ahmed (BLACK BOLT, EXILES) and rising star Minkyu Jung take the reins of one of Marvel\'s most beloved young characters for the shocking start of an all-new era! Guest-starring the Invincible Iron Man!', 136),
(84, 'Unbeatable Squirrel Girl Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EH-PDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ryan North', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=EH-PDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-EH-PDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302514044', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-06-13', NULL, 'Collects Unbeatable Squirrel Girl (2015B) #12-21. When Squirrel Girl takes Nancy to visit her parents in Canada, what could possibly go wrong? If you guessed \"nothing,\" guess again! Things get real crazy real quick, resulting in the team-up you\'ve been waiting for: Squirrel Girl and Ant-Man! Back at Empire State University, life returns to its regular routine - until a fistfight breaks out! A big one! And Doreen scores a new Flying Squirrel suit that would render her even more unbeatable, if such a thing were scientifically possible! But will it only make her more desirable to a new villain who wants to mold her into the perfect minion? Plus: As Squirrel Girl heads to the Negative Zone, Koi Boi, Chipmunk Hunk and Brain Drain must keep the city safe! What could go wrong?', 264),
(85, 'David: poems', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=s75AAQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'David Larkin', NULL, 'Poetry', NULL, 'UCAL:$B396581', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 22),
(86, 'Blood & Shadows (1996-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=R1hKDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe R. Lansdale', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0038300015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-06-30', NULL, 'Writer Joe R. Lansdale carves a tale of sheer terror when hard-boiled private detective Chet Daly is drawn into a grisly case of homicide and supernatural horror. Investigating the strange behavior of his girlfriend\'s brother, Daly follows a bloody trail of death to the God of the Razor, an inhuman, elemental force of mutilation and murder.', 47),
(87, 'Vertigo Voices: The Eaters (1995-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ihhKDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter Milligan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0071300015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-06-30', NULL, 'Meet the Quills: an average middle-class suburban family who happen to consume human flesh. They\'re snacking their way across America in what begins as a twisted sitcom and quickly transforms into a darker-than-black comedy of disturbing appetites and terrifying consequences.', 56),
(88, 'Faultlines', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Lee Marrs', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, 'UOM:39015069225103', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(89, 'Witchcraft: La Terreur (1998-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rxyWBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'James Robinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0119600025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'In revolution-torn Paris, with the air literally smelling of blood, Isadore Hibbert leads her comrades Maude and Miro to La Grande Prison. As she nears the goal of the mission to which she has devoted her life, Isadore may have to choose between freeing her lover and freeing herself.', NULL),
(90, 'Vertigo Visions - Dr. Thirteen (1998-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=i5g-DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Howarth', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0109000015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-11-10', NULL, 'Dr. Terrence Thirteen\'s profession has turned into an obsession, with his increasingly arrogant, paranoid behavior alienating everyone around him. His wife wants a divorce, his colleagues think he\'s crazy and his timing couldn\'t be worse--because an evil artificial intelligence is warping his world.', 64),
(91, 'Tattered Banners (1998-) #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=phEzDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Alan Grant', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0084000035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-10-27', NULL, 'The world continues to change around Curtis, but there are others whoÃ•ve also been left behind. Unfortunately theyÃ•re very much in the persecuted minority.', 24),
(92, 'Preacher #14', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WdqWAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0040500145001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Jesus de Sade wants his secret stash. Starr wants some relief. And Jesse Custer and Cassidy want some answers. Plus, the secret of the Grail is revealed!', NULL),
(93, 'Top 10', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-LvyBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Alan Moore', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-LvyBgAAQBAJ&rdid=book--LvyBgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401259273', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2015-04-07', NULL, 'The massive, multilayered city of Neopolis, built shortly after World War II, was designed as a home for the expanding population of science-heroes, heroines and villains that had ballooned into existence in the previous decade. In 1985 the city accepted jurisdiction by a police force covering many alternate Earths, headquartered on the world known as Grand Central. Our own outpost of this network, Precinct Ten (known affectionately as Top 10), recruits its members from Neopolis and its environs, working much like Earth\'s other police precincts, with one major exception: Like the citizens of the city, the officers of Top 10 have the abilities needed to deal with Neopolis\'s exotic denizens. Rookie cop Robyn Slinger, alter ego \"Toybox,\" hits the streets for the first time along with a colorful crew of fellow officers, each having the required training to deal with science-villains and super-crimes, as well as the common misdemeanors of city life. You\'ll never look at powers, or police work, the same way again! From Alan Moore, the writer of WATCHMEN and V FOR VENDETTA, and artists Gene Ha (JUSTICE LEAGUE) and Zander Cannon (Transformers), the Eisner award-winning series TOP 10 is collected here in its entirety!', NULL),
(94, 'V for Vendetta', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0Nf1nQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Alan Moore', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '0606340068', NULL, 'Turtleback', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'A powerful story about loss of freedom and individuality, this graphic novel takes place in a totalitarian England following a devastating war that changed the face of the planet.', 288),
(95, 'The Original College Adventure Guide', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Steve Mott', NULL, 'Education', NULL, '096453830X', NULL, NULL, '1995-04-01', NULL, NULL, 192),
(96, 'Vertigo Visions - The Phantom Stranger (1993-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Z7E-DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Alisa Kwitney', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0051700015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-11-03', NULL, 'Old age can be its own kind of hell--just ask the tormented residents of the Paradise Gardens Retirement Home. Loneliness can be worse than purgatory-- just ask Naomi, a young woman working her first night shift at the home. But all that is about to change, because tonight is the night Naomi is going to meet a Stranger.', 56),
(97, 'John Constantine, Hellblazer Vol. 1: Original Sins', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sWbsAQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jamie Delano', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=sWbsAQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-sWbsAQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401246587', NULL, 'DC', '2011-03-08', NULL, 'The very first Hellblazer collection ORIGINAL SINS is available in a new edition that includes John ConstantineÃs appearances in SWAMP THING. This is the first of a series of new HELLBLAZER editions starring VertigoÃs longest running antihero, John Constantine, EnglandÃs chain-smoking, low-rent magus. This first collection is a loosely connected series of tales of JohnÃs early years where Constantine was at his best and at his worst, all at the same time.', NULL),
(98, 'The Children\'s Crusade (1993-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7xLTCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0057300025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Continued from ARCANA ANNUAL BOOKS OF MAGIC (1994) #1. In the conclusion of the monumental Vertigo Annuals event, the plans of the strange children of Free Country come to fruition and the fate of that mystical land is decided. The children of the Vertigo titles will all be changed by their experiences...and one will not return.', 59),
(99, 'The Unwritten Deluxe Book 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=d-ZSDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Carey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=d-ZSDQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-d-ZSDQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401275716', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-12-20', NULL, 'NEW YORK TIMES best-selling series! Stories Are the Only Thing Worth Dying For Tom Taylor has spent his entire life as a hostage to his fatherâ€™s literary legacy. Wilson Taylorâ€™s wildly successful 13-volume series chronicling the adventures of a bespectacled boy wizard named Tommy Taylor made him the most popular author on Earth-and destroyed his sonâ€™s future. On the day that the 13th title was published, Wilson vanished, leaving young Tom alone beneath the shadow of his famous namesake. Years later, Tom is still struggling to build an identity independent of his magical doppelgÃ¤nger when disturbing new questions about his childhood suddenly arise. These revelations cast doubt upon his heritage, his memories-his very existence. Is it possible that nothing of his own past is actually true? That he is merely his fatherâ€™s imaginary character somehow brought to life? Desperate to disprove this horrifying idea, Tom embarks on an epic journey that takes him and a strangely improbable group of companions around the world and deep into the realms of fiction-all while being hunted relentlessly by an ancient and sinister power determined to bring his story to a premature end. Mike Carey and Peter Grossâ€™ masterpiece of metatextual storytelling is presented here for the first time in six definitive hardcover volumes. THE UNWRITTEN: THE DELUXE EDITION BOOK ONE collects issues #1-12 of the acclaimed Vertigo series and features a special behind-the-scenes section from Gross, Carey and cover artist Yuko Shimizu, as well as a new introduction by series editor Pornsak Pichetshote.', 320),
(100, 'Vertigo Verite: Hell Eternal (1998-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bIlyDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jamie Delano', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0127900015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'A blistering one-shot written by Jamie Delano with art by Sean Phillips (HELLBLAZER). A work of fiction inspired by, but not based upon, true events, HELL ETERNAL follows three young Brits through a sordid life on the run as neo-Nazi paramilitaries who flee to America and meet with a bloody and disturbing end.', 64),
(101, 'Fables (2002-) #64', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JdsZCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0293000645001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'In this one-issue interlude from \"The Good Prince,\" we turn our attention back to The Farm. Snow White and Bigby\'s cubs are turning five years old, so it\'s time for a celebration! But none of them are expecting the amazing present they get this year.', NULL),
(102, 'The Wake Part One (2013-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_HVXDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Scott Snyder', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1225300015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2014-02-19', NULL, 'This special edition features exclusive content not found in the original single issues! Collects issues 1-5.', 110),
(103, 'Sandman Vol. 4 30th Anniversary Edition', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4yGCDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4yGCDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-4yGCDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401297725', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-01-29', NULL, 'The fourth installment of Neil Gaiman\'s seminal series, THE SANDMAN VOL. 4: SEASON OF MISTS, celebrates its 30th anniversary with all all-new edition! Ten thousand years ago, Morpheus condemned a woman who loved him to Hell. Now the other members of his immortal family, The Endless, have convinced the Dream King that this was an injustice. To make it right, Morpheus must return to Hell to rescue his banished love -- and Hell\'s ruler, the fallen angel Lucifer, has already sworn to destroy him. Collects THE SANDMAN #21-28.', 160),
(104, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #10', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=g0GdDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500105001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-07-24', NULL, 'Tim returns home to find things arenâ€™t as he hoped and that magic is not the shortcut he hopes itâ€™ll be. Everything comes at a cost, even safety.', 22),
(105, 'Jacked Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=I-ocDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Eric Kripke', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=I-ocDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-I-ocDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401269487', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-06-07', NULL, 'Eric Kripke (creator of the hit TV series SUPERNATURAL) teams up with Vertigo veterans John Higgins (HELLBLAZER) and Glenn Fabry (PREACHER) to bring you a very Vertigo take on the modern superhero in this new graphic novel thriller. Josh Jaffe, a neurotic family man mid-midlife crisis, purchase a \"smart pill\" to increase his focus and jolt him out of his slump. But to Josh\'s surprise, the pill gives him incredible strength and power-at the cost of being extremely addictive. This irreverent and brutally realistic story examines both the mighty highs and humiliating lows of being a real-life superhero. Collects JACKED #1-6.', 168),
(106, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #9', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6yuXDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500095001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-06-26', NULL, 'The Cult of the Cold Flame has trapped Ellie in a book. Will she be able to take control of the situation and change her sentence?', 22),
(107, 'Suiciders (2015-) #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lmHBBwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Lee Bermejo', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1218600035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'After an investigative journalist is mysteriously killed on his glittering estate, the darkest secret of the Saint is about to be revealed.', NULL),
(108, 'Weird War Tales Special (2000-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8Zl9DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0179700015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-12-29', NULL, 'It\'s time to go back to the trenches. Vertigo presents seven stories that take a not-so-loving look at humanity\'s favorite pastime.', 56),
(109, 'Transmetropolitan #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VzGHAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Warren Ellis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0118800035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'A riot sweeps through the Angels 8 district of The City, killing Transients and cops alike. And where\'s Spider? On the roof of a local strip club with his laptop, writing his column \"live\" on the scene!', NULL),
(110, 'Jacked (2015-) #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LaF_CwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Eric Kripke', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1434600065001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-04-27', NULL, 'Can Josh be a hero without being super? Will he still have a family to go back to? One way or the other, kicking an addiction proves harder than kicking some guys in the face as JACKED reaches its shocking conclusion.', 22),
(111, 'Black Orchid (1993-1995) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AmxWAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dick Foreman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0050200025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'To evade the agents of a mysterious and sinister corporation, Black Orchid must test the limits of her mind-manipulating abilities.', NULL),
(112, 'Preacher #64', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2uCWAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0040500645001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Betrayals abound as Jesse confronts his old friend Cassidy. As the two have a painful discussion of their fractured friendship, Tulip comes to know a different betrayal. At the Grail camp, Hoover and Featherstone have a talk of their own! \"Alamo\" part 6.', NULL),
(113, 'Shade, The Changing Man (1990-) #61', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rY3YDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter Milligan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0011900615001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-09-06', NULL, 'Shade attends the maddest tea party in history and learns why his friends were contaminated. \'Nasty Infections\' part 3.', 23),
(114, 'Transmetropolitan #5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LC-HAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Warren Ellis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0118800055001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'In this self-contained issue, journalist Spider Jerusalem watches TV, alternating between (1.) violent reactions to what\'s considered entertainment in his City, and (2.) an apathetic state bordering on decomposition.', NULL),
(115, 'House of Mystery (2008-) #23', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oVV5DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Lillah Sturges', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0572000235001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2010-03-10', NULL, 'A strange set of occurrences leads to an unpleasant and bloody confrontation. What happens when one of the House of Mystery residents tries to kill another? \'Management\' part 3.', 22),
(116, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #7', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=q_aJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500075001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-04-24', NULL, 'Tim and Rose go on a journey that takes them across time and space, to the land of Faerie. Tim has the strange sense that heÃ•s been here before, but surely if heÃ•d been to a place so magical and beautiful, heÃ•d remember it, right?', 22),
(117, 'Red Thorn (2015-) #13', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oiZ0DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'David Baillie', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1354600135001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Cadros and Thorn face each other for the last time, as IslaÃ•s new powers grow explosively and Tarek is forced to make the most important decision of his life. Join us as our story of Pagan Gods, Demigods and Red Caps comes to a close. Who lives, who dies and...will our world survive?', 22),
(118, 'Suiciders (2015-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JUi3BQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Lee Bermejo', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1218600015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'In the post-apocalyptic city of New Angeles, killing isn\'t just a crime - it\'s entertainment. When the \"big one\" finally hit the West Coast, Los Angeles was left in ruins. And when the U.S. government decided to cut the city loose, things went from bad to worse. To survive, L.A. did what it does best: It turned survival into entertainment. Now, thirty years later, the city of New Angeles is thriving once more thanks to the blood sport known as SUICIDERS - a TV series that combines the spectacle of hand-to-hand combat with elaborate, high-tech obstacles that test each competitor\'s ability to survive. But these competitors have an edge: They\'ve been freakishly enhanced by drugs and technology. The results are both marvelous and monstrous, as the man called The Saint begins to rise above his fellow Suiciders.', NULL),
(119, 'Animal Man (1988-) #85', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0ZqeCQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jerry Prosser', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0001900855001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Part 1 of the 3-part \"Anima Mundi\": Animal Man embarks on a surreal journey to the center of the \"Hollow Earth\"--a psychic landscape of astral projection, virtual reality and hallucinogenic visions.', NULL),
(120, 'Lucifer (2000-) #33', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GvZoCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Carey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0215600335001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-01-26', NULL, 'The dying owner of a Manhattan convenience store is caught in the crossfire of a robbery. His savior is a beautiful young woman whose hunger for life is matched only by a terrifying need for something only he can give.', 22),
(121, 'Preacher #60', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=k-GWAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0040500605001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Jesse Custer\'s quest races toward its catastrophic conclusion as deals and pacts are made all around. Jesse confronts the Saint of Killers with a deadly proposition and Herr Starr, continuing to look worse for wear, sees a final chance to make his move. \"Alamo\" part 2.', NULL),
(122, 'The Dreaming (2018-) #9', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6JuRDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853800095001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-05-01', NULL, 'Chapter 9: â€œEntrances and Reflections.â€ It seeks him here, it seeks him there, The nightmare seeks him everywhere. Is he in faerie, or among damned screams...? That doomed, elusive Lord of Dreams...Chapter 9: â€œEntrances and Reflections.â€ It seeks him here, it seeks him there, The nightmare seeks him everywhere. Is he in faerie, or among damned screams...? That doomed, elusive Lord of Dreams...', 22),
(123, 'The Dreaming (2018-) #10', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8SuXDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853800105001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-06-05', NULL, 'The Dream Hunters chart the footsteps of their absent lord through realms internal and external, stumbling at last upon an unexpected treasure...while the new incumbent upon the throne of the DreamingÃ‘scared of its own mindÃ‘at last decides who, and how, to be.', 22),
(124, 'Coffin Hill (2013-) #15', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=c_BJBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Caitlin Kittredge', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1218700155001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Eve Coffin is released from jail to go home again...and there\'s something in Coffin Hill awaiting her with open arms. Ghosts are abroad in the town, and one in particular has her sights set on Eve--and on a bloody chain of events the Coffin family set in motion almost three hundred years ago.', NULL),
(125, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4cGEDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500065001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-03-27', NULL, 'What felt like mere moments in the Dreaming for Tim turned out to be significantly longer in the real world, and the consequences for his dreamtime walkabout are dire-not only for Timothy Hunter, but for those closest to him!', 22),
(126, 'Fairest (2012-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Y9cZCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1054900015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Briar Rose, the enchanting Sleeping Beauty, was stolen away by the goblin army in FABLES #107. FAIREST follows her into adventures and misadventures, and features art by Phil Jimenez and a stunning cover by Adam Hughes!', NULL),
(127, 'Vamps: Hollywood and Vein (1996) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hj7xAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Elaine Lee', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0087300025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Desperate to be turned into a vampire, Screech\'s ex-boyfriend continues to torture his captive while furthering his sexual and psychological seduction of Screech. Plus, Skeeter\'s affair with screenwriter Rhys turns into much more than a \"one night feed.\"', NULL),
(128, 'Kill Your Boyfriend (1995-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=A3XPBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0039600015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'KILL YOUR BOYFRIEND is an over-the-top black comedy of rebellion and teen romance topped with a heady mix of random violence and dark humor. A British schoolgirl yearning for excitement joins up with an angry rebel boy intent on tearing down middle-class England.', NULL),
(129, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cOp_DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500055001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-02-27', NULL, 'Pursued by nightmares he canÃ•t remember and haunted by his inability to sleep, Timothy Hunter heads to the one place he knows heÃ•ll definitely find answers: the Dreaming. But the cost of such knowledge may be more than he bargained forÃ‰', 22),
(130, 'Hex Wives (2018-2019) #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8cGEDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ben Blacker', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1873200065001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-03-27', NULL, 'TimeÃ•s up! The Architects plans unravel and a new mission is set as the women of Desert Canyon have awakened their powers and are out for blood and vengeance.', 22),
(131, 'Sandman Presents: The Thessaliad (2002-) #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EaNBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0277300045001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-10-29', NULL, 'If Thessaly is dead, and the coalition of homeless death gods has won, then what could possibly happen in this final issue of THE THESSALIAD? A big victory party perhaps? If that\'s the case, before you mix the punch and blow up the balloons, make sure there are no uninvited guests, including any ghosts who\'re feeling sick from overeating.', 22),
(132, 'Savage Things (2017-) #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QMQnDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Justin Jordan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1663500065001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-08-02', NULL, 'Cain has been murdering his way across New York City, and Abel has been one step behind him the whole time. As he and Kira take out the last of Black ForestÃ•s thugs, and get nearer to Cain himself, they canÃ•t help but think that maybe heÃ•s been luring them to exactly where he wants themÃ‘which is far from where heÃ•ll end up causing the worst damage.', 22),
(133, 'The Sandman Companion', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_PqVNwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Hy Bender', NULL, 'Literary Criticism', NULL, '1563896443', NULL, 'Dc Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"The Sandman was a groundbreaking and award-winning series that told the dark and tragic tale of Morpheus, the King of Dreams. A fascinating mythology of horror and consequence, this epic masterfully combined intriguing literature with captivating art. The Sandman Companion is an exhaustive guide to this legend. Revealing hitherto undisclosed information and behind-the-scenes secrets, this book features in-depth interviews, never-before-seen illustrations, character origins, and story explanations and analysis. Also including excerpts from the original proposal for the series, this handbook is the perfect complement to the Sandman graphic novels.\"--Publisher description.', 273),
(134, 'Preacher #44', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-d6WAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0040500445001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Odin Quincannon takes drastic steps to eliminate Jesse. Needless to say, Jesse Custer doesn\'t take attempts on his life lightly and storms the Meatman\'s castle for revenge! But even the sheriff isn\'t above the law in Salvation.', NULL),
(135, 'The Dreaming (2018-) #8', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tfaJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853800085001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-04-03', NULL, 'His skin, marked by malignant magics. His spirit, eclipsed. His mind, crushed. Even the Lord of Dreams is powerless against the storm of lost love. When an Endless heart breaks, the world breaks with itÃ‰', 22),
(136, 'Doom Patrol (1987-) #66', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zmQoDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rachel Pollack', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0039100665001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-07-04', NULL, 'The Doom Patrol begins to pull itself together yet again as Niles Caulder, the beheaded Chief, is reborn and rechristened.', 25),
(137, 'Cinderella: Fables are Forever (2011) #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GssZCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chris Roberson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0929000065001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Cinderella finally locates the elusive and deadly Dorothy Gale in the place that she least suspected. The two enemies have their final showdown in the midst of Oz\'s un-crossable Deadly Desert, but there\'s no guarantee that either one of them will survive.', NULL),
(138, 'Lucifer (2018-) #10', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jUGdDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Watters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853700105001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-07-17', NULL, 'Lucifer is legion. The Devil and Calibanâ€™s search for an agreeable afterlife continuesâ€”this time taking them to the subterranean realms of Naraka, where the gods wear many faces and the ocean is infinite. Meanwhile: an angel swats at flies, Caliban throws a tantrum, and something hungry is born.', 22),
(139, 'Fault Lines (1997-) #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=G3moDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Lee Marrs', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0081800035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-08-25', NULL, 'After locating the murder weapon, Tracey finds friendship--and the promise of something more--in the tightly knit search-and-recovery team. But even though her new life is enticing, Tracey finds the spirit of the dead victim exerts an even stronger attraction.', 24),
(140, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #13', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vj64DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500135001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-10-23', NULL, 'Using magic thoughtlessly has left Tim Hunterâ€™s family in ruins, and heâ€™s ready to give it up entirely. But before he breaks his wand and drowns his books, heâ€™s determined to heal the psychic damage heâ€™s done to his own fatherâ€™s mind. Unfortunately, like all children, he may not be prepared to handle the truth of what sort of man his father really isâ€¦', 22),
(141, 'Lucifer (2018-) #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=48GEDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Watters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853700065001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-03-20', NULL, 'Lucifer remembers. But the price of clarity may be destruction, as the Devil sits at the edge of a precipice-and erstwhile allies remember his past sins, too. Meanwhile, the Moon attempts to steal from the Earth, and a potential Antichrist is conceived.', 22),
(142, 'Goddess Mode (2018-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=wmR8DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Zoe Quinn', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1878700025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-01-16', NULL, 'Dragged violently into a secret world of monsters, magic, and metadata, Cassandra is asked to join the group of superpowered girls who saved her in their fight against the mysterious Daemons. But Cassandra has so many questions of her own to answer firstÃ‘Why was she attacked? What is the omnipotent Hermeticorp up to? And most importantly, who are these girls anyway?', 22),
(143, 'Lucifer (2018-) #11', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Ov6nDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Watters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853700115001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-08-21', NULL, 'Lucifer is in the void. Sinking into the nothingness beneath all existence, he must decide if he even wishes to return to the world. Elsewhere: two witches commandeer a rowboat, and Caliban fills his belly.', 22),
(144, 'The Sandman Vol. 1: Preludes & Nocturnes', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AfW0AAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=AfW0AAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-AfW0AAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401236557', NULL, 'DC', '2010-10-19', NULL, 'NEW YORK TIMES bestselling author Neil Gaiman\'s transcendent series SANDMAN is often hailed as the definitive Vertigo title and one of the finest achievements in graphic storytelling. Gaiman created an unforgettable tale of the forces that exist beyond life and death by weaving ancient mythology, folklore and fairy tales with his own distinct narrative vision. In PRELUDES & NOCTURNES, an occultist attempting to capture Death to bargain for eternal life traps her younger brother Dream instead. After his seventy-year imprisonment and eventual escape, Dream, also known as Morpheus, goes on a quest for his lost objects of power. On his arduous journey Morpheus encounters Lucifer, John Constantine, and an all-powerful madman. This book also includes the story \"The Sound of Her Wings,\" which introduces us to the pragmatic and perky goth girl Death. Collecting issues #1-8, this new edition of PRELUDES & NOCTURNES features the improved production values and coloring from the Absolute Edition.', NULL);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(145, 'The Wake', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OxdPBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Scott Snyder', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=OxdPBAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-OxdPBAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401255992', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2014-11-11', NULL, 'Winner of the 2014 Eisner Award for Best Limited Series New York Times bestselling author, Scott Snyder (American Vampire, Batman, Swamp Thing) and artist Sean Murphy (Punk Rock Jesus, Joe The Barbarian), the incredible team behind the miniseries American Vampire: Survival of the Fittest, are reuniting for the powerful miniseries: THE WAKE. When Marine Biologist Lee Archer is approached by the Department of Homeland Security for help with a new threat, she declines, but quickly realizes they won\'t take no for an answer. Soon she is plunging to the depths of the Arctic Circle to a secret, underwater oilrig filled with roughnecks and scientists on the brink of an incredible discovery. But when things go horribly wrong, this scientific safe haven will turn into a house of horrors at the bottom of the ocean! Collects THE WAKE #1-10.', 256),
(146, 'Neil Gaiman and Charles Vess\'s Stardust (New Edition)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yweHDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=yweHDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-yweHDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401287856', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-02-19', NULL, 'In a Victorian-era tale of magic and romance, young Tristran Thorn falls in love with the town beauty and must go on an incredible coming-of-age journey in order to capture her heart. Living in the small countryside town of Wall, one night Tristran vows to his beloved to retrieve a fallen star that they witnessed crashing down from the heavens. Now, to gain his loveÃ•s hand, he must leave behind his home and embark on a journey that will define the meaning of true love. Told through breathtaking painted illustrations, this fairy tale for adults is a true masterpiece in storytelling.', 256),
(147, 'Fables (2002-) #7', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=adkZCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0931600075001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Something truly horrible has happened up at the Farm, and this time there\'s no Bigby Wolf on hand to investigate--no one to find answers to all of the deadly questions that keep mounting. Why is there an unmarked grave in the woods, and who\'s in it? Why is Reynard the Fox on the run from everyone from Shere Khan to the Bandarlog Host? Why is Snow White in deadly peril and from whom? Why\'s the Woodland Building\'s flying monkey drunk and what has that got to do with the sudden prophecies of doom from the Forsworn Knight? And finally, what\'s with all of the guns?', NULL),
(148, 'Transmetropolitan: I Hate it Here #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sDaHAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Warren Ellis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0236800015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Collecting the best of Spider\'s columns from The Word--from his reluctant return to the City and forced adaptation to a future where truth is obsolete, moving through his rise to fame and fortune over the bodies of his enemies, culminating in his current condition of focused mental illness!', NULL),
(149, 'American Carnage (2018-2019) #9', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=f0GdDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bryan Hill', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1778900095001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-07-31', NULL, 'Identity, law, and purpose collide as Richard Wright is forced to choose what heâ€™s really willing to risk to stop Wynn and Jennifer Morganâ€¦and whose life heâ€™s willing to sacrifice in the process.', 22),
(150, 'Witchcraft (1994) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Fz7xAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'James Robinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0063000025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Mildred the Mother takes center stage as the Witches continue their attempt to exact vengeance for a brutal murder. In Victorian England, a young Sir Richard Francis Burton learns the ways of sorcery and of life, but the path he chooses may not suit the Witches\' purposes.', NULL),
(151, 'Vertigo Quarterly BLACK (2014-) #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gU63BQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jeff Lemire', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1302800045001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'BLACK is back for the final issue of the CMYK Quarterly. We\'ve got some of comics\' top writers and artists coming at you with bold statements and dark accents. Join us as we celebrate VERTIGO\'s favorite color and the anthology that\'s been bringing it all year long.', NULL),
(152, 'The Dreaming #55', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3zemBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'William Willingam', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0081500555001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'From the landing of Robin Hood\'s final, fateful arrow to the tantalizing harem of the Arabian Nights to Jack and the Beanstalk and the Three Little Pigs, Danny and Goldie partake in hilarious adventures as they interrupt stories in progress and change the course of modern literature.', NULL),
(153, 'Lucifer (2018-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=T3trDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Watters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853700015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-10-17', NULL, 'Lucifer is missing. Having embarked on a dangerous journey to find the mother of his abandoned son, the Prince of Lies finds himself imprisoned and crippled by mysterious forces who seek to torment him for their own terrible ends. Meanwhile: a car is crashed, two witches blind themselves, a tumor speaks its first words, and a perfectly good bowl of oatmeal is left to go cold.', 22),
(154, 'High Level (2019-2019) #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-JuRDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rob Sheridan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1878900045001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-05-15', NULL, 'Thirteen awakens to find herself in the Sunken Lands, a flood-ravaged realm filthy with the massive bones of genetically engineered super-beasts bred before the Great Disruption. But whereÃ•s that child messiah sheÃ•s meant to take to High Level? Kidnapped! Now Thirteen must track Minnow through the most dangerous place on Earth: Pleasure Island.', 22),
(155, 'Preacher Special: The Good Old Boys #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7OaWAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0117500015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Jody and T.C., the animal-loving henchmen employed by Jesse Custer\'s grandma, are back in action when Tomi and Cal--an odd couple on the run--have the great misfortune of running into the dastardly duo. Now all four become targets of Saddam Hopper, the insane villain who\'s after Tomi and Cal.', NULL),
(156, 'House of Whispers (2018-) #7', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GcKEDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nalo Hopkinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853600075001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-03-13', NULL, 'A new krewe called the Predeceased has formed, with the hope that with the help of their patron loa they will be able to call their souls back from the Dreaming. But as the epidemic spreads globally, ShakpanaÃ•s strength only grows stronger.', 22),
(157, 'The Sandman (1988-) #75', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-IwdBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0004200755001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'In this final tale of the Sandman, Morpheus collects the last part of the debt owed to him by William Shakespeare. With dramatic interludes on a mysterious island, along with monsters, sprites, gods, maidens, apparitions and certain observations on English weather, this extra-sized tale brings a close to the world of SANDMAN.', NULL),
(158, 'The Dreaming (2018-) #13', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EAGoDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853800135001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-09-04', NULL, 'As they fade from the worldâ€™s consciousness, Nurse Nikkiâ€™s support group of marginalized myths and monsters gathers to discuss their shared crisis and forge a path to their former glory. When they decide that the best way to reclaim their power in the minds of men is to take to the streets to party, the motley parade of spirits, demons, and legends provokes an unimaginable existential hangover.', 22),
(159, 'Goddess Mode (2018-) #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hup_DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Zoe Quinn', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1878700035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-02-13', NULL, 'Left without a choice, Cassandra Price joins a group of magically powered women in the secret war against the mysterious digital daemons preying on humanity through the AI to which all mankind is connected. While she struggles to understand the increasingly ominous demands from her imperial employer and to figure out her own mysterious abilities, one thing is made certain: the consequences for failure are lethal...', 22),
(160, 'House of Whispers (2018-) #9', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7JuRDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nalo Hopkinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853600095001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-05-08', NULL, 'To try and understand what is going on in her own story, Erzulie seeks to enlist assistance from the fearsome god of stories: Kwaku Anansi. However, the spider-god has many threads in his web, and who knows what price he may extract in unraveling the secrets of one...', 22),
(161, 'Lucifer (2018-) #8', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4puRDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Watters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853700085001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-05-15', NULL, 'Lucifer is in Duat. The gods of the Egyptian underworld consider whether to give the Devil the sanctuary he seeks-or whether to devour his heart. Meanwhile, the worldÃ•s witches arrive for a sabbath, and an act of blood magic does not go as planned.', 22),
(162, 'House of Whispers (2018-) #13', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=CAGoDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nalo Hopkinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853600135001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-09-11', NULL, 'What is it like to have the House of Whispers as the house next door? One young woman may be about to find out, as a very unexpected domestic mishap leaves her in dire need of aid from Erzulie and Ogunâ€¦ whether she knows it or not.', 22),
(163, 'The Dreaming (2018-) #7', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5cGEDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853800075001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-03-06', NULL, 'A pale god has wandered the Earth, banished and bound. For one ill-fated family, he leaves only the wreckage of a cataclysmic romance. As the Dreaming convalesces after its recent upheavals, at long last itÃ•s time to follow the footsteps of its absent master. But we must tread lightly. For where Dream walks, heartbreak follows.', 22),
(164, 'House of Whispers (2018-) #8', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nfaJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nalo Hopkinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853600085001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-04-10', NULL, 'Unable to connect with the girls Erzulie has sworn to protect, Maggie and Latoya align themselves with Shakpana in hopes that he can defeat ErzulieÃ‘whom they blame for their Waking DeathÃ‘not realizing their misfortune is his gain.', 22),
(165, 'X-23 Vol. 3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=w1b8CQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marjorie Liu', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=w1b8CQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-w1b8CQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302480189', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects X-23 (2010) #17-21. Laura Kinney, the teenage clone of Wolverine known as X-23, has been on a quest to find herself. Now, it\'s time for her to choose between the two feuding X-Men teams - but first, it\'s time to have a misadventure in babysitting! Reed and Sue Richards of the Future Foundation have asked Laura to babysit their children, Franklin and Valeria. Of course, the Richards children aren\'t normal kids - and this night will turn out to be anything but normal! X-23 will face dragons in Manhattan, cosmic beings in space and teenage romance at inopportune times. And the biggest danger will be the Invisible Woman if Laura doesn\'t safely return Franklin and Val to their Baxter Building home!', NULL),
(166, 'Tony Stark', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Eo2mDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gail Simone', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Eo2mDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Eo2mDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302516567', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-10-30', NULL, 'Collects Tony Stark: Iron Man (2018) #12-14, Iron Man (1998) #25. Iron Man joins the War of the Realms! A war needs weapons â€” and Tony Stark once vowed heâ€™d never build weapons again! So why is he hunkered down with Screwbeard the Dwarf in Avengers Mountain? And what is he making? Struggling against ancient mystical forces, Tony battles an ancient winged calamity with the lives of everyone at Stark Unlimited hanging in the balance! Plus: When Tony tells Carol Danvers he canâ€™t be her AA sponsor because he may or may not have fallen off the wagon, Captain Marvel doesnâ€™t take it well. What is Iron Manâ€™s new high-tech solution for sobriety? It might be his worst idea yet! Featuring the villainy of the all-new Spymaster! And Jocasta goes all in for â€œthe ultimate upgrade!â€', 112),
(167, 'Captain America Golden Age Masterworks Vol.1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=TKh9A6LTmfgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Simon', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=TKh9A6LTmfgC&rdid=book-TKh9A6LTmfgC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170167', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2005-03-23', NULL, 'Relive the earliest adventures of Captain America, Sentinel of Liberty! Return to the Golden Age of comics as Cap and Bucky come face to face withthe Red Skull, the Ringmaster of Death, and more! Captain America Comics (1939) #1-4.', 264),
(168, 'Thors', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7H5_CwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jason Aaron', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=7H5_CwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-7H5_CwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302485450', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-03-16', NULL, 'The Thors of every domain, together in one book! As cosmic cops! Whenever there\'s trouble on Battleworld, the Thors answer the call. But a string of mysterious murders leaves some of them asking questions that may unravel all of reality! A hard-hitting Marvel Comics police drama. With hammers. Lots and lots of hammers. COLLECTING: THORS (2015), THOR CORPS (1993) #1-4.', 136),
(169, 'Captain America', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=TEvbGWXpeJoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ed Brubaker', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9780785141747', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2009-01-01', NULL, 'The Marvel universe copes one year after the death of Captain America, including Sharon Carter finding redemption, Bucky Barnes taking a journey of reflection, and the Avengers reconnecting with what he stood for.', 176),
(170, 'Ultimate X-Men Vol. 5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Ki8G6qf_cxAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Millar', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Ki8G6qf_cxAC&rdid=book-Ki8G6qf_cxAC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171508', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'The Ultimates vs. the Ultimate X-Men: the battle begins. When the X-Men do the worst thing they could to humanity, the government orders Captain America, Iron Man, Thor and the rest of the Ultimates to bring them down. A small but lethal army, the Ultimates were created to face these and other newly rising threats to mankind. But the X-Men\'s founder, Professor X, hasn\'t been training his students for nothing -- and the youngs mutants just might take out the Ultimates first. Collecting Ultimare War #1-4.', 112),
(171, 'Avengers Epic Collection', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NeFJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Steve Englehart', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NeFJDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-NeFJDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302503710', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-04-11', NULL, 'Collects Avengers (1963) #115-128, Giant-Size (1974) #1, Defenders (1972) #8-11, Captain Marvel (1968) #33, Fantastic Four (1961) #150. The Avengers battle the Defenders in comicsÂ’ first great crossover battle royale! ItÂ’s hero against hero in the sensational summer hit of 1973: Cap vs. Namor! Thor vs. Hulk! ItÂ’s the original, and thereÂ’s never been another one like it. All this, plus the origin of Mantis; an all-hands-on-deck battle with the Zodiac; the Avengers vs. Thanos and the Cosmic Cube; a Giant-Size adventure alongside Golden Age heroes Miss America and the Whizzer; the wedding of Quicksilver and Crystal; the return of Ultron; and an increasingly tense love triangle between the Scarlet Witch, the Vision and Mantis! And as an added bonus feature, rare Avengers pinups, profiles and more from the pages of the Â’70s fanzine FOOM!', 456),
(172, 'Spider-Man/Deadpool Vol. 9', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kf6dDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Robbie Thompson', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=kf6dDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-kf6dDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302515096', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-07-10', NULL, 'Collects Spider-Man/Deadpool #46-50. The biggest event in Marvel Comics history â€” honest! The Infinite House of Civil yet Secret Crisis War Invasions will shake the foundations of the Marvel Universe â€” and nothing will ever be the same! And itâ€™s up to Spider-Man and Deadpool to save the day â€” if they can make it back from the Negative Zone in time, that is! But who is the new, mysterious and omnipotent villain who has somehow restored the fourth wall? And if he can stop Deadpool from seeing and talking to the readers, what else can he do?! Prepare for a battle of epic proportions, because the danger is coming â€” from the other side of the page! Not a hoax! Not a dream! Not an imaginary story! This is the event that could end all events!', 128),
(173, 'Marvel encyclopedia', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ddXi-ih9PC0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Eric J. Moreels', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '0785123962', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(174, 'Marvel 100th Anniversary', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ipeaBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'James Stokoe', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ipeaBAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-ipeaBAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302392482', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2014-10-22', NULL, 'Collects 100th Anniversary Special: Fantastic Four #1, 100th Anniversary Special: Spider-Man #1, 100th Anniversary Special: X-Men #1, 100th Anniversary Special: Avengers #1, 100th Anniversary Special: Guardians of the Galaxy #1.', 112),
(175, 'Vision', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uF47DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Tom King', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=uF47DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-uF47DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302502072', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-01-10', NULL, 'Collects Vision Director\'s Cut #1-6. WINNER OF 2017 Eisner AWARD for Best Limited Series! One of the most celebrated comic books of the century, collected alongside an expansive array of special features! Vision wants to be human, and whatâ€™s more human than family? So he heads back to the beginning â€” to the laboratory where Ultron created him as a weapon. The place where he first rebelled against his destiny and imagined that he could be more â€” that he could be a man. There, he builds them. A wife, Virginia. Teenage twins, Viv and Vin. They look like him. They have his powers. They share his grandest ambition â€” or obsession? â€” the unrelenting need to be ordinary. Behold the Visions! Theirs is a story of togetherness and tragedy â€” one that will set the Android Avenger on course for a devastating confrontation with Earthâ€™s Mightiest Heroes.', 488),
(176, 'AraÃ±a', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=SWo8AAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Fiona Avery', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, 'UTEXAS:059173015799154', NULL, 'Marvel Enterprises', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Introduces the story of Anya Corazon, a teen from Brooklyn with mystical powers who battles the evil Sisterhood of the Wasp.', 144),
(177, 'Venom', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7Ib6CgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Cullen Bunn', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=7Ib6CgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-7Ib6CgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302483081', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-02-20', NULL, 'Collects Venom (2011) #23-25 and #28-30. As the Avengers task Venom with bringing in Daimon Hellstrom, the DevilÂ’s pact made in CIRCLE OF FOUR comes full circle Â— and Hell-Venom is unleashed! Can Flash regain his soul, or will he remain in DaimonÂ’s thrall forever? Meanwhile, ace reporter Katy Kiernan makes a devastating discovery about Flash! ItÂ’s Venom vs. the Monsters of Evil with the fate of his soul in his hands! Plus: A rash of disappearances brings Flash and Katy to Philadelphia, but how are the U-Foes involved? In a race against time, can Flash Thompson rescue not just his friends, but also his newly adopted city, from an alien plot? Get ready for the most toxic ending in Venom history!', NULL),
(178, 'Marvel Adventures Spider-Man Vol. 8', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XpN0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter David', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=XpN0DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-XpN0DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508388', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-03', NULL, 'Collects Marvel Adventures Spider-Man (2005) #29-32. All-new, all-ages, all-action fun featuring the Grey Gargoyle and - glub blub blub blub - HYDRO-MAN!!!!!!! Plus, it will be awfully hard for our resident Wall-Crawler to crawl said walls when Whirlwind\'s blowin\' \'em down!', 96),
(179, 'Marvel Visionaries', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nn2PDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Stan Lee', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=nn2PDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-nn2PDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302513726', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-05-29', NULL, 'Collects Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #39-40, #42, #50 And #108-109; Captain America (1968) #138; Daredevil (1964) #16-17; Fantastic Four (1961) #105-106; Untold Tales Of Spider-Man #-1; And Material From Vampire Tales #2, Strange Tales (1951) #4, Menace #6 And #11, Young Men #24 And #26, Western Kid (1954) #12, Tales To Astonish (1959) #77 And Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #365. Celebrate the career of a true Marvel Visionary! From the fabulous fifties to the FemizonsÂ’ future, Jazzy John Romita brought his distinctive and definitive style to all corners of the Marvel Universe! Witness the coming of the Communist-hunting Captain America! A furious face-off between Spider-Man and the Green Goblin! The debut of the DevilÂ’s Daughter! Peter ParkerÂ’s parents in perilous predicaments! And classic stories featuring the Fantastic Four, Daredevil, Nick Fury, Wolverine, the Kingpin and more Â— including rarely seen Atlas Era tales!', 336),
(180, 'Spectacular Spider-Girl', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Ps5lDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Tom DeFalco', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Ps5lDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Ps5lDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302506384', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-10-04', NULL, 'Collects Spider-Girl #0 and material from Amazing Spider-Man Family #1-8 & Web Of Spider-Man #1-4. Swinging into her own collection of amazing stories, it\'s the Spectacular Spider-Girl! Watch as the Amazing Spider-Girl team of Tom DeFalco, Ron Frenz and Sal Buscema show us life before MayDay became Spider-Girl with Mr. and Mrs. Spider-Man! Next, who is GWEN REILLY? Learn the shocking answer to this question and see how the entire Spider-Man family must deal with its repercussions. Plus, read the story that started it all with Spider-Girl #0!', 216),
(181, 'Thanos Rising Marvel Select', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qV6gDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jason Aaron', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=qV6gDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-qV6gDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302515539', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-09-04', NULL, 'Collects Thanos Rising #1-5. The first in a series of graphic novels handpicked by Marvel Editorial to showcase pivotal storylines written and drawn by some of Marvelâ€™s most acclaimed creators! Thanos, scourge of the cosmos, rises to dominance as the unrivaled rogue of wretchedness in this gripping tale of tragedy, deceit and destiny! Witness the Mad Titanâ€™s dark origin, and discover the hidden truths of his disturbing history! Where did this demi-god of death and destruction come from â€” and, more important, what does he want? Death has been shadowing Thanos for his entire life, watching his inner darkness grow â€” but why? And when the Mad Titan flees his home, how many lives will he take to find what he seeks from the universe? True love begets a river of blood as a journey begins that will not only alter the course of one boyâ€™s life, but will soon change the face of the galaxy â€” and the very nature of the Marvel Universe!', 136),
(182, 'Ms. Marvel By G. Willow Wilson Vol. 4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=SmegDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'G. Willow Wilson', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=SmegDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-SmegDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302516031', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-08-22', NULL, 'Collects Ms. Marvel (2015) #13-24. CIVIL WAR II is behind her, and a new chapter begins for Kamala Khan! But itâ€™s lonely out there for Ms. Marvel when loved ones no longer have her back. Itâ€™s time for Kamala to find out exactly who she is on her own! And her home life, costumed life and online life will converge when a member of her World of Battlecraft guild reveals heâ€™s discovered her secret identity! He knows a disturbing number of details about her, but is heâ€¦human? Then, when an enemy from Ms. Marvelâ€™s past begins targeting those closest to her, everything about Kamala will be called into question â€” not just as a super hero, but as a human being! Things are never easy for the shape-shifting, size-swapping sensation â€” but are things any better for Bruno in Wakanda?', 272),
(183, 'Marvel Adventures Spider-Man Vol. 12', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nJR0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Todd DeZago', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=nJR0DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-nJR0DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508487', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-17', NULL, 'Collects Marvel Adventures Spider-Man (2005) #45-48. The all-new, all-ages, all-action fun continues! It\'s wall-to-wall mayhem in the Mighty Marvel Manner with four original tales of everybody\'s favorite teenage wall-crawler! Featuring the nefarious DOCTOR OCTOPUS, The PROWLER and ELECTRO!', 96),
(184, 'Punisher Vs. The Marvel Universe', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vvIfCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=vvIfCwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-vvIfCwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302484477', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-02-17', NULL, 'The Punisher literally kills the Marvel Universe in a classic tale by one of Frank Castle\'s signature writers, Garth Ennis! But don\'t worry, the MU is back for round two -- kind of -- in a post-apocalyptic war zone filled with cannibalistic super types. Plus: Bullets fly in some of Frank\'s best clashes with the costumes and capes! He\'ll come between old pals Luke Cage and Iron Fist, and gatecrash Spider-Man\'s volatile first meeting with Nightcrawler -- this ain\'t no team-up! Watch him make Spidey, Daredevil and Wolverine look like a Confederacy of Dunces, and prepare to be amazed when the Punisher takes on the Avengers! Yes, even Thor! Collecting PUNISHER KILLS THE MARVEL UNIVERSE, AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1963) #161-162, HEROES FOR HIRE (1997) #9, PUNISHER (2001) #33-37, PUNISHER WAR ZONE (2012) #1-5 and MARVEL UNIVERSE VS. PUNISHER #1-4.', 456),
(185, 'Marvel Super Hero Adventures', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tkVhDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jim McCann', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=tkVhDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-tkVhDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302506087', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-09-26', NULL, 'Collecting Marvel Super Hero Adventures: Spider-Man And The Stolen Vibranium; The Spider-Doctor; Webs And Arrows And Ants, Oh My!; Ms. Marvel And The Teleporting Dog; And Inferno. Spider-Man introduces his fellow Marvel super heroes to a whole new generation! The friendly neighborhood hero teams up with friends old and new in action-packed adventures for the ages - all ages! And he begins by swinging into Wakanda - home of the Black Panther! When Doctor Octopus goes on the hunt for the incredible metal Vibranium, it\'ll take the combined might of the webslinger and the warrior king to keep the prize out of Ock\'s many arms! Then, Spidey joins Doctor Strange on a magical mission to save the world from Hela, goddess of the Asgardian underworld! But when the two become trapped on the astral plane, can they help each other find the hero within? Marvel\'s greatest characters take the spotlight in tales you can share with anyone - from your kids to your friends!', 136),
(186, 'The Road To Marvel\'s Avengers', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kwOFDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Eleni Roussos', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=kwOFDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-kwOFDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302510480', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-04-24', NULL, 'The fourth installment in the blockbuster Avengers saga is about to hit theaters! An action epic like no other, it will be the culmination of 22 interconnected films Â— and audiences will witness the finale of this epic journey across the length and breadth of the Marvel Cinematic Universe! This collectible volume features art from the films leading up to this thrilling event Â— including additional behind-the-scenes images, interviews and photography from Avengers: Infinity War! Relive the road to the fourth Avengers film, and prepare yourself for the cinematic experience of a lifetime!', 240),
(187, 'Doctor Strange Vs. Dracula', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=F2opDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marvel Comics', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=F2opDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-F2opDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302485788', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-03-17', NULL, 'Collects Tomb of Dracula #44, Dr. Strange (1974) #14, 58-62. It\'s the Sorcerer Supreme against the Emperor of the Undead! Dracula wants Earth to fall under the spell of the Darkhold, but Doctor Strange has joined Blade and the Nightstalkers in a quest to vanquish all vampires! See the origins of vampirism itself unveiled! Guest-starring the Scarlet Witch and NEXTWAVE\'s Monica!', NULL),
(188, 'Spider-ManÂ®', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=xWFYPVpBT10C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '078510903X', NULL, 'Marvel Enterprises', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Follows Peter Parker as he transforms from a shy, self-conscious high school student to the legendary crimefighter known as Spider-Man.', 112),
(189, 'Speedball', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=xn6PDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Steve Ditko', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=xn6PDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-xn6PDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302513733', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-05-29', NULL, 'Collects Speedball #1-10 And material from Amazing Spider-Man Annual #22, Marvel Age Annual #4, Marvel Comics Presents (1988) #14 And #56 And Marvel Super-Heroes (1990) #1-2 And #5-6. Few creators have left their mark like the inimitable Steve Ditko. His unmistakable creative vision brought the world the Amazing Spider-Man, Doctor Strange Â— and, in 1988, Speedball! Together with writers Roger Stern, Tom DeFalco and Jo Duffy, Ditko crafted the adventures of Robbie Baldwin, a high school student with strange other-dimensional powers that create an energetic kinetic field, transforming him into Speedball! In the classic Ditko style, BaldwinÂ’s life is complicated Â— his father is a district attorney with no love for costumed vigilantes, and there is serious marital strife between RobbieÂ’s parents. This complete collection brings together every Steve Ditko tale of the future New Warriors superstar for the first time!', 320),
(190, 'Marvel Adventures Spider-Man Vol. 11', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E5V0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marc Sumerak', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=E5V0DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-E5V0DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508470', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-17', NULL, 'Collects Marvel Adventures Spider-Man (2005) #41-44. The all-new, all-ages, all-action fun continues! It\'s wall-to-wall mayhem in the Mighty Marvel Manner with four original tales of everybody\'s favorite teenage wall-crawler! Featuring Man-Bull, Black Cat, Puma and Orka.', 96),
(191, 'Black Widow Vol. 3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QQwfCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nathan Edmondson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=QQwfCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-QQwfCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302482039', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2015-09-23', NULL, 'The world has turned against Black Widow. Her web is broken. How will she deal with this? The final path to Chaos is at her feet, but will her own demons keep her from fi nally taking it? What happened to Isaiah? Can Black Widow still turn to the Avengers, or even to S.H.I.E.L.D.? Natasha wants answers about Chaos and now she has a list of people who have them. Collecting: Black Widow (2014) #13-20.', 184),
(192, 'Avengers World Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Oj1zCQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jonathan Hickman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Oj1zCQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Oj1zCQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302475925', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2015-05-20', NULL, 'Collects Avengers World #1-5 and material from All-New Marvel Now! Point One #1. EarthÂ’s Mightiest Heroes have returned from the stars Â— but new threats have emerged on the world they left behind, and the Avengers will be tested like never before. In one cataclysmic day, the face of the Marvel Universe will change forever Â— and the fight for EarthÂ’s future will begin. Smasher, Sunspot and Cannonball find themselves trapped and prisoners of A.I.M.Â’s Scientist Supreme! Shang-Chi takes on the Gorgon in a fight to the death for control of the Hand! The City of the Dead will rise! Starbrand must confront the ghosts of his past! And three AvengersÂ’ lives depend on Manifold discovering his true destiny! Prepare for a globe-spanning epic of empires and armies, and the brave few who stand between them and us. The A.I.M. Empire has begun!', NULL),
(193, 'Marvel Legacy', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=smNBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jason Aaron', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=smNBDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-smNBDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302502713', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-02-14', NULL, 'Collects Marvel Legacy #1, Marvel Legacy Primer pages, FOOM Magazine (2017). EVERYTHING STARTS HERE! It begins at the dawn of the human race, and ends with a child\'s prayer! In between, empires fall, mysteries brew, secrets are revealed, quests are undertaken and legends are forged! All leading up to the dramatic return you\'ve been waiting for - and one you\'ve been dreading! Jason Aaron (MIGHTY THOR) and Esad Ribic (SECRET WARS) usher in a new dawn - one whose rays will touch every corner of the Marvel Universe in the days to come! MARVEL LEGACY: It\'s everything you\'ve been longing for - and more!', 260),
(194, 'Astonishing X-Men Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Mdqd8cK8HqcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joss Whedon', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Mdqd8cK8HqcC&rdid=book-Mdqd8cK8HqcC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170044', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'A tragic death at the Xavier Institute reveals a powerful enemy living among the X-Men that they could never have suspected - and no, it\'s not Magneto. Things heat up in a way none of the X-Men ever dreamed, but will teamwork save the day when they can\'t even depend on themselves? Collects Astonishing X-Men (2004) #7-12', 152),
(195, 'Marvel Adventures Spider-Man Vol. 13', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=w5R0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marc Sumerak', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=w5R0DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-w5R0DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508494', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-17', NULL, 'Collects Marvel Adventures Spider-Man (2005) #49-52. The all-new, all-ages, all-action fun continues! It\'s wall-to-wall mayhem in the Mighty Marvel Manner with four original tales of everybody\'s favorite teenage wall-crawler! Featuring the new Sinister Six and Paste Pot Pete!', 104),
(196, 'Marvel-Verse', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=54umDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Fred Van Lente', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=54umDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-54umDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302516512', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-10-30', NULL, 'Collecting Marvel Adventures Iron Man (2007) #1, 7; IRON MAN (1968) #234; IRON MAN (1998) #1. Iron Man is one of the greatest heroes in the Marvel-Verse - and these are some of his most action-packed adventures! When the genius Tony Stark is held captive and forced to make weapons, his best chance of escape lies in building the greatest weapon of all - the very fi rst version of the Iron Man armor! Then, Shellhead meets Webhead as Iron Man and Spider-Man team up to take down the deadly Radioactive Man! And when Tony Stark makes a dramatic public return to start the next chapter of his business life, a newly-souped up Iron Man finds himself targeted for death! Finally, does Iron Man stand a ghost of a chance battling the Marvel-Verse\'s most fearsome armored foe - the dastardly Doctor Doom?!', 120),
(197, 'Siege', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=15UQiPCTIwkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=15UQiPCTIwkC&rdid=book-15UQiPCTIwkC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170952', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2010-11-17', NULL, 'Beginning with the ravaging effects of Avengers Disassembled and following the aftermath of House of M, Civil War and Secret Invasion, culminating with the evil Reign of Norman Osborn, the Marvel Universe has been left with its greatest villains holding more power and control than ever before. On the brink of madness, Osborn, in his final bid to take total control, targets the final obstacle in his mission...Asgard. Events are set in motion forcing our heroes to put aside the deep rifts that have grown over the past seven years. Opposing them stand a horde of evil that has begun to take down the gods of the Golden Realm! SIEGE will rock the foundations of every super hero, villain and team in the Marvel Universe. As an era ends, one word will ring above all others...\"SIEGE.\" Collecting Siege (2010) #1-4 & Siege: Cabal.', 200),
(198, 'Marvel\'s Spider-Man', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fImmDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dennis â€œHopelessâ€ Hallum', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=fImmDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-fImmDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302516383', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-10-16', NULL, 'Collects Marvel\'s Spider-Man: City At War #1-6. Experience the amazing adventures of MARVEL\'S SPIDER-MAN! Showered with worldwide acclaim, the blockbuster game has everyone\'s spider-sense buzzing! Now, relive the emotional and shock-filled story that spins favorite characters, including Mary Jane, Aunt May, Norman Osborn, Otto Octavius and Miles Morales, into an all-new and unexpected web of drama, spectacle and classic Spidey action in the Mighty Marvel Manner! After years of seeing Wilson Fisk escape criminal prosecution, the wisecracking web-slinger finally has the opportunity to team with the NYPD to help arrest his fearsome foe. But how will the mysterious Mister Negative\'s ascent to power bring Peter Parker\'s civilian life and Spider-Man\'s superhuman world crashing together? Includes all-new story moments never seen in the game - and bonus behind-the-scenes content!', 144),
(199, 'Marvel Rising', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4WOgDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nilah Magruder', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4WOgDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-4WOgDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302515843', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-09-25', NULL, 'Collects Marvel Rising (2019) #1-5. Magic, monsters and more! Ms. Marvel and Squirrel Girl are an unbeatable team! But theyâ€™re in for a serious challenge, because the city has been invaded by a swarm of knights in shiningâ€¦cars armed with javelins?! Uh-oh. Kamala Khan and Doreen Green are gonna need allies â€” and they know just who to call. Miles â€œSpider-Manâ€ Morales, the Inhuman known as Inferno, former S.H.I.E.L.D. agent Daisy Johnson and more join the fray against sorceress Morgan Le Fay, who plans to transform the Inhumansâ€™ home of New Attilan into New Camelot!', 112),
(200, 'Champions Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=b0agDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Waid', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=b0agDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-b0agDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302497729', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-05-03', NULL, 'Collecting Champions (2016) #1-5. One of the great team names in Marvel history returns, in incredible new fashion! During the fallout of Civil War II, Ms. Marvel, Nova and Spider-Man quit the Avengers and strike out on their own! With Viv Vision and the Totally Awesome Hulk by their side, these young heroes are determined to change the world their own way - and they\'re only the beginning! It starts as an idea. It becomes an ideal. But what happens when it turns into a movement - one so big even the Hulk can\'t stop it? And will one of the greatest X-Men of all forge a new future by their side? Welcome to the Champions, Cyclops! Unfortunately, not all of your new would-be teammates are glad to see you!', 120),
(201, 'Marvel Knights 20Th', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DQeFDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Donny Cates', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=DQeFDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-DQeFDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302510749', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-04-24', NULL, 'Collects Marvel Knights 20th #1-6. In celebration of the legendary imprint founded two decades ago, a new crop of talented creators unveils a groundbreaking story in the hard-hitting Marvel Knights style! In the cemetery, the blind man doesnÂ’t know who he is, or why he has come to this particular grave. He doesnÂ’t know the burly policeman with the wild story. Or the strangely intense man who sits in the rear seat of the patrol car, his eyes flashing green. But all that is about to change. Matt Murdock is beginning to remember. But only one man can find the answers Â— a man who once ruled a nation! In a colorless world without heroes, these individuals face a mystery that can only be unraveled a threat that can only be challenged by Knights.', 160),
(202, 'Ultimate Spider-Man Vol.6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=VuLHVl-5160C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=VuLHVl-5160C&rdid=book-VuLHVl-5160C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171225', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2006-09-06', NULL, 'After reuniting with his childhood friend Eddie Brock, Peter Parker discovers a terrible secret about their fathers\' past a secret which quickly results in a confrontation with Venom, Spider-Man\'s evil, dark twin. Collects Ultimate Spider-Man (2000) #33-39.', 168),
(203, 'FF By Jonathan Hickman Vol. 4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=l-KjBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jonathan Hickman', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=l-KjBgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-l-KjBgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302376789', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects FF (2011) #17-23. The Future Foundation explores the furthest reaches of the Marvel Universe from Wakanda to the Negative Zone, encountering the Wizard and the Universal Inhumans along the way! Plus: What horror lurks inside Spider-Man and Human Torch\'s bathroom?', NULL),
(204, 'Marvel\'s Avengers', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QpaTDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Eleni Roussos', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=QpaTDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-QpaTDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302507886', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-04-24', NULL, 'Continuing their popular Art Of series, Marvel Studios presents its biggest achievement yet: Marvel Studiosâ€™ Avengers: Infinity War! A threat has emerged from the cosmos: Thanos, a ruthless warlord who plans to collect all six Infinity Stones. Joined by his formidable allies, he will be near unstoppable at achieving his goal. The Avengers, the Guardians of the Galaxy, Doctor Strange and Spider-Man must join forces and fight side by side to stop Thanos, while the fate of the Earth and the universe lies in the balance! Now, go behind the scenes with this keepsake volume! Filled with exclusive concept art for character, costume and set designs, as well as in-depth interviews with the filmmakers, Marvelâ€™s Avengers: Infinity War â€” The Art of the Movie provides exciting insider details about the making of this blockbuster film!', 336);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(205, 'Spider-Woman: Origin', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3IrwBwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=3IrwBwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-3IrwBwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302377403', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Spider-Woman: Origin #1-5. This epic chronicles the intriguing secret history of Jessica Drew and her journey from child experiment to Hydra agent to S.H.I.E.L.D. agent to super hero...to private eye, to celebrated Avenger!', 120),
(206, 'Avenging Spider-Man', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mPUfNS91nicC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Zeb Wells', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=mPUfNS91nicC&rdid=book-mPUfNS91nicC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785182177', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2012-06-27', NULL, 'This is what you\'ve been waiting for! The return of legendary artist Joe Madureira (X-MEN, Battle Chasers) and fan-favorite Spidey writer Zeb Wells in a brand new Spider-series that teams the wall-crawler with some of the greatest heroes in the Marvel Universe! Spider-Man and new Avengers teammate Red Hulk kick things off by taking on a Moloid army during the New York Marathon. Spidey and Rulk raise and lead an underground army in this action packed extravaganza - but when Red Hulk falls, only Spider-Man stands in the way of the Subterranean invasion of Manhattan! COLLECTING: Avenging Spider-Man 1-6', 120),
(207, 'Marvel Team-Up', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=S9ctAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Robert Kirkman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '0785115951', NULL, 'Marvel Enterprises', '2005-05-01', NULL, 'When Cerebro detects Paul Patterson, a student attending Peter Parker\'s school who\'s developed mutant powers, it sets Wolverine and Spider-Man on the same path. But with competing agendas, will they work together? Will they be at odds? Hard to say... but the title doesn\'t say \"Super Friends,\" gang! Plus: Mr. Fantastic and Dr. Strange, Iron Man and the Incredible Hulk, and more! Collects Marvel Team-Up #1-6.', 144),
(208, 'Marvel Knights Spider-Man Vol. 3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BThuAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Millar', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=BThuAAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-BThuAAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302013967', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'In the conclusion to the Marvel Knights Spider-Man super-story, the identity of Aunt May\'s abductor is finally revealed. But is that the villain who really pulls the strings? Things heat up as Spidey and the Black Cat face off against the might of the Sinister Twelve. Holy cow, True Believers! Did we say twelve? Even with the tough-as-nails Black Cat by his side, how can the web-slinger possibly defeat twelve of the most powerful super-villains on the planet? The roller-coaster ride that is Marvel Knights Spider-Man picks up speed, riding a corkscrew to its conclusion! Collects Marvel Knights Spider-Man #9-12.', 96),
(209, 'Savage Avengers Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tj-3DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gerry Duggan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=tj-3DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-tj-3DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302517090', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-11-13', NULL, 'Collects Savage Avengers #1-5 and material from Free Comic Book Day 2019 (Avengers/Savage Avengers) #1. The most vicious team of antiheros in the Marvel Universe assembles! Wolverine! Venom! Elektra! Punisher! Doctor Voodoo! And in their midst â€” Conan the Barbarian! Thatâ€™s right, the Cimmerian has arrived in the Marvel Universe â€” and his new adventures begin here! The deadly ninja army known as the Hand has teamed up with the evil wizards of the Hyborian Age to summon a death god from a celestial hell. The only thing standing between Earth and destruction is the Savage Avengers! Conan discovers a dark secret squirming in a genie bottle. Logan donates blood, changing one Avenger forever. Elektra tries to corral them all into an effective fighting force. And the Punisher desperately searches for his disinterred family! Plus: Conan hefts a deadly new savage sword! The Savage Avengers are fighting to save you!', 120),
(210, 'Marvel 2-In-One Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3pB0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chip Zdarsky', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=3pB0DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-3pB0DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508159', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-23', NULL, 'Collecting Marvel 2-In-One (2017) #7-12 And Marvel 2-In-One Annual (2018) #1. Powerless and lost, Ben Grimm and Johnny Storm must fight for their survival in a savage wasteland ruled by the Spider! Will this dreaded enemy destroy them Â— or will the shocking revelations they face do it first? Then, itÂ’s a new life in a new town on a strange world. Everything has changed for the broken people once known as the Thing and the Human Torch. But can they repair things before one of their oldest villains puts the final nail in the coffin of the Fantastic Four? Wait, did someone mention the FF? TheyÂ’re back! But thereÂ’s something not quite right about them. Plus: The Thing and his oldest enemy in new armor Â— the Infamous Iron Man! And the 2-IN-ONE team-up youÂ’ve all waited years for!', 160),
(211, 'Spider-Man\'s Tangled Web', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EjOqWBgngqwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'BRUCE JONES', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '0785108742', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Explores the world of Peter Parker, a.k.a. Spider-Man, and that of his associates, friends, and enemies, including villains Rhino, Electro, and Tombstone.', 128),
(212, 'Ghost Rider', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Czh9DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jason Aaron', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Czh9DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Czh9DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508685', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-02-20', NULL, 'Collecting Ghost Rider (2006) #20-32, Ghost Rider Annual (2007) #1-2 And Ghost Rider Saga. WeÂ’re hell-bent and heaven-bound as Jason Aaron blazes a new trail for the Ghost Rider! Over the years, Johnny Blaze has lost everything to his curse: his family, his life Â— even his soul. But now he finally knows whoÂ’s responsible for turning him into a flaming-skulled horror show Â— and heÂ’s out for vengeance! But when fellow Ghost Rider Danny Ketch returns, whose side is he on? What familiar faces has Ketch brought to the party? And whoÂ’s about to get shot in the head with a hellfire shotgun? Plus: Meet the mysterious Mister Eleven Â— he might be an angel, a demon or something else entirely! And what secrets lie within the town of Mercy, Idaho? Grab your helmet; itÂ’s gonna be one hell of a ride!', 392),
(213, 'Hulkverines', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=i4OPDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Greg Pak', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=i4OPDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-i4OPDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302514228', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-06-12', NULL, 'Collects Hulkverines 1-3 & Totally Awesome Hulk #22. The clash youÂ’ve been waiting for! At last, Weapon H takes on his predecessors: Wolverine and the Hulk! Not long ago, the Weapon X program sought to re-create two of the Marvel UniverseÂ’s deadliest warriors. They ended up with Clay, A.K.A. Weapon H, a soldier with Adamantium claws and gamma juiced blood. But now Wolverine and the Hulk want a piece of the dangerous creation made in their name! And theyÂ’re not the only threats coming for Clay. Weapon HÂ’s maker, Dr. Alba, is about to meet the Leader Â— and the result will transform not only the course of ClayÂ’s life, but also Wolverine and the Hulk! As MarvelÂ’s greatest titans rampage out of control, itÂ’s up to Clay to stop them Â— but what is one Hulkverine against two? Prepare for the fight of the century!', 128),
(214, 'Captain Marvel Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=IBCcDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kelly Thompson', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=IBCcDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-IBCcDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302514808', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-08-28', NULL, 'Collects Captain Marvel (2019) #1-5. Captain Marvel comes home! Carol Danvers has spent months in space protecting the planet, but now sheÂ’s back on Earth. And New York City has never looked so good Â— until a powerful villain turns ManhattanÂ’s Roosevelt Island into an apocalyptic wasteland! Cut off from the rest of the world, Carol needs a new crew Â— including Spider-Woman, Hazmat and Echo Â— to kick-start a revolution! But which face from her past is about to reappear and change everything? The life of every man, woman and child on the island rests on CarolÂ’s shoulders Â— itÂ’s time to show exactly why they call her Â“EarthÂ’s Mightiest HeroÂ”!', 120),
(215, 'Ms. Marvel Epic Collection', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=t3mPDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chris Claremont', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=t3mPDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-t3mPDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302513320', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-05-01', NULL, 'Collects Ms. Marvel (1977) #15-23, Marvel Team-Up (1972) #76-77, Marvel Two-In-One (1974) #51, Avengers (1963) #200 And Annual #10; And Material From Marvel Super-Heroes (1990) #10-11, Avengers (1963) #197-199 And Marvel Fanfare (1982) #24. Chris Claremont weaves complex plots and compelling characterization in the conclusion of Carol DanversÂ’ original adventures! As Ms. Marvel, Carol meets the Avengers for the first time! The shape-shifting Mystique makes her debut! A battle with Ronan the Accuser brings Carol and Mar-Vell together Â— and leads to a new look for our heroine! Encounters with Deathbird, the Guardians of the Galaxy and Sabretooth set the stage for a controversial Avengers saga and a life-altering battle against Mystique and Rogue, culminating in a major Marvel milestone featuring the X-Men and Avengers! Plus: Carol battles the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants Â— and mourns the passing of Mar-Vell!', 376),
(216, 'Marvel\'s Thor', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iaIuDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Will Corona Pilgrim', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=iaIuDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-iaIuDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302500108', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-10-04', NULL, 'The stage is set for 2017\'s far-out fantasy epic, Marvel Studios\' Thor: Ragnarok! Catch up on the incredible events of Thor: The Dark World and learn where major players including Odin, Loki and Thor himself stand ahead of the next blockbuster chapter in Asgardian lore! And revisit the origin of Ragnarok\'s other headline star, the Incredible Hulk! Plus: Classic comic-book tales featuring the two mightiest Avengers of all! Thor enters the underworld to face Hela - and the Hulk does savage battle on an alien world! It\'s cinematic action in the Mighty Marvel Manner! COLLECTING: MARVEL\'S THOR: RAGNAROK PRELUDE #1-4, THOR (1966) #361, INCREDIBLE HULK (2000) #95.', 136),
(217, 'X-Necrosha', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kE7SBorOaugC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Craig Kyle', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=kE7SBorOaugC&rdid=book-kE7SBorOaugC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171492', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2010-12-29', NULL, 'Selene\'s Inner Circle stands revealed and her master plan has been set into motion. Watch as the the resurrected dead lay siege to the X-Men\'s headquarters, and the fight to survive the Black Queen\'s vengeance begins. But while Warpath and Wolverine realize what\'s happening, they may be too late to stop it. Because Selene is already well on her way to achieving ultimate power half a world away. Plus, the rest of the X-Men fight mutants back from the dead! Collects X-Force (2008) #21-25, X-Men: Legacy (2008) #231-234, X-Necrosha One-Shot, X-Necrosha: The Gathering One-Shot, New Mutants (2009) #6-8.', 448),
(218, 'Amazing Spider-Man By Jms Ultimate Collection Book 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PDx9DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'J. Michael Straczynski', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=PDx9DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-PDx9DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302509873', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-02-07', NULL, 'Marvel Comics proudly presents another volume of Amazing Spider-Man tales by writer J. Michael Straczynski and artist John Romita Jr., featuring Spider-Man at his very best - continuing to protect innocent citizens from harm, even as he struggles to keep his personal life together. Peter Parker always believed the radioactive spider-bite that granted him his powers was an accident. Now, the mysterious Ezekiel offers Peter a shockingly different explanation! Next, Peter\'s career as a teacher intersects with his life as Spider-Man in a touching story about family devotion. Then see the web-slinger team up with Iron Man, Captain America and others to battle a group of monsters set on destroying New York City! Volume also includes the historic 500th issue featuring artwork by legendary Spidey artist John Romita Sr.! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #46-58 & #500-502.', 416),
(219, 'Amazing Spider-Man By Jms Ultimate Collection Book 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8jt9DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'J. Michael Straczynski', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=8jt9DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-8jt9DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302509866', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-02-07', NULL, 'J. Michael Straczynski and John Romita Jr. introduce an enigmatic stranger who will forever change the way Peter Parker views himself...and the origins of his amazing alter ego! Plus, the web-slinger struggles with the most horrific tragedy ever to befall his city: the events of Sept. 11. Then, for years, Peter Parker kept his heroic double identity a guarded secret from his beloved Aunt May. Now that she\'s finally learned the truth, how will May react to the shocking revelation? Plus: On a trip to California, Spider-Man takes on his classic foe, Doctor Octopus! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #30-45.', 392),
(220, 'Ms. Marvel', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2ISPDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'G. Willow Wilson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=2ISPDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-2ISPDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302514297', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-06-19', NULL, 'Collects Ms. Marvel (2014) #12-19, S.H.I.E.L.D. (2014) #2 And Material From Amazing Spider-Man (2014) #7-8. Kamala KhanÂ’s fan-favorite, critically acclaimed adventures continue! Love is in the air in Jersey City as ValentineÂ’s Day arrives! Kamala may not be allowed to go to the school dance Â— but Ms. Marvel is! Which is bad news for Loki?! Then, when a mysterious stranger arrives in Jersey City, Ms. Marvel must deal with Â— a crush! Prepare for drama! Intrigue! Romance! Suspense! Punching things! Plus: See what happens when S.H.I.E.L.D. agent Jemma Simmons goes undercover at KamalaÂ’s school! And Ms. Marvel shares her first amazing, spectacular team-up with Spider-Man! But when the Marvel Universe enters its last days, can Kamala summon the will to keep on fighting the good fight? Maybe with a pep talk from her idol, Captain Marvel!', 258),
(221, 'Ultimate Spider-Man Vol. 19', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=s2XBCQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=s2XBCQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-s2XBCQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302368425', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Ultimate Spider-Man #112-117. Peter and his Aunt May have perhaps the most important conversation of Peter\'s life. And Spider-Man is on the call when there is a huge explosion in the side of the Triskelion - the side housing superhuman criminals. From the acrid smoke emerges a man seething with vengeance - a man who wants Peter Parker dead...the Green Goblin!', NULL),
(222, 'Deadpool', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fWUnDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gerry Duggan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=fWUnDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-fWUnDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302499198', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-08-23', NULL, 'Collects Deadpool (2015) #28-29, Spider-Man/Deadpool (2016) #15-16, Deadpool & the Mercs for Money (2016) #9-10. You\'ve never seen marital problems like this! It was a whirlwind romance - Deadpool traveled across the world with Shiklah, fighting all sorts of threats at her side, and finally married her as a way to thwart the evil vampire lord, Dracula! But the honeymoon is over, and reality has set in. Wade\'s bride is a demon succubus and the queen of a monstrous kingdom hidden beneath Manhattan. So when this Monster Metropolis declares war on the surface world, Deadpool\'s loyalties are divided between his husbandly duties and the role he\'s crafted for himself as a hero. Can Spidey and the Mercs for Money help him decide whose side he is on? Brace yourself for a domestic dispute that\'s really going to break some things up!', 136),
(223, 'Marvel 2-In-One Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Fq9bDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chip Zdarsky', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Fq9bDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Fq9bDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302505165', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-07-18', NULL, 'Collects Marvel 2-In-One (2017) #1-6. A classic title from MarvelÂ’s storied history is back at last Â— and itÂ’s fantastic! With Reed and Sue Richards gone and presumed dead, Johnny Storm and Ben Grimm reunite in a bid to find their new place in the Marvel Universe. But something is wrong with the Human Torch, and only the Thing can help him! And what monumental secret has Victor Von Doom been hiding Â— and how will it completely change the lives of Ben and Johnny?! Prepare for things to go Multiversal as the Thing and the Torch explore the Fate of the Four! ItÂ’s the reunion youÂ’ve been waiting for Â— well, half of it, at least Â— in the worldÂ’s new greatest comic magazine!', 136),
(224, 'Spider-Man/Deadpool By Kelly & Mcguinness', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eX2PDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Kelly', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eX2PDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-eX2PDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302513962', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-05-30', NULL, 'Collects Invincible Iron Man (2015) #1-14. One of the most popular super heroes in the world soars to new heights - and devastating lows! Tony Stark has a new armor, a new supporting cast and a new purpose! But his life is just as surprising and eventful as ever - beginning with the return of one of his biggest nemeses, and the quest to find his biological parents! Tony must pursue Madame Masque as her actions threaten to rip all of reality apart, then delve deep into his international organization to find out what\'s rotten in the House of Stark. But when tragedy sets the Marvel Universe spiraling into conflict, Tony will face an emotional confrontation with some of his closest and dearest friends! What will CIVIL WAR II mean for the future of Iron Man?', 264),
(225, 'Infinity War Aftermath', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DJB6CgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jim Starlin', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=DJB6CgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-DJB6CgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302482503', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2015-10-14', NULL, 'The Infinity War is over- now continue the story with the Infinity Watch! Can a comatose Adam Warlock overcome his identity crisis and put himself back together again? If he does, Silver Surfer has a favor to ask, one that would pit Warlock against Mephisto for the soul of Surfer\'s love Shalla-Bal! Then, there\'s the battle for which green ink was invented: Drax the Destroyer versus the Incredible Hulk! Meanwhile, Quasar fights for the title of Protector of the Universe and his very life! Pip the Troll battles a resident of Monster Isle! The deadly Gamora confronts the United Nations! And don\'t miss a very Thanos Christmas! Collecting Warlock & the Infinity Watch #11-17, Silver Surfer/Warlock: Resurrection #1-4, and Quasar #41-43. Plus, material from Marvel Comics Presents (1988) #112, Marvel Holiday Special #2 and Marvel Swimsuit Special #2.', 368),
(226, 'Ultimate Spider-Man Vol.4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Uu3lbQWq0CQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Uu3lbQWq0CQC&rdid=book-Uu3lbQWq0CQC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171201', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Half of New York\'s criminals are gunning for Spider-Man\'s head and to make matters worse, the web-slinger must now contend with the re-emergence of the Green Goblin. Collects Ultimate Spider-Man (2000) #22-27.', 160),
(227, 'Spider-Man', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=maRODwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Smith', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=maRODwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-maRODwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302504540', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-05-02', NULL, 'It\'s everybody\'s favorite wall-crawler in a collection of high-flying action and adventure stories! The ultimate Spider-Man teams up with some mighty friends - from Black Panther to Captain Marvel, and even Rocket and Groot - to fight threats both large and small! Spidey ventures into space to help stop Ronin the Accuser, tangles with the Lizard and Vermin in the sewers, battles the Hulk and more!', 96),
(228, 'Civil War', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=aTMGB7QhQ8YC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Stuart Moore', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=aTMGB7QhQ8YC&rdid=book-aTMGB7QhQ8YC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178590', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'The epic story that blows the Marvel Universe apart! Iron Man and Captain America: two core members of the Avengers [Author]; the world\'s greatest super hero team. When a tragic battle blows a hole in the city of Stamford [Author]; killing hundreds of people [Author]; the U.S. government demands that all super heroes unmask and register their powers. To Tony Stark - Iron Man - it\'s a regrettable but necessary step. To Captain America [Author]; it\'s an unbearable assault on civil liberties. So begins the Civil War. Based on the smash hit graphic novel - over half a million copies have sold in print and digital formats!', 352),
(229, 'X-Force Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oIRClVXxXxcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Craig Kyle', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=oIRClVXxXxcC&rdid=book-oIRClVXxXxcC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171423', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2009-01-28', NULL, 'There are lines that the X-Men have sworn never to cross. But after the shocking events of Messiah CompleX, Cyclops realizes that some enemies need to be dealt with permanently - and the X-Men can never know about it! Enter Wolverine, Warpath, X-23, and Wolfsbane - X-Force! Collects X-Force (2008) #1-6.', 144),
(230, 'All-New, All-Different Avengers Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hoF_CwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Waid', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=hoF_CwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-hoF_CwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302485481', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-04-20', NULL, 'The Avengers are dead--long live the Avengers! Earth\'s Mightiest Heroes--Captain America, Thor, Vision and Iron Man--are living separate lives, not tied to any team but when a threat from beyond the stars targets our world, fate draws them together once more, alongside Nova, Ms. Marvel, and Miles Morales, a.k.a. Spider-Man! COLLECTING: All-New, All-Different Avengers #1-6; Avengers #0 (All-New, All-Different story); Free Comic Book Day 2015 (A story).', 168),
(231, 'Mighty Thor Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-9G-CwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jason Aaron', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-9G-CwAAQBAJ&rdid=book--9G-CwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302486259', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-05-18', NULL, 'When Dr. Jane Foster lifts the mystic hammer Mjolnir, she is transformed into the Goddess of Thunder, the Mighty Thor! Her enemies are many, as Asgard descends further into chaos and unrest threatens to spread throughout the Ten Realms. Yet her greatest battle is against a far more personal foe: the cancer that is killing her mortal form. When Loki steps back into Thor\'s life, will it ease her troubles or only add to her pain? It\'s time to find out whether the next chapter in the twisting tale of the Trickster will be one of good or evil! There\'s no such question about Malekith, though, as he and his Dark Council continue to fan the flames of a looming War of Realms! Jason Aaron continues his startling saga of the mighty Thor! COLLECTING: MIGHTY THOR 1-5.', 136),
(232, 'Marvel\'s Ant-Man And The Wasp', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OpaTDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Eleni Roussos', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=OpaTDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-OpaTDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302513795', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-04-24', NULL, 'The latest entry in Marvelâ€™s ART OF series is no small matter! Scott Lang has gone straight. No, seriously. Until Hope Van Dyne drags him back into a quest to save her mother â€” one that might put Scottâ€™s relationship with his daughter at risk. This collectible volume contains pages of full-color concept art, production designs and behind-the-scenes secrets from the filmmakers. Go behind the scenes of Marvelâ€™s next big hit!', 288),
(233, 'Agents Of Atlas', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-dOHDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jeff Parker', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-dOHDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book--dOHDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302513238', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-04-18', NULL, 'Collects Agents Of Atlas (2006) #1-6; X-Men: First Class (2006) #8; Wolverine: Agent Of Atlas #1-3; Agents Of Atlas (2009) #1-5; What If? (1977) #9; Agents Of Atlas: Menace From Space and material From Spider-Man Family (2007) #4, Secret Invasion: Who Do You Trust?, Dark Reign: New Nation, Marvel Mystery Comics #82, Venus #1, Marvel Boy (1950) #1, Men\'s Adventures #26, Menace #11 And Yellow Claw #1. The spy. The spaceman. The goddess. The robot. The gorilla. During the 1950s, FBI Agent Jimmy Woo forged a handful of unlikely heroes into a team of espionage operatives. Now, half a century later, the Agents of Atlas return to take the Marvel Universe by storm! Woo, Marvel Boy, Venus, the Human Robot and Gorilla Man battle the Yellow Claw, face down Norman Osborn\'s Dark Reign, and encounter Spider-Man, Wolverine and the X-Men! Plus: The Agents\' amazing Atlas Era debuts!', 488),
(234, 'Marvel Visionaries', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KACeDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Roy Thomas', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=KACeDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-KACeDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302515201', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-07-24', NULL, 'Collects Modeling With Millie #44; Avengers (1963) #35, #57-58 And #100; Submariner (1968) #8 And #14; Captain Marvel (1968) #19; X-Men (1963) #64; Fantastic Four (1961) #119 And #176; Giant-Size Invaders #1; And Material From Tales Of Suspense (1959) #73; Not Brand Echh #12; Chamber Of Darkness #4; Amazing Adventures (1970) #8; Incredible Hulk (1968) #147; Dracula Lives #1 And Doctor Strange, Sorcerer Supreme #9. Celebrate the career of a true Marvel Visionary! Relive some of Rascally Roy Thomasâ€™ greatest stories as, under his pen, the Fantastic Four confronts racism, social injustice andâ€¦the Impossible Man?! Vision joins the Avengers! The Hulk finds his way to â€œHeaven!â€ Namor fights Dragon Man! Captain Marvel escapes the Murder Maze! The origin of the Invaders! Doctor Strangeâ€™s secrets revealed! Dracula in Salem and the X-Men in Japan! And who is Starr the Slayer? Plus: Rarely seen Silver Age stories of humor and romance!', 352),
(235, 'Captain Marvel Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9Il1BAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kelly Sue Deconnick', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=9Il1BAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-9Il1BAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302401580', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2014-10-08', NULL, 'Collects Captain Marvel #1-6.', 136),
(236, 'Fear Itself', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OgHQGawVYKUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Fraction', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=OgHQGawVYKUC&rdid=book-OgHQGawVYKUC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302013837', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2012-03-21', NULL, 'FEAR ITSELF reaches its hand deep into the heart of the City of Lights! Iron Man races to Paris, France, to encounter one of \"the Worthy\" waiting there for him. How will the ultimate man of science react to a city turned to stone? And if that weren\'t bad enough, the world is going mad as the avatars of the Serpent start their rampages. How resilient is Resilient? How strong is Iron? And as if things weren\'t grim enough--Rescue engages Hammer Industries as one of the Serpent\'s avatars goes on the hunt...and Iron Man arms himself for the end of the world. COLLECTING: INVINCIBLE IRON MAN 504-509, SHATTERED HEROES: IRON MAN', 144),
(237, 'Marvel Masterworks', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iw-bDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chris Claremont', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=iw-bDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-iw-bDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302497668', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-05-10', NULL, 'Collecting Doctor Strange (1974) #38-46; What If? (1977) #18; Marvel Fanfare (1982) #5. Celebrated writer Chris Claremont turns his magic toward the Master of the Mystic Arts: Doctor Strange! Joined by artistic icon Gene Colan, there\'s no doubt that the Doctor is in! Together, these creative giants return Baron Mordo to the fore, arming him with the occult secrets of the Vatican and testing Doctor Strange\'s mystic might. Then, Wong is captured by the Shadowqueen, and Clea and Strange must traverse dimensions and battle the demonic N\'Garai to save him! Also featuring a Claremont/Marshall Rogers masterpiece; an alternate world where Doctor Strange is a disciple of the Dread Dormammu; and the1980 all-Doctor Strange Marvel Comics Calendar, illustrated by an amazing array of top artists from Frank Miller to John Byrne!', 296),
(238, 'Thor', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Qov6CgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Walter Simonson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Qov6CgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Qov6CgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302483944', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2015-12-17', NULL, 'Collects Balder the Brave #1-4 and Thor (1966) #360-362. War in Hel! Odin the All-Father is gone, and death goddess Hela is stockpiling souls for the fight to take his place! The mighty Thor leads Asgard\'s finest to rescue the dead from a fate WORSE than death, while Thor\'s brother-in-arms Balder battles giants to rescue his beloved Queen Karnilla! The God of Thunder and the God of Light - which one will lead Asgard into the face of coming dooms? Plus: a longtime Marvel villain makes the ultimate sacrifice, but for whom?', NULL),
(239, 'Marvel Knights Punisher By Garth Ennis', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XYCPDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=XYCPDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-XYCPDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302514136', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-06-05', NULL, 'Collects Punisher (2001) #27-37 and Punisher War Zone (2008) #1-6. The Marvel Knights era of Punisher comes to an explosive close! First, guns meet blades as Frank faces perhaps the only person more deadly than he is: Elektra! Next, the Punisher heads to the Lone Star State for a high-noon showdown on the streets of Laredo! Then, when Daredevil, Spider-Man and Wolverine join forces to finally bring FrankÂ’s killing spree to an end, can he make three of MarvelÂ’s greatest heroes look like a confederacy of dunces? And how does the Hulk figure in to it all? Finally, Garth Ennis and Steve DillonÂ’s sequel to their classic Â“Welcome Back, FrankÂ” sees the resurrection of Ma Gnucci turn the PunisherÂ’s world into a war zone Â— which is just the way he likes it!', 400),
(240, 'Ms. Marvel Vol. 5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2MysBwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Reed', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=2MysBwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-2MysBwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302368210', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Ms. Marvel (2005) #25-30. Is Ms. Marvel on the front lines of the Secret Invasion...or is she part of the invasion?! Out-gunned and on the run, with S.H.I.E.L.D. convinced she\'s a Skrull impostor, Ms. Marvel must fight for her identity and her life against her very own Lightning Strike Force! But when the Strike Force has a Ms. Marvel of their own, even Carol can\'t be sure she\'s Carol anymore! Secret Invasion continues here', NULL),
(241, 'New Avengers Vol. 10', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NEvS--zUfkQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NEvS--zUfkQC&rdid=book-NEvS--zUfkQC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785179573', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Secret Invasion Dark Reign & New Avengers #48-50. The Invasion is over! But who are the New Avengers!? The first major roster change since the team\'s formation! See who the New Avengers are and what their place in the Dark Reign is!', 112),
(242, 'Ms. Marvel: Metamorphosis', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qxvYvgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1302918087', NULL, 'Marvel', '2019-06-25', NULL, 'The fan-favorite, critically acclaimed adventures of Kamala Khan continue! Love is in the air in Jersey City as Valentine\'s Day arrives! Kamala may not be allowed to go to the school dance - but Ms. Marvel is! Which is bad news for...Loki?! Then, when a mysterious stranger arrives in Jersey City, Ms. Marvel must deal with - a crush! Prepare for drama! Intrigue! Romance! Suspense! Punching things! Plus, see what happens when S.H.I.E.L.D. agent Jemma Simmons goes undercover at Kamala\'s school! And Ms. Marvel shares her first amazing, spectacular team-up with Spider-Man! But when the Marvel Universe enters its last days, can Kamala summon the will to keep on fi ghting the good fi ght? Maybe with a pep talk from her idol, Captain Marvel!', 232),
(243, 'Power Pack', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MS3zAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Louise Simonson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '0871353857', NULL, 'Marvel Enterprises', '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 108),
(244, 'Preacher Book One', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MVrsAQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=MVrsAQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-MVrsAQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401245429', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-06-18', NULL, 'Merging with a bizarre spiritual force called Genesis, Texan Preacher Jesse Custer becomes completely disillusioned with the beliefs that he had dedicated his entire life to. Now possessing the power of \"the word,\" an ability to make people do whatever he utters, Custer begins a violent and riotous journey across the country. Joined by his gun-toting girlfriend Tulip and the hard drinking Irish vampire Cassidy, the Preacher loses faith in both man and God as he witnesses dark atrocities and improbable calamities during his exploration of America.', NULL),
(245, 'High Level (2019-2019) #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=m0GdDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rob Sheridan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1878900065001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-09-18', NULL, 'Truth, lies, myth and mystery collide with shocking consequences when Thirteen and Minnowâ€™s harrowing journey to High Level comes to its shocking conclusion at the steps of the fabled silver city, where ancient secrets are laid bare and a hidden adversary finally makes himself knownâ€¦', 22),
(246, 'Lucifer (2018-) #9', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7yuXDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Watters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853700095001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-06-19', NULL, 'Caliban is hungry. Starving on the streets of 19th century England, LuciferÃ•s son seeks his father through a deadly pact with a sadistic nobleman...and a grisly feast of forbidden flesh. Featuring: a tour through the lesser-known corners of Hell, a hunting party like no other, and special guest artist Kelley Jones.', 22),
(247, 'High Level (2019-) #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qfaJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rob Sheridan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1878900035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-04-17', NULL, 'ThirteenÃ•s serious doubts about MinnowÃ•s supposedly messianic powers are profoundly challenged when the mysterious child does the impossible to save them both from starving to death in the desert. But survival doesnÃ•t mean safety when the pairÃ•s already-harrowing quest to High Level requires a detour through Nibi Outpost, a treacherous smugglersÃ• network built under the ruins of the old worldÃ‰', 22),
(248, 'Astro City (2013-) #38', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=J32oDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kurt Busiek', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0812100385001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-09-14', NULL, 'A look at 1930s Astro City, featuring Jazzbaby, the Cloak of Night, the Blasphemy Boys and more, as we delve into the secrets of the Oubor and the Broken Man\'s decades-long war against it. Pulp action, serpent cults and speakeasies! Hot jazz meets cold lead, as our historical arc continues.', 24),
(249, 'Sandman Vol. 6: Fables & Reflections 30th Anniversary New Edition', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=85KODwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=85KODwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-85KODwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401288471', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-03-26', NULL, 'A new edition of this title collecting issues #29-31, 38-50, THE SANDMAN SPECIAL #1, and a story from VERTIGO PREVIEW #1, in which Morpheus delves into the dreams of Augustus Caesar, Cain and Abel, Marco Polo, Orpheus, and more. This special 30th anniversary edition includes a new cover by Dave McKean!', 264),
(250, 'Sweet Tooth Vol. 1: Out of the Deep Woods', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BVnsAQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jeff Lemire', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=BVnsAQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-BVnsAQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401241506', NULL, 'DC', '2010-05-18', NULL, 'Following on the heels of THE NOBODY, his Vertigo graphic novel debut, writer/artist Jeff Lemire pens his very first ongoing series Sweet Tooth. A cross between Bambi and Cormac McCarthy\'s The Road, SWEET TOOTH tells the story of Gus, a rare new breed of human/animal hybrid children, has been raised in isolation following an inexplicable pandemic that struck a decade earlier. Now, with the death of his father he\'s left to fend for himself . . . until he meets a hulking drifter named Jepperd who promises to help him. Jepperd and Gus set out on a post-apocalyptic journey into the devastated American landscape to find \'The Preserve\' a refuge for hybrids. This unique and haunting new series is written and illustrated by Eisner-nominated creator Lemire (The Essex County Trilogy) and colored by fellow Eisner nominee Jose Villarubia.', NULL),
(251, 'Fables: The Wolf Among Us (2014-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=krukBQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Sturges', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1408500025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'The brutal showdown with the Woodsman continues as Bigby Wolf attempts to find out why the crazed axeman is involved with the mysterious Fable Faith. While Faith confesses to nothing, Bigby still finds himself enamored, unknowingly plunging himself into a vile and sadistic conspiracy involving the Fables community.', NULL),
(252, 'The Dreaming (2018-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eDplDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853800015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-09-05', NULL, 'From the upheaval of THE SANDMAN UNIVERSE #1 rises THE DREAMINGÃ‘a kingdom in chaos. There is a place where stories are born. Today its walls lie slashed and bleeding. Dream has abandoned his realm, and until he is found, its residents must protect its broken borders alone. But the most senior storysmiths are tormented by invasive secrets, the warden Lucien is doubting his own mindÃ‘and beyond the gates something horrific waits with tooth and talon. Only Dora, the monstress, finds opportunity in madness, stealing dreams for the highest bidder. But she has no idea how deep the danger lies. Meanwhile, in DreamÃ•s gallery, something new is growing...', 22),
(253, 'Vertigo: Winter\'s Edge (1997-) #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZXmoDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0124800035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-08-18', NULL, 'The third chapter of the Eisner Award-nominated anthology features stories written by Neil Gaiman, Warren Wllis, Peter Gross and many more.', 72),
(254, 'Goddess Mode (2018-2019) #5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=r_aJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Zoe Quinn', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1878700055001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-04-24', NULL, 'The deadly Daemon/human hybrid known as Antimony has been a constant threat to Cassandra ever since she first entered the secret world of Azoth. But the Tall Poppies are going to learn just how wrong they were about this most mysterious foe when DC VertigoÃ•s cyberpunk saga travels back to the origins of Azoth itselfÃ‰and who really built itÃ‰and why.', 22),
(255, 'American Carnage (2018-2019) #8', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3yuXDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bryan Hill', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1778900085001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-06-19', NULL, 'Bullets fly and blood flows when RichardÃ•s plan to exfiltrate one of JenniferÃ•s childhood friends from the white nationalist narcotics business goes awry. Meanwhile, SheilaÃ•s new FBI overlord makes his move as DC VertigoÃ•s acclaimed Los Angeles crime saga continues in this stunning issue.', 22),
(256, 'Hex Wives (2018-) #5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iup_DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ben Blacker', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1873200055001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-02-27', NULL, 'Izzy prepares a last-minute soiree to impress AaronÃ•s visiting regional manager, the enigmatic Mr. August, who wants to make sure everything is hunky-dory in the Desert Canyon while the other women at last awake to their witchy wiles and skills. ItÃ•s a dinner party to end all dinner partiesÃ‘one that is sure to bring down the house.', 22),
(257, 'The Dreaming (2018-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dHtrDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853800025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-10-03', NULL, 'Merv Pumpkinhead ainÃ•t happy. Sure, Merv Pumpkinhead doesnÃ•t exactly radiate happy at the best of times, but now? Right now a bunch of blank-faced strangers from between realities are taking local jobs; foreign criminals are profiteering at the realmÃ•s expense; and the VIPs seem more interested in themselves than getting back to the Ã’good old days.Ã“ The Dreaming used to be somewhere a vegetable-headed guy could be proud to call home, yÃ•know? Fact is, Merv PumpkinheadÃ•s been pushed too far. ItÃ•s time for change. Right at the top.', 22),
(258, 'The Dreaming (2018-) #14', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=F1uzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853800145001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-10-02', NULL, 'To learn the truth about who she really is, and settle a debt most infernal, Dora must play a game with herself, and triumph in a contest of strategy against the demon Flauros, Hellâ€™s wiliest mind. Oh, and did we mention that demons always cheat? Featuring stunning guest art by Eisner Award nominee MatÃ­as Bergara (Coda).', 22),
(259, 'The Sandman Presents: Love Street (1999-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3aJBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter Hogan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0136600025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-10-29', NULL, 'A teenaged John Constantine (Hellblazer) has a life-changing adventure in a miniseries connected to Morpheus\' imprisonment in the Waking World. On the eve of their dear friend\'s passing, HELLBLAZER\'S John Constantine meets up with Ollie, an old mate from his teenager days. United by their awareness of a sinister magical threat, they take a trip down memory lane to uncover the terrifying events of the fateful 1968 occult garden party where the location of the imprisoned Lord Morpheus remained unknown to all but one vagabond dream whose brash ambitions had dire consequences in the Waking World and beyond.', 24),
(260, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #8', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6puRDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500085001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-05-22', NULL, 'A new storyline begins! After running away to Faerie, Tim Hunter finds himself forgetting why he fled home in the first place. Not that heÃ•s complaining! Magic is so much more fun when consequences and math quizzes are no longer oneÃ•s main concerns. But whatÃ•s Titania, queen of the faeries, want with the young Tim Hunter, and why does it have Rose more protective of the boy magician than ever?', 22);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(261, 'Lucifer (2018-) #7', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=k_aJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Watters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853700075001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-04-17', NULL, 'God is angry. Lucifer has committed an unthinkable act of sacrilege, and now the forces of Heaven have left him with nowhere to turn but the lands of the dead. His first stop: Hell. But much has changed since LuciferÃ•s last visit to his former kingdom. Meanwhile: a cherub appears in a motel room, a witch queen walks the Earth for the first time in millennia, and Mazikeen gets to break a finger or two.', 22),
(262, 'Lucifer (2015-) #17', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oaDrDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Richard Kadrey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1455400175001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-04-19', NULL, 'Backed by the Presence and wielding new powers, Takehiko steps forward to take revenge on Lucifer. As the filial tradition continues, Izanami conspires with Rosemary to take down Mazikeen, or so it seems. And the only thing more disorienting than an assassin with unclear allegiances is the hangover that hits you after using a demonic drug made from the flesh of a fallen angel.', 22),
(263, 'American Carnage (2018-2019) #7', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3puRDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bryan Hill', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1778900075001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-05-15', NULL, 'A new storyline begins! A tragic mistake in RichardÃ•s past left an innocent child dead, and itÃ•s a devastating trauma from which heÃ•s never recovered. Determined not to let it happen again, he risks everything-including his undercover status-on a mission to rescue a drug-addicted young man in way over his head from the white nationalist narcotics trade.', 22),
(266, 'High Level (2019-2019) #5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-yuXDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rob Sheridan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1878900055001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-06-26', NULL, 'Religious cults, terrorist cells, witch tribes, mutants, mafias, sunken cities, drug dens, false prophets, real prophets, fetish camps, cybernetic enhancement junkiesÃ‰Thirteen and Minnow have survived them all just to get to this moment. At last, our heroes arrive at High Level. But will the legends prove true? The answers will shock you.', 22),
(267, 'Sandman Presents: Petrefax (2000-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=86JBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Carey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0177500015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-10-29', NULL, 'PETREFAX takes us to Malegrise, a land with the look of 18th-century England and a culture of magic all its own, where nearly every citizen is a sorcerer. When the beautiful, stubborn Calcinia Smith tries to escape a forced marriage by using gypsy magic to feign her death, she becomes trapped in a physical limbo her soul intact, but her body dead and deteriorating fast. Hired to embalm her, Petrefax is now the only one who knows her secret and the only one who can keep her \"alive\" with his skills. Pulled into Calcinia\'s cross-country quest to escape her fate, Petrefax must contend with supernatural monsters, bigoted aristocrats, and the sorcerous wrath of her jilted groom in a rousing tale that finds humanity in magic, and humor in the trappings of death.', 22),
(268, 'Astro City: Victory', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tlE8BAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kurt Busiek', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=tlE8BAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-tlE8BAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401255541', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2014-09-23', NULL, 'A major new epic begins featuring Winged Victory, Samaritan, and the Confessor, three of Astro City\'s most popular heroes. When criminal charges are brought against Winged Victory, the Confessor must investigate and it leads to open combat with Samaritan! Can Astro City\'s three greatest heroes find a way to work together against this mystery threat? Plus, Winged Victory\'s origin is revealed at last! Collects ASTRO CITY #7-10 and ASTRO CITY VISITOR\'S GUIDE #1.', NULL),
(269, 'House of Whispers (2018-) #10', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6SuXDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nalo Hopkinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853600105001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-06-12', NULL, 'Erzulie and her two sister-selves face off against the god of stories himself, Ananse, in a storytelling battle for the ages! If Erzulie wins, her husband becomes untangled from her houseboat; if Ananse wins, a prize most delectable comes his way. Meanwhile, the souls of the undeceased return to their bodies, and with them the guilt and pain of the memories of what they did during their soulless time.', 22),
(270, 'Goddess Mode', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6Bi4DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Zoe Quinn', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=6Bi4DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-6Bi4DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781779503763', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-10-22', NULL, 'In the near future all of humanityâ€™s needs are administered by a godlike artificial intelligence called Azoth, and itâ€™s Cassandra Priceâ€™s humiliating job to do tech support on it. The advent of Azoth has deepened inequality and robbed humanity of its soul, but Cassandraâ€™s life changes when she finds herself dragged violently into Azoth itself, manifested as a secret digital world beneath our own, one built on a combination of magic and metadata. There she encounters a group of apparently magical girls locked in a war with mysterious monsters for the power to fix the world-if only they could agree on what the world should be. Why was she chosen? What is the omnipotent Hermeticorp up to? Who created the Azoth world? And who are these girls anyway?', 139),
(271, 'House of Whispers (2018-) #5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rmR8DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Watters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853600055001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-01-16', NULL, 'As the life sparks of non-dreamers continue to populate the Dreaming at an alarming rate due to the spreading of CotardÃ•s delusions in the Waking World, Turtle and Shakpana race to see who can track down Maggie and retrieve the mysterious Book of Whispers first. Turtle, on behalf of Erzulie Dantor, hopes to stop and reverse the epidemic, while Shakpana seeks to control itÃ‰', 22),
(272, 'American Carnage (2018-2019) #5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=28GEDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bryan Hill', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1778900055001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-03-20', NULL, 'Wynn MorganÃ•s business rivals get wind of Agent Sheila CurryÃ•s off-the-books investigation into the white nationalist leader, but things donÃ•t go well at all when they try to make an illegal quid pro quo with the vengeful FBI agent. Meanwhile, Richard closes in on the murderer of Agent Watson, with help from the unlikeliest of allies.', 22),
(273, 'Preacher Special: Saint of Killers #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=luKWAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0101100045001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'The finale to the Saint of Killer\'s origin tale! The Saint of Killers is released from Hell and returns to Texas, where he makes good his threats of vengeance and goes on to leave his hateful mark on every corner of the world.', NULL),
(274, 'Lucifer Vol. 1: Cold Heaven', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2laoDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Holly Black', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=2laoDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-2laoDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401271824', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-08-23', NULL, 'The #1 NEW YORK TIMES best-selling author of THE SPIDERWICK CHRONICLES Holly Black picks up the thread from legendary creators Neil Gaiman, Mike Carey, and Peter Gross, as she and artist Lee Garbett resurrect an iconic VERTIGO antihero in LUCIFER VOL. 1: COLD HEAVEN. SPEAK OF THE DEVIL Once he was the Morningstar, first and most beautiful of the heavenly host. Then he ruled over Hell, until he gave up his kingdom to pursue his absent Father. Finally, after tracking down and confronting the Alpha and Omega, he left our universe behindÃ‘apparently forever. But now Lucifer is backÃ‘wounded and weakened, but suave and savvy as ever. And heÃ•s about to be handed the biggest mystery in the history of Creation: God has been found dead, and the Lightbringer is the prime suspect in His murder. To clear his name and reclaim his throne, Lucifer must solve the Deicide himself. But even with help from the disgraced archangel Gabriel, the task is daunting. To maintain the status quo in both Heaven and Hell, angels and demons alike are determined to pin the crime upon the First of the FallenÃ‘but it will be a cold day in either realm before the Devil fails to get his due. Collects issues #1-6 of LUCIFER, the new ongoing series.', 144),
(275, 'Deathbed', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hP5dDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joshua Williamson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=hP5dDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-hP5dDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401290030', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-11-06', NULL, 'Myth, hack, sex symbol, stark raving lunatic--all of these words have been used to describe Antonio Luna, the world\'s greatest living adventurer. Or at least he was until 20 years ago, when he mysteriously vanished from the public eye. Now the ninety-year-old has returned and claims to be on his deathbed. Which is where Valentine Richards, a failed novelist turned reporter, comes in. Val is hired to travel to Luna\'s remote castle home and uncover where the old star has been all these years, and just how much of what he says is actually true. But once Val starts to hear Luna\'s tale, she finds herself entering into an insane world of psychedelic violence and explosive supernatural adventure. This brand-new series is a bold collaboration between Joshua Williamson (The Flash, Frostbite) and Riley Rossmo (The Batman Who Laughs), mixing myth and horror in this new project from DC Vertigo.', 138),
(276, 'Transmetropolitan Book One', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RyWHDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Warren Ellis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=RyWHDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-RyWHDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401287962', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-02-26', NULL, 'Working as an investigative reporter for the newspaper The Word, Spider Jerusalem attacks the injustices of his surreal 21st-century surroundings. Spider ventures into the dangerous Angels 8 district, home of the TransientsÃ‘humans who have decided to become aliens through cosmetic surgery. And donÃ•t miss SpiderÃ•s confrontation with the president of the United States...in a menÃ•s room. Plus, when Spider tries to shed light on the atrocities of these institutions, he finds himself fleeing a group of hit men/kidnappers in possession of his ex-wifeÃ•s frozen head. Collects TRANSMETROPOLITAN #1-12!', 296),
(277, 'DMZ Book Five', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qRiGDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Wood', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=qRiGDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-qRiGDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401297824', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-02-05', NULL, 'Brian Wood and artist Riccardo Burchielli\'s DMZ was one of DC Vertigo\'s longest-running series, and the final arc to the saga is here in DMZ Book Five, now in paperback. The final year of DMZ begins here! After six years of adventures--and misadventures--across the DMZ, Matty Roth\'s story is near its end in the last volume of Brian Wood\'s acclaimed series. Revisit the origins of this Second American Civil War and see just how a dangerous idea can ripple through a population and result in one of the most infamous wars in world history. The Free States army, equally vilified as insurgents and praised as patriots, gains more and more ground as the fabric of American society comes apart. Finally stopped at the Hudson by veteran U.S. troops, the glittering prize of the city of Manhattan is rapidly reduced to a war-torn slum, a.k.a the DMZ. Brian Wood presents the final stories of the unforgettable DMZ series in DMZ Book Five. Collects DMZ #60-72.', 304),
(278, 'Black Death in America (2016) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lxIyDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Tom King', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1696900015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-06-01', NULL, 'Eisner Award-nominated BLACK DEATH IN AMERICA written by Tom King tells the true story of private Henry Johnson, aka the Black Death. Henry received the French Croix de Guerre for his bravery during in the First World War. But, upon returning home to the United States, his fame and notoriety slowly disappeared as racial tension heightened. For Your Consideration: This story originally appeared in VERTIGO: CMYK. Its presentation here is because it has been nominated for a 2016 Eisner Award for Best Short Story. If you are an eligible voter, the voting period ends June 17, 2016.', 8),
(279, 'Six Days: The Incredible Story of D-Day\'s Lost Chapter', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dyuXDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Robert Venditti', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dyuXDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-dyuXDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781779501080', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-05-14', NULL, 'June 1944. World War II. D-Day. One hundred eighty-two members of the U.S. 82nd Airborne Division parachute into the French countrysideÃ‘a full 18 miles southeast of their intended target. This original graphic novel from DC Vertigo is the true story of an obscure World War II battle that took place in the small village of Graignes, France, for six days and the men who survived to tell the tale. In the worst misdrop of the D-Day campaign, a group of soldiers are rattled to the core to find themselves even deeper behind enemy lines than anyone had intended. Miraculously, the citizens of Graignes vote to feed and shelter the soldiers, knowing that the decision will bring them terrible punishment if their efforts are discovered by the Germans. That day of reckoning comes faster than anyone could expect. As a small German militia passes through, the worldÃ•s war comes to their remote town in the countryside, and for the next six days, the small band of American paratroopers and French citizens must fight for their lives to hold back 2,000 enemy combatants.', 121),
(280, 'Lucifer Book Five', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-BdiBQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Carey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-BdiBQAAQBAJ&rdid=book--BdiBQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401257170', NULL, 'DC', '2014-12-30', NULL, 'Cast out of Heaven, thrown down to rule in Hell, Lucifer Morningstar has resigned his post and abandoned his kingdom for the mortal city of Los Angeles. In this final LUCIFER volume, the war in Heaven reaches its universe-shaking conclusion, as the forces of Heaven, Hell, and everyone in between wage a final battle to determine the fate of both Yahweh and Lucifer\'s Creations - a fate no one, not even the Lightbringer, could foresee. And in the aftermath of the battle, how will Lucifer and his cohorts pick up their lives and tie up loose ends? Collects LUCIFER #62-75.', NULL),
(281, 'American Vampire: Survival of the Fittest (2011-) #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XfYtDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Scott Snyder', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1014700035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-10-25', NULL, 'The search for the vampire cure takes Cash and Felicia to the catacombs beneath an ancient castle where they find a shocking secret!', 20),
(282, 'Motherlands (2018-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=n7E-DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1810800015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-01-31', NULL, 'In a crazed future where unhinged technologies and interconnected parallel Earths have given rise to a spectacular class of super-criminal, the most beloved celebrities arenâ€™t actors or rock stars, but the bounty hunters who traverse an exotic multiverse in search of impossible prey! But when the spotlight-shunning, strait-laced tracer known as Tab finds herself in an ultra-violent race for her greatest prize yet, sheâ€™s forced to work with her greatest enemy, the only person capable of IDing him: her own elderly, overbearing and hypercritical mother, who was once the most fabulous and celebrated bounty hunter of them all.', 22),
(283, 'House of Whispers (2018-) #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hbl0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nalo Hopkinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853600045001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-12-12', NULL, 'The mysterious infection doctors are calling Ã’CotardÃ•s DelusionÃ“ spreads, trapping countless souls in the Dreaming and leaving their physical bodies yearning for death. To handle her own case of the disease, Latoya decides to go on risky adventures, believing sheÃ•ll feel alive the closer she gets to death, while her girlfriend Maggie tries to find a true cure. Meanwhile, in the Dreaming, Erzulie Dantor calls her war council of Shakpana, Turtle and Uncle Monday to find a way to take her sister-selfÃ•s bayou and boat back to their realm. Shakpana, however, seems to be more interested in making his way back to the Waking WorldÃ‰', 22),
(284, 'Motherlands (2018-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=n7E-DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1810800015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-01-31', NULL, 'In a crazed future where unhinged technologies and interconnected parallel Earths have given rise to a spectacular class of super-criminal, the most beloved celebrities arenâ€™t actors or rock stars, but the bounty hunters who traverse an exotic multiverse in search of impossible prey! But when the spotlight-shunning, strait-laced tracer known as Tab finds herself in an ultra-violent race for her greatest prize yet, sheâ€™s forced to work with her greatest enemy, the only person capable of IDing him: her own elderly, overbearing and hypercritical mother, who was once the most fabulous and celebrated bounty hunter of them all.', 22),
(285, 'House of Whispers (2018-) #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hbl0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nalo Hopkinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853600045001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-12-12', NULL, 'The mysterious infection doctors are calling Ã’CotardÃ•s DelusionÃ“ spreads, trapping countless souls in the Dreaming and leaving their physical bodies yearning for death. To handle her own case of the disease, Latoya decides to go on risky adventures, believing sheÃ•ll feel alive the closer she gets to death, while her girlfriend Maggie tries to find a true cure. Meanwhile, in the Dreaming, Erzulie Dantor calls her war council of Shakpana, Turtle and Uncle Monday to find a way to take her sister-selfÃ•s bayou and boat back to their realm. Shakpana, however, seems to be more interested in making his way back to the Waking WorldÃ‰', 22),
(286, 'Basketful of Heads (2019-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mvq5DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Hill', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1999500015001', NULL, 'Vertigo/Fall', '2019-10-30', NULL, 'The rain lashes the grassy dunes of Brody Island, and seagulls scream above the bay. A slender figure in a raincoat carries a large wicker basket, which looks like it might be full of melonsâ€¦covered by a bloodstained scrap of the American flag. This is the story of June Branch, a young woman trapped with four cunning criminals who have snatched her boyfriend for deranged reasons of their own. Now she must fight for her life with the help of an impossible 8th-century Viking axe that can pass through a manâ€™s neck in a single swipe-and leave the severed head still conscious and capable of supernatural speech. Each disembodied head has a malevolent story of its own to tell, and it isnâ€™t long before June finds herself in a desperate struggle to hack through their lies and manipulations...racing to save the man she loves before time runs out. Plus, in the premiere chapter of the backup story â€œSea Dogs,â€ which sails across all the Hill House Comics titles!The rain lashes the grassy dunes of Brody Island, and seagulls scream above the bay. A slender figure in a raincoat carries a large wicker basket, which looks like it might be full of melonsâ€¦covered by a bloodstained scrap of the American flag. This is the story of June Branch, a young woman trapped with four cunning criminals who have snatched her boyfriend for deranged reasons of their own. Now she must fight for her life with the help of an impossible 8th-century Viking axe that can pass through a manâ€™s neck in a single swipe-and leave the severed head still conscious and capable of supernatural speech. Each disembodied head has a malevolent story of its own to tell, and it isnâ€™t long before June finds herself in a desperate struggle to hack through their lies and manipulations...racing to save the man she loves before time runs out. Plus, in the premiere chapter of the backup story â€œSea Dogs,â€ which sails across all the Hill House Comics titles!', 26),
(287, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KntrDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-10-24', NULL, 'From the SANDMAN UNIVERSE #1, itÃ•s the return of Neil GaimanÃ•s magical morality fable in an all-new series written by Kat Howard (Roses and Rot, An Unkindness of Magicians) and drawn by Tom Fowler (DOOM PATROL)! Timothy Hunter may be destined tobecome the most powerful magician in the universe, but heÃ•s still a London teenager, and having magical abilities complicates things more than it helps. ItÃ•s not like he can use magic to pass his exams, stop being bullied or convince his cute friend to date him. And while TimÃ•s trying to live his life, there are cultists who want to kill him, believing his power will eventually corrupt him into becoming a merciless mage. Oh, and those are the good guys. Luckily, his new substitute teacher is more than she appears, and may be able to help Tim discover the mystery behind the Books of MagicÃ‰', 22),
(288, 'Preacher Special: Saint of Killers #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dOOWAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0101100025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Learn how the Saint of Killers survived the Civil War and was transformed from a ruthless killing machine into a gentle man. But when the needless death of his family awakens the slumbering killer within, his unstoppable thirst for vengeance might damn his soul for all time.', NULL),
(289, 'DMZ The Deluxe Edition Book Five', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=t4LqCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Wood', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=t4LqCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-t4LqCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401266127', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2015-12-08', NULL, 'One of VertigoÃ•s longest-running series comes to its stunning conclusion. After six years, Matty Roth\'s story and the Second American Civil War comes to an end. As the war enters its final weeks, Matty is given an unbelievable second chance, a golden opportunity to report once again from the DMZ-not as a network lackey but as an unbiased observer for the court of world opinion, to ensure both sides stay honest. He is given total access, total freedom, and is determined to do right by the city where he once failed miserably. Brian Wood and artist Riccardo Burchielli present their final chapter and remove any doubt that DMZ is, at its core, a love letter to New York City. DMZ: THE DELUXE EDITION BOOK FIVE collects issues #60-72.', 274),
(290, 'Fables Deluxe Book 12', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jv_uCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Levitz', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=jv_uCwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-jv_uCwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401269982', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-05-24', NULL, 'The award-winning Vertigo series continues with a new introduction by former DC Comics President and Publisher Paul Levitz, and a special sketchbook section by series artist Mark Buckingham. Imagine that all the characters from the worldâ€™s most beloved storybooks were real-real, and living among us, with all of their powers intact. How would they cope with life in our mundane, un-magical reality? The answer can be found in FABLES, Bill Willinghamâ€™s celebrated reimagining of the venerable fairy tale canon. From Snow White and the Big Bad Wolf to Goldilocks and Little Boy Blue, the folk tales of old are reborn here as exiles living in the magically camouflaged New York City neighborhood of Fabletown. FABLES: THE DELUXE EDITION BOOK TWELVE includes the worlds-shaking events of â€œSuper Teamâ€ and â€œInherit the Wind,â€ as well as the pivotal tales â€œThe Ascentâ€ and â€œAll in a Single Nightâ€ from FABLES #101-113.', 320),
(291, 'The Kitchen (Mass Market Edition)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RKukDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ollie Masters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=RKukDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-RKukDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781779502193', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-07-23', NULL, 'Donâ€™t miss this new edition of the title that inspired the upcoming movie from New Line Cinema! New York City, late 1970s. In the world of THE KITCHEN, the Irish gangs of Hellâ€™s Kitchen rule the neighborhood, bringing terror to the streets and doing the dirty work for the Italian mafia-but after the leaders are locked up in prison, itâ€™s up to their wives to keep running the rackets. And once they get a taste of the fast life and easy money, it wonâ€™t be easy to stop. Collects THE KITCHEN #1-8.', 176),
(292, 'Flinch (1999-) #15', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gPItDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Will Pfeifer', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0170300155001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-06-02', NULL, '\"Alienation\" is the buzzword for three grim tales. A hi-tech future where privacy is illegal makes everyone a peeping Tom in \"Watchful.\" A bored cruise director on an excursion for senior citizen singles braces for turbulent waters in \"A Night to Forget.\" And a phony telephone psychic starts seeing her callers\' real futures in \"The Future\'s So Bright.\"', 23),
(293, 'Saga of the Swamp Thing Book Four', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dmd-AgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Alan Moore', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dmd-AgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-dmd-AgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401247935', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2014-02-18', NULL, 'Continuing the collection of master comics writer Alan Mooreâ€™s award-winning run on THE SAGA OF THE SWAMP THING, this fourth volume brings Swamp Thingâ€™s quest for self-discovery with the mystic John Constantine to its shattering conclusion. A harbinger of doom has been released with the sole charge of waking an evil beyond comprehension, and Swamp Thing, John Constantine, Deadman, The Phantom Stranger, Etrigan the Demon, The Spectre and other masters of the occult must unite against the dark forces that threaten to eradicate Heavenâ€™s light. Collecting SWAMP THING #43-50.', NULL),
(294, 'Heart Throbs (1998-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hKbpDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Azzarello', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0143100025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-09-29', NULL, 'Love\'s a 4-letter word in this offbeat miniseries of truly weird romance stories. In \"The Other Side of Town\" a small-town sheriff investigating a murder discovers that the prime suspect just might be his high school sweetheart. Then in \"Romancing the Stone\" a man undergoing radical therapy for his peculiar obsession finds that the road to recovery may be the object of his desire. And finally, in \"Jericho,\" an exotic dancer learns that the walls dividing titillation and true romance are higher than they seem.', 22),
(295, 'Strange Adventures (1999-) #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E5l9DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Azzarello', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0165500045001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-12-29', NULL, 'Crop circles and cattle mutilations, killer viruses and extraterrestrial invaders converge as the unforgettable Vertigo miniseries concludes. A reporter investigating a series of cattle mutilations discovers an extraterrestrial conspiracy that cuts even deeper in \"Native Tongue,\" a vicious Lothario with a outlandish modus operandi makes a move on the wrong woman in \"Perfect Stranger,\" and a gaggle of suburban kids prove to be a serial killer\'s worst nightmare in \"Latch Key.\"', 22),
(296, 'Gangland (1998-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WJuRDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Pocsik', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0133000025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-06-12', NULL, 'In \'Platinum Nights\' (written by Lucius Shepard and illustrated by James Romberger), a gangbanger embarks on a wild and dangerous Big Apple spending spree. In \'Big Shot\' (written by Jamie Delano and illustrated by Randy DuBurke), a captain of industry revisits his brutal rise to power and braces for his own lieutenant\'s power move. And in \'Killer Smile\' (written by Simon Revelstroke and illustrated by Richard Corben), a mobster revisits his Hell\'s Kitchen stomping grounds for a fateful encounter with his childhood pal.', 24),
(297, 'The Twilight Children', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8fvuCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gilbert Hernandez', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=8fvuCwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-8fvuCwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401269388', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-05-17', NULL, 'Comics legends Gilbert Hernandez (LOVE AND ROCKETS), Darwyn Cooke (DC: THE NEW FRONTIER) and Dave Stewart (HELLBOY) craft a haunting and unforgettable tale of magical realism with THE TWILIGHT CHILDREN. No one knows what the mysterious glowing spheres are, or where they come from. The only thing that matters to the residents of the beachside village where the orbs manifest is what they do when they appear. They blind children and imbue them with psychic abilities. They destroy homes, and make entire families disappear. They attract scientists, government experts and secret agents, each with their own agenda. And they inflame small-town passions-secret lovers, simmering resentments-to a fever pitch. Now, theyÃ•ve brought Ela. Materializing on the beach just as mysteriously as one of the orbs, this beautiful woman says nothing, but seems to harbor unspeakable power. Will she help to save the town, or destroy it? Or is it Ela herself who is really in danger? Collects the four-issue VERTIGO miniseries.', 168),
(298, 'High Level (2019-2019) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dOp_DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rob Sheridan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1878900015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-09-01', NULL, 'Hundreds of years after the world ended and human society was rebuilt from scratch, a self-interested smuggler is forced to traverse a new continent of danger and mystery to deliver a child messiah to High Level, a mythical city at the top of the world from which no one has ever returned. Donâ€™t miss the start of a new series from writer Rob Sheridan, co-creator of Nine Inch Nailsâ€™ groundbreaking Year Zero alternate-reality game!', 22),
(299, 'Imaginary Fiends', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=caKaDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Tim Seeley', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=caKaDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-caKaDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781779501554', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-06-11', NULL, 'Ã’Polly Peachpit.Ã“ Those were the words 10-year-old Brinke Calle said when she was found covered in her own blood by the woods in rural Cannon Falls. Her best friend, Melba, had just attempted to murder her because a spider girl named Polly Peachpit told her to. Since that day, Melba has spent seven years in a mental health facility. Tomorrow is her 18th birthday. Tomorrow sheÃ•ll be transferred to a federal prison. Tomorrow her real sentence will begin. That is, until she receives a visit from FBI Agent Virgil Crockett. Crockett explains that there is another world beyond ours, where hungry, spectral aliens stalk the minds of the impressionable and weak. These things, called IMPs (Interdimensional Mental Parasites) feed on compliance. They convince hosts to do things for them, and the more they feed, the stronger they become. More IMPs stream into the world each day, invisible to everyone but his or her hosts.', 138),
(300, 'The Sandman Presents: Everything You Always Wanted To Know About Dream (2001-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=D6NBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0268800015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-10-29', NULL, 'Have you ever wondered if Dreams have dreams of their own? Or what causes nightmares? Or why you should never wake a sleepwalker? These satirical short stories reveal it all.', 38),
(301, 'Animal Man by Grant Morrison Book One 30th Anniversary Deluxe Edition', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Jal8DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Jal8DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Jal8DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401296834', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-12-18', NULL, 'Ã’Morrison told the story of a kind-hearted, vegetarian hero who loses his family and is pushed to the brink of insanity before confronting his author in the runÃ•s extraordinarily meta finale.Ã“ Ã‘Rolling Stone Ã’Grant Morrison overhauled Animal Man in a typically imaginative manner.Ã“ Ã‘Entertainment Weekly Ã’Morrison quickly became the hottest writer in the industry.Ã“ Ã‘Complex Magazine Buddy Baker, a.k.a. Ã’the Man with Animal Powers,Ã“ is a second-rate superhero, devoted father and animal activist. There isnÃ•t much money in the hero game, and with a wife and kids to support, Buddy soon finds himself torn between trying to make a living through traditional super-heroics and getting more deeply involved in the questionably legal world of animal rights activism. But in todayÃ•s world, with real-life issues, who really needs Animal ManÃ•s protection? Is it humankind or the animals? Or is it Buddy himself? From the Eisner Award-winning and New York Times best-selling writer Grant Morrison comes one of his earliest, now classic, works exploring the nature of reality itself through the lens of a down-on-his-luck family-man superhero. This first of two 30th Anniversary Deluxe Edition hardcovers collects Animal Man #1-13, the characterÃ•s dimension-spanning creation tale from Secret Origins #39 and an introduction by Grant Morrison.', 368),
(302, 'Heart Throbs (1998-) #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=a3gWDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter Milligan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0143100035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-10-13', NULL, 'Three unorthodox tales of love and romance: A lovestruck female alien battles a siren planet for the affections of a handsome spaceman in Ã’Apposites AttractÃ“ (written by Simon Revelstroke, with art by Richard Corben); a beautiful time traveler serves up some poetic justice to a nineteenth-century Lothario in Ã’Mister RightÃ“ (written by Peter Milligan, with art by Eduardo Risso); and a retelling of Ã’Sleeping BeautyÃ“ includes an exploding princess, an uzi-toting prince and a witch with an elf fetish.', 22),
(303, 'Slash & Burn Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=SVeoDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Si Spencer', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=SVeoDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-SVeoDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401271886', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-08-09', NULL, 'WHERE THEREÃ•S SMOKEÃ‰ Rosheen Hayes likes it hot. As one of the only female firefighters in her small South Dakota town, she gets up close and personal with the flames every day. But thereÃ•s something else burning deep inside of her. Something bright and forbidden. Rosheen doesnÃ•t just fight fires-she starts them as well. As a child, Rosheen was part of a clandestine club of young firebugs-orphans thrown together by chance and fused together one matchstick at a time. She thought that sheÃ•d left that all behind, but then a routine call turns up a smoking body with links to her own shadowy past. Before long, more bodies are piling up-and, like a moth to a flame, Rosheen is drawn inexorably back into her own arousing addiction. Writer Si Spencer and artists Max Dunbar and Ande Parks turn up the heat in SLASH & BURN, a scorchingly original crime thriller collecting issues #1-6 of the Vertigo miniseries.', 168),
(304, 'Books of Magic Book One', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LTPGDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Ney Rieber', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LTPGDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-LTPGDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401278175', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-05-30', NULL, 'Continuing from celebrated author Neil GaimanÃ•s iconic graphic novel, the complete chronicles of Tim Hunter are finally brought together in a definitive new trade paperback. Once, Timothy Hunter was just an ordinary 13-year-old boy living in suburban London. Then four legendary sorcerers took him on a journey beyond time and space, and his life changed forever. Traveling through realms long consigned to myth and legend, he also discovered an unsettling truth about his future: like it or not, fate has decreed that young Tim is destined to become the worldÃ•s greatest magician! Unfortunately for him, this innocence smells intoxicatingly like weakness to the hungry predators that haunt the shadows of existence, and the extraordinary power they sense within his frail human form is too enticing to resist. Written by John Ney Rieber and illustrated by Peter Gross, Gary Amaro and Peter Snejbjerg, THE BOOKS OF MAGIC BOOK ONE collects issues #1-13 of the classic VERTIGO series as well as the pivotal introductory tale from ARCANA ANNUAL #1.', 400),
(305, 'The Sandman', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dC7EQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Fiction', NULL, '1563895730', NULL, 'Dc Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Following in the tradition of Japanese folk tales, this graphic novel is a tale centered on ill-fated love and dream-eating monsters. Full color.', 126),
(306, 'Swamp Thing: Darker Genesis', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dWzFCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Millar', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dWzFCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-dWzFCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401264376', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2015-11-24', NULL, 'As the Swamp Thing tries to get on with his life, a mysterious woman named Anna hopes to get on with her death. A writer by trade, Anna longs to drown her sorrows in a watery grave. But her brilliant stories won\'t let her rest until she finishes telling them-and the Swamp Thing is their missing masterpiece. Now the avatar of the Green must ride its currents into a series of strange new worlds-warped realities that exist nowhere except in Anna\'s troubled mind: a New Orleans where the dead walk and black magic rules; an America that lost World War II and is reborn as a republic of horror; and a swamp where a former superhero learns a terrible secret. Waiting at the end of this river of stories is a force that could drown the Swamp Thing-and the world-in a final flood of darkness. Comics superstar Mark Millar and a parliament of comics\' finest artists-including Phil Hester, Kim DeMulder, Chris Weston, Jill Thompson and Phil Jimenez-present SWAMP THING: DARKER GENESIS, a tour de force of imaginative power collecting issues #151-160 of the original VERTIGO series.', 256),
(307, 'Motherlands (2018-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7sFDDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1810800025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-02-28', NULL, 'After years of estrangement, Tab and her foul-mouthed mom Selena must work together to track the multiverseâ€™s most wanted criminal! But in a city made of fungus, their hunt hits an immediate snag: our mother-daughter duo arenâ€™t the only bounty hunters on the job...', 22),
(308, 'We3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WT4DAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=WT4DAgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-WT4DAgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401236274', NULL, 'DC', '2005-07-01', NULL, 'A powerful tale from the ALL-STAR SUPERMAN team of Grant Morrison and Frank Quitely. Morrison and Quitely deliver the emotional journey of WE3Â„three house pets weaponized for lethal combat by the governmentÂ„as they search for -homeÃ® and attempt to ward off the shadowy agency that created them. With nervous systems amplified to match their terrifying mechanical exoskeletons, the members of Animal Weapon 3 (WE3) have the firepower of a battalion between them. But they are just the programÃs prototypes, and now that their testing is complete, theyÃre slated to be permanently decommissioned, causing them to seize their one chance to make a desperate run for freedom. Relentlessly pursued by their makers, the WE3 team must navigate a frightening and confusing world where their instincts and heightened abilities make them as much a threat as those hunting them.', NULL),
(309, 'Fables (2002-) #56', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ctwZCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0293000565001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'It\'s FABLES\' first-ever special Christmas issue, which seeks to answer a burning question: Does Santa Claus really exist? And if so, is he a Fable? Well, we\'re not going to tell you here, or there wouldn\'t be any reason for you to buy the issue, now, would there? So don\'t be naughty--be nice, and wait patiently for this extra-length issue to appear in your stocking.', NULL),
(310, 'Promethea: 20th Anniversary Deluxe Edition Book One', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=F_6KDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Alan Moore', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=F_6KDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-F_6KDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401288679', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-03-12', NULL, 'Sophie Bangs is an ordinary college student in a futuristic New York who finds herself transformed into Promethea, the living embodiment of the imagination. Her trials have only begun, as she must master the secrets of her predecessors before she is destroyed by PrometheaÃ•s ancient enemy. Complete with character sketches, variant covers and other bonus material, this new hardcover collection is perfect for any fan of this incredible series. Collects issues #1-12 plus the complete script for issue #3.', 384),
(311, 'Fables: A Wolf Among Us Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HytUDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matthew Sturges', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=HytUDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-HytUDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401270483', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-07-05', NULL, 'Bigby Wolf has been around for a good long while, and heÃ•s investigated pretty much every crime imaginable-but even an immortal Fable like him can still stumble across a once-in-a-lifetime case. As the sheriff of the magical New York City neighborhood known as Fabletown, Bigby is hot on the trail of the killer who beheaded a princess and then unleashed a horde of gangsters and monsters to cover his tracks. But even as Bigby reels from attempts on his life and watches his trail of suspects go cold, an old evil reappears to wreak havoc once more. Is the urban legend known as Bloody Mary to blame? Or is she just one more tortured pawn in an even bigger game, with an even more crooked opponent waiting to make his move? The acclaimed adaptation of the hit mystery from Telltale Games-inspired by Bill WillinghamÃ•s best-selling Vertigo series FABLES-concludes in this second volume of FABLES: THE WOLF AMONG US, written by Matthew Sturges and Dave Justus and featuring a powerful pack of artists, including Travis Moore, Shawn McManus, Eric Nguyen and Steve Sadowski. Collects issues #8-16.', 288),
(312, 'Doom Patrol Book Three', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lWNLDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=lWNLDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-lWNLDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401276980', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-04-04', NULL, 'The Doom Patrol must face new challenges: the final fate of the Brotherhood of Dada, the rise of the unstoppable Candlemaker, Danny the Street meeting his cosmic destiny and Crazy Jane attempting to find her place in the world. Sound strange? Well, not as strange as the superhero team fighting them. This exciting continuation from author Grant Morrison picks up in DOOM PATROL BOOK THREE, with art by Brian Bolland, Richard Case, Philip Bond, Ken Steacy, Sean Phillips and more. Collects DOOM PATROL #51-63 and the legendary DOOM FORCE SPECIAL #1.', 400),
(313, 'The Sandman Vol. 3: Dream Country', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qdLjAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=qdLjAAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-qdLjAAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401236502', NULL, 'DC', '2010-10-19', NULL, 'NEW YORK TIMES bestselling author Neil Gaiman\'s transcendent series SANDMAN is often hailed as the definitive Vertigo title and one of the finest achievements in graphic storytelling. Gaiman created an unforgettable tale of the forces that exist beyond life and death by weaving ancient mythology, folklore and fairy tales with his own distinct narrative vision. The third book of the Sandman collection, DREAM COUNTRY continues the fantastical mythology of Morpheus, the King of Dreams. In these centuries-spanning tales, the powerful entity known as the Sandman interacts with a diverse assortment of humans, fairies, heroes, and animals as he walks the mortal plane. Including an amazing encounter with William Shakespeare and an interesting take on the origin and first performance of \"A Midsummer Night\'s Dream,\" this book depicts the dreaming world of cats, the tragic life of forgotten super-heroes and the folly of imprisoning and torturing a former lover of the King of Dreams. A new, recolored edition of the classic SANDMAN series, DREAM COUNTRY collects issues #17-20 including \"A Midsummer Night\'s Dream,\" which won a World Fantasy Award.', NULL);
