(314, 'Sandman Presents: Thessaly: Witch for Hire (2004-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E6NBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0359400025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-10-29', NULL, 'The second thrilling miniseries focusing on THE SANDMAN\'s Thessaly continues. Now that Thessaly has Fetch right where she wants him, trapped in a mirror and at her mercy, he\'s quite possibly the most annoying captive ever. But when the deadly witch literally pulls information out of him, the bodies start to pile up. It seems Fetch has one last trick up his sleeve...will this new monster be Thess\'s last stand?', 22),
(316, 'Strange Adventures (1999-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JyJ0DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Bolland', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0165500015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Crop circles and cattle mutilations, mad scientists and the top writers and artists in comics converge in a four-issue Vertigo short-story anthology exploring the limits of the imagination. Globe-hopping adventurers bear witness to the bizarre mystery of \"The Kapas,\" a mad scientist struggles to decipher the \"Riddle of the Random Realities,\" and a trio of plague survivors suffer the insidious side effects of being \"Immune.\"', 22),
(317, 'Everafter: From the Pages of Fables (2016-) #10', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=1lWFDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dave Justus', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1593000105001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-06-07', NULL, 'After Bobby SpecklandÃ•s rescue attempt takes a shocking turn, long years pass for the captives in the CubeÃ‘but a young leader emerges as a new generation of hostages comes of age in oppressive darkness. A quiet revolution simmers, and some surprising assistance may be the force that breaks the barrier to freedom once and for all.', 22),
(318, 'Fables Vol. 5: The Mean Seasons', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eSrfAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eSrfAAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-eSrfAAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401236069', NULL, 'DC', '2005-04-01', NULL, 'WINNER OF FOURTEEN EISNER AWARDS. This volume features two tales of Bigby\'s exploits during World War II as well as \"The Year After,\" which follows the aftermath of the Adversary\'s attempt to conquer Fabletown-including the birth of Snow White and Bigby\'s children! Collects issues 22 and 28-33 of creator Bill Willingham-s celebrated Vertigo series.', NULL),
(319, 'American Carnage (2018-2019) #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=w_aJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bryan Hill', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1778900065001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-04-17', NULL, 'Richard is trapped. What began as a routine undercover mission for his next paycheck has devolved into a nightmare of mortal consequences. Having disrupted WynnÃ•s inner network and catapulted well past the point of no return, Richard fears he must sever himself from SheilaÃ•s original assignment in order to surviveÃ‘but before he can implement their final plan, a revelation from Jennifer forces him to accept his ultimate function within WynnÃ•s white nationalist empire.', 22),
(320, 'Vertigo', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uXgergEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Pierre Boileau', NULL, 'Fiction', NULL, '1782270809', NULL, 'Pushkin Vertigo', '2015-09-10', NULL, 'The story could have happened to any of us, but it happened to a man named Flavieres. His days as a detective were over, and everyone knew he had his reasons. But when an old friend appeared out of nowhere with concerns about his withdrawn and mysterious wife, Flavieres didn\'t have the heart to refuse. And soon he would be scouring the streets of Paris in search of an answer - in search of a girl who belonged to no one, not even to herself. Soon intrigue would be replaced by obsession, and dreams replaced by nightmares. This is the story of a desperate man. A man who ended up compromising his own morality beyond all measure, while World War Two raged outside his front door. A man tormented - and destroyed - by a dark, terrible secret. This sinister, mindbending roman noir was turned into a 1958 Hollywood classic, starring James Stewart and Kim Novak, directed by the great Alfred Hitchcock.\"', 272),
(321, 'Lucifer Vol. 3: Blood in the Streets', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dlw6DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Richard Kadrey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dlw6DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-dlw6DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401282738', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-10-31', NULL, 'HeÃ•s faced down God Himself, and lived (and died, and lived again) to tell the tale. Now Lucifer Morningstar, the most irresistible antihero in all of Creation, is free to turn the final page on his past and begin a brand-new chapter in his legendarily eventful life. But before he can start booking retirement cruises, thereÃ•s still one small matter that requires his attention: an all-powerful entity has usurped his deceased FatherÃ•s place in Heaven and is preparing to extinguish every last vestige of free will throughout the universe. The Lightbringer has always been the contrary type, and heÃ•s not about to change his ways for anyoneÃ‘or anythingÃ‘just because they occupy the Throne of Light. And while the former Lord of Hell now rules only within the boundaries of his nightclub, Ex Lux, he still has powerful allies and devoted enemiesÃ‘all of whom are ripe for manipulation. Together, this motley militia is poised to take their fight from the heights of the Silver City to the depths of the Inferno. Against them stand multiple armies of angels, demons, and every dreaded thing imaginable that lies between them. Can Lucifer overcome their onslaught and keep his club, his city, and his indomitable independence intact? Or, after countless millennia, has the DevilÃ•s tab finally come due? Find out in LUCIFER VOL. 3: BLOOD IN THE STREETSÃ‘the shocking conclusion to the newest saga of the Fallen One from the acclaimed creative team of Richard Kadrey, Lee Garbett, Antonio Fabela, Holly Black, Marco Rudy and Ben Templesmith, collecting issues #13-19 of the signature VERTIGO series.', 168),
(322, 'The Unwritten Vol. 11: Apocalypse', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4DSNBwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Carey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4DSNBwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-4DSNBwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401259563', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2015-05-26', NULL, 'Tom Taylor-the real-life counterpart of his father\'s famous fictional boy-wizard creation, a living bridge between our reality and the realities of every tale ever told-knows the power of stories only too well. Now he\'s the star of his most important story yet. It\'s a quest straight out of King Arthur, filled with black knights, ensorcelled swords, and maidens who are fair to a fault. If his heart is pure and his courage true, he can enter the Chapel Perilous, find the Grail, complete his quest, and save existence as we know it. If not, we are verily screwed. Hark! Storytellers Mike Carey, Peter Gross, and Chris Chuckry approach, singing tales of valor and treachery in THE UNWRITTEN: APOCALYPSE! This final volume in THE UNWRITTEN saga collects issues #6-12.', NULL),
(323, '100 Bullets Book Two', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jLzyBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Azzarello', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=jLzyBgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-jLzyBgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401259358', NULL, 'DC', '2015-04-21', NULL, 'How far would you go for revenge? If you were given a chance at deadly retribution with a guarantee that the law could not touch you, would you take it? That\'s the opportunity that a man called Agent Graves provides, in the form of a special briefcase containing an untraceable gun and one hundred rounds of ammunition. To the damaged and downtrodden living on the fringes of society, the offer is a once-in-a-lifetime chance to even their scores. But beyond the dilemma of whether or not to pull the trigger lies a deeper and even more troubling concern: just who is making these actions possible - and why? This second of five volumes reprinting all 100 issues of writer Brian Azzarello and artist Eduardo Risso\'s 100 BULLETS collects issues #20-36 of their acclaimed Vertigo series, and also includes Azzarello\'s original script for \"The Mimic\" from issue #20.', NULL),
(324, 'Ms. Marvel: Metamorphosis', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qxvYvgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1302918087', NULL, 'Marvel', '2019-06-25', NULL, 'The fan-favorite, critically acclaimed adventures of Kamala Khan continue! Love is in the air in Jersey City as Valentine\'s Day arrives! Kamala may not be allowed to go to the school dance - but Ms. Marvel is! Which is bad news for...Loki?! Then, when a mysterious stranger arrives in Jersey City, Ms. Marvel must deal with - a crush! Prepare for drama! Intrigue! Romance! Suspense! Punching things! Plus, see what happens when S.H.I.E.L.D. agent Jemma Simmons goes undercover at Kamala\'s school! And Ms. Marvel shares her first amazing, spectacular team-up with Spider-Man! But when the Marvel Universe enters its last days, can Kamala summon the will to keep on fi ghting the good fi ght? Maybe with a pep talk from her idol, Captain Marvel!', 232),
(325, 'Power Pack', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MS3zAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Louise Simonson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '0871353857', NULL, 'Marvel Enterprises', '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 108),
(326, 'Daredevil by Mark Waid Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iccSBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Waid', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=iccSBAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-iccSBAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785182665', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2014-08-27', NULL, 'Collects Daredevil #1-6. Matt Murdock is back and hoping to resuscitate his law practice, he takes on a police-brutality case, but someone is trying to silence the victim. Then, Klaw, master of sound, makes his deadly return! And the blind literally lead the blind as a visually impaired client targeted for assassination holds the key to a global conspiracy.', 152),
(327, 'Captain America Epic Collection', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=80a9CAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Gruenwald', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=80a9CAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-80a9CAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302480868', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2015-06-17', NULL, 'Captain America joins the war on drugs! When Cap targets the gang that\'s selling the new designer narcotic, Ice, he receives an accidental overdose that combines with the Super Soldier Serum in his blood. Left permanently enraged, a volatile shield-slinger finds himself in the middle of a street war between the Red Skull and the Kingpin. With deadly villains Crossbones and Bullseye on each side, Cap will need to rely on his friends - but the Ice-induced rage is alienating him from allies like Daredevil and the Black Widow. Collecting: Captain America (1968) #372-386.', 512),
(328, 'Marvel Universe Captain America', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=d_MfCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Howard Chaykin', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=d_MfCwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-d_MfCwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302484453', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-02-10', NULL, 'The major players of 2016\'s biggest blockbuster showcase their skills in all-ages adventures!To save the Earth, Captain America must rescue the Red Skull from his oldest friend: the Winter Soldier! When the Time Stone affects Iron Man, can a de-aging Tony Stark take on dinosaurs? Black Panther shares a high-stakes trust exercise with Hawkeye, then teams with the Hulk to defuse Hydra\'s Madbomb! It\'s up to Falcon to save the day after a mysterious foe turns the Avengers into evil ghosts! When the Avengers \"Hulk out,\" only Black Widow can rescue her teammates! Captain America and Iron Man must go undercover disguised as villains! Collecting MARVEL UNIVERSE AVENGERS ASSEMBLE #3, #11 and #13; MARVEL UNIVERSE AVENGERS ASSEMBLE SEASON 2 #4 and #6; and material from AVENGERS: EARTH\'S MIGHTIEST HEROES (2011) #1 and MARVEL UNIVERSE AVENGERS: EARTH\'S MIGHTIEST HEROES #8.', 128),
(329, 'Zombies Assemble Vol. 1 Manga', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JogzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Yusaku Komiyama', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=JogzDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-JogzDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302501143', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-11-08', NULL, 'Collecting Zombies Assemble #1-3, 0. The original manga is adapted into English for the first time! Time and again, the Avengers have assembled to save the Earth from destruction. But they\'ve never had to face a threat as gruesome and as UNDEAD as this one! Now, Earth\'s Mightiest Heroes must fight to contain an outbreak of horrifying zombies, and stop them from spreading across the Earth! But not all of the Avengers will escape uninfected...', 168),
(330, 'Marvel Cinematic Universe Guidebook', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bl47DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Oâ€™Sullivan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=bl47DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-bl47DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302502065', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-01-03', NULL, 'Collects Guidebook to the Marvel Cinematic Universe - Marvel\'s Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. Season One, Two, Three, Four; Marvel\'s Agent Carter Season One, Two. Level 7 access granted! Just as the MCU exploded onto TV screens, the Guidebooks expand their coverage to take on Marvelâ€™s Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. and Marvelâ€™s Agent Carter â€” including an ALL-NEW exclusive chapter on S.H.I.E.L.D. Season Four! We reveal everything you need to know about the past and present of S.H.I.E.L.D., from the early days of Agent Peggy Carterâ€™s SSR to Agent Phil Coulsonâ€™s ragtag team! Featuring fact sheets, comic-book counterparts, behind-the-scenes artwork and production stills, this Guidebook is packed with profiles of all the major players, including Carter; Coulson; Daisy Johnson, a.k.a. Quake, A.K.A. Skye; Melinda May; Leo Fitz; Jemma Simmons; and Grant Ward. Plus: Howard Stark, Edwin Jarvis, Deathlok, Ghost Rider, the Inhumans and more!', 120),
(331, 'Scholastic Hulk: Misunderstood Monster Digest', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GwTBu0vSd70C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Juan Santacruz', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '0785130403', NULL, 'Marvel Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'See how brilliant scientist Bruce Banner was cursed to transform into the rampaging Hulk.', 96),
(332, 'Secret Wars', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uS0KDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Al Ewing', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=uS0KDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-uS0KDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302488420', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-06-01', NULL, 'Before Secret Wars arrives, everything must end! In the final hours of the Marvel Universe, everyone is a Mighty Avenger! Facing Ragnarok, King Loki makes his move! Magneto, once Earth\'s enemy, fights to be its savior! Black Widow meets her fate still seeking redemption! On the brink of disaster, Ms. Marvel meets Captain Marvel! Punisher goes out with a bang! Silk seeks her family before the sky falls! Ant-Man dances with destiny! Collects CAPTAIN AMERICA AND THE MIGHTY AVENGERS #8-9, LOKI: AGENT OF ASGARD #14-17, MAGNETO #18-21, BLACK WIDOW #19-20, MS. MARVEL #16-19, THE PUNISHER #19-20, SILVER SURFER #13-15, ANT-MAN: LAST DAYS #1, SILK #7, and SPIDER-WOMAN #10.', 528),
(333, 'Captain Marvel', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uzV9DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Michele Fazekas', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=uzV9DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-uzV9DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508562', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-02-13', NULL, 'Collecting Captain Marvel (2016) #1-10. ItÂ’s a bold new frontier for Carol Danvers, soaring to ever greater heights as the leader of the all-new Alpha Flight space program! Yup, Alpha Flight Â— including classic favorites Puck, Sasquatch and Aurora! As EarthÂ’s first line of defense, Carol and her team aim to protect the planet from extraterrestrial threats. But can Carol be both a soldier and a diplomat? DonÂ’t ask Tony Stark! These two old friends are about to face off as bitter enemies in an event that will change Captain MarvelÂ’s life forever! As Inhuman visions of the future kick off a second superhuman civil war, Captain Marvel is at the forefront of the conflict Â— with Iron Man now her implacable enemy. But when tragedy hits close to home, how far will Carol go to protect what she believes in?', 232),
(334, 'Ultimate Galactus Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DduBOtzrqEsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Warren Ellis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=DduBOtzrqEsC&rdid=book-DduBOtzrqEsC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178538', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'The second story arc in the great Ultimate Universe trilogy that began with Ultimate Nightmare! A hidden alien race is trying desperately to keep Man from reaching the stars. Cape Canaveral scientist Phillip Lawson knows of the hideous plan and will use all his considerable power to stop it...the power of Captain Mahr Vehl! While the Kree shock troops send regiment after regiment to strike at the secret S.H.I.E.L.D. facility, the Ultimates and the Ultimate Fantastic Four infiltrate the alien mothership to learn whoor whatGah Lak Tus is! And believe us when we say they get more than they bargained for!', 96),
(335, 'New X-Men by Grant Morrison Vol. 6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EaJCQx8knLAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=EaJCQx8knLAC&rdid=book-EaJCQx8knLAC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785182382', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Once believed to be dead, Magneto, the X-Men\'s greatest adversary, has instead been hiding, waiting to make a move against the team that has thwarted his plans again and again.', 136),
(336, 'Marvel 1602 by Neil Gaiman', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9mcnCKkyq2MC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=9mcnCKkyq2MC&rdid=book-9mcnCKkyq2MC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170747', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2010-02-24', NULL, 'Neil Gaiman\'s vision of the Marvel Universe in the year 1602! The year is 1602, and strange things are stirring in England. In the service of Queen Elizabeth, court magician Dr. Stephen Strange senses that the bizarre weather plaguing the skies above is not of natural origin. Her majesty\'s premier spy, Sir Nicholas Fury, fends off an assassination attempt on the Queen by winged warriors rumored to be in service to a mad despot named Doom. News is spreading of \"witchbreed\" sightings - young men bearing fantastic superhuman powers and abilities. And in the center of the rising chaos is Virginia Dare, a young girl newly arrived from the New World, guarded by a towering Indian warrior. Can Fury and his allies find a connection to these unusual happenings before the whole world ends? Collects Marvel 1602 (2003) #1-8.', 248),
(337, 'Marvel Universe', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=p750DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Saladin Ahmed', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=p750DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-p750DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508197', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-30', NULL, 'Collecting Amazing Spider-Man Annual (2018) #1, Captain America Annual (2018) #1, Daredevil Annual (2018) #1, Silver Surfer Annual (2018) #1, Spider-Man Annual #1, X-Men: Gold Annual #2 And Journey Into Mystery: The Birth Of Krakoa. Untold tales of your favorite Marvel heroes! Before Spider-Man discovered his black costume was a symbiote, what nighttime adventures did it take him on? On an advance scouting mission during World War II, Captain America and Bucky face one of their longest nights! Discover the first meeting between Daredevil and hero-hating NYPD Detective Misty Knight! Join the Silver Surfer on a fateful hunt for a planet to feed to his master, Galactus! Learn what spiderpowered teen Miles Morales was up to during the Skrull Secret Invasion! Witness Kitty PrydeÂ’s first kiss! And join Sgt. Fury and the Howling Commandos as they encounter the living island Krakoa!', 232),
(338, 'X-Men Gold Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AYgzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marc Guggenheim', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=AYgzDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-AYgzDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302501129', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-11-15', NULL, 'Collecting X-Men Gold (2017) #7-12. What does the Secret Empire event have in store for the X-Men? Find out what the new landscape of the Marvel Universe looks like for Kitty, Storm, Colossus, Nightcrawler, Rachel Grey and Old Man Logan. Will they be able to survive in a world dominated by Hydra?', 136),
(339, 'Marvel Horror', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=I6UuDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chris Claremont', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=I6UuDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-I6UuDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302500276', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-10-11', NULL, 'Marvel\'s supernatural superstars star in lavishly illustrated tales of horror! And many of these bizarre adventures from the age of the black-and-white magazine are collected here for the very first time! Blade hunts, Dracula stalks and the Zombie shambles! Meanwhile, night brings the daughter of the diabolical Satana! You\'ll meet Gabriel, Devil Hunter! Discover the magic of Lady Daemon! Fear the Death-Dealing Mannikin! And brave the Haunt of Horror and the Vault of Evil! They\'re rarely seen creepy classics fi lled with werewolves, vampires and monsters unleashed - read them if you dare! COLLECTING: MARVEL PREVIEW #3; MATERIAL FROM MARVEL PREVIEW #7-8, #12; HAUNT OF HORROR (1974) #1-2; MONSTERS UNLEASHED (1973) #3-9; BIZARRE ADVENTURES #25, #33.', 264),
(340, 'Amazing Spider-Man', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UQjz5P14no4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Tom Cohen', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=UQjz5P14no4C&rdid=book-UQjz5P14no4C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178606', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Amazing Spider-Man: The Movie #1-2 & Amazing Spider-Man #75-77. As Peter Parker swings into action as Spider-Man, heÂ’s about to face his first challenge as a super hero! Go Â“between the scenesÂ” with this story-inspired and based upon the new The Amazing Spider-Man movie! Plus, a bonus Spidey tale featuring the Lizard.', 112),
(341, 'Marvel\'s Agents Of S.H.I.E.L.D.', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dm9EDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Troy Benjamin', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dm9EDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-dm9EDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302500771', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-09-13', NULL, 'Marvel\'s Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.Ã¿returns for an action-packed third season! Director Phil Coulson and Agent Daisy Johnson lead the charge amassing a new breed of warrior as Inhumans emerge across the globe. But Coulson and his team soon find out they\'re not alone - there are others on the hunt for these Inhumans, and while some may be friend, others may be foe. Meanwhile, the evil organization Hydra rebuilds from the ground up under a new and deadly leader. Get the top-secret details in this keepsake volume showcasing never-before-seen photography, production-design details, and exclusive behind-the-scenes information and interviews with cast and crew. The events ofÃ¿Marvel\'s Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.\'s third season will rock the characters you know and love to their core. Don\'t miss a single detail with Season Three Declassified!', 248),
(342, 'Amazing Spider-Man By Nick Spencer Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iERrDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nick Spencer', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=iERrDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-iERrDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302507206', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-11-28', NULL, 'Collecting Amazing Spider-Man (2018) #1-5 And Material From Free Comic Book Day 2018 (Amazing Spider-Man). ItÂ’s a new beginning for the Amazing Spider-Man! Peter ParkerÂ’s life is turned upside down when a revelation from the past puts his job, relationships and whole life in jeopardy! And as if thatÂ’s not enough, Spidey must deal with an alien invasion (with a mysterious twist), a new roommate (whoÂ’s secretly the villainous Boomerang), new wrinkles in his love life Â— and a dangerous new enemy! But are you ready for Peter Parker vs. Spider-Man? Someone out there is impersonating Peter but why? Be here as Nick Spencer and Ryan Ottley kick off a brand new era in Spider-ManÂ’s life!', 152),
(343, 'Ultimate X-Men Vol. 7', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KsIJKCmapkIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=KsIJKCmapkIC&rdid=book-KsIJKCmapkIC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178798', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Ultimate X-Men #34-39. Wolverine returns to New York after a short time away from the X-Men -- with a strange strike force armed with sophisticated military technology on his tail. To survive, he\'s forced to rely on the Big Apple\'s own Spider-Man and Daredevil, with a little help from his fellow X-Men!', 144),
(344, 'Avengers', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6HKdAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gerry Conway', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=6HKdAwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-6HKdAwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302377038', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2014-06-25', NULL, 'Collects Avengers (1963) #157-166. It\'s a marathon of villainy as the Avengers face one powerhouse after another! Ultron wants his wedding to herald the Avengers\' funerals, but he\'s only one item on the team\'s calendar of criminals to contain! There\'s also Graviton and the Grim Reaper - the wrath of a god and the wrath of a godslayer! And two Avengers turn against the team - or do they? Guest-starring the Champions, the Defenders, and lots and lots of ants! Featuring heroes of the Wild West, the Golden Age and the X-books!', 184),
(345, 'X-Men', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3E9-MuTiYOUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ed Brubaker', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=3E9-MuTiYOUC&rdid=book-3E9-MuTiYOUC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171461', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2008-11-12', NULL, 'Just when it looked like there was no possibility of a future for mutants, hope arrives. But the X-Men aren\'t there to meet it - the Marauders and Purifiers beat them to it. Now the race is on to get the first new mutant since House of M! This crossover epic may spell the end of mutantkind unless the X-Men can save their entire species from some of their deadliest enemies. Collects X-Men: Messiah Complex One-Shot, Uncanny X-Men (1963) #492-494, New X-Men (2004) #44-46, X-Men (2004) #205-207, X-Factor (2005) #25-27', 352),
(346, 'Pride and Prejudice', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bCQyCCPxlyIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nancy Butler', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=bCQyCCPxlyIC&rdid=book-bCQyCCPxlyIC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170877', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2010-09-22', NULL, 'Tailored from the adored Jane Austen classic, Marvel Comics is proud to present PRIDE AND PREJUDICE! Two-time Rita Award-Winner Nancy Butler and fan-favorite Hugo Petrus fathfully adapt the whimsical tale ofLizzy Bennet and her loveable-if-eccentric family, as they navigate through tricky British social circles. Will Lizzy\'s father manage to marry off his five daughters, despite his wife\'s incessant nagging? And will Lizzy\'s beautiful sister Jane marry the handsome, wealthy Mr. Bingley, or will his brooding friend Mr. Darcy stand between their happiness? Pride and Prejudice #1-5.', 120),
(347, 'Punisher War Journal By Matt Fraction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BTZ9DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Fraction', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=BTZ9DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-BTZ9DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508555', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-02-06', NULL, 'Collecting Punisher War Journal (2006) #1-12 And #1 B&W Edition. The Punisher is back Â— with a vengeance! When a superhuman Civil War breaks out, Frank Castle finds himself square in the crosshairs of G.W. Bridge, a S.H.I.E.L.D. big gun who always gets his man. Frank should be lying low, but when spandex-clad bad guys start carrying badges well, thatÂ’s something he just canÂ’t abide. But can the Punisher play by Captain AmericaÂ’s rules? In the warÂ’s aftermath, Frank infiltrates a super-militia bent on igniting a bloody race war Â— and led by a new Hate-Monger! With Bridge in hot pursuit, can the Punisher disrupt the National ForceÂ’s plans Â— or will he succumb to hate? Plus: An all-new look for the Punisher brings the Winter Soldier out of the woodwork. And can Frank stand up to the alien madness of WORLD WAR HULK?', 344),
(348, 'Avengers Assemble', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3QOFDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ralph Macchio', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=3QOFDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-3QOFDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302510497', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-04-03', NULL, 'Collects Thor: Where Walk the Frost Giants #1, Black Panther: The Sound and the Fury #1, Avengers: Shards of Infinity #1, Ant-Man and the Wasp: Living Legends #1, Captain Marvel: Braver & Mighter #1. Your favorite movie heroes in action-packed comic book adventures! When tragedy strikes Asgard, Thor must hit back against the ice giant Ymir! The villainous Klaw visits sound and fury on Wakanda Â— and the Black Panther! TÂ’Challa joins Black Widow, Captain America and the Falcon on a mission to the moon Â— where awaits a deadly weapon powered by shards of the Cosmic Cube! Scott Â“Ant-ManÂ” Lang lives up to Hank PymÂ’s heroic legacy when he teams with the Wasp for a return trip to Dimension Z Â— home of the Living Eraser! And on Carol Danvers Day, will the Mighty Captain Marvel make it to her own celebration?', 112),
(349, 'Spidey Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=CggyDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Robbie Thompson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=CggyDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-CggyDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302490041', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-08-10', NULL, 'Think you know everything about Peter Parker? Think again! Expect action, adventure and hilarity in equal measure as we head back to high school to explore Pete\'s early days! Modern talent combines with the classic Marvel flavor to present the web-slinging wonder\'s younger years in truly amazing, spectacular, sensational style. It\'s a return to the hassles of overdue homework, not knowing how to talk to girls and a never-ending merry-go-round of madness courtesy of the best roguesÂ’ gallery in comics, each one more incredible than the last. You\'ll love watching Spidey tangle with Doctor Octopus and dig Sandman, the walking beach. With these and more faces from Peter\'s past -both familiar and surprising figures -you\'ll remember what made Spider-Man the world\'s greatest hero in the first place! COLLECTING: SPIDEY #1-6.', 136),
(350, 'Secret Wars', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WcioIYB0Dk8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jim Shooter', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=WcioIYB0Dk8C&rdid=book-WcioIYB0Dk8C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170938', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2008-12-31', NULL, '\"I am from Beyond! Slay your enemies and all you desire shall be yours! Nothing you dream of is impossible for me to accomplish!\" With those words began an era of change rarely rivaled before or since as an awesome entity set heroes and villains against each other, only to learn that the difference between the two was not so clear-cut as it seemed! Loyalties, loves, and line-ups change in the mini-series where one world\'s battles shook a universe! Plus: new looks for Spider-Man, the Thing, and more! Starring the Fantastic Four, the Avengers, the X-Men, and villains of all kinds! Collects Secret Wars (1984) #1-12.', 496),
(351, 'Venom By Donny Cates Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rURrDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Donny Cates', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=rURrDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-rURrDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302507190', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-11-21', NULL, 'Collecting Venom (2018) #1-6. An ancient and primordial evil has been awakened beneath the streets of New York. With it, something equally evil has been awakened in that most wicked of web-slingers: Venom! The symbiote may still be a Lethal Protector of innocents in New York, but this never-before-seen threat could possibly force Venom to relinquish everything it holds dear Â— including its human host, Eddie Brock! As Eddie and Venom summon the strength to defend New York against the most powerful foe theyÂ’ve ever faced, thereÂ’s one more thing standing in their way: Miles Morales, Spider-Man! Two of the hottest creators in comics today, Donny Cates and Ryan Stegman, join forces to deliver a Venom adventure a thousand years in the making!', 136),
(352, 'Amazing Spider-Man', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=s5ATDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Slott', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=s5ATDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-s5ATDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302489199', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-07-06', NULL, 'One of Spider-Man\'s most terrifying villains, MISTER NEGATIVE, has followed him to Shanghai. In Mister Negative\'s service are two beloved Marvel heroes. Wait, TWO HEROES?! What is Mister Negative\'s plan and how did he convince two fan-favorite heroes to join him? COLLECTING: AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (2015) #6-11.', 136),
(353, 'Avengers', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nt9JDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter David', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=nt9JDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-nt9JDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302503628', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-04-04', NULL, 'Collects Avengers: Season One, Avengers (2016) #1. The early days of the Avengers Â— as youÂ’ve never seen them before! A hidden foe manipulates the newly assembled team from the shadows, meticulously sowing the seeds of discord and mistrust Â— and causing the new allies to question the very ties that bind them together as they hunt for the fugitive Hulk. Thor Â— a shape-shifting alien with a secret agenda? Captain America Â— a hoax? Iron Man Â— an enemy conspirator? Their confidence in each other shattered, will the heroes destroy each other before the enemy is revealed? Only the smartest among them will see through the deception...and itÂ’s not whom you think! Plus: The modern-day Avengers come together to stand against their deadliest foe! Captain America, Thor, Vision, Wasp, Spider-Man and Hercules face Kang War One.', 152),
(354, 'Marvel Knights Punisher By Golden, Sniegoski & Wrightson', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fr50DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Christopher Golden', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=fr50DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-fr50DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508180', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-30', NULL, 'Collecting Punisher (1998) #1-4 And Wolverine/Punisher: Revelation #1-4. ItÂ’s a Punisher era like no other! Frank Castle died Â— but that wasnÂ’t the end of his story. Heaven had other plans for the Punisher, and now heÂ’s back from the grave as an angel of vengeance! With a new armory of supernatural weapons, Frank renews his war on crime! HeÂ’s caught between heaven and hell, but his soul has a second chance Â— and if he seizes it, perhaps one day he can see his family again! The PunisherÂ’s deadly mission used to be about vengeance Â— now itÂ’s about redemption! But what happens when Frank joins Wolverine to unravel the mystery of a deadly young mutant named Revelation? Bullet-flying, bone-clawing, maybe even world-ending actionÂ—thatÂ’s what! Featuring the work of legendary horror artist Bernie Wrightson!', 200),
(355, 'Ultimate Spider-Man Vol.8', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=d5j34xvhf6wC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=d5j34xvhf6wC&rdid=book-d5j34xvhf6wC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171249', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Sam Bullit is running for Mayor of New York City on an anti-Spider-Man campaign, and Daily Bugle Editor-in-Chief J. Jonah Jameson is backing him 100%. But who is pulling Bullit\'s strings? None other than the Kingpin of Crime! Collects Ultimate Spider-Man (2000) #46-53.', 184),
(356, 'X-Men', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Q2cgyjR90sMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Greg Pak', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Q2cgyjR90sMC&rdid=book-Q2cgyjR90sMC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171478', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2006-05-31', NULL, 'The mysterious and powerful Phoenix Force is life incarnate, and yet it consumes whole worlds in a moment. Its long history with the X-Men is fraught with tragedy... especially concerning one of the most beloved of their number, Jean Grey. What will happen when the Phoenix returns to Earth in search of the one mortal who could ever contain its power... only to find her dead? Collects X-Men: Phoenix Endsong (2005) #1-5.', 128),
(357, 'Dark Reign', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=spN0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Adam Felber', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=spN0DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-spN0DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508425', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-10', NULL, 'Collects Dark Reign; Skrull Kill Crew #1-5. THE INVASION AINÂ’T DONE UNTIL THE FAT SKRULL SINGS! Pulled from the ashes of 1994 straight to the 21st century, the Skrull Kill Krew is back and more brutal than ever! Television writer and novelist Adam Felber (HBOÂ’s REAL TIME; SchrodingerÂ’s Cat) and superstar artist Paulo Siqueira (Ms.Marvel; Amazing Spider-Man) bring you a disturbing and violent tale of a man with a couple of big guns and a bunch of alien shape shifters who harken back to the earliest days of the Marvel Universe. Pull up a chain gun and join us, wonÂ’t you?', 136),
(358, 'Black Panther', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Mbg3DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Don McGregor', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Mbg3DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Mbg3DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302501495', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-12-27', NULL, 'Collects material from Marvel Comics Presents (1988) #13-37. A Black Panther epic by one of his signature writers, Don McGregor, and true artistic legend Gene Colan! He is T\'Challa, strong, sleek, resilient - prowling the night with panther-like grace! And this is his quest - a stealth mission in South Africa, following rumors that the mother he never knew may still be alive! The Panther will take on soldiers and social injustice in a harrowing tale filled with tragedy and hard-hitting action. He\'ll face bloody, brutal combat as he closes in on his prey as only the Black Panther can - with supreme strength of will. Discover a hidden gem in a Black Panther saga that unfolded across 25 chapters!', 240),
(359, 'Hawkeye Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Slfa87-x0S8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Fraction', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Slfa87-x0S8C&rdid=book-Slfa87-x0S8C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302367749', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Hawkeye #1-5 & Young Avengers Presents #6.Ã¿ The breakout star of this summer\'s blockbuster Avengers film, Clint Barton - aka the self-made hero Hawkeye - fights for justice! With ex-Young Avenger Kate Bishop by his side, he\'s out to prove himself as one of Earth\'s Mightiest Heroes! SHIELD recruits Clint to intercept a packet of incriminating evidence - before he becomes the most wanted man in the world.', 136),
(360, 'Guardians Of The Galaxy', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QZzHDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=QZzHDQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-QZzHDQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302496555', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-03-29', NULL, 'The galaxy is bigger than ever in this giant-sized treasury edition - and this bunch is just the team to guard it! In the wake of two Annihilation events that rocked the Marvel Universe, Peter Quill, the Star-Lord, unites a ragtag group of misfits and loners to stand as its protectors. Among them, the deadly Gamora, Drax the Destroyer, fiery furball Rocket Raccoon and the tree that walks, Groot! Prepare to learn plenty about them - along with the space-faring Iron Man, who joins up as they renew their mission with a special focus on defending the Earth! Plus, join Rocket on the run when he becomes the galaxy\'s most wanted raccoon! It\'s a cosmic mix of action, adventure and fun! COLLECTING: GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY (2013) #0.1, #1; GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY (2008) #1; ROCKET RACCOON (2014) #1.', NULL),
(361, 'Avengers K Book 3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DhIXDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Si Yeon Park', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=DhIXDQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-DhIXDQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302494438', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-11-09', NULL, 'Scarlet Witch. Captain America. Iron Man. Witness the historic fall of the Avengers in South Korean style! Collected for the first time in English, leading Korean publisher Daewon C.I.Â’s original manhwa reimagines some of the most historic Avengers stories of all time for a whole new audience! The return of a long-dead hero. The annihilation of Avengers Mansion. The death of a beloved Avenger. As tragedy mounts on tragedy, will the Avengers turn on each other? Who is behind the worst day in Avengers history? Experience the heartbreaking psychological drama that changed the Avengers forever Â— in brilliant manhwa format. Established South Korean artists and writers take on a famous Avengers saga!', 160),
(362, 'Spider-Man/Deadpool Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=wAcyDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Kelly', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=wAcyDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-wAcyDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302490034', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-08-10', NULL, 'The Webbed Wonder and the Merc with a Mouth are teaming up for their first series EVER! It\'s action, adventure and just a smattering of (b)romance in this episodic epic featuring the WORLD\'S GREATEST SUPER HERO and the star of the WORLD\'S GREATEST COMICS MAGAZINE. Talk about a REAL dynamic duo! COLLECTING: SPIDER-MAN/DEADPOOL #1-6.', 136),
(363, 'Weapon X', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QGJBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Greg Pak', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=QGJBDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-QGJBDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302502584', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-02-21', NULL, 'Collects Weapon X (2017) #7-11. Origin of a monster! The newly reformed Weapon X program took DNA from the most savage genetic anomalies in the world to create a rage-fi lled behemoth of epic proportions. But before they meddled with nature, they started with man. Who volunteered to be experimented on, and what made them the perfect test subject? Learn the startling answers here! The most savage X-book on the stands continues as the Weapon X program\'s lethal agenda rolls on!', 184),
(364, 'Ultimate Galactus Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DduBOtzrqEsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Warren Ellis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=DduBOtzrqEsC&rdid=book-DduBOtzrqEsC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178538', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'The second story arc in the great Ultimate Universe trilogy that began with Ultimate Nightmare! A hidden alien race is trying desperately to keep Man from reaching the stars. Cape Canaveral scientist Phillip Lawson knows of the hideous plan and will use all his considerable power to stop it...the power of Captain Mahr Vehl! While the Kree shock troops send regiment after regiment to strike at the secret S.H.I.E.L.D. facility, the Ultimates and the Ultimate Fantastic Four infiltrate the alien mothership to learn whoor whatGah Lak Tus is! And believe us when we say they get more than they bargained for!', 96),
(365, 'New X-Men by Grant Morrison Vol. 6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EaJCQx8knLAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=EaJCQx8knLAC&rdid=book-EaJCQx8knLAC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785182382', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Once believed to be dead, Magneto, the X-Men\'s greatest adversary, has instead been hiding, waiting to make a move against the team that has thwarted his plans again and again.', 136);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(366, 'Marvel 1602 by Neil Gaiman', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9mcnCKkyq2MC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=9mcnCKkyq2MC&rdid=book-9mcnCKkyq2MC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170747', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2010-02-24', NULL, 'Neil Gaiman\'s vision of the Marvel Universe in the year 1602! The year is 1602, and strange things are stirring in England. In the service of Queen Elizabeth, court magician Dr. Stephen Strange senses that the bizarre weather plaguing the skies above is not of natural origin. Her majesty\'s premier spy, Sir Nicholas Fury, fends off an assassination attempt on the Queen by winged warriors rumored to be in service to a mad despot named Doom. News is spreading of \"witchbreed\" sightings - young men bearing fantastic superhuman powers and abilities. And in the center of the rising chaos is Virginia Dare, a young girl newly arrived from the New World, guarded by a towering Indian warrior. Can Fury and his allies find a connection to these unusual happenings before the whole world ends? Collects Marvel 1602 (2003) #1-8.', 248),
(367, 'Marvel Universe', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=p750DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Saladin Ahmed', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=p750DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-p750DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508197', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-30', NULL, 'Collecting Amazing Spider-Man Annual (2018) #1, Captain America Annual (2018) #1, Daredevil Annual (2018) #1, Silver Surfer Annual (2018) #1, Spider-Man Annual #1, X-Men: Gold Annual #2 And Journey Into Mystery: The Birth Of Krakoa. Untold tales of your favorite Marvel heroes! Before Spider-Man discovered his black costume was a symbiote, what nighttime adventures did it take him on? On an advance scouting mission during World War II, Captain America and Bucky face one of their longest nights! Discover the first meeting between Daredevil and hero-hating NYPD Detective Misty Knight! Join the Silver Surfer on a fateful hunt for a planet to feed to his master, Galactus! Learn what spiderpowered teen Miles Morales was up to during the Skrull Secret Invasion! Witness Kitty PrydeÂ’s first kiss! And join Sgt. Fury and the Howling Commandos as they encounter the living island Krakoa!', 232),
(368, 'X-Men Gold Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AYgzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Marc Guggenheim', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=AYgzDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-AYgzDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302501129', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-11-15', NULL, 'Collecting X-Men Gold (2017) #7-12. What does the Secret Empire event have in store for the X-Men? Find out what the new landscape of the Marvel Universe looks like for Kitty, Storm, Colossus, Nightcrawler, Rachel Grey and Old Man Logan. Will they be able to survive in a world dominated by Hydra?', 136),
(369, 'Marvel Horror', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=I6UuDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chris Claremont', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=I6UuDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-I6UuDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302500276', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-10-11', NULL, 'Marvel\'s supernatural superstars star in lavishly illustrated tales of horror! And many of these bizarre adventures from the age of the black-and-white magazine are collected here for the very first time! Blade hunts, Dracula stalks and the Zombie shambles! Meanwhile, night brings the daughter of the diabolical Satana! You\'ll meet Gabriel, Devil Hunter! Discover the magic of Lady Daemon! Fear the Death-Dealing Mannikin! And brave the Haunt of Horror and the Vault of Evil! They\'re rarely seen creepy classics fi lled with werewolves, vampires and monsters unleashed - read them if you dare! COLLECTING: MARVEL PREVIEW #3; MATERIAL FROM MARVEL PREVIEW #7-8, #12; HAUNT OF HORROR (1974) #1-2; MONSTERS UNLEASHED (1973) #3-9; BIZARRE ADVENTURES #25, #33.', 264),
(370, 'Amazing Spider-Man', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UQjz5P14no4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Tom Cohen', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=UQjz5P14no4C&rdid=book-UQjz5P14no4C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178606', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Amazing Spider-Man: The Movie #1-2 & Amazing Spider-Man #75-77. As Peter Parker swings into action as Spider-Man, heÂ’s about to face his first challenge as a super hero! Go Â“between the scenesÂ” with this story-inspired and based upon the new The Amazing Spider-Man movie! Plus, a bonus Spidey tale featuring the Lizard.', 112),
(371, 'Marvel\'s Agents Of S.H.I.E.L.D.', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dm9EDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Troy Benjamin', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dm9EDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-dm9EDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302500771', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-09-13', NULL, 'Marvel\'s Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.Ã¿returns for an action-packed third season! Director Phil Coulson and Agent Daisy Johnson lead the charge amassing a new breed of warrior as Inhumans emerge across the globe. But Coulson and his team soon find out they\'re not alone - there are others on the hunt for these Inhumans, and while some may be friend, others may be foe. Meanwhile, the evil organization Hydra rebuilds from the ground up under a new and deadly leader. Get the top-secret details in this keepsake volume showcasing never-before-seen photography, production-design details, and exclusive behind-the-scenes information and interviews with cast and crew. The events ofÃ¿Marvel\'s Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.\'s third season will rock the characters you know and love to their core. Don\'t miss a single detail with Season Three Declassified!', 248),
(372, 'Amazing Spider-Man By Nick Spencer Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iERrDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nick Spencer', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=iERrDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-iERrDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302507206', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-11-28', NULL, 'Collecting Amazing Spider-Man (2018) #1-5 And Material From Free Comic Book Day 2018 (Amazing Spider-Man). ItÂ’s a new beginning for the Amazing Spider-Man! Peter ParkerÂ’s life is turned upside down when a revelation from the past puts his job, relationships and whole life in jeopardy! And as if thatÂ’s not enough, Spidey must deal with an alien invasion (with a mysterious twist), a new roommate (whoÂ’s secretly the villainous Boomerang), new wrinkles in his love life Â— and a dangerous new enemy! But are you ready for Peter Parker vs. Spider-Man? Someone out there is impersonating Peter but why? Be here as Nick Spencer and Ryan Ottley kick off a brand new era in Spider-ManÂ’s life!', 152),
(373, 'Ultimate X-Men Vol. 7', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KsIJKCmapkIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=KsIJKCmapkIC&rdid=book-KsIJKCmapkIC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178798', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Ultimate X-Men #34-39. Wolverine returns to New York after a short time away from the X-Men -- with a strange strike force armed with sophisticated military technology on his tail. To survive, he\'s forced to rely on the Big Apple\'s own Spider-Man and Daredevil, with a little help from his fellow X-Men!', 144),
(374, 'Avengers', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6HKdAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gerry Conway', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=6HKdAwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-6HKdAwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302377038', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2014-06-25', NULL, 'Collects Avengers (1963) #157-166. It\'s a marathon of villainy as the Avengers face one powerhouse after another! Ultron wants his wedding to herald the Avengers\' funerals, but he\'s only one item on the team\'s calendar of criminals to contain! There\'s also Graviton and the Grim Reaper - the wrath of a god and the wrath of a godslayer! And two Avengers turn against the team - or do they? Guest-starring the Champions, the Defenders, and lots and lots of ants! Featuring heroes of the Wild West, the Golden Age and the X-books!', 184),
(375, 'X-Men', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3E9-MuTiYOUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ed Brubaker', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=3E9-MuTiYOUC&rdid=book-3E9-MuTiYOUC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171461', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2008-11-12', NULL, 'Just when it looked like there was no possibility of a future for mutants, hope arrives. But the X-Men aren\'t there to meet it - the Marauders and Purifiers beat them to it. Now the race is on to get the first new mutant since House of M! This crossover epic may spell the end of mutantkind unless the X-Men can save their entire species from some of their deadliest enemies. Collects X-Men: Messiah Complex One-Shot, Uncanny X-Men (1963) #492-494, New X-Men (2004) #44-46, X-Men (2004) #205-207, X-Factor (2005) #25-27', 352),
(376, 'Pride and Prejudice', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bCQyCCPxlyIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nancy Butler', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=bCQyCCPxlyIC&rdid=book-bCQyCCPxlyIC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170877', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2010-09-22', NULL, 'Tailored from the adored Jane Austen classic, Marvel Comics is proud to present PRIDE AND PREJUDICE! Two-time Rita Award-Winner Nancy Butler and fan-favorite Hugo Petrus fathfully adapt the whimsical tale ofLizzy Bennet and her loveable-if-eccentric family, as they navigate through tricky British social circles. Will Lizzy\'s father manage to marry off his five daughters, despite his wife\'s incessant nagging? And will Lizzy\'s beautiful sister Jane marry the handsome, wealthy Mr. Bingley, or will his brooding friend Mr. Darcy stand between their happiness? Pride and Prejudice #1-5.', 120),
(377, 'Punisher War Journal By Matt Fraction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BTZ9DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Fraction', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=BTZ9DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-BTZ9DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508555', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-02-06', NULL, 'Collecting Punisher War Journal (2006) #1-12 And #1 B&W Edition. The Punisher is back Â— with a vengeance! When a superhuman Civil War breaks out, Frank Castle finds himself square in the crosshairs of G.W. Bridge, a S.H.I.E.L.D. big gun who always gets his man. Frank should be lying low, but when spandex-clad bad guys start carrying badges well, thatÂ’s something he just canÂ’t abide. But can the Punisher play by Captain AmericaÂ’s rules? In the warÂ’s aftermath, Frank infiltrates a super-militia bent on igniting a bloody race war Â— and led by a new Hate-Monger! With Bridge in hot pursuit, can the Punisher disrupt the National ForceÂ’s plans Â— or will he succumb to hate? Plus: An all-new look for the Punisher brings the Winter Soldier out of the woodwork. And can Frank stand up to the alien madness of WORLD WAR HULK?', 344),
(378, 'Avengers Assemble', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3QOFDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ralph Macchio', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=3QOFDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-3QOFDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302510497', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-04-03', NULL, 'Collects Thor: Where Walk the Frost Giants #1, Black Panther: The Sound and the Fury #1, Avengers: Shards of Infinity #1, Ant-Man and the Wasp: Living Legends #1, Captain Marvel: Braver & Mighter #1. Your favorite movie heroes in action-packed comic book adventures! When tragedy strikes Asgard, Thor must hit back against the ice giant Ymir! The villainous Klaw visits sound and fury on Wakanda Â— and the Black Panther! TÂ’Challa joins Black Widow, Captain America and the Falcon on a mission to the moon Â— where awaits a deadly weapon powered by shards of the Cosmic Cube! Scott Â“Ant-ManÂ” Lang lives up to Hank PymÂ’s heroic legacy when he teams with the Wasp for a return trip to Dimension Z Â— home of the Living Eraser! And on Carol Danvers Day, will the Mighty Captain Marvel make it to her own celebration?', 112),
(379, 'Spidey Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=CggyDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Robbie Thompson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=CggyDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-CggyDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302490041', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-08-10', NULL, 'Think you know everything about Peter Parker? Think again! Expect action, adventure and hilarity in equal measure as we head back to high school to explore Pete\'s early days! Modern talent combines with the classic Marvel flavor to present the web-slinging wonder\'s younger years in truly amazing, spectacular, sensational style. It\'s a return to the hassles of overdue homework, not knowing how to talk to girls and a never-ending merry-go-round of madness courtesy of the best roguesÂ’ gallery in comics, each one more incredible than the last. You\'ll love watching Spidey tangle with Doctor Octopus and dig Sandman, the walking beach. With these and more faces from Peter\'s past -both familiar and surprising figures -you\'ll remember what made Spider-Man the world\'s greatest hero in the first place! COLLECTING: SPIDEY #1-6.', 136),
(380, 'Secret Wars', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WcioIYB0Dk8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jim Shooter', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=WcioIYB0Dk8C&rdid=book-WcioIYB0Dk8C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170938', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2008-12-31', NULL, '\"I am from Beyond! Slay your enemies and all you desire shall be yours! Nothing you dream of is impossible for me to accomplish!\" With those words began an era of change rarely rivaled before or since as an awesome entity set heroes and villains against each other, only to learn that the difference between the two was not so clear-cut as it seemed! Loyalties, loves, and line-ups change in the mini-series where one world\'s battles shook a universe! Plus: new looks for Spider-Man, the Thing, and more! Starring the Fantastic Four, the Avengers, the X-Men, and villains of all kinds! Collects Secret Wars (1984) #1-12.', 496),
(381, 'Venom By Donny Cates Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rURrDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Donny Cates', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=rURrDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-rURrDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302507190', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-11-21', NULL, 'Collecting Venom (2018) #1-6. An ancient and primordial evil has been awakened beneath the streets of New York. With it, something equally evil has been awakened in that most wicked of web-slingers: Venom! The symbiote may still be a Lethal Protector of innocents in New York, but this never-before-seen threat could possibly force Venom to relinquish everything it holds dear Â— including its human host, Eddie Brock! As Eddie and Venom summon the strength to defend New York against the most powerful foe theyÂ’ve ever faced, thereÂ’s one more thing standing in their way: Miles Morales, Spider-Man! Two of the hottest creators in comics today, Donny Cates and Ryan Stegman, join forces to deliver a Venom adventure a thousand years in the making!', 136),
(382, 'Amazing Spider-Man', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=s5ATDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Slott', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=s5ATDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-s5ATDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302489199', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-07-06', NULL, 'One of Spider-Man\'s most terrifying villains, MISTER NEGATIVE, has followed him to Shanghai. In Mister Negative\'s service are two beloved Marvel heroes. Wait, TWO HEROES?! What is Mister Negative\'s plan and how did he convince two fan-favorite heroes to join him? COLLECTING: AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (2015) #6-11.', 136),
(383, 'Avengers', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nt9JDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter David', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=nt9JDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-nt9JDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302503628', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-04-04', NULL, 'Collects Avengers: Season One, Avengers (2016) #1. The early days of the Avengers Â— as youÂ’ve never seen them before! A hidden foe manipulates the newly assembled team from the shadows, meticulously sowing the seeds of discord and mistrust Â— and causing the new allies to question the very ties that bind them together as they hunt for the fugitive Hulk. Thor Â— a shape-shifting alien with a secret agenda? Captain America Â— a hoax? Iron Man Â— an enemy conspirator? Their confidence in each other shattered, will the heroes destroy each other before the enemy is revealed? Only the smartest among them will see through the deception...and itÂ’s not whom you think! Plus: The modern-day Avengers come together to stand against their deadliest foe! Captain America, Thor, Vision, Wasp, Spider-Man and Hercules face Kang War One.', 152),
(384, 'Marvel Knights Punisher By Golden, Sniegoski & Wrightson', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fr50DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Christopher Golden', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=fr50DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-fr50DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508180', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-30', NULL, 'Collecting Punisher (1998) #1-4 And Wolverine/Punisher: Revelation #1-4. ItÂ’s a Punisher era like no other! Frank Castle died Â— but that wasnÂ’t the end of his story. Heaven had other plans for the Punisher, and now heÂ’s back from the grave as an angel of vengeance! With a new armory of supernatural weapons, Frank renews his war on crime! HeÂ’s caught between heaven and hell, but his soul has a second chance Â— and if he seizes it, perhaps one day he can see his family again! The PunisherÂ’s deadly mission used to be about vengeance Â— now itÂ’s about redemption! But what happens when Frank joins Wolverine to unravel the mystery of a deadly young mutant named Revelation? Bullet-flying, bone-clawing, maybe even world-ending actionÂ—thatÂ’s what! Featuring the work of legendary horror artist Bernie Wrightson!', 200),
(385, 'Ultimate Spider-Man Vol.8', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=d5j34xvhf6wC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=d5j34xvhf6wC&rdid=book-d5j34xvhf6wC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171249', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Sam Bullit is running for Mayor of New York City on an anti-Spider-Man campaign, and Daily Bugle Editor-in-Chief J. Jonah Jameson is backing him 100%. But who is pulling Bullit\'s strings? None other than the Kingpin of Crime! Collects Ultimate Spider-Man (2000) #46-53.', 184),
(386, 'X-Men', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Q2cgyjR90sMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Greg Pak', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Q2cgyjR90sMC&rdid=book-Q2cgyjR90sMC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785171478', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2006-05-31', NULL, 'The mysterious and powerful Phoenix Force is life incarnate, and yet it consumes whole worlds in a moment. Its long history with the X-Men is fraught with tragedy... especially concerning one of the most beloved of their number, Jean Grey. What will happen when the Phoenix returns to Earth in search of the one mortal who could ever contain its power... only to find her dead? Collects X-Men: Phoenix Endsong (2005) #1-5.', 128),
(387, 'Dark Reign', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=spN0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Adam Felber', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=spN0DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-spN0DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302508425', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-01-10', NULL, 'Collects Dark Reign; Skrull Kill Crew #1-5. THE INVASION AINÂ’T DONE UNTIL THE FAT SKRULL SINGS! Pulled from the ashes of 1994 straight to the 21st century, the Skrull Kill Krew is back and more brutal than ever! Television writer and novelist Adam Felber (HBOÂ’s REAL TIME; SchrodingerÂ’s Cat) and superstar artist Paulo Siqueira (Ms.Marvel; Amazing Spider-Man) bring you a disturbing and violent tale of a man with a couple of big guns and a bunch of alien shape shifters who harken back to the earliest days of the Marvel Universe. Pull up a chain gun and join us, wonÂ’t you?', 136),
(388, 'Black Panther', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Mbg3DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Don McGregor', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Mbg3DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Mbg3DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302501495', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-12-27', NULL, 'Collects material from Marvel Comics Presents (1988) #13-37. A Black Panther epic by one of his signature writers, Don McGregor, and true artistic legend Gene Colan! He is T\'Challa, strong, sleek, resilient - prowling the night with panther-like grace! And this is his quest - a stealth mission in South Africa, following rumors that the mother he never knew may still be alive! The Panther will take on soldiers and social injustice in a harrowing tale filled with tragedy and hard-hitting action. He\'ll face bloody, brutal combat as he closes in on his prey as only the Black Panther can - with supreme strength of will. Discover a hidden gem in a Black Panther saga that unfolded across 25 chapters!', 240),
(389, 'Hawkeye Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Slfa87-x0S8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Fraction', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Slfa87-x0S8C&rdid=book-Slfa87-x0S8C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302367749', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Hawkeye #1-5 & Young Avengers Presents #6.Ã¿ The breakout star of this summer\'s blockbuster Avengers film, Clint Barton - aka the self-made hero Hawkeye - fights for justice! With ex-Young Avenger Kate Bishop by his side, he\'s out to prove himself as one of Earth\'s Mightiest Heroes! SHIELD recruits Clint to intercept a packet of incriminating evidence - before he becomes the most wanted man in the world.', 136),
(390, 'Guardians Of The Galaxy', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QZzHDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=QZzHDQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-QZzHDQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302496555', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-03-29', NULL, 'The galaxy is bigger than ever in this giant-sized treasury edition - and this bunch is just the team to guard it! In the wake of two Annihilation events that rocked the Marvel Universe, Peter Quill, the Star-Lord, unites a ragtag group of misfits and loners to stand as its protectors. Among them, the deadly Gamora, Drax the Destroyer, fiery furball Rocket Raccoon and the tree that walks, Groot! Prepare to learn plenty about them - along with the space-faring Iron Man, who joins up as they renew their mission with a special focus on defending the Earth! Plus, join Rocket on the run when he becomes the galaxy\'s most wanted raccoon! It\'s a cosmic mix of action, adventure and fun! COLLECTING: GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY (2013) #0.1, #1; GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY (2008) #1; ROCKET RACCOON (2014) #1.', NULL),
(391, 'Avengers K Book 3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DhIXDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Si Yeon Park', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=DhIXDQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-DhIXDQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302494438', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-11-09', NULL, 'Scarlet Witch. Captain America. Iron Man. Witness the historic fall of the Avengers in South Korean style! Collected for the first time in English, leading Korean publisher Daewon C.I.Â’s original manhwa reimagines some of the most historic Avengers stories of all time for a whole new audience! The return of a long-dead hero. The annihilation of Avengers Mansion. The death of a beloved Avenger. As tragedy mounts on tragedy, will the Avengers turn on each other? Who is behind the worst day in Avengers history? Experience the heartbreaking psychological drama that changed the Avengers forever Â— in brilliant manhwa format. Established South Korean artists and writers take on a famous Avengers saga!', 160),
(392, 'Spider-Man/Deadpool Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=wAcyDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Kelly', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=wAcyDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-wAcyDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302490034', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-08-10', NULL, 'The Webbed Wonder and the Merc with a Mouth are teaming up for their first series EVER! It\'s action, adventure and just a smattering of (b)romance in this episodic epic featuring the WORLD\'S GREATEST SUPER HERO and the star of the WORLD\'S GREATEST COMICS MAGAZINE. Talk about a REAL dynamic duo! COLLECTING: SPIDER-MAN/DEADPOOL #1-6.', 136),
(393, 'Weapon X', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QGJBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Greg Pak', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=QGJBDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-QGJBDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302502584', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-02-21', NULL, 'Collects Weapon X (2017) #7-11. Origin of a monster! The newly reformed Weapon X program took DNA from the most savage genetic anomalies in the world to create a rage-fi lled behemoth of epic proportions. But before they meddled with nature, they started with man. Who volunteered to be experimented on, and what made them the perfect test subject? Learn the startling answers here! The most savage X-book on the stands continues as the Weapon X program\'s lethal agenda rolls on!', 184),
(394, 'Thanos', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=V-BJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jim Starlin', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=V-BJDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-V-BJDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302503673', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-04-04', NULL, 'Jim Starlin and Alan Davis return in the first of a new trilogy! The Mad Titan has everything he ever wanted - but satisfaction is not in Thanos\' vocabulary. When a temporal distortion on Titan draws his attention, he finds the purpose he\'s been searching for: saving himself! An old enemy lurks in the far future, and it\'ll take the combined wits of Thanos, his brother Eros, and time-travel master Kang the Conqueror to stop it - and save the multiverse. But there are other players in this cosmic chess game - and Thanos may fi nd himself outmatched! What lies ahead for the so-called Avatar of Death?', 112),
(395, 'Ax', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RofLFA4c1KQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Ernie ColÃ³n', NULL, 'Fantasy comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '087135490X', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 40),
(396, 'Fantastic Four', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0C25_tXs4lcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Frost', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '0785118098', NULL, 'Marvel Enterprises', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'The comic book adaptation of the 2005 movie Fantastic Four, which describes how they became superheroes. Includes three classic comic book adventures of the Four.', 120),
(397, 'Thor Epic Collection', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qBQXDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Stan Lee', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=qBQXDQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-qBQXDQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302494681', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2016-11-02', NULL, 'Collects Journey Into Mystery (1952) #110-125 and Annual #1, Thor (1966) #126-130, and material from Not Brand Echh #3. Stan Lee and Jack Kirby, the creative team that sparked the Marvel revolution, set off on Asgardian adventures featuring the fight to end all fights between Thor and the Incredible Hulk! ThereÂ’s also the return of the Grey Gargoyle, the debut of the Absorbing Man and the unstoppable Destroyer, Thor and LokiÂ’s exile to Skornheim and the introduction of Hercules and the Greek gods! And it all leads to an epic adventure that pits Thor against Hercules and concludes in the depths of PlutoÂ’s Underworld! Lest we forget, Tales of Asgard backs up every issue with the origins of MarvelÂ’s Norse pantheon of heroes, villains and mystic lands; the secrets of Ragnarok; and much more!', 504),
(398, 'Deadpool Classic Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PU71qmpI1uUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Fabian Nicieza', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=PU71qmpI1uUC&rdid=book-PU71qmpI1uUC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785170396', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2008-05-07', NULL, 'He\'s the Merc with a Mouth, Deadpool, and with sidekick Weasel in tow, he sets out on a quest for romance, money, and mayhem - not necessarily in that order - only to learn he\'s being hunted by an enemy he killed years before! As if that isn\'t enough, the Juggernaut crashes into the action, and it\'s the unstoppable vs. the un-shut-up-able! But all may not be lost if the sultry Siryn can inject a little sanity into the proceedings! Will Deadpool be steered toward a better life by his new heartthrob, or stay the chaotic course he\'s set for himself? The answer is Yes! Guest-starring the New Mutants, Banshee, Sasquatch, and more! Collects Deadpool (1993) #1-4, Deadpool (1994) #1-4, Deadpool (1997) #1.', 264),
(399, 'Weapon X', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zWBZj3ntEr4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Barry Windsor-Smith', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '0785100334', NULL, 'Marvel Enterprises', '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 128),
(400, 'Thor', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rsSDBQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Carey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=rsSDBQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-rsSDBQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302368357', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2014-12-10', NULL, 'Collects Thor: Wolves of the North, Thor: The Truth of History & Thor Annual #1.Ã¿ Hela lays siege to Asgard, and demon hordes are loose on Earth. Thor must make a dangerous bargain with a mortal woman in order to launch a last assault on the forces of death. Then legendary writer-artist Alan Davis sends Thor on one of his most epic adventures in history! Plus, enemies from Thor\'s past are back and howling for revenge!', 104),
(401, 'Wolverine Noir', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=L_esbcQcr4AC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Stuart Moore', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=L_esbcQcr4AC&rdid=book-L_esbcQcr4AC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785182184', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'The Bowery, 1937. Jim Logan, the fiercest knife expert in New York, runs a seedy detective agency called \"LOGAN & LOGAN\"...along with his useless, halfwit brother, Dog. They\'re the best they are at what they do. But when a swanky dame named Mariko Yashida struts into the office, she opens up a world of hurt for Logan, forcing him to revisit his painful, bloody past. The latest in the Marvel Noir series, Wolverine Noir reunites the acclaimed Wolverine team of Stuart Moore (Iron Man) and C.P. Smith (The Programme). Collects Wolverine Noir #1-4.', 112),
(402, 'Incredible Hulk Epic Collection', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KGOgDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Roy Thomas', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=KGOgDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-KGOgDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302515829', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-09-25', NULL, 'Collects Incredible Hulk (1968) #118-137, Marvel Super-Heroes (1967) #16. Itâ€™s time to Hulk out! We begin with bare-fisted battles against the Sub-Mariner, the Inhumans and the bizarre swamp beast the Glob! Then, the Hulk and the Thing go mano a mano! With Reed Richardsâ€™ help, the man inside the monster is freed, allowing Bruce Banner to step up to the wedding altar with Betty Ross. But when the Leader and the Rhino return, happily ever after is the last thing they have in mind! Thereâ€™s also an earth-shaking battle between the Hulk and the Avengers, the menace of the Absorbing Man, a team-up with Dr. Strange, the unbelievable separation of Banner and the Hulk into separate beings â€” and donâ€™t forget the hordes of Hydra! This Hulk-sized Epic Collection will leave you feeling green and loving it! Collecting INCREDIBLE HULK (1968) #118-137 and MARVEL SUPER-HEROES (1967) #16.', 440),
(403, 'Avengers Vs. Thanos', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ed9JDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Caramagna', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ed9JDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-ed9JDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302503611', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-04-04', NULL, 'Collects Marvel Universe Avengers Assemble Season 2 #2, 11-12, 15-16 and material from #1. Featuring screen-capture images from MARVELÂ’S AVENGERS ASSEMBLE SEASON TWO! The Avengers face the machinations of the Mad Titan himself Â— Thanos! And you know he must be bad when even the Red Skull is fleeing from him! Thanos seeks the cosmic Power Stone Â— but will the robotic Arsenal, built by Tony StarkÂ’s father, help keep it out of the TitanÂ’s grasp? Thanos has targeted all the Stones necessary to form the Infinity Gauntlet Â— and if he succeeds, heÂ’ll have ultimate power in the palm of his hand! Black Widow has a plan to save the universe Â— but it will take all of the Avengers to pull it off! Captain America and Iron Man donÂ’t see eye-to-eye, but can they put aside their differences in time to come together for the final battle to save everything?', 128),
(404, 'Motherlands (2018-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=n7E-DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1810800015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-01-31', NULL, 'In a crazed future where unhinged technologies and interconnected parallel Earths have given rise to a spectacular class of super-criminal, the most beloved celebrities arenâ€™t actors or rock stars, but the bounty hunters who traverse an exotic multiverse in search of impossible prey! But when the spotlight-shunning, strait-laced tracer known as Tab finds herself in an ultra-violent race for her greatest prize yet, sheâ€™s forced to work with her greatest enemy, the only person capable of IDing him: her own elderly, overbearing and hypercritical mother, who was once the most fabulous and celebrated bounty hunter of them all.', 22),
(405, 'House of Whispers (2018-) #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hbl0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nalo Hopkinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853600045001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-12-12', NULL, 'The mysterious infection doctors are calling Ã’CotardÃ•s DelusionÃ“ spreads, trapping countless souls in the Dreaming and leaving their physical bodies yearning for death. To handle her own case of the disease, Latoya decides to go on risky adventures, believing sheÃ•ll feel alive the closer she gets to death, while her girlfriend Maggie tries to find a true cure. Meanwhile, in the Dreaming, Erzulie Dantor calls her war council of Shakpana, Turtle and Uncle Monday to find a way to take her sister-selfÃ•s bayou and boat back to their realm. Shakpana, however, seems to be more interested in making his way back to the Waking WorldÃ‰', 22),
(406, 'Basketful of Heads (2019-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mvq5DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Hill', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1999500015001', NULL, 'Vertigo/Fall', '2019-10-30', NULL, 'The rain lashes the grassy dunes of Brody Island, and seagulls scream above the bay. A slender figure in a raincoat carries a large wicker basket, which looks like it might be full of melonsâ€¦covered by a bloodstained scrap of the American flag. This is the story of June Branch, a young woman trapped with four cunning criminals who have snatched her boyfriend for deranged reasons of their own. Now she must fight for her life with the help of an impossible 8th-century Viking axe that can pass through a manâ€™s neck in a single swipe-and leave the severed head still conscious and capable of supernatural speech. Each disembodied head has a malevolent story of its own to tell, and it isnâ€™t long before June finds herself in a desperate struggle to hack through their lies and manipulations...racing to save the man she loves before time runs out. Plus, in the premiere chapter of the backup story â€œSea Dogs,â€ which sails across all the Hill House Comics titles!The rain lashes the grassy dunes of Brody Island, and seagulls scream above the bay. A slender figure in a raincoat carries a large wicker basket, which looks like it might be full of melonsâ€¦covered by a bloodstained scrap of the American flag. This is the story of June Branch, a young woman trapped with four cunning criminals who have snatched her boyfriend for deranged reasons of their own. Now she must fight for her life with the help of an impossible 8th-century Viking axe that can pass through a manâ€™s neck in a single swipe-and leave the severed head still conscious and capable of supernatural speech. Each disembodied head has a malevolent story of its own to tell, and it isnâ€™t long before June finds herself in a desperate struggle to hack through their lies and manipulations...racing to save the man she loves before time runs out. Plus, in the premiere chapter of the backup story â€œSea Dogs,â€ which sails across all the Hill House Comics titles!', 26),
(407, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KntrDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-10-24', NULL, 'From the SANDMAN UNIVERSE #1, itÃ•s the return of Neil GaimanÃ•s magical morality fable in an all-new series written by Kat Howard (Roses and Rot, An Unkindness of Magicians) and drawn by Tom Fowler (DOOM PATROL)! Timothy Hunter may be destined tobecome the most powerful magician in the universe, but heÃ•s still a London teenager, and having magical abilities complicates things more than it helps. ItÃ•s not like he can use magic to pass his exams, stop being bullied or convince his cute friend to date him. And while TimÃ•s trying to live his life, there are cultists who want to kill him, believing his power will eventually corrupt him into becoming a merciless mage. Oh, and those are the good guys. Luckily, his new substitute teacher is more than she appears, and may be able to help Tim discover the mystery behind the Books of MagicÃ‰', 22),
(408, 'Preacher Special: Saint of Killers #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dOOWAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0101100025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Learn how the Saint of Killers survived the Civil War and was transformed from a ruthless killing machine into a gentle man. But when the needless death of his family awakens the slumbering killer within, his unstoppable thirst for vengeance might damn his soul for all time.', NULL),
(409, 'DMZ The Deluxe Edition Book Five', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=t4LqCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Wood', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=t4LqCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-t4LqCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401266127', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2015-12-08', NULL, 'One of VertigoÃ•s longest-running series comes to its stunning conclusion. After six years, Matty Roth\'s story and the Second American Civil War comes to an end. As the war enters its final weeks, Matty is given an unbelievable second chance, a golden opportunity to report once again from the DMZ-not as a network lackey but as an unbiased observer for the court of world opinion, to ensure both sides stay honest. He is given total access, total freedom, and is determined to do right by the city where he once failed miserably. Brian Wood and artist Riccardo Burchielli present their final chapter and remove any doubt that DMZ is, at its core, a love letter to New York City. DMZ: THE DELUXE EDITION BOOK FIVE collects issues #60-72.', 274),
(410, 'Fables Deluxe Book 12', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jv_uCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Levitz', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=jv_uCwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-jv_uCwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401269982', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-05-24', NULL, 'The award-winning Vertigo series continues with a new introduction by former DC Comics President and Publisher Paul Levitz, and a special sketchbook section by series artist Mark Buckingham. Imagine that all the characters from the worldâ€™s most beloved storybooks were real-real, and living among us, with all of their powers intact. How would they cope with life in our mundane, un-magical reality? The answer can be found in FABLES, Bill Willinghamâ€™s celebrated reimagining of the venerable fairy tale canon. From Snow White and the Big Bad Wolf to Goldilocks and Little Boy Blue, the folk tales of old are reborn here as exiles living in the magically camouflaged New York City neighborhood of Fabletown. FABLES: THE DELUXE EDITION BOOK TWELVE includes the worlds-shaking events of â€œSuper Teamâ€ and â€œInherit the Wind,â€ as well as the pivotal tales â€œThe Ascentâ€ and â€œAll in a Single Nightâ€ from FABLES #101-113.', 320),
(411, 'The Kitchen (Mass Market Edition)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RKukDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ollie Masters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=RKukDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-RKukDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781779502193', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-07-23', NULL, 'Donâ€™t miss this new edition of the title that inspired the upcoming movie from New Line Cinema! New York City, late 1970s. In the world of THE KITCHEN, the Irish gangs of Hellâ€™s Kitchen rule the neighborhood, bringing terror to the streets and doing the dirty work for the Italian mafia-but after the leaders are locked up in prison, itâ€™s up to their wives to keep running the rackets. And once they get a taste of the fast life and easy money, it wonâ€™t be easy to stop. Collects THE KITCHEN #1-8.', 176),
(412, 'Flinch (1999-) #15', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gPItDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Will Pfeifer', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0170300155001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-06-02', NULL, '\"Alienation\" is the buzzword for three grim tales. A hi-tech future where privacy is illegal makes everyone a peeping Tom in \"Watchful.\" A bored cruise director on an excursion for senior citizen singles braces for turbulent waters in \"A Night to Forget.\" And a phony telephone psychic starts seeing her callers\' real futures in \"The Future\'s So Bright.\"', 23),
(413, 'Saga of the Swamp Thing Book Four', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dmd-AgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Alan Moore', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dmd-AgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-dmd-AgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401247935', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2014-02-18', NULL, 'Continuing the collection of master comics writer Alan Mooreâ€™s award-winning run on THE SAGA OF THE SWAMP THING, this fourth volume brings Swamp Thingâ€™s quest for self-discovery with the mystic John Constantine to its shattering conclusion. A harbinger of doom has been released with the sole charge of waking an evil beyond comprehension, and Swamp Thing, John Constantine, Deadman, The Phantom Stranger, Etrigan the Demon, The Spectre and other masters of the occult must unite against the dark forces that threaten to eradicate Heavenâ€™s light. Collecting SWAMP THING #43-50.', NULL),
(414, 'Heart Throbs (1998-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hKbpDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Azzarello', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0143100025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-09-29', NULL, 'Love\'s a 4-letter word in this offbeat miniseries of truly weird romance stories. In \"The Other Side of Town\" a small-town sheriff investigating a murder discovers that the prime suspect just might be his high school sweetheart. Then in \"Romancing the Stone\" a man undergoing radical therapy for his peculiar obsession finds that the road to recovery may be the object of his desire. And finally, in \"Jericho,\" an exotic dancer learns that the walls dividing titillation and true romance are higher than they seem.', 22),
(415, 'Strange Adventures (1999-) #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E5l9DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Azzarello', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0165500045001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-12-29', NULL, 'Crop circles and cattle mutilations, killer viruses and extraterrestrial invaders converge as the unforgettable Vertigo miniseries concludes. A reporter investigating a series of cattle mutilations discovers an extraterrestrial conspiracy that cuts even deeper in \"Native Tongue,\" a vicious Lothario with a outlandish modus operandi makes a move on the wrong woman in \"Perfect Stranger,\" and a gaggle of suburban kids prove to be a serial killer\'s worst nightmare in \"Latch Key.\"', 22),
(416, 'Gangland (1998-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WJuRDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Pocsik', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0133000025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-06-12', NULL, 'In \'Platinum Nights\' (written by Lucius Shepard and illustrated by James Romberger), a gangbanger embarks on a wild and dangerous Big Apple spending spree. In \'Big Shot\' (written by Jamie Delano and illustrated by Randy DuBurke), a captain of industry revisits his brutal rise to power and braces for his own lieutenant\'s power move. And in \'Killer Smile\' (written by Simon Revelstroke and illustrated by Richard Corben), a mobster revisits his Hell\'s Kitchen stomping grounds for a fateful encounter with his childhood pal.', 24);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(417, 'The Twilight Children', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8fvuCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gilbert Hernandez', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=8fvuCwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-8fvuCwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401269388', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-05-17', NULL, 'Comics legends Gilbert Hernandez (LOVE AND ROCKETS), Darwyn Cooke (DC: THE NEW FRONTIER) and Dave Stewart (HELLBOY) craft a haunting and unforgettable tale of magical realism with THE TWILIGHT CHILDREN. No one knows what the mysterious glowing spheres are, or where they come from. The only thing that matters to the residents of the beachside village where the orbs manifest is what they do when they appear. They blind children and imbue them with psychic abilities. They destroy homes, and make entire families disappear. They attract scientists, government experts and secret agents, each with their own agenda. And they inflame small-town passions-secret lovers, simmering resentments-to a fever pitch. Now, theyÃ•ve brought Ela. Materializing on the beach just as mysteriously as one of the orbs, this beautiful woman says nothing, but seems to harbor unspeakable power. Will she help to save the town, or destroy it? Or is it Ela herself who is really in danger? Collects the four-issue VERTIGO miniseries.', 168),
(418, 'High Level (2019-2019) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dOp_DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rob Sheridan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1878900015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-09-01', NULL, 'Hundreds of years after the world ended and human society was rebuilt from scratch, a self-interested smuggler is forced to traverse a new continent of danger and mystery to deliver a child messiah to High Level, a mythical city at the top of the world from which no one has ever returned. Donâ€™t miss the start of a new series from writer Rob Sheridan, co-creator of Nine Inch Nailsâ€™ groundbreaking Year Zero alternate-reality game!', 22),
(419, 'Imaginary Fiends', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=caKaDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Tim Seeley', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=caKaDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-caKaDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781779501554', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-06-11', NULL, 'Ã’Polly Peachpit.Ã“ Those were the words 10-year-old Brinke Calle said when she was found covered in her own blood by the woods in rural Cannon Falls. Her best friend, Melba, had just attempted to murder her because a spider girl named Polly Peachpit told her to. Since that day, Melba has spent seven years in a mental health facility. Tomorrow is her 18th birthday. Tomorrow sheÃ•ll be transferred to a federal prison. Tomorrow her real sentence will begin. That is, until she receives a visit from FBI Agent Virgil Crockett. Crockett explains that there is another world beyond ours, where hungry, spectral aliens stalk the minds of the impressionable and weak. These things, called IMPs (Interdimensional Mental Parasites) feed on compliance. They convince hosts to do things for them, and the more they feed, the stronger they become. More IMPs stream into the world each day, invisible to everyone but his or her hosts.', 138),
(420, 'The Sandman Presents: Everything You Always Wanted To Know About Dream (2001-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=D6NBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0268800015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-10-29', NULL, 'Have you ever wondered if Dreams have dreams of their own? Or what causes nightmares? Or why you should never wake a sleepwalker? These satirical short stories reveal it all.', 38),
(421, 'Animal Man by Grant Morrison Book One 30th Anniversary Deluxe Edition', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Jal8DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Jal8DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Jal8DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401296834', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-12-18', NULL, 'Ã’Morrison told the story of a kind-hearted, vegetarian hero who loses his family and is pushed to the brink of insanity before confronting his author in the runÃ•s extraordinarily meta finale.Ã“ Ã‘Rolling Stone Ã’Grant Morrison overhauled Animal Man in a typically imaginative manner.Ã“ Ã‘Entertainment Weekly Ã’Morrison quickly became the hottest writer in the industry.Ã“ Ã‘Complex Magazine Buddy Baker, a.k.a. Ã’the Man with Animal Powers,Ã“ is a second-rate superhero, devoted father and animal activist. There isnÃ•t much money in the hero game, and with a wife and kids to support, Buddy soon finds himself torn between trying to make a living through traditional super-heroics and getting more deeply involved in the questionably legal world of animal rights activism. But in todayÃ•s world, with real-life issues, who really needs Animal ManÃ•s protection? Is it humankind or the animals? Or is it Buddy himself? From the Eisner Award-winning and New York Times best-selling writer Grant Morrison comes one of his earliest, now classic, works exploring the nature of reality itself through the lens of a down-on-his-luck family-man superhero. This first of two 30th Anniversary Deluxe Edition hardcovers collects Animal Man #1-13, the characterÃ•s dimension-spanning creation tale from Secret Origins #39 and an introduction by Grant Morrison.', 368),
(422, 'Heart Throbs (1998-) #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=a3gWDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter Milligan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0143100035001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-10-13', NULL, 'Three unorthodox tales of love and romance: A lovestruck female alien battles a siren planet for the affections of a handsome spaceman in Ã’Apposites AttractÃ“ (written by Simon Revelstroke, with art by Richard Corben); a beautiful time traveler serves up some poetic justice to a nineteenth-century Lothario in Ã’Mister RightÃ“ (written by Peter Milligan, with art by Eduardo Risso); and a retelling of Ã’Sleeping BeautyÃ“ includes an exploding princess, an uzi-toting prince and a witch with an elf fetish.', 22),
(423, 'Slash & Burn Vol. 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=SVeoDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Si Spencer', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=SVeoDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-SVeoDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401271886', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-08-09', NULL, 'WHERE THEREÃ•S SMOKEÃ‰ Rosheen Hayes likes it hot. As one of the only female firefighters in her small South Dakota town, she gets up close and personal with the flames every day. But thereÃ•s something else burning deep inside of her. Something bright and forbidden. Rosheen doesnÃ•t just fight fires-she starts them as well. As a child, Rosheen was part of a clandestine club of young firebugs-orphans thrown together by chance and fused together one matchstick at a time. She thought that sheÃ•d left that all behind, but then a routine call turns up a smoking body with links to her own shadowy past. Before long, more bodies are piling up-and, like a moth to a flame, Rosheen is drawn inexorably back into her own arousing addiction. Writer Si Spencer and artists Max Dunbar and Ande Parks turn up the heat in SLASH & BURN, a scorchingly original crime thriller collecting issues #1-6 of the Vertigo miniseries.', 168),
(424, 'Books of Magic Book One', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LTPGDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Ney Rieber', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LTPGDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-LTPGDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401278175', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-05-30', NULL, 'Continuing from celebrated author Neil GaimanÃ•s iconic graphic novel, the complete chronicles of Tim Hunter are finally brought together in a definitive new trade paperback. Once, Timothy Hunter was just an ordinary 13-year-old boy living in suburban London. Then four legendary sorcerers took him on a journey beyond time and space, and his life changed forever. Traveling through realms long consigned to myth and legend, he also discovered an unsettling truth about his future: like it or not, fate has decreed that young Tim is destined to become the worldÃ•s greatest magician! Unfortunately for him, this innocence smells intoxicatingly like weakness to the hungry predators that haunt the shadows of existence, and the extraordinary power they sense within his frail human form is too enticing to resist. Written by John Ney Rieber and illustrated by Peter Gross, Gary Amaro and Peter Snejbjerg, THE BOOKS OF MAGIC BOOK ONE collects issues #1-13 of the classic VERTIGO series as well as the pivotal introductory tale from ARCANA ANNUAL #1.', 400),
(425, 'The Sandman', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dC7EQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Fiction', NULL, '1563895730', NULL, 'Dc Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Following in the tradition of Japanese folk tales, this graphic novel is a tale centered on ill-fated love and dream-eating monsters. Full color.', 126),
(426, 'Swamp Thing: Darker Genesis', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dWzFCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Millar', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dWzFCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-dWzFCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401264376', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2015-11-24', NULL, 'As the Swamp Thing tries to get on with his life, a mysterious woman named Anna hopes to get on with her death. A writer by trade, Anna longs to drown her sorrows in a watery grave. But her brilliant stories won\'t let her rest until she finishes telling them-and the Swamp Thing is their missing masterpiece. Now the avatar of the Green must ride its currents into a series of strange new worlds-warped realities that exist nowhere except in Anna\'s troubled mind: a New Orleans where the dead walk and black magic rules; an America that lost World War II and is reborn as a republic of horror; and a swamp where a former superhero learns a terrible secret. Waiting at the end of this river of stories is a force that could drown the Swamp Thing-and the world-in a final flood of darkness. Comics superstar Mark Millar and a parliament of comics\' finest artists-including Phil Hester, Kim DeMulder, Chris Weston, Jill Thompson and Phil Jimenez-present SWAMP THING: DARKER GENESIS, a tour de force of imaginative power collecting issues #151-160 of the original VERTIGO series.', 256),
(427, 'Motherlands (2018-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7sFDDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Spurrier', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1810800025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2018-02-28', NULL, 'After years of estrangement, Tab and her foul-mouthed mom Selena must work together to track the multiverseâ€™s most wanted criminal! But in a city made of fungus, their hunt hits an immediate snag: our mother-daughter duo arenâ€™t the only bounty hunters on the job...', 22),
(428, 'We3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=WT4DAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=WT4DAgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-WT4DAgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401236274', NULL, 'DC', '2005-07-01', NULL, 'A powerful tale from the ALL-STAR SUPERMAN team of Grant Morrison and Frank Quitely. Morrison and Quitely deliver the emotional journey of WE3Â„three house pets weaponized for lethal combat by the governmentÂ„as they search for -homeÃ® and attempt to ward off the shadowy agency that created them. With nervous systems amplified to match their terrifying mechanical exoskeletons, the members of Animal Weapon 3 (WE3) have the firepower of a battalion between them. But they are just the programÃs prototypes, and now that their testing is complete, theyÃre slated to be permanently decommissioned, causing them to seize their one chance to make a desperate run for freedom. Relentlessly pursued by their makers, the WE3 team must navigate a frightening and confusing world where their instincts and heightened abilities make them as much a threat as those hunting them.', NULL),
(429, 'Fables (2002-) #56', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ctwZCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0293000565001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'It\'s FABLES\' first-ever special Christmas issue, which seeks to answer a burning question: Does Santa Claus really exist? And if so, is he a Fable? Well, we\'re not going to tell you here, or there wouldn\'t be any reason for you to buy the issue, now, would there? So don\'t be naughty--be nice, and wait patiently for this extra-length issue to appear in your stocking.', NULL),
(430, 'Promethea: 20th Anniversary Deluxe Edition Book One', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=F_6KDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Alan Moore', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=F_6KDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-F_6KDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401288679', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-03-12', NULL, 'Sophie Bangs is an ordinary college student in a futuristic New York who finds herself transformed into Promethea, the living embodiment of the imagination. Her trials have only begun, as she must master the secrets of her predecessors before she is destroyed by PrometheaÃ•s ancient enemy. Complete with character sketches, variant covers and other bonus material, this new hardcover collection is perfect for any fan of this incredible series. Collects issues #1-12 plus the complete script for issue #3.', 384),
(431, 'Fables: A Wolf Among Us Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HytUDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matthew Sturges', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=HytUDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-HytUDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401270483', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2016-07-05', NULL, 'Bigby Wolf has been around for a good long while, and heÃ•s investigated pretty much every crime imaginable-but even an immortal Fable like him can still stumble across a once-in-a-lifetime case. As the sheriff of the magical New York City neighborhood known as Fabletown, Bigby is hot on the trail of the killer who beheaded a princess and then unleashed a horde of gangsters and monsters to cover his tracks. But even as Bigby reels from attempts on his life and watches his trail of suspects go cold, an old evil reappears to wreak havoc once more. Is the urban legend known as Bloody Mary to blame? Or is she just one more tortured pawn in an even bigger game, with an even more crooked opponent waiting to make his move? The acclaimed adaptation of the hit mystery from Telltale Games-inspired by Bill WillinghamÃ•s best-selling Vertigo series FABLES-concludes in this second volume of FABLES: THE WOLF AMONG US, written by Matthew Sturges and Dave Justus and featuring a powerful pack of artists, including Travis Moore, Shawn McManus, Eric Nguyen and Steve Sadowski. Collects issues #8-16.', 288),
(432, 'Doom Patrol Book Three', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lWNLDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=lWNLDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-lWNLDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401276980', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-04-04', NULL, 'The Doom Patrol must face new challenges: the final fate of the Brotherhood of Dada, the rise of the unstoppable Candlemaker, Danny the Street meeting his cosmic destiny and Crazy Jane attempting to find her place in the world. Sound strange? Well, not as strange as the superhero team fighting them. This exciting continuation from author Grant Morrison picks up in DOOM PATROL BOOK THREE, with art by Brian Bolland, Richard Case, Philip Bond, Ken Steacy, Sean Phillips and more. Collects DOOM PATROL #51-63 and the legendary DOOM FORCE SPECIAL #1.', 400),
(433, 'The Sandman Vol. 3: Dream Country', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qdLjAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=qdLjAAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-qdLjAAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401236502', NULL, 'DC', '2010-10-19', NULL, 'NEW YORK TIMES bestselling author Neil Gaiman\'s transcendent series SANDMAN is often hailed as the definitive Vertigo title and one of the finest achievements in graphic storytelling. Gaiman created an unforgettable tale of the forces that exist beyond life and death by weaving ancient mythology, folklore and fairy tales with his own distinct narrative vision. The third book of the Sandman collection, DREAM COUNTRY continues the fantastical mythology of Morpheus, the King of Dreams. In these centuries-spanning tales, the powerful entity known as the Sandman interacts with a diverse assortment of humans, fairies, heroes, and animals as he walks the mortal plane. Including an amazing encounter with William Shakespeare and an interesting take on the origin and first performance of \"A Midsummer Night\'s Dream,\" this book depicts the dreaming world of cats, the tragic life of forgotten super-heroes and the folly of imprisoning and torturing a former lover of the King of Dreams. A new, recolored edition of the classic SANDMAN series, DREAM COUNTRY collects issues #17-20 including \"A Midsummer Night\'s Dream,\" which won a World Fantasy Award.', NULL),
(434, 'Sandman Presents: Thessaly: Witch for Hire (2004-) #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E6NBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0359400025001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2013-10-29', NULL, 'The second thrilling miniseries focusing on THE SANDMAN\'s Thessaly continues. Now that Thessaly has Fetch right where she wants him, trapped in a mirror and at her mercy, he\'s quite possibly the most annoying captive ever. But when the deadly witch literally pulls information out of him, the bodies start to pile up. It seems Fetch has one last trick up his sleeve...will this new monster be Thess\'s last stand?', 22),
(436, 'Strange Adventures (1999-) #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JyJ0DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Bolland', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T0165500015001', NULL, 'Vertigo', NULL, NULL, 'Crop circles and cattle mutilations, mad scientists and the top writers and artists in comics converge in a four-issue Vertigo short-story anthology exploring the limits of the imagination. Globe-hopping adventurers bear witness to the bizarre mystery of \"The Kapas,\" a mad scientist struggles to decipher the \"Riddle of the Random Realities,\" and a trio of plague survivors suffer the insidious side effects of being \"Immune.\"', 22),
(437, 'Everafter: From the Pages of Fables (2016-) #10', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=1lWFDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dave Justus', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1593000105001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-06-07', NULL, 'After Bobby SpecklandÃ•s rescue attempt takes a shocking turn, long years pass for the captives in the CubeÃ‘but a young leader emerges as a new generation of hostages comes of age in oppressive darkness. A quiet revolution simmers, and some surprising assistance may be the force that breaks the barrier to freedom once and for all.', 22),
(438, 'Fables Vol. 5: The Mean Seasons', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eSrfAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eSrfAAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-eSrfAAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401236069', NULL, 'DC', '2005-04-01', NULL, 'WINNER OF FOURTEEN EISNER AWARDS. This volume features two tales of Bigby\'s exploits during World War II as well as \"The Year After,\" which follows the aftermath of the Adversary\'s attempt to conquer Fabletown-including the birth of Snow White and Bigby\'s children! Collects issues 22 and 28-33 of creator Bill Willingham-s celebrated Vertigo series.', NULL),
(439, 'American Carnage (2018-2019) #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=w_aJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bryan Hill', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1778900065001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-04-17', NULL, 'Richard is trapped. What began as a routine undercover mission for his next paycheck has devolved into a nightmare of mortal consequences. Having disrupted WynnÃ•s inner network and catapulted well past the point of no return, Richard fears he must sever himself from SheilaÃ•s original assignment in order to surviveÃ‘but before he can implement their final plan, a revelation from Jennifer forces him to accept his ultimate function within WynnÃ•s white nationalist empire.', 22),
(440, 'Vertigo', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uXgergEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Pierre Boileau', NULL, 'Fiction', NULL, '1782270809', NULL, 'Pushkin Vertigo', '2015-09-10', NULL, 'The story could have happened to any of us, but it happened to a man named Flavieres. His days as a detective were over, and everyone knew he had his reasons. But when an old friend appeared out of nowhere with concerns about his withdrawn and mysterious wife, Flavieres didn\'t have the heart to refuse. And soon he would be scouring the streets of Paris in search of an answer - in search of a girl who belonged to no one, not even to herself. Soon intrigue would be replaced by obsession, and dreams replaced by nightmares. This is the story of a desperate man. A man who ended up compromising his own morality beyond all measure, while World War Two raged outside his front door. A man tormented - and destroyed - by a dark, terrible secret. This sinister, mindbending roman noir was turned into a 1958 Hollywood classic, starring James Stewart and Kim Novak, directed by the great Alfred Hitchcock.\"', 272),
(441, 'Lucifer Vol. 3: Blood in the Streets', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dlw6DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Richard Kadrey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dlw6DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-dlw6DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401282738', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2017-10-31', NULL, 'HeÃ•s faced down God Himself, and lived (and died, and lived again) to tell the tale. Now Lucifer Morningstar, the most irresistible antihero in all of Creation, is free to turn the final page on his past and begin a brand-new chapter in his legendarily eventful life. But before he can start booking retirement cruises, thereÃ•s still one small matter that requires his attention: an all-powerful entity has usurped his deceased FatherÃ•s place in Heaven and is preparing to extinguish every last vestige of free will throughout the universe. The Lightbringer has always been the contrary type, and heÃ•s not about to change his ways for anyoneÃ‘or anythingÃ‘just because they occupy the Throne of Light. And while the former Lord of Hell now rules only within the boundaries of his nightclub, Ex Lux, he still has powerful allies and devoted enemiesÃ‘all of whom are ripe for manipulation. Together, this motley militia is poised to take their fight from the heights of the Silver City to the depths of the Inferno. Against them stand multiple armies of angels, demons, and every dreaded thing imaginable that lies between them. Can Lucifer overcome their onslaught and keep his club, his city, and his indomitable independence intact? Or, after countless millennia, has the DevilÃ•s tab finally come due? Find out in LUCIFER VOL. 3: BLOOD IN THE STREETSÃ‘the shocking conclusion to the newest saga of the Fallen One from the acclaimed creative team of Richard Kadrey, Lee Garbett, Antonio Fabela, Holly Black, Marco Rudy and Ben Templesmith, collecting issues #13-19 of the signature VERTIGO series.', 168),
(442, 'The Unwritten Vol. 11: Apocalypse', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4DSNBwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Carey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4DSNBwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-4DSNBwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401259563', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2015-05-26', NULL, 'Tom Taylor-the real-life counterpart of his father\'s famous fictional boy-wizard creation, a living bridge between our reality and the realities of every tale ever told-knows the power of stories only too well. Now he\'s the star of his most important story yet. It\'s a quest straight out of King Arthur, filled with black knights, ensorcelled swords, and maidens who are fair to a fault. If his heart is pure and his courage true, he can enter the Chapel Perilous, find the Grail, complete his quest, and save existence as we know it. If not, we are verily screwed. Hark! Storytellers Mike Carey, Peter Gross, and Chris Chuckry approach, singing tales of valor and treachery in THE UNWRITTEN: APOCALYPSE! This final volume in THE UNWRITTEN saga collects issues #6-12.', NULL),
(443, '100 Bullets Book Two', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jLzyBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Azzarello', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=jLzyBgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-jLzyBgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401259358', NULL, 'DC', '2015-04-21', NULL, 'How far would you go for revenge? If you were given a chance at deadly retribution with a guarantee that the law could not touch you, would you take it? That\'s the opportunity that a man called Agent Graves provides, in the form of a special briefcase containing an untraceable gun and one hundred rounds of ammunition. To the damaged and downtrodden living on the fringes of society, the offer is a once-in-a-lifetime chance to even their scores. But beyond the dilemma of whether or not to pull the trigger lies a deeper and even more troubling concern: just who is making these actions possible - and why? This second of five volumes reprinting all 100 issues of writer Brian Azzarello and artist Eduardo Risso\'s 100 BULLETS collects issues #20-36 of their acclaimed Vertigo series, and also includes Azzarello\'s original script for \"The Mimic\" from issue #20.', NULL),
(444, 'Dark Horse Comics/DC Comics: Mask', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nNgpDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Arcudi', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=nNgpDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-nNgpDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630089368', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-09-26', NULL, 'Grifter and the Mask team up and face off against smugglers at a Las Vegas weapons show. After destroying a planet, the Mask has a bounty on his head and Lobo hot on his tail in a mind-bending, time twisting showdown between madmen. And last, but not least, the Joker stumbles upon the mask which inspires a new super-powered reign for the Clown Prince of Crime! This volume collects Grifter/The Mask #1-#2, Lobo vs. the Mask #1-2, and Joker/Mask #1-4.', 256),
(445, 'The Dark Horse Comics/DC: Superman', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tnB3DAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=tnB3DAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-tnB3DAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630088057', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-08-16', NULL, 'Superman vs. Aliens! In the first ever collection of the DC/Dark Horse Superman crossover stories, the Man of Steel faces the universeâ€™s deadliest foe, but is he truly strong enough to defeat the xenomorph? Follow the Last Son of Krypton through the world of Madman and explore the jungles of East Africa with him alongside Tarzan, son of the jungle. Collects Superman vs. Aliens Volume 1, Superman vs. Aliens Volume 2: God War, Superman/Tarzan: Sons of the Jungle, and The Superman/Madman Hullabaloo. * Over 400 pages of material contains four full Superman arcs from Dan Jurgens, Chuck Dixon, and Mike Allred, original covers, and pinup and sketchbook art from the original creative teams. * In this 30th-anniversary year of Aliens, fans can rediscover the Man of Steel combating the xenomorphâ€”for the first time since 2002.', 416),
(446, 'Dark Horse Comics/DC Comics: Justice League', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=urkFDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=urkFDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-urkFDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630088149', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-03-29', NULL, 'In this collection of DC Comics crossovers, Dark Horse brings never republished material featuring a host of heroes back to fans in a single volume. The JLA take on the most frightening hunters in the universe--the Predators--in adaptive superhero form! Batman teams up with Tarzan to resist the claws of the Catwoman as two orphan heroes protect their own jungles. Kyle Rayner must don the mantle of Green Lantern to turn back the tide of Aliens that Hal Jordan once permitted to live. Super-teens join forces as Spyboy and his friends work alongside Young Justice to defeat nightmarish foes.', 328),
(447, 'The Dark Horse Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DaKvDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chuck Dixon', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506702148', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"Superman faces the universe\'s deadliest foe, but is he truly strong enough to emerge victorious over the Aliens? Then, follow Superman on a voyage into the world of Madman and explore an alternate history in which the last son of Krypton crashes not in Kansas, but in the jungles of eastern Africa, usurping Tarzan\'s place in legend.\"--Provided by publisher.', 416),
(448, 'The Art of Super Mario Odyssey', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZOi9DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, 'Nintendo video games', NULL, '9781506713755', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 367),
(449, 'Choke Gasp! The Best of 75 Years of EC Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9k6iDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Harvey Kurtzman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506715858', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-12-17', NULL, 'A premiere collection of the best stories of EC Comics, curated in a deluxe hardcover, just in time to celebrate the legendary publisher\'s 75th anniversary! This volume collects stories from EC Comics\' most famous titles, featuring classic stories from the hands of legendary creators Al Feldstein, Harvey Kurtzman, Johnny Craig, Jack Davis, Wally Wood, and more! Collects material from issues of Crime SuspenStories, Frontline Combat, Haunt of Fear, Impact, Shock SuspenStories, Tales from the Crypt, Two-Fisted Tales, Vault of Horror, Weird Fantasy, Weird Science, and Weird Science-Fantasy.', 528),
(450, 'The Art Of Splatoon', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uuW2DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '9781506713748', NULL, NULL, '2019-11-12', NULL, NULL, 384),
(451, 'Creepy Archives', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=M595DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '9781506711614', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '2018-08-08', NULL, 'Creepy Archives Volume 27 opens one crypt too many to expose a writhing mass of frightful fun, reanimating classic tales of terror from the most harrowing horror series in comics history! Featuring stories by the finest writers and artists of the day, including William DuBay, Alfredo Alcala, Nicola Cuti, and Budd Lewis, Creepy Archives brings the fear to new generations of readers . . . and victims!', 280),
(452, 'Dark Horse Presents #15', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zWGjCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Sam K', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=zWGjCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-zWGjCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:20940', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2012-07-18', NULL, 'Arvid Nelson\'s critically acclaimed _Rex Mundi_ returns with artist Juan Ferreyra in another jam-packed issue of _DHP_! Plus, Mike Baron and Steve Rude continue delivering new _Nexus_ material! * A creator-owned comics celebration with Bo Hampton\'s _Riven_, Cosby and Shaner\'s _Buddy Cops_, Oeming\'s _The Wild Rover_, McNeil\'s _Finder_, and Tony Puryear\'s _Concrete Park_! * More of DeConnick and Noto\'s _Ghost_!', 90),
(453, 'Web of Horror Archives', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZQUfswEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1616559411', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '2016-03-29', NULL, 'Collected for the first time, the brief but brilliant run of Web of Horror is presented in Dark Horse\'s celebrated archive format! Including every issue of the legendary series plus the unpublished stories that appeared in various fanzines, and the never-before-seen \"lost\" stories, this volume is a deluxe presentation of some of the earliest work from some of horror comics\' greatest visionaries. This compilation of classic horror and science fiction from 1969 and 1970 highlights the work of artists such as Bernie Wrightson, Michael Wm. Kaluta, Jeffrey Jones, Ralph Reese, and others, plus lots of extras!', 200),
(454, 'Shag', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1596173394', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(455, 'MPD Psycho', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oD4YBwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Eiji Otsuka', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=oD4YBwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-oD4YBwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630084172', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-03-11', NULL, 'MPD-Psycho has earned praise for its complex, shocking story arcs and artist Sho-u Tajima\'s stark, arresting art style-that draws comparison with artist Charles Burns\' work. Adult fans of the Death Note and Paranoia Agent anime series, the Takashi Miike MPD-Psycho television adaptation, and nihilistic parables like the Kurosagi Corpse Delivery Service, Monster, and Death Note manga will be surprised by the inventive murders, mysterious sci-fi touches, and surprisingly humorous moments in this smart series. Step onto this crazy ride, as even more strange deviants are introduced and writer Eiji Otsuka continues to astound with his inventive plot twists and atrocities. Named one of Publishers Weekly\'s best reads of 2007!', 208),
(456, 'The American', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=qkANAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Verheiden', NULL, 'Superheroes', NULL, '1569710058', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'He\'s the ultimate all American hero. Since the Fifties he has been a symbol of hope and courage for the entire country; an indestructible one-man army standing up for freedom, justice and the American way all over the globe. But what\'s the real truth behind The American? When reporter Dennis Hough is assigned to cover a story about his boyhood hero, he begins to see the cracks in the legend.', 117),
(457, 'Basil Wolverton in Space', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BinwPAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Basil Wolverton', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1569712387', NULL, NULL, '1997-03-01', NULL, 'Famous for his inimitable grotesqueries and his alliterative humor, Basil Wolverton sold his first cartoons at the Vancouver, Washington Farmers\' Market. He was 11 at the time. After an early vaudeville career and several near-misses with newspaper strips, he sold his first stories to America\'s Humor in 1926. In 1938, he began comic-book work for Globe with \'Spacehawks\' and \'Disk-Eyes\' in Circus. This fat little book of classic, one-of-a-kind Basil Wolverton material collects all kinds of stories and strips.', 117),
(458, 'Kurosagi Corpse Delivery Service', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jsqWBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Eiji Otsuka', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=jsqWBAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-jsqWBAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630080662', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2014-09-24', NULL, 'Your body is their business! Five young students at a Buddhist university, three guys and two girls, find little call for their job skills in today\'s Tokyo . . . among the living, that is! But all that stuff in college they were told would never pay off-you know, channeling, dowsing, ESP-gives them a direct line to the dead . . . the dead who are still trapped in their corpses and can\'t move on to the next reincarnation. The five form the Kurosagi (\"Black HeronÃ®-their ominous bird logo) Corpse Delivery Service: whether suicide, murder, accident, or illness, they\'ll carry your body wherever it needs to go to free your soul! The kids from Kurosagi can smell a customer a mile away--it\'s a good thing one of the girls majored in embalming! â€¢ Original Japanese format. â€¢ 18+ content advisory. \"While there is cruelty, gore, violence, and implied unnatural sexual acts, the manga is also a complex and slyly ironic social commentary. Acquire this manga for adult collections for the naturalistic artwork that shows attention to human emotion, the social observation, and the banter between members of the delivery service. \" (Christine Gertz, Library Journal)', 192),
(459, 'Rachel Williams', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=FgXyIgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1596174277', NULL, NULL, '2006-02-01', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(460, 'Dead Rider', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=wEe9BgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kevin Ferrara', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=wEe9BgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-wEe9BgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630084820', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-03-18', NULL, 'The complete saga in print for the first time! In legend a ghostly outlaw shrouded in mystery, the Dead Rider is in reality a corpse turned living dead by the sinister Bog Witch. With the law closing in, the Rider sets in motion a desperate plan to destroy the witch forever and regain his soul! Collects Dead Rider #1â€“#2 and a brand-new conclusion! * Gorgeous artwork in the best Wrightson-Frazetta tradition! â€œAbsolutely top-notch in presentation, and . . . worth a look to fans of classic horror comics.â€Â¬â€”IGN', 112),
(461, 'Gary Baseman', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1596173572', NULL, NULL, '2006-02-01', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(462, 'Star Wars Panel to Panel', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sHzmNwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Randy Stradley', NULL, 'Art', NULL, '1593072619', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Presents a selection of Star Wars cover illustrations and interior pages that originally appeared in Dark Horse comics and graphic novels during the 1990s.', 191),
(463, 'Felix the Cat\'s Greatest Hits', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0scAAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569718113', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'One of America\'s genuine cartoon classics, Felix the Cat has delighted and entertained audiences for over eighty years, reaching nearly every corner of the globe in newspaper strips, animated cartoons, toys, games, and comic books, becoming so famous that Felix was chosen as Charles Lindbergh\'s mascot for his landmark transatlantic flight as well as being the very first image broadcast over television airwaves! And now, with Felix still appearing in everything from animated cartoons to video games to music CDs, Dark Horse adds Felix the Cat\'s Greatest Hits to the playlist, presenting a selection of stories featuring Felix, his friends and foes, and, of course, his Magic Bag of Tricks!', 96),
(464, 'Freak Show', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NnpOPgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Kyle Baker', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1878574329', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'This cutting-edge comic is based upon concepts and characters found on the popular Freak Show album by the Residents available in record shops across the country. Each features story and art based on one of the songs. Included are: Herman and the Human Mole by Richard Sala, Wanda the Worm Woman by John Bolton, Jello Jack by Matt Howarth, Mickey the Mumbling Midget by Savage Pencil, Bouncing Benny the Bump by Pore No Graphics, Lillie by Dave McKean and Tex the Barker by Kyle Baker. This 80-page trade paperback includes both black-and-white and full-color art and features a full-color cover by Charles Burns.', 117),
(465, 'The Serpent\'s Heir', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GzgdDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dean DeBlois', NULL, 'Dragons', NULL, '9781616559311', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-02-28', NULL, '\"As the new chief, Hiccup must bring order to his village after the recent attack by Drago Bludvist and his Bewilderbeast. Another opportunity to prove himself comes when the earthquake-plagued island of Nepenthe calls for assistance. But once on the island, it becomes clear the tremors are just a part of the problem\"--Back cover.', 80),
(466, 'Creepy Archives', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7dzZ56aMVhYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=7dzZ56aMVhYC&rdid=book-7dzZ56aMVhYC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621154471', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2009-05-19', NULL, 'Fans of horror comics and jawdropping artwork, rejoice! Dark Horse Comics continues to showcase its dedication to bringing you the highestquality horror comics ever made with this third bloodcurdling collection of Warren Publishing\'s groundbreaking horror magazine Creepy. This landmark archive series brings readers, for the first time ever, each and every eerie story from Creepy magazine\'s original run, featuring work from many of the best artists ever to work in the medium of comics. Frank Frazetta, Gray Morrow, Alex Toth, Joe Orlando, and Angelo Torres are just a sampling of the artists whose work bring horror to life in startling and gorgeously gruesome detail in this third huge collected volume. * Features art by Frank Frazetta, Gray Morrow, Alex Toth, Joe Orlando, Angelo Torres, and others! * Features the original backandwhite artwork meticulously restored, with the original covers of each issue reprinted in luscious full color! \"Since the stock is much finer than the authentic newsprint, visually, these pages are better than the originals, with moodly, dark blacks that punctuate the shock endings.\" Publishers Weekly', 160),
(467, 'Buffy Lunch Box', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YhdKYgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1616591226', NULL, NULL, '2011-07-26', NULL, 'After the end of the television series, Dark Horse and creator Joss Whedon teamed up to keep Sunnydale\'s favorite daughter alive and well in comic-book format. Dark Horse has dived into the rich archive of Jo Chen\'s award-winning cover art to bring you the latest in their line of acclaimed accoutrements - a shiny new Buffy lunch box!', NULL),
(468, 'Nine eleven', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0CLNeGkutSMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1563898810', NULL, 'DC Comics', '2002-01-01', NULL, 'A collection of personal and profoundly moving stories from some of the greatest writers and artists in comics about the tragic events of September 11, 2001 includes Frank Millers reflections on the power of faith, Jim Mahfoods personal view of the Arab-American experience before and after September 11, and Bryan Talbot\'s reflection on the meaning of entertainment in the days after the attacks. A Graphic Novel. Original.', 191),
(469, 'Baltimore Volume 4: Chapel of Bones', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XlUbAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Mignola', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=XlUbAwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-XlUbAwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630080143', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2014-06-24', NULL, 'The world\'s greatest monster hunter wages war against a plague of vampires intent on resurrecting a demonic god, an evil witch in league with a clan of undead, and his mortal nemesis, leading to a final showdown in London! Written by award-winning, bestselling writers Mike Mignola and Christopher Golden.', 144),
(470, 'Curse of the Gesu', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fL4mPAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569711755', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Pai is a strange, provincial woman who has come to Tokyo from the Tibetan highlands. Somewhere in Tokyo is a young man who can help her in her quest... to become human! When Pai finally finds Yakumo, they set off in search of the artifact that can transform her, but it will take all of her mystical powers to keep the reckless Yakumo alive, even if she has to steal his soul to protect him!', 152),
(471, 'Visions', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RT0AGQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Arthur Suydam', NULL, 'Graphic novels', NULL, '1569710449', NULL, NULL, '1995-10-17', NULL, NULL, 117),
(472, 'Buffy the Vampire Slayer Supernatural Defense Kit', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mFMLQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '159617966X', NULL, NULL, '2010-05-04', NULL, 'Back by popular demand! One of our most interesting book packages was the Buffy Supernatural Defense Kit. Long out-of-print, \"die-hard\" Buffy fans just kept asking for this book and keepsake package. Well, it is returning from the grave. This handsome, slipcased package combines a great Buffy adventure with a dazzling trio of specially crafted items that are featured in the story. The book is a deluxe hardcover, about 80% of comic book size, thread-sewn, utilizing a fine matte artpaper stock. The story is an expansion of \"The Final Cut,\" part of which originally appeared ages ago as Buffy: The Vampire Slayer #8. New pages were added by creative team Cliff Richards, Jason Pearson, Joe Pimentel, and Guy Major. Actual elements from the story have been created, and are visible through die-cut windows in the extra thick, custom-crafted slipcase: Buffy\'s trademark gold-colored cross, the traditional \"Claddagh\" ring, and a striking glass vial of \"holy\" water with silver flakes suspended in the fluid. Defend yourself in style or provide the special someone in your life with a unique gift.', 32),
(473, 'Buffy the Vampire Slayer', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cCJiGQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Andi Watson', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '156971486X', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 30),
(474, 'Ragner Coasters', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1596174250', NULL, NULL, '2006-02-01', NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(475, 'Futurama Paper Doll Book', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Kj2CPQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, 'Art', NULL, '1569717192', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2002-01-28', NULL, 'A 25-year-old pizza delivery boy named Fry spends New Years Eve 1999 lamenting his lame existence. That night, he accidentally freezes himself in a cryogenics lab and awakens at the dawn of the year 3000! With the past 1,000 years behind him, Fry decides to make a fresh start. So begins Futurama, the hilarious animated Fox TV series from Simpsons\' creator, Matt Groening. Dark Horse travels back from the future to bring you a line of Futurama goodies. Calling all slaves to fashion! The Futurama Paper Doll Book is finally here, and it\'s bustin\' at the seams with haute 30th Century couture! Put Leela in a sassy spacesuit, or Amy in a hot micromini. You\'ll have fun dressing -- and undressing -- your favorite Futurama glama queens! Outfits galore and hours of fabulous fun, for the supermodel inside us all!', NULL),
(476, 'Free Comic Book Day 2019 (General)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=SwuUDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jody Houser', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=SwuUDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-SwuUDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3005886', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-05-08', NULL, 'Dark Horse is thrilled to announce tales from two diverse worlds in our FCBD Gold Offering featuring Netflix\'s Stranger Things and a spooky trip into Jeff Lemire and Dean Ormston\'s Eisner Award-winning series Black Hammer with a cover by Chun Lo. In Stranger Things, writer Jody Houser and artist Ibrahim Moustafa bring the adventuring party back together after Eleven\'s disappearance, as Nancy and Steve find a way to lift the spirits of a despondent Mike. Perhaps all it takes is a roll of the dice. Then, in the world of the Eisner Award-winning Black Hammer series creator Jeff Lemire, guest writer Ray Fawkes, and artist David Rubâ€™n, take the reader on an EC-style tour through Madame Dragonfly\'s mysterious Cabin of Horrors to witness two groups of brand-new Black Hammer heroes from the past! Learn more at FreeComicBookDay.com.', 32),
(477, 'Brain Boy', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fsQQBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Fred Van Lente', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=fsQQBgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-fsQQBgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630081065', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-01-06', NULL, 'Agent Price\'s new mission pits him against a doomsday cult leader with a political agenda that poses a direct threat to the president. But a mysterious hive mind has more menacing plans for Brain Boy. He\'ll have no choice but to go head to head--brain to brain--with the mysterious Men from G.E.S.T.A.L.T.! The Men from G.E.S.T.A.L.T. collects New York Times best-selling author Fred Van Lente\'s electrifying second arc of psychic spy Brain Boy\'s continuing adventures!', 112),
(478, 'Doomworld', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=q4NLNwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Roy Thomas', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1569717540', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics presents classic Star Wars stories not seen in more than 20years, which were originally printed by Marvel.', 369),
(479, 'The Art of Emily the Strange', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ekoYBwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rob Reger', NULL, 'Art', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ekoYBwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-ekoYBwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630084684', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-03-11', NULL, 'In her fifteen-plus years in existence, oddballs, outcasts, and art freaks the world over have grown to know and love a strange young girl named Emily. With roots in the punk-rock art scene of Santa Cruz skate culture and an early appeal to European trend spotters, the iconic image of Emily and her philosophy of devout individualism have become deeply rooted in global culture. The Art of Emily Volume One is the first-ever collection of images showing the wide and inspired range of artistic styles and mediums that have been used to create the world of Emily the Strange. From skateboard stickers to custom rock-and-roll album art, large-scale psychedelic paintings, and insanely intricate Mongolian paper cutting, the fantastic and artful imaginings of Rob Reger, Buzz Parker, and a staggeringly talented array of collaborators will give insight and inspiration to any Emily fan.', 120),
(480, 'Free Comic Book Day 2018 (All Ages): The Legend of Korra / ARMS', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7pFyDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ian Flynn, Michael Dante DiMartino', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=7pFyDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-7pFyDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3001732', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2018-05-05', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics is excited to feature all-ages stories from Nickelodeon\'s The Legend of Korra and Nintendo\'s ARMS for our Free Comic Book Day Silver offering on May 5, 2018! First, Avatar Korra pairs up with an unlikely sidekick for a super-important, top-secret mission to track down a pack of lost pets in a story written by The Legend of Korra co-creator Michael Dante DiMartino with art by Jayd Ait-Kaci and Vivian Ng. In a story based on Nintendo\'s exclusive fighting game ARMS, a young fighter trains tirelessly to reach the top in the ARMS League GrandÃ‘Prixbut first, he must defeat 599 other contenders! ARMS is written by Ian Flynn (Sonic the Hedgehog, Mega Man) with art by Joe Ng (Street Fighter, Overwatch: Binary). Visit FreeComicBookDay.com to learn more!', 28),
(481, 'The Art of Comic Book Inking', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_EOwDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gary Martin', NULL, 'Art', NULL, '9781506711911', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'The industry-standard manual for aspiring inkers and working professionals returns in a new expanded edition. Gain insights into the techniques, tools, and approaches of some of the finest ink artists in comics, including Terry Austin, Mark Farmer, Scott Williams, Alex Garner, and many more. This expanded edition features new art and text by author Gary Martin and a bonus chapter on digital inking by artist Leo Vitalis. Also included are eight full-sized blue-lined art boards featuring pencil art by top comics illustrators, present and past, to use for practice or as samples to show editors and publishers. Along with pen, brush, and stylus, no inking tool is more useful than The Art of Comic-Book Inking.', 216),
(482, 'Run from the Future', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=f51KPQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Adam Warren', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569715777', NULL, NULL, '2002-01-15', NULL, 'In the cyberpunk future, the Worlds Welfare Work Association is an important weapon against crime. 3WA\'s best operatives, Kei and Yuri - the Lovely Angels - also have a reputation for causing catastrophe in the execution of their duties, and have earned a new nickname: the Dirty Pair.', 136),
(483, 'Aliens: The Essential Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ciRcDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Verheiden', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ciRcDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-ciRcDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506710129', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-11-06', NULL, 'These are the comics stories that kept fear alive. Since 1988, whether there was an Alien film on the horizon or not, Dark Horse Comics delivered scares that audiences demanded. From the depths of space, to bizarre alien worlds, and even to surface of our own dear Earth, in the pages of comic books there were dozens of sequels and spinoffs to the films, as well as original stories that carried the monsters and the mythos to new heights. These are the Aliens Essential Comics--stories which have stood the test of time . . . and kept readers awake at night. In this first volume is the initial Aliens trilogy--Outbreak, Nightmare Asylum, and Earth War, in which Hicks and Newt--and eventually Ripley--join forces to battle an infestation of Aliens both on Earth and in the wider galaxy (all of these stories were written before the film Alien3 chronicled the deaths of the heroes of Aliens). Written by Mark Verheiden (who went on to write The Mask, Timecop, Battlestar Galactica, Daredevil, and many other films and television shows), and beautifully illustrated by Mark A. Nelson, Den Beauvais, and Sam Kieth, these stories are the perfect starting point for readers new to the Aliens mythos, and a volume to be treasured by longtime fans.', 368),
(484, 'Edgar Rice Burroughs\' Minidoka', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NkY2NgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Michael William Kaluta', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '1569712816', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Dark Horse is proud to present an all-new tale by the Master of Adventure himself, Edgar Rice Burroughs! Written before the twin blockbusters of A Princess of Mars and Tarzan of the Apes, Minidoka is a whimsical fantasy in the tradition of Jonathan Swift\'s Gulliver\'s Travels and Lewis Carroll\'s The Hunting of the Snark. Illustrated by comics legend Michael Wm. Kaluta, and featuring a never-before-published cover painting by J. Allen St. John, this fractured fairy tale for children of all ages is sure to become a highly sought-after collectible!', 63),
(485, 'Creepy Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_17ZCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616558284', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-09-29', NULL, 'When Dark Horse began their massive reprint programme for hallowed magazines Creepy and Eerie they also obtained the rights to create new stories in the same vein. This is the fourth collection of all-new Creepy material. Creepy Comics enters its second half-century of horrifying readers! Don\'t miss malicious missives from Fred Van Lente, Ray Fawkes, Alex de Campi, Richard P. Clark, Matthew Southworth, Tom Coker, Ted Naifeh and many more - it\'s a heap of creep!', 160),
(486, 'The Goon Library', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nGLZCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781616558420', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Collects The Goon, volume 0: Rough stuff; The Goon, volume 1: Nothin\' but misery; The Goon, volume 2: My murderous childhood (and other grievous yarns); and The Goon, volume 3: Heaps of ruination.', 496),
(487, 'Oreimo Comic Anthology', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=w805DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '9781506700243', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Contributors include Ayato Sasakura, Keito Koume, abec, Shin Kyogoku and many more! The original light novel (manga) series, Oreimo, was published in North America by Dark Horse, as was the spin-off, Oreimo: Kuroneko. It also inspired a television anime series in 2010 and a second season in 2013. In Oreimo Comic Anthology, Sakura Ikeda, artist of these series, joins 20 other artists in this collection of spin-off stories.', 160),
(488, 'Aliens Vs. Predator Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cPYHDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781593078294', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'As mankind\'s most lethal adversaries battle for supremacy, terrifying images of pursuit, disfigurement, and bloody death invade Caryn Delacroix\'s dreams, and soon, corporate magnate Lucien Delacroix discovers that nightmares do come true and that there are fates worse than death. Original.', 458),
(489, 'Conan Volume 18: The Damned Horde', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9T9BCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781630082932', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-09-15', NULL, 'Conan and his allies are thrown into battle against an army of brigands! Conan enters into an uncertain alliance to steal a legendary treasure that leads him on a perilous journey! Writer Fred Van Lente tackles the worldâ€™s most famous barbarian in this collection of issues #7â€“#12 of Dark Horse Comicsâ€™ Conan the Avenger. *The complete smash-hit second Conan the Avenger arc by Fred Van Lente! â€œThis is classic Conan here, folks, and itâ€™s great fun to read.â€â€”The Fandom Post', 152),
(490, 'The Witcher', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=k1_ZCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Tobin', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '9781616557935', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"\'The Witcher\' game and comic book are based on the novels of Andrzej Sapkowski\'\"--Colophon.', 188),
(491, 'Conan Volume 10: Iron Shadows in the Moon', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=01Unv1Xcs50C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Timothy Truman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781621150374', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2011-05-03', NULL, 'On the run from the army of Turan, Conan and fellow fugitive Olivia hide out on a small island in the Vilayet Sea. They soon find themselves stalked by an unseen terror in the jungles and threatened by a group of pirates belonging to the Red Brotherhood, which is led by Conan\'s sworn enemy-Sergius of Koth! However, those may be the least of Conan\'s concerns, because when the moon rises on this island, the ruins of a lost civilization stir and an ancient, deadly curse awakens! Conan will be pushed to his limits as he and Olivia fight to survive! * Collects Conan the Cimmerian issues #22-#25, plus the Weight of the Crown one-shot with its MySpace Dark Horse Presents short-story prologue. * This collection completes the epic Dark Horse series Conan the Cimmerian. * Features a foreword by series writer Timothy Truman and an afterword by Robert E. Howard biographer and genre writer Mark Finn!', 160),
(492, 'Simon Thorpe Vampires Stationery', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1596173580', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(493, 'Murder Book', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BEa9BgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ed Brisson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=BEa9BgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-BEa9BgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630081713', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-03-31', NULL, 'The graphic novel anthology Murder Book collects gritty and unrelenting crime comics by Ed Brisson (Sheltered, The Field, Sons of Anarchy) that chronicle the demise of the immoral and the innocent alike. Featuring art from Michael Walsh (Secret Avengers), Simon Roy (The Field), Johnnie Christmas (Sheltered), Declan Shalvey (Moon Knight), and many more, this collection is an essential for crime and noir fans.', 176),
(494, 'Life Between Panels', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=P2tDDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ethan Young', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=P2tDDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-P2tDDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506704753', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-04-17', NULL, 'A semiautobiographical comic by Ethan Young, the acclaimed writer and artist of Nanjing: The Burning City and The Battles of Bridget Lee graphic novel series In this blend of autobiography and fantasy, a cartoonist records his life in New York City: his job, his creative career, his friends, his herd of cats, and a runaway comic strip come to life! Ethan\'s life as one of the many cartoonists living in NYC might look mundane at first glance--living with his parents, working a day job, playing with cats. But things get crazy when he starts to draw his comic strip Crusader Cat! Soon, Ethan can\'t tell the difference between real life and the comic panel!', 384),
(495, 'Vampire Hunter D Volume 16: Tyrant\'s Stars Parts 1 & 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KkjSo05Fd4YC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Hideyuki Kikuchi', NULL, 'Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=KkjSo05Fd4YC&rdid=book-KkjSo05Fd4YC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621155027', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2011-04-12', NULL, 'In this chilling adventure, Vampire Hunter D has been dispatched to vanquish the ancient vampiric Noble Count Braujou, guardian of an ancient buried treasure. But when a mysterious object crashes into the earth, destroying half of the northern Frontier, D faces an even more terrifying opponent-the renegade vampire Valcua, the Ultimate Noble! Having been exiled to outer space, Valcua took his entire kingdom of strange and deadly creatures with him, and swore that when the time was right they would return to have their revenge. Unfortunately for D, that time is now . . .', 256),
(496, 'Vampire Hunter D Volume 15: Dark Road', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eNKRyl-4RyMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Hideyuki Kikuchi', NULL, 'Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eNKRyl-4RyMC&rdid=book-eNKRyl-4RyMC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621155010', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2012-10-09', NULL, 'Vampire Hunter D takes on his greatest challenge yet! The ruthless vampire Noble General Gaskell commands the loyalty of some of the most infamous and deadly vampires in history, and Gaskell has no patience for D\'s interference, heroic or not! With the odds stacked against him, D must prevail â€” or perish * Features seven gorgeous black-and-white line illustrations by Yoshitaka Amano.', 160),
(497, 'Vampire Hunter D Volume 17: Tyrant\'s Stars Parts 3 & 4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-FozxDUkhN0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Hideyuki Kikuchi', NULL, 'Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-FozxDUkhN0C&rdid=book--FozxDUkhN0C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621155034', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2011-10-04', NULL, 'Vampire Hunter D continues his quest to overcome the interstellar evil brought to Earth by the ultimate Noble, the terrifying renegade vampire Valcua! Wielding a sword that can cut through the fabric of space and time, Valcua has a score to settle with the bloodline of humans responsible for his exile. The family has enlisted D to protect them from Valcua\'s wrath, and the Vampire Hunter might be their only chance at survival.', 216),
(498, 'Vampire Hunter D Volume 13: Twin-Shadowed Knight Parts 1 & 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=xsJd6ZMHNYsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Hideyuki Kikuchi', NULL, 'Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=xsJd6ZMHNYsC&rdid=book-xsJd6ZMHNYsC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621154990', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2012-10-09', NULL, 'When Vampire Hunter D entered the town of Sedoc it was in search of answers to the meaning of a dying vampire\'s last words: \"Find Muma.\" But when he meets Mia, the daughter of the local fortuneteller, he learns the mists emanating from a smoking crater on the outskirts of Sedoc have reanimated thousands of corpses, compelling them to crawl from their graves and hurl themselves into the smoking chasm. When D goes to investigate, he finds himself split in two: a second Vampire Hunter D, full of passion and lust and hunger for the company of women, is born! * Features eleven black-and-white line illustrations by Yoshitaka Amano. \"Richly descriptive, filled with bone crushing action and horror aplenty, this is one wild ride down the highway to Hell.\" - Active Anime', 320),
(499, 'Criminal Macabre Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ENt73DyQcp4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Steve Niles', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ENt73DyQcp4C&rdid=book-ENt73DyQcp4C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621153382', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2011-08-23', NULL, 'In 2003 Steve Niles, creator of the 30 Days of Night comics series, launched a series of occult detective stories featuring the monstrously hard-boiled Cal McDonald. A pill-popping alcoholic reprobate, Cal is the only line of defense between Los Angeles and a growing horde of zombies, vampires, possessed muscle cars, mad scientists, werewolves, and much more weirdness! * I literally screamed HOLY $#@% when I put this book down. It is that good... Cal McDonald is truly one of the coolest characters in comics.\" â€”Ain\'t It Cool News\"', 240),
(500, 'Predator: The Original Comics Series - Concrete Jungle and Other Stories', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jruvDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Verheiden', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=jruvDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-jruvDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630089320', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-06-27', NULL, 'Celebrate the thirtieth anniversary of one of the great action movies of all time with this collection of original comics sequels to the film. Before Predator 2 was ever conceived as a film, writer Mark Verheiden and artist Chris Warner created an acclaimed comic-book sequel to Predator that took the alien trophy hunters from the jungles of Central America to the concrete jungle of New York City--where they face Dutch Schaefer\'s big brother, who\'s an NYPD detective! Also included in this volume are Verheiden\'s two subsequent Predator stories--Cold War, which finds the Predators crash-landed in Siberia, and Dark River, in which the hero of Concrete Jungle traces the path of his younger brother to find out what really happened to him after the events in the movie Predator. Three now-classic tales in one over-sized, deluxe hard cover volume designed to sit on your bookshelf beside the Aliens 30th Anniversary edition! Collects: Collects Predator: Concrete Jungle (#1-#4), Predator: Cold War (#1-#4), and Predator: Dark River', 320),
(501, 'Creepy Comics #21', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Ie2jCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Archie Goodwin', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Ie2jCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Ie2jCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:29063', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2014-02-12', NULL, 'Hot summer nights make for the very best frights, right here in good ol\' _Creepy Comics_! Featuring spooky sequential storytelling from such graphic greats as Jeff Parker, Vera Greentea, and Sandy Jarrellplus another _Creepy_ classic from the vile vault! You\'ll be sweating with sickening satisfaction! * Featuring a story from _Batman \'66_ team Jeff Parker and Sandy Jarrell! * Beautiful and haunting cover by Juliï¿½ï¿½n Totino Tedesco! * Winner of the Ghastly Award for Best Anthology!', 33),
(502, 'The Shaolin Cowboy: Shemp Buffet', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vUa9BgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Geof Darrow', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=vUa9BgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-vUa9BgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630082024', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-03-17', NULL, 'Collects the complete Dark Horse Comics Shaolin Cowboyseries! â€œA LITTLE LESS CONVERSATION, A LITTLE MORE ACTION!!â€â€”Elvis The Saga of one manâ€™s fight against The Walking Dead as youâ€™ve never seen it before! The action never lets up as a chainsaw of events pits the comic worldâ€™s favorite Shaolin Cowboy against a legion of gourmets from the fourth level of hell, intent on turning Americaâ€™s finest youth into an endless Shemp buffet. Strap on your six-guns, gas up your chainsaw, and hang on, â€™cuz you arenâ€™t in Downton Abbey anymore. *Featuring bonus material not available before in stores.', 144),
(503, 'Mogworld', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cGVqW3auGz8C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Yahtzee Croshaw', NULL, 'Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=cGVqW3auGz8C&rdid=book-cGVqW3auGz8C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621151593', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2008-04-22', NULL, 'In a world full to bursting with would-be heroes, Jim couldn\'t be less interested in saving the day. His fireballs fizzle. He\'s awfully grumpy. Plus, he\'s been dead for about sixty years. When a renegade necromancer wrenches him from eternal slumber and into a world gone terribly, bizarrely wrong, all Jim wants is to find a way to die properly, once and for all. On his side, he\'s got a few shambling corpses, an inept thief, and a powerful death wish. But he\'s up against tough odds: angry mobs of adventurers, a body falling apart at the seams â€” and a team of programmers racing a deadline to hammer out the last few bugs in their AI. *Mogworld is the debut novel from video-game icon Yahtzee Croshaw (Zero Punctuation)! With an exclusive one-chapter preview of Yahtzee Croshaw\'s next novel, Jamâ€”coming to bookstores in October 2012! *Ben \"Yahtzee\" Croshaw\'s video review site, Zero Punctuation, receives over 2,500,000 unique hits a month, and has been licensed by G4 Television. *Yahtzee\'s blog receives about 150,000 hits per day. \"The first legitimate breakout hit from the gaming community in recent memory.\" -Boing Boing', 350),
(504, 'Vampire Hunter D Volume 14: Dark Road Parts 1 & 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sO24HaO8zjgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Hideyuki Kikuchi', NULL, 'Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=sO24HaO8zjgC&rdid=book-sO24HaO8zjgC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621155003', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2012-10-09', NULL, 'D has crossed over the southern border, into the domain of the cruelest and most evil of the royalty, General Gaskell. On the way, he picks up a \"victim\" â€” one of few survivors in the villages-and makes way with her and the Deliverers. Along the way, he is attacked by the Drowned, and fights many more unspeakably horrible enemies. All of this suggests that Gaskell â€” who was supposed to have been put to death under the light of the sun â€” is still very much alive. But why? * Features twelve black-and-white line illustrations by Yoshitaka Amano.', 176),
(505, 'Vampire Hunter D Volume 19: Mercenary Road', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NXjnc32RsTgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Hideyuki Kikuchi', NULL, 'Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=NXjnc32RsTgC&rdid=book-NXjnc32RsTgC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621156765', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2013-03-19', NULL, 'When a quartet of robbers leaves a trail of slaughter through a town, the mayor looks to hire a pair of bounty hunters to bring them to justice. But their path is blocked by an army of soldiers! If they want to survive the journey, they must enlist the help of the Vampire Hunter known only as D. * All-new volume of the bestselling series. * Seven line illustrations by Final Fantasy designer Yoshitaka Amano.', 208),
(506, 'Lobster Johnson: The Satan Factory', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=1CyIQXBN7fQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Thomas E. Sniegoski', NULL, 'Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=1CyIQXBN7fQC&rdid=book-1CyIQXBN7fQC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621154440', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2009-07-21', NULL, 'Hellboy\'s premier crime fighter in an all-new novel! Where greed and the occult walk hand in hand, where mobsters and monsters prowl the streets, none escape the justice of Lobster Johnson! In the years before World War II, Jonas Chapel was a respected physician, until his appetite for vice got the best of him and he found himself on the run from one of New York\'s most powerful mob bosses. On the lam in Mexico, Chapel stumbles across a powerful witch and a cursed skeleton â€” and the power to transform men into monsters. Now, he\'s back in New York, selling his creations to the highest bidder. Only one man, backed by his team of trusted sidekicks, stands in his way. But will the Lobster\'s resolve be enough to shut down Chapel\'s twisted Satan Factory â€” before New York itself is consumed?', 256),
(507, 'Hellboy: The Fire Wolves', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZtEG1l74Y9EC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Tim Lebbon', NULL, 'Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ZtEG1l74Y9EC&rdid=book-ZtEG1l74Y9EC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621154419', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2009-03-31', NULL, 'Hellboy is called to Amalfi, Italy, by Franca, a young member of the Esposito family. She fears that a dark curse on her family is about to claim her cousin as its next victim. Hellboy makes his way to their large home... and he encounters a flaming demona fire wolfwhich he successfully fights off. Hellboy and Franca make their way to Pompeii, where Franca remembers seeing an image of the fire wolf whilst on an archaeological dig. Hellboy unearths the shriveled corpse of a demon hunter who was buried during the AD 79 eruption of Vesuvius, and it tells him of the fire demon that escaped the grip of the volcano... leading to that devastating eruption. As the volcano rumbles again, with a new thirst for human blood, an eruption even more devastating than that historical catastrophe looks very, very close \"Tim Lebbon is an immense talent and he\'s become a new favorite. He has a style and approach unique to the genre.\" â€”Joe R. Lansdale', 256),
(508, 'Predator: The Essential Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_SFcDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Verheiden', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=_SFcDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-_SFcDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506710150', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-12-24', NULL, 'The essential introduction to Predator in the comics! Brutal, invisible, nearly unstoppable. He is the hunter from the stars . . . the Predator. They seek the strongest, the most dangerous game--good or evil. They come in the hottest years (unless they crash land in the middle of a Siberian winter), and they don\'t leave until they\'ve taken their quota of trophies (usually human skulls). But if NYPD detectives Schaefer and Rasche have anything to say about it, the hunt if over! From the Big Apple to the Russian steppes to the jungles of Central America, the detectives and their allies pursue their quarries. And they always get their . . . alien. Before the film Predator 2, there were these comics--a four-color sequel to one of the greatest action films of all time. Written by Mark Verheiden (before he went on to write The Mask, Timecop, Battlestar Galactica, Daredevil and more of your favorite films and TV shows), and illustrated by comics mainstays Chris Warner (creator of Barb Wire) and Ron Randall (creator of Trekker).', 336),
(509, 'Edgar Rice Burroughs\' Tarzan', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dTwCDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Edgar Rice Burroughs', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616557539', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Twenty realistic scenes, accompanied by an abridged text, capture all the excitement of the original tale -- from Tarzan\'s adoption by a family of apes to his clashes later in life with feared jungle predators.', 96),
(510, 'Eve: True Stories', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zVUbAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Daniel Way', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616552725', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"In the early hours of February 5, 2009, one spy single-handedly destroyed the aggressive Band of Brothers alliance and brought an end to the Great War, the largest war in the history of EVE Online\"--', 68),
(511, 'Aw Yeah Comics!', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=L805DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Art Baltazar', NULL, 'JUVENILE FICTION', NULL, '9781506700236', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"This volume collects Aw Yeah Comics!: Action Cat & Adventure Bug #1-#4, originally published by Dark Horse Comics.\"', 104),
(512, 'Creepy Archives Volume 1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=t6lej9kykgIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=t6lej9kykgIC&rdid=book-t6lej9kykgIC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621154358', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2008-08-26', NULL, 'Gather up your wooden stakes, your blood-covered hatchets, and all the skeletons in the darkest depths of your closet, and prepare for a horrifying adventure into the darkest corners of comics history. Dark Horse Comics further corners the market on high quality horror storytelling with one of the most anticipated releases of the decade, a hardcover archive collection of legendary Creepy Magazine. This groundbreaking material turned the world of graphic storytelling on its head in the early 1960s, as phenomenal young artists like Bernie Wrightson and Neal Adams reached new artistic heights with their fascinating explorations of classic and modern horror stories. *Brilliant, classic Creepy stories from 1964-1966 raised from the dead after twenty-five years. *Featuring work by such comics luminaries as Joe Orlando, Al Williamson, Alex Toth, and Frank Frazetta. * Archive editions of Creepy will be the cornerstone of any comic-book library. *Volume One reprints the first five terrifying issues of the magazine\'s original run, reprinted in the original magazine size!', 160),
(513, 'Matt Wagner\'s Grendel Omnibus: The legacy', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4JoBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Wagner', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781595828941', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Celebrates the thirtieth anniversary of Matt Wagner\'s series about millionaire Hunter Rose and his alter ego, the criminal mastermind Grendel.', 548),
(514, 'Tim Biskup', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1593070500', NULL, NULL, '2005-09-01', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(515, 'Star Wars Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vJJ5QgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1595824189', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Collected here are nine stories of Boba Fett\'s high risk and high adventure missions. From settling diplomatic disputes (with extreme prejudice) to a bounty hunter free-for-all, from a duel with Darth Vader to dealing with Boba Fett imposters, if the price is right, there is no job too perilous for this mysterious man in Mandalorian armor!', 494),
(516, 'Jerry and the Joker: Adventures and Comic Art', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QbqvDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jerry Robinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=QbqvDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-QbqvDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630087722', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-10-17', NULL, 'In this memoir, penned by the late Jerry Robinson in his final years, he tells the story of a seventeen-year-old college hopeful who became the artist on Detective Comics, and later Batman, shares his thoughts on creating the Joker as the first super villain, and relates the celebrity-studded journeys that a long life in comics afforded him. In this volume, you\'ll also find never before published original artwork from iconic comics like Detective Comics #76 and Batman #14 and cover artwork featuring Batman, Robin, and the Joker, delving deep into imagery that has shaped the evolution of comics\' most famous villain. \"I always thought that heroes were essentially dull. Villains were more exotic and could do more interesting things\". -Jerry Robinson', 192),
(517, 'The Untold Tales of Dog Mendonca & Pizzaboy (one-shot)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=y3mjCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Filipe Melo', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=y3mjCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-y3mjCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:23101', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2011-04-20', NULL, 'Flanked by his demonic assistant Pazuul and the \"unpaid intern\" known as PizzaBoy, overweight Portuguese werewolf \"Dog\" Mendonca narrates his own bizarre origin story, taking us from a traveling circus to a Nazi laboratory to the depths of Loch Ness! And when we catch up with the present-day MendonÌ¤a, can his team adjust to the new fame and outrageous fortune that come from being published by Dark Horse Comics? Bite into the raucous adventure that was first serialized in _Dark Horse Presents_now in one comic! * Find out how Dog MendonÌ¤a got his powers! * Author Filipe Melo deliberately breaks the fourth wall for an ironic commentary on the comics industry itself. * From the pages of _Dark Horse Presents_!', 34),
(518, 'Angel Season 11', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=P7NDDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joss Whedon', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506703473', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Chasing a vision that links his shameful past with impending doom, Angel reluctantly uses the time-traveling power of Fred\'s alternate form, the goddess Illyria. Not quite sure what will bring changes to the future with only pieces of Angel\'s vision to guide them, they find themselves aboard a cargo ship on the high seas. With Angel\'s past self, Angelus, and his vampire companion, Darla, aboard the ship, Angel and Fred try to keep hidden as Angel begins to remember this voyage that was filled with slaughter and held a mysterious treasure that sank to the bottom of the sea along with the ship...', 104),
(519, 'Drifters', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sTcCDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kohta Hirano', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616553395', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Allied with the elves, samurai warrior Shimazu Toyohisa makes a bold plan to form an alliance between the elves and their generational enemies--the dwarves.', 233),
(520, 'Aw Yeah Comics! And. . Action!', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Bl4BDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Art Baltazar', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '9781616555580', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Features the adventures of Action Cat, Adventure Bug, and their friends as they battle evil and protect the innocent.', 152),
(521, 'Empowered and the Soldier of Love', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cAFSDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Adam Warren', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=cAFSDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-cAFSDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506707112', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-07-10', NULL, 'Crimefighters Empowered and Ninjette struggle with a superhero community fatally inflamed by rampant romance, courtesy of the passion powers of embittered \"magical-girl\" The Soldier of Love. If she prevails, love is toast! Collects Empowered and the Soldier of Love #1-3 plus Adam Warren\'s \"Pew! Pew! Pew!\" Empowered one-shot.', 128),
(522, 'The Terminator: The Original Comics Series-Tempest and One Shot', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Uh05DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Arcudi', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Uh05DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Uh05DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506705514', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-12-19', NULL, 'Heartless, mechanical cruelty meets dogged human courage and perseverance! In the aftermath of the events in James Cameronâ€™s The Terminator (1984), John Connor sends a strike team into the past to destroy Cyberdyne, the company that will eventually create the world-controlling computer Skynet. But the machines counter by sending a team of Terminators to block the attemptâ€”turning Los Angeles into a war zone! Before Terminator 2: Judgment Day or any of the other film sequels, Dark Horse Comics carried the torch for the Terminator saga, creating a continuity that carried the action across the world and across time. The story in this volume, by John Arcudi and Chris Warner, paved the way for a rich parade of sequel tales. Also included in this volume: The Terminator: One Shot, by writer James Robinson and artist Matt Wagner! Introduction by John Arcudi.', 150),
(523, 'Will Eisner\'s the Spirit', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0RTaCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781616559489', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"Denny Colt, a young criminologist believed to have lost his life in a fight against crime, was buried in a state of suspended animation. He awoke one day in Wildwood Cemetery, ready to carry on his struggle . . . his true identity known only to Police Commissioner Dolan. He is feared by criminals of all stripes as THE SPIRIT!\"--', 245),
(524, 'Hellboy Volume 1: Seed of Destruction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0sQvhUmjdbQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Mignola', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=0sQvhUmjdbQC&rdid=book-0sQvhUmjdbQC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621150541', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2004-02-03', NULL, 'Dark Horse presents new editions of the entire Hellboy line with new covers, beginning with Seed of Destruction, the basis of director Guillermo del Toro\'s blockbuster films. Hellboy is one of the most celebrated comics series in recent years. The ultimate artists\' artist and a great storyteller whose work is in turns haunting, hilarious, and spellbinding. Mike Mignola has won numerous awards in the comics industry and beyond. When strangeness threatens to engulf the world, a strange man will come to save it. Sent to investigate a mystery with supernatural overtones, Hellboy discovers the secrets of his own origins, and his link to the Nazi occultists who promised Hitler a final solution in the form of a demonic avatar. \" ... Hellboy is a brilliant example of how to elevate the comic of the future to a higher literary level while achieving a higher pitch of excitement.\" â€”Robert Bloch, from his introduction', 128),
(525, 'Ring of Fire', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-6lIFgK_JwAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569714827', NULL, 'Tarcher', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Buffy\'s lover, Angel, loses his soul and emerges as the murderous Angelus, a vampire feared throughout Europe for decades, now thirsting for power and for the blood of the Slayer.', 117),
(526, 'Father\'s Day', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UoAkCQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Richardson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=UoAkCQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-UoAkCQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630081843', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-07-07', NULL, 'Once a feared Chicago mob enforcer, Silas Smith has gone underground and found peace in seclusion. . . until his estranged daughter shows up on his doorstep with a major axe to grind. And though Silas abandoned his violent past, his former bosses are now on his trail with swcores to settle, intent on teaching Silas that crime doesn\'t play! From Mike Richardson, creator of The Mask and TimeCop, Father\'s Day is a white-knuckle crime thriller loaded with action, laughs, and heart.', 104),
(527, 'Creepy Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RTgCDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Arcudi', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616553463', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'What\'s that huge, terrifying thing clawing its way onto your bookshelf? It\'s the biggest, bloodiest, most creepy collection of new terror tales you\'ll find this year!', 176),
(528, 'Mystery Science Theater 3000, the Comic', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9r-rDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joel Hodgson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506709475', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"Jonah Heston, Tom Servo, and Crow T. Robot are subjected to life within old public domain comic books by mad scientist Kinga Forrester\"--', 160),
(529, 'Beanworld', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JrkFDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=JrkFDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-JrkFDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630087647', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-07-04', NULL, 'The most peculiar comic book experience returns in an all-new volume--Beanworld Volume 4: Hoka Hoka Burb\'l Burb\'l! The Boom\'r Band coaxes a new healing power out of Chow, leading to a visit from Dreamishness\'s relatives--the Windy Songsterinos--who bring their gift of rain. The storm causes great changes to Mr. Spook, Beanish and the Pod\'l\'pool Cuties. Marder\'s deceptively simple artwork illustrates a self-contained ecological fantasy realm with its own unique rules and lingo. Beanworld has delighted readers from grade school to grad school for more than a generation, earning a spot on the New York Times Graphic Books Best Sellers List. \"I have yet to find a comic book as challenging and inventive and downright fun as Beanworld.\" -Scott McCloud, author of Understanding Comics and The Sculptor', 152),
(530, 'Aliens Vs. Predator: the Essential Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=l0CzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Randy Stradley', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506715674', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '2019-10-29', NULL, 'Fourteen years before the first AVP film, the comics laid the groundwork. Now collected for the first time in one volume is the complete Machiko Noguchi/Aliens Versus Predator trilogy--over 400 pages of extraterrestrial action! Two of cinema\'s greatest monsters clash in a battle that spans the galaxy and extends across one woman\'s lifetime! Machiko Noguchi\'s life was altered when she was caught in the middle of a collision between a ravenous Alien horde and a hunting party of Predators. That initial conflict ended her living and hunting with the Predators for a time--until the hunters zeroed in on human prey, forcing Machiko to decide where her loyalties truly lie.', 424),
(531, 'Toss the Bones', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UDwCDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Tobin', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781616557768', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"Nimble Jack returns to drive Boston mad, and only Declan Thomas can stop him. With his body failing and his sanity crumbling, Declan balances between falling into madness and instant death\"--', 136),
(532, 'Blood of a Thousand', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=z7pkBBadvR4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Hiroaki Samura', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569712395', NULL, 'Dark Horse Manga', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Manji, a ronin warrior of feudal Japan, has been cursed with immortality and to rid his eternal suffering and lift the curse, he must slay one thousand enemies, and his quest begins with a young girl who seeks revenge on her parents\' killers.', 136),
(533, 'No One Left to Fight #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6a-qDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Aubrey Sitterson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=6a-qDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-6a-qDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3004925', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-10-02', NULL, 'The comic you always wanted continues to give you exactly what you need with \'\'Enter! The Arboreal Sanctum!\'\' From Aubrey Sitterson (The Comic Book Story of Professional Wrestling, G.I. Joe) and Fico Ossio (Spider- Man, Revolution), the iconic heroes of No One Left to Fight believe they\'ve found a peaceful retreat, until they\'re confronted by a monstrous threat from their pastâ€”revivified, improved, and ready to finish what he started.', 32);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(534, 'Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MihlAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Steve Duin', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569713448', NULL, 'Tarcher', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'This lavish volume takes an in-depth look at the history of comics in a manner decidedly unlike the dry timelines and profiles of most reference-style titles. Via alphabetical entries, the authors take an irreverent, often hilarious, behind-the-scenes look at creators, companies, characters, collectors, and conventions, pulling no punches when exposing some of the darker sides of the industry. Containing countless stories gleaned from over 150 interviews of comics industry veterans, Comics Between the Panels is loaded with more than half a century of insider information on the talented and eccentric creators who forged the comics industry and art form. Features 670 illustrations and photos - including dynamic and bizarre cover art compiled under such curious headings as Atomic Bombs, Death with Indignity, Gorillas, Headlights, Hooded Menaces, and Skulls.', 498),
(535, 'He-Man and the Masters of the Universe the Newspaper Comic Strips', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RIvmDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'James Shull', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506700731', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'For over four years, Masters of the Universe had its own newspaper comic strip! This story continued the tales from the Filmation cartoon bridged the saga to the space-themed New Adventures of He-Man cartoon relaunch. The comic strip only ran in selected newspapers and was never reprinted, so most fans have never read it... until now! For the first time ever Dark Horse brings you a collection of these strips, restored and ready for you to unleash the Power!', 496),
(536, 'Uncle Scrooge Comics Character #3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rlNrPgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Deluxe', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1596178043', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2009-10-28', NULL, 'Dark Horse is giving one of the comic-book medium\'s most revered cast of characters the Syroco-style treatment in a new series of statuettes based on Disney\'s Uncle Scrooge stories. The third character in this series is Duckburg\'s most famous inventor, Gyro Gearloose. This statue of Gyro also features his tiny assistant \"Helper\" sitting in the palm of his hand. Limited to 650 numbered pieces, this statuette is packaged in a special litho-printed, full-color tin box with a vintage-style pin-back button and booklet.', NULL),
(537, 'The EC Archives: Tales from the Crypt', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=l5HCDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=l5HCDQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-l5HCDQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630089474', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-08-23', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics brings you the legendary Tales from the Crypt in all its gory glory! This grisly grimoire has been digitally recoloredâ€”using Marie Severinâ€™s original colors as a guideâ€”and features stories drawn by all-star comic artists Jack Davis, Joe Orlando, Jack Kamen, Graham Ingels, George Evans, Reed Crandall, Bill Elder, and Bernie Krigstein! Collects Tales from the Crypt issues #35â€“#40 in full color! * Foreword by industry legend Russ Cochran! * Includes all the original ads, text pieces, and letters! * Look for more additions to the EC line! Two-Fisted Tales, Weird Fantasy, and more! â€œPossibly, the greatest line of comics ever produced.â€ â€”Mike Richardson', 216),
(538, 'Fallout: New Vegas', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=keun-GQdhEoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chris Avellone', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=keun-GQdhEoC&rdid=book-keun-GQdhEoC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621155461', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2007-11-13', NULL, 'Bethesda Softworks teams up with Dark Horse Comics to create Fallout: New Vegasâ€”All Roads, a complete graphic novel previously only available in the Fallout: New Vegas collector\'s edition! All Roads introduces the world of New Vegas, a town of dreamers and desperadoes being torn apart by warring factions vying for complete control of this desert oasis, and tells an intriguing tale of loyalty and violence that leads right up to the beginning of the game. Written by Chris Avellone, the game\'s senior designer, All Roads is tightly integrated into the story of New Vegas, even containing clues to ingame missions for the sharpeyed reader. Artists Jean Diaz (Incorruptible) and Wellinton Alves (Shadowland: Blood on the Streets, Nova) and cover artist Geof Darrow (Hard Boiled, The Matrix Comics, The Big Guy and Rusty the Boy Robot) stunningly interpret the world of New Vegas!', 47),
(539, 'Dark Horse Number Ones', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5TBSDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gerard Way', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506702964', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Dark Horse brings you eight complete first issues of series by top industry talents to introduce you to your next favorite read. Fantasy, mystery, sci-fi, adventure, and horror tales open the door to new storytelling worlds. Including Gerard Way and Gabriel Ba\'s Umbrella Academy #1, Mike Mignola\'s Hellboy in Hell #1, Joelle Jones and Jamie S. Rich\'s Lady Killer #1, Jeff Lemire and Dean Ormston\'s Black Hammer #1, Matt Kindt and Sharlene Kindt\'s Dept. H #1, Brian Wood and Mark Chater\'s Briggs Land #1, Kurtis Wiebe and Mindy Lee\'s Bounty #1, and Cullen Bunn and Tyler Crook\'s Harrow County #1.', 208),
(540, 'The Tomorrows', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E2qoDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Curt Pires', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=E2qoDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-E2qoDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630085285', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-09-20', NULL, 'A brain-bursting sci-fi thrill ride from the mind of Curt Pires! The Future: art is illegal. Everything everyone ever posted online has been weaponized against them. The reign of The Corporation is quickly becoming as absolute as it is brutal--unless The Tomorrows can stop it. Artists, terrorists, they fight with explosives, they fight with ideas, they fight to reclaim the future we sold. Collects issues #1-6, the complete first volume of Pires mind-bending series, each issue illustrated by a different artist!', 144),
(541, 'Black Hammer/Justice League: Hammer of Justice! #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6jybDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jeff Lemire', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=6jybDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-6jybDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3004083', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-07-10', NULL, 'DC Comics and Dark Horse Comics present the ultimate superhero crossover event of 2019! A strange man arrives simultaneously on Black Hammer Farm and in Metropolis, and both worlds are warped as Starro attacks! Batman, Green Lantern, Flash, Wonder Woman, Superman, and more crossover with Golden Gail, Colonel Weird, and the rest of the Black Hammer gang!', 32),
(542, 'Lone', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4cZwtvR9HYIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Stuart Moore', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1593072651', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Sharpshooter Luke and his brother Mark must track down a legendary gunman known as Lone to help fight zombies who have overrun the town of Desolation.', 152),
(543, 'Axe Cop Vol. 4: President of the World', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=SqqvJ68WnLgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Malachai Nicolle', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=SqqvJ68WnLgC&rdid=book-SqqvJ68WnLgC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621156758', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2013-07-16', NULL, 'Axe Cop is now president of the whole world! But a bunch of outer-space bad guys are on their way to Earth, and they\'re bringing big trouble with them! Collects the three-issue miniseries. * Axe Cop will be part of a new Fox Animated television programming block!', 96),
(544, 'Creepy Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=dCYDDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Braun', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781595827500', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'What\'s that huge, terrifying thing clawing its way onto your bookshelf? It\'s the biggest, bloodiest, most creepy collection of new terror tales you\'ll find this year!', 176),
(545, 'Living with the Dead', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=virBBQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Richardson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=virBBQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-virBBQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621152361', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2014-12-17', NULL, 'Two survivors of a global catastrophe disguise themselves as corpses to survive in a land of the walking dead. Soon the two friends save a lovely young gun-crazy woman named Betty, who becomes a source of rivalry between them. With hundreds of zombies out for a snack, the three try their best to blend in so as not become the next item on the menu. From the mind of Mike Richardson, creator of The Mask and The Secret, comes this hilariously frightening tale of Straw and Whip who have lived through a plague that\'s left the world with seven billion brain-hungry zombies. * Be sure to catch this heart pounding and hilarious graphic novel with art by Ben Stenbeck, and cover by legendary Richard Corben (Hulk: Banner; Punisher: The End; and Hellboy: Makoma). * Collecting the three-issue miniseries.', 88),
(546, 'Tales of the Beanworld', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AZoBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781595828972', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Gathers sequences of the author\'s comic featuring a peculiar universe filled with beanlike creatures trying to live their lives in harmony, with new color added, along with more recent stories that originally appeared in print or online.', 64),
(547, 'Astro boy', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zlpQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Osamu Tezuka', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, 'UOM:39015060565713', NULL, NULL, '2003-01-22', NULL, 'The robotic Astro Boy battles a deadly underground tank, helps solve a murder, and prevents the world from being destroyed by a robot bomb.', 216),
(548, 'Tomb Raider Archives', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UoclDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Jurgens', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '9781506703527', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-04-11', NULL, '\"There\'s only one woman capable of tracking down the world\'s rarest artifacts: Lara Croft. Armed with her iconic twin pistols, Lara crisscrosses the globe in search of adventure\"--', 464),
(549, 'Avatar: The Last Airbender - Smoke and Shadow', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DZLVCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gene Luen Yang', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=DZLVCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-DZLVCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630085933', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-12-29', NULL, 'With the disappearances of children in the Fire Nation capital, Avatar Aang and his friends are doing everything they can to find out whoâ€”or whatâ€”is responsible. Aang and Zuko must work together to keep the peace, but the emergence of the New Ozai Society, and the appearance of the mysterious Kemurikage of legend, may prove to be too much even for the Avatar when the true culprit of the kidnappings is revealed! * The official continuation of Airbender from its creators, Michael Dante DiMartino and Bryan Konietzko! * The perfect companion to The Legend of Korra!', 80),
(550, 'Dota 2 the Comic Collection', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NXcqDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Valve CORPORATION', NULL, 'Battles', NULL, '9781506703480', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'DEFENSE OF THE ANCIENTS is a highly popular Multiplayer online battle arena video game currently developed by Valve Corporation who have achieved considerable successes in the video game industry with the Half-Life and Portal franchises. Based on the Warcraft III engine, the original game was a huge favourite at gaming conventions and received considerable acclaim. After the property was acquired by Valve a standalone sequel DOTA 2 was produced and was also a huge hit and for a time was the video game with the highest of users in Steam history. Now alongside Dark Horse Valve have produced a new collection of tie-in comics that expand on the DOTA world.', 200),
(551, 'False Memories', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0GVYrYX45ecC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Jim Pascoe', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569717362', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'When Dawn vanishes, the Scooby gang has no clue where to find her, but Buffy will stop at nothing to find Dawn, even if she has to face a cadre of crazed, bloodsucking monks and a former Vampire Slayer turned Slayer Vampire.', 96),
(552, 'Frank Miller\'s Sin City', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fGjNDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Frank Miller', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506700700', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Frank Miller is arguably the most important cartoonist (writer AND artist) working in comics over the last 25 years. Mr. Miller is back in the spotlight with the release of DC\'s Dark Knight III- The Master Racein late 2015.Frank Miller\'s Sin City- The Hard Goodbye Curator\'s Collection includes the entire Eisner Award-winning graphic novel, now scanned from the original artwork in Frank Miller\'s personal archives and reproduced at the actual size he originally drew it. Twenty-five years after its first publication in the pages of Dark Horse Presents, get ready to experience one of the most groundbreaking graphic novels of all time as few have ever seen it! Produced and assembled under the Kitchen Sink Books/Dark Horse Books imprint, Frank Miller\'s Sin City- The Hard Goodbye Curator\'s Collectionshowcases the entire Eisner Award-winning graphic novel, now scanned from the original artwork in Frank Miller\'s personal archives and reproduced at full size. Introduction by film director Robert Rodriguez, with an afterword by Dark Horse publisher Mike Richardson and an interview about the artistic process with Frank Miller! This Curator\'s Collection includes- The Sin Citychapters from Dark Horse Presentsissues #51 to #62 and the Dark Horse Presents- 5th Anniversary Special. Previously collected in TR and HC as Sin City- The Hard Goodbye. The Curator\'s Collectionwill also include a new introduction, afterword, and interview content. \"Miller is the most important comic book artist of the last 25 years.\" -Los Angeles Times', 224),
(553, 'Pros and (Comic) Cons', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XV6IDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Hope Nicholson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=XV6IDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-XV6IDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506711829', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-06-11', NULL, 'Following the bestselling The Secret Loves of Geeks comes this brand-new anthology featuring comics and prose stories by cartoonists and professional geeks about the world of comic book conventions from the guests who\'ve attended them across the world. Featuring stories that are funny, sad, sweet, embarrassing, and heartfelt; of a geek culture life that shapes us, encourages us, and exhausts us every summer. Featuring work by Brian Michael Bendis (The Man of Steel), Jim Zub (Wayward), Kieron Gillen (The Wicked and the Divine), Sina Grace (Iceman), and many more.', 196),
(554, 'Brom', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1593070454', NULL, NULL, '2005-09-01', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(555, 'Ghost Omnibus Volume 3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UiQCDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Martin Lodewyk', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781595823748', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Ghost, the spectral protector of Chicago, defends the world against extradimensional demons and all-too-human monsters.', 368),
(556, 'Empowered', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=X0-NDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Adam Warren', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=X0-NDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-X0-NDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506715063', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-10-01', NULL, 'Costumed crimefighter Empowered finds herself the desperate prey of a maniacal supervillain whose godlike powers have turned an entire city of suprahumans against her. Not good! Outnumbered and under siege, aided only by a hero\'s ghost, can Emp survive the relentless onslaught long enough to free her enslaved teammates and loved ones, or is this--*gulp*--The End? From comics overlord Adam Warren comes Empowered, the acclaimed sexy superhero comedy--except when it isn\'t, as in this volume\'s no-nonsense, wall-to-wall brawl guaranteed to bring tears to the eye and fists to the face!', 216),
(557, 'Buffy the Vampire Slayer: Tales', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QopUwPpIzSoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joss Whedon', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781621156581', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2011-01-11', NULL, 'Before Season Eight, Joss Whedon brought generations of Slayers and vampires to comics with the help of his acclaimed TV writing team and some of the best artists to ever grace the comics page. Now all those stories, plus selected stories from Season Eight, are collected in one deluxe collection with a new cover by Jo Chen. Joss writes multiple tales: a somber vamp tale, drawn by Cameron Stewart; the story of the first Slayer, drawn by Leinil Yu; and more. Buffy the Vampire Slayer: Tales also reprints for the first time new Season Eight stories written by novelist Jackie Kessler (Hell\'s Belles) and awardwinning cartoonist Becky Cloonan (Demo), featuring vampires living in the public eye, killing Slayers and killing each other. * This book collects stories from MySpace Dark Horse Presents #31 and Tales of the Vampires: Carpe Noctem parts 1 and 2; Buffy: Tales of the Vampires oneshot; Buffy the Vampire Slayer: Tales of the Vampires #1#5; Buffy the Vampire Slayer: Tales of the Slayers #1\"Broken Bottle of Djinn\"; Buffy the Vampire Slayer: Tales of the Slayers TPB. Before Season Eight . . .', 296),
(558, 'The Art of Akaneiro', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YDUCDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ben Kerslake', NULL, 'Art', NULL, '9781616552206', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'From the brilliant imagination of video game auteur American McGee comes a dazzling reenvisioning of Red Riding Hood set in the wondrous world of Japanese folklore! A young woman torn between two cultures takes on an epic adventure battling devious yokaifor the fate of her world! Collects the three-issue miniseries. * Based on the hot new game by American McGee\'s Spicy Horse Games! * Written by Justin Aclin (Star Wars- The Clone Wars), and illustrated by Vasilis Lolos (Conan the Barbarian)!', 96),
(559, 'Conan', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9UsBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Roy Thomas', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781595828170', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"It\'s a pirate\'s life for Conan, commanding a ship of mongrel sailors and pillaging across the Vilayet Sea. But his swashbuckling days are cut short when his companion Olivia receives a vision of her royal father, who sold her into slavery, wishing for her return. Conan and Olivia set out on the fabled Road of Kings, but the journey is a treacherous one, filled with monsters, angry victims of Conan\'s light fingers, and other thieving highwaymen. While Conan becomes caught up in palace intrigue along the way, a slaver kidnaps Olivia, determined to collect a ransom from her father!\"--Page 4 of cover.', 143),
(560, 'Think Like a Mountain', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7HdQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1593075596', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Presents the adventures of Concrete, a political speech writer who finds himself trapped in an alien body made of living stone.', 205),
(561, 'Disney Zootopia: Friends to the Rescue (Younger Readers)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7qFaDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Disney', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '9781506710617', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-09-25', NULL, 'Collects two stories of teamwork and creativity from the childhood years of Judy Hopps and Nick Wilde--two characters from the animated film--especially for younger readers! Judy is excited to tour the fun at the Bunnyburrow County Fair with her Pop Pop, but Dinah has to sneak out of the house to join her! Then, when Pop Pop says no to a hot air balloon ride, Judy still gets her chance in the air when Dinah stumbles into trouble and needs rescuing! It will take both their talents, rabbit and sloth, to ensure that everyone makes it safely home at the end of the day. Meanwhile, Nick learns it\'s the thought that counts when he saves the day at his friend Hedy\'s birthday party. While he might not have enough money to buy a gift, Nick has other talents that he puts to good use for a truly unforgettable celebration. This story collection from writer Jimmy Gownley (Amelia Rules!) and artist Leandro Ricardo da Silva, with colors by Wes Dzioba (Serenity, Star Wars: Invasion, Aliens vs. Predator: Three World War) and letters by Chris Dickey (Cable, X-Men: The Hidden Years), shares two tales of how talent and teamwork can overcome sticky situations. Written for younger readers, this volume will appeal to Zootopia fans of all ages with its adventurous characters and engaging artwork. Also included in this volume are a variety of story-related activities and special features!', 48),
(562, 'Octopus Girl', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fIpQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'UOM:39015069208281', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Being able to change herself into a teenage head with octopus tentacles allows her to discover horrors in the ocean as well as in Japan. Octopus Girl and Sakae face satanic cults, pregnancy, death-trap elevators, violent family strife, and their own backbiting rivalry! Cutting a crass, comical niche into modern horror manga, Toru Yamazaki\'s Octopus Girlserves up the most disgusting dishes of heartbreak and revenge found on land or at sea, and these shocking vignettes will hypnotize fans of the macabre and the absurd!', 190),
(563, 'New Recruits', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=BiXuAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1593073836', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'A collection of stories from newcomers in comics, including Andrew Krahnke\'s \"Zombiekiller\" and Ian Culbard\'s \"The Way of All Flesh.\"', 142),
(564, 'Catalyst Comix', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=yUdEAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Casey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=yUdEAwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-yUdEAwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621159667', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2014-07-15', NULL, 'Straight from the glory of Comics\' Greatest World, Frank \"Titan\" Wells, Amazing Grace, and the Agents of Change are back, baby! But you\'ve never seen them like this! Superstar writer Joe Casey--along with the widest array of artistic talent this side of the Renaissance--gives superhero comics a back-alley facelift, as these very different champions confront cosmic threats, personal demons, superheroes\' role as global activists, an alien love invasion, and the strangest virtual reality you\'ve ever experienced--but not before they face the end of the world as we know it! Collects Catalyst Comix #1-#9!', 284),
(565, 'Halo', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5w_aCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Reed', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '9781616557591', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-09-29', NULL, 'Halo 4 Spartan Ops continues here as the UNSC Infinity battles the Covenant for control of the all-powerful Forerunner Janus Key. Plus, Spartan Tanaka\'s thrilling origin story revealed - all in this volume collecting Halo: Escalation issues #13 -#18. After working directly with the developers of Mass Effect (Microsoft) for their series of graphic novel adaptations, Dark Horse have now become the publisher of choice for many video game companies, and this latest addition looks set to become one of the smash hits of 2014.', 144),
(566, 'The Savage Sword of Conan', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UaefCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Roy Thomas', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781630085759', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-11-10', NULL, 'Inheriting the captaincy of a Barachan pirate ship, Conan and his crew are captured and imprisoned in a Kushite dungeon, with no seeming avenue of escape. That is, until Conan makes a pact with a mysterious prisonerâ€”Imhotep, the Ravager of Worlds, one of Conanâ€™s deadliest enemies! Collects Conan stories from Marvelâ€™s The Savage Sword of Conan the Barbarian #202â€“#212.', 576),
(567, 'You Deserved It', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7XdQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1593073909', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Is Bob Fingerman a cynical misanthrope or a disappointed humanitarian? Dare we suggest maybe both? In You Deserved It, the sensitive creator of the acclaimed graphic novel Beg the Question accesses his darker side, serving up this caustic collection of comical cautionary chronicles. What Beg the Question was to sex and romance, You Deserved It is to wanton violence and social wrongness. From \"Otis Goes Hollywood,\" the epic saga of a homicidally puritanical meat packer with dreams of making it big in Hollywood, to \"Missing Pieces,\" a yarn about the extracurricular activities of paramedics, to \"Buying Bologna,\" about a guy who just really, really loves his luncheon meat, to \"Yiffy Situation,\" a fuzzy fable about fornicating Furries, You Deserved It serves up enough yarns to make one hilariously misanthropic sweater, all in living - and dying - color!', 87),
(568, 'Plants vs. Zombies Volume 1: Lawnmageddon', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=TULGAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Tobin', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=TULGAAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-TULGAAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621158462', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2013-11-19', NULL, 'The confusing-yet-brilliant inventor known only as Crazy Dave helps his niece, Patrice, and young adventurer Nate Timely fend off a \"fun-dead\" neighborhood invasion in Plants vs. Zombies: Lawnmageddon! Winner of over thirty \"Game of the Year\" awards, Plants vs. Zombies is now determined to shuffle onto all-ages bookshelves to tickle funny bones and thrill... brains. * The first Plants vs. Zombies comic book! *', 80),
(569, 'The Legend of Zelda', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=J1u1vAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, 'Games & Activities', NULL, '1506710115', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '2018-11-20', NULL, NULL, 424),
(570, 'Midnight Society: The Black Lake', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MHrqCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Drew Edward Johnson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=MHrqCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-MHrqCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630083939', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-02-02', NULL, 'Forty years ago, Englandâ€™s greatest adventurers shattered their friendship, making a terrible choice that would come to haunt humanity. Forty years later, when sheâ€™s sent on a desperate rescue operation to Scotlandâ€™s Loch Ness, secret agent Matilda Finn faces the consequences of that choice and questions her already-loose ties to human society. Collects Midnight Society: The Black Lake #1â€“#4. â€œA gem of a comic book.â€â€”Oscar Maltby, Newsarama â€œDrew Johnson has drawn a beautifully elucidated world . . . The word â€˜impeccableâ€™ comes to mind.â€â€”Walter Simonson', 128),
(571, 'Oh My Goddess!.', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sBQ04pUzDjwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1569714312', NULL, 'Dark Horse Manga', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'After lonely college student Keiichi dials a wrong number, his wish of having a goddess as a companion is granted, and many adventures ensue involving him, his goddess girlfriend, her older sister, and other unworldly friends.', 117),
(572, 'H. G. Wells\' the War of the Worlds', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=g3BQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Ian Edginton', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'UOM:39015063295516', NULL, NULL, '2006-04-19', NULL, 'Humans battle evil aliens to save Earth and its people from certain doom when the Martians land in England.', 71),
(573, 'Black Hammer \'45: From the World of Black Hammer', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bYWODwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jeff Lemire', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=bYWODwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-bYWODwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506708720', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-10-29', NULL, 'From the world of the Eisner-award winning Black Hammer series comes a gripping World War II action adventure tale! During the Golden Age of superheroes, an elite Air Force crew called the Black Hammer Squadron bands together to combat the Nazis, a host of occult threats, and their ultimate aerial warrior the Ghost Hunter. This volume collects Black Hammer \'45 #1-4 from the all-star creative team of Ray Fawkes, Jeff Lemire, and Matt Kindt, as well as a sketchbook section.', 120),
(574, 'Crash Test Demons', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=X4dboUwnWosC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Pimente', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569714614', NULL, 'Tarcher', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'In Buffy\'s senior year in high school she is confronted with Selke, her old enemy, who is contemplating a scheme to get her vengence on Buffy. Original.', 117),
(575, 'Strayed #4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eXKzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Carlos Giffoni', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eXKzDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-eXKzDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3005320', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-11-20', NULL, 'An explosive development makes Premier Peely\'s dreams a palpable reality. Lou struggles with illness as the world around him falls into total disarray.', 32),
(576, 'Beanworld Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5AFSDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Larry Marder', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=5AFSDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-5AFSDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506707983', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-07-10', NULL, 'The iconic inhabitants of Larry Marder\'s unique Beanworld universe are introduced in this complete collection of Beanworld comic-book issues #1-#21! Join Mr. Spook, Professor Garbanzo, Beanish, and many others as they experience adventures in their world that prove, whether friends or adversaries, they are all ultimately dependent on each other for survival. Marder\'s deceptively simple artwork illustrates a self-contained ecological fantasy realm with its own unique rules, truths, and lingo. Beanworld has delighted readers from grade school to grad school for more than a generation, earning a spot on the New York Times Graphic Books Best Sellers List.', 607),
(577, 'Choke Gasp! The Best of 75 Years of EC Comics Sampler', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PRSjDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Gaines', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=PRSjDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-PRSjDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3006107', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-08-14', NULL, 'Four free stories from the upcoming Choke Gasp! The Best of 75 Years of EC Comics, a premiere collection of the best stories of EC Comics, curated in a deluxe volume, just in time to celebrate the legendary publisher\'s 75th anniversary! The full volume, on sale December 18th for both print and digital, features classic stories from the hands of legendary creators Al Feldstein, Harvey Kurtzman, Johnny Craig, Jack Davis, Wally Wood, and more! Included in this sampler are the classic stories Master Race, Taint the Meat . . . It\'s the Humanity!, Yellow!, and Judgment Day! â€¢ Four free classics from EC Comics! â€¢ Comics from legendary creators Bernie Krigstein, Jack Davis, Bill Gaines, and Al Feldstein! â€¢ Free preview for a deluxe volume with 65 classic tales!\"[EC Comics had] the first intelligent sci-fi comics.\"â€“Steven Spielberg \"EC Comics has an indelible impact on me.\"â€“George Lucas \"[Tales from the Crypt] was seminal in the history of graphic horror. [. . .] This little comic book was pulp horror at its finest.\"â€“John Carpenter', NULL),
(578, 'Abe Sapien #18', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2yWiCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Mignola', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=2yWiCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-2yWiCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:24532', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2014-12-10', NULL, 'Having joined a Santa Muerte cult, Abe settles into a small Gulf town with hidden ties to the zombie massacre he failed to stop in Arizona. With more lives depending on him than ever, will he fail again? The first five-part arc starts here! You\'d be a fool to miss out on _Abe Sapien_. Fine comics indeed.ï¿½Bloody Disgusting _Abe Sapien_ is another strong monthly dose of horror, and now\'s a great time to find out for yourself.ï¿½Comic Book Resources I read a ton of Dark Horse titles each month and really each week, but for my money _Abe Sapien_ really is one of the best they publish.ï¿½Comic Bastards', 25),
(579, 'Flaming Carrot Comics Presents Flaming Carrot, Man of Mystery!', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QUsLAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Bob Burden', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569712638', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'The legendary, cult classic, runaway hit of the 1980s returns like Kaiser Sosse on the midnight tide! Before Madman and Bone, before Hate and Hellboy and Eightball (and before Ritalin), all fandom\'s avante garde lunatic fringe had to read was the Flaming Carrot. Long out of print, this buried treasure, this manic, zany, oddball title is coming back home just when the comic marketplace needs him the most!', 126),
(580, 'The Dark Horse Book of Hauntings', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PTRZAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'P. Craig Russell', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PSU:000056684179', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Hellboy Investigates a hidden cellar and discovers his own uncanny connection to the spirits within ... a young boy leads friends and family alike into an abandoned house from which no one ever leaves ... and an unprecedented fisticuffs ensues between a world traveler and the ancient spirit of an English mansion ... These ghostly stories and more await you within The Dark Horse Book of Hauntings, a collection of original short horror stories by an award-winning lineup of comics\' top talent.', 92),
(581, 'Dragon Age: Magekiller', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Zm53DAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Zm53DAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Zm53DAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630080716', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-08-09', NULL, 'â€œDragon Age: Magekiller is a fun and engaging fantasy story for anyone who enjoys the genre.â€â€”Comic Book Resources Tessa and Marius are mercenary partners who eliminate those that use magic to hurt others. When they betray a powerful patron intending to kill them, theyâ€™re forced to flee and join the Inquisition. Collects issues #1â€“#5 of the miniseries.', 120),
(582, 'The Best of Milligan & McCarthy', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sSPXDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter Milligan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=sSPXDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-sSPXDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621158271', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-02-12', NULL, 'One of comics\' most fruitful collaborations gets its due in this deluxe collection of hard-to-find gems from Peter Milligan (Hellblazer, X-Statix) and Brendan McCarthy (Judge Dredd, The Zaucer of Zilk)! Collecting twenty years\' worth of the pair\'s finest work from Vanguard Illustrated, Strange Days, 2000 AD, and Vertigo, this beautiful hardcover includes art that has been newly touched up by McCarthy and features original commentary by both creators. There is still nothing else like Freakwave, Paradax!, Skin, and Rogan Gosh, and this volume is both the perfect retrospective for fans and the ideal starting place for new readers!', 264),
(583, 'Predator Versus Judge Dredd Versus Aliens: Splice and Dice', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bbgFDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=bbgFDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-bbgFDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630087791', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-02-06', NULL, 'The ultimate science-fiction crossover pits the legendary lawman, Judge Dredd, against the universe\'s supreme hunters, the Predators, as they both try to survive an onslaught by the galaxy\'s ultimate killing machines, the Aliens! Judge Dredd and Judge Anderson have tracked a criminal cult across the Cursed Earth and into the Alabama morass, where a mad genetic scientist with destructive designs has acquired the best genes that evolution has to offer--a xenomorph skull! A Predator, attracted to the warm climate and superior prey, has declared hunting season as he calls for backup. All paths will cross in a mind-blowing scifi showdown with the fate of the Earth at stake! -Collects issues #1-#4 of the Dark Horse Comics series Predator vs. Judge Dredd vs. Aliens. -Written by Eisner-Award winning, NYT Bestselling Chew creator John Layman! -Covers by Eisner-Award winner Glenn Fabry! -The ultimate science-fiction crossover! -Three of the universe\'s most ruthless killers cross paths -\"Exactly as awesome as it sounds.\"--Comics Alliance', 104),
(584, 'Demo', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Uw_aCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Wood', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616556822', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'It\'s hard enough being a teenager. Now try being a teenager with powers... Demo chronicles the lives of young people who are on their separate journeys to self-discovery in a world - just like our own - where being different is feared. This definitive edition of Demo by Brian Wood (The New York Four, The Massive [Dark Horse, also available from Turnaround]) and Becky Cloonan (The True Lives of the Fabulous Killjoys [Dark Horse, also available from Turnaround]) collects the entirety of the series, 18 short stories across multiple genres and stands as an indie comics classic.', 496),
(585, 'The Chronicles of Conan Volume 30', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JF_ZCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Michael Higgins', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781616555894', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Collects Conan the Barbarian #233-240, originally published by Marvel Comics in 1990-1991.', 200),
(586, 'Ghost Volume 1: In the Smoke and Din', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3DAI3IcX8RYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kelly Sue DeConnick', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=3DAI3IcX8RYC&rdid=book-3DAI3IcX8RYC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621157830', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2013-08-13', NULL, 'Supernatural! One warm night in Chicago\'s Resurrection Cemetery, paranormal investigators Vaughn and Tommy accidentally summon a beautiful, transparent woman. Their search for her true identity uncovers a dark, hidden history of the city and a deadly alliance between political corruption and demonic science! In the middle of it all stands a woman trapped between two worlds! Collects Ghost #0-#4. * Kelly Sue DeConnick (Captain Marvel). * Phil Noto (Angel & Faith, X-23). \"Kelly Sue DeConnick provides further evidence of why she\'s so highly rated amongst other comic book professionals with [Ghost], a story that I struggle to classify, despite enjoying what I\'ve read so far.\" â€”Comic Bastards', 120),
(587, 'StarCraft: Survivors #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ezybDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jody Houser', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ezybDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-ezybDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3003449', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-07-24', NULL, 'Jody Houser and Gabriel GuzmÃ¡n continue the tale of StarCraft: Scavengers! After surviving a murderous dark templar\'s rampage, a terran space engineer named Caleb is forced to do the protoss\'s bidding: infiltrating a munitions factory in the Umojan Protectorate to find a mysterious source of power. This official expansion of the StarCraft universe in comics is based on an original story by Jody Houser and Blizzard Entertainment\'s StarCraft game team! Official StarCraft comics--written by Jody Houser!', 32),
(588, 'The Goon Library Volume 3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rWQqDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781616559861', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-06-14', NULL, 'The Goon is a series written and drawn by Eric Powell (often with colours by multi-Eisner winner Dave Stewart). The series mixes comedy and violence with a supernatural slant. The Goon Library series collects a number of The Goon trades in a deluxe, oversize hardcover format. Fear and misery plague the town on the edge of Horse-Eater\'s Wood. After the death of a friend and ally reveals the return of Labrazio, the Goon\'s sworn enemy thought long gone, the Goon realises that something darker is going on in the town than anyone suspected.', 416),
(589, 'Plants Vs. Zombies', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HBg3DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Tobin', NULL, 'JUVENILE FICTION', NULL, '9781506702049', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"Crazy Dave--the babbling-yet-brilliant inventor and top-notch neighborhood defender--helps his niece, Patrice, and young adventurer Nate Timely fend off Zomboss\'s latest attack in Plants vs. Zombies!\"--', 80),
(590, 'Blade of the Immortal', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cMc3AQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'UCSD:31822033269408', NULL, 'Dark Horse Manga', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Manji, a ronin warrior of feudal Japan, has been cursed with immortality and to rid his eternal suffering and lift the curse, he must slay one thousand enemies, and his quest begins with a young girl who seeks revenge on her parents\' killers.', 232),
(591, 'Predator Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nzbjFYHTQQ4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=nzbjFYHTQQ4C&rdid=book-nzbjFYHTQQ4C&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621156109', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2007-08-21', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics set the comics industry on its ear with its comics expansion of the Predator mythos, a comics series so true to the spirit of the original 20th Century Fox film blockbuster that concepts from the first Predator comics series were incorporated into the Predator screen universe. Now, the three core Dark Horse Predator graphic novels-Concrete Jungle, Cold War, and Dark River-and several other chilling Predator tales, some never before reprinted, are collected together for the first time, in a value-priced, quality-format omnibus, featuring over 400 explosive story pages in full color. Written by screen and television scribe Mark Verheiden (The Mask, Battlestar Galactica) and comics legend Dan Barry and illustrated by Chris Warner, Ron Randall, Dan Barry, and others, Predator Omnibus Vol. 1 is an essential piece of the Predator mythos and a great entry point into the storied Dark Horse Predator library. The definitive comics collection of all things Predator starts here!', 440),
(592, 'City of Others (10th Anniversary Edition)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZV6IDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Steve Niles', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ZV6IDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-ZV6IDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506713007', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-06-18', NULL, 'A masterwork from two horror comics legends in a deluxe oversized edition! From the writer who created 30 Days of Night and the artist who created Swamp Thing comes a horror graphic novel like no other! Stosh Bludowski is a killer, born with the capacity for no apparent human emotion other than rage. Killing comes easy for Blud, and he makes a good living doing what\'s easy--until the day he meets two jobs in an alley who just won\'t die, and a grotesque mystery unfolds right in front of him. Soon, the remorseless killer is confronted by a reality he could never imagine, and he will be invited to make a decision once and for all . . . is he human, or is he Other? Collects City of Others #1-4', 124),
(593, 'Black Hammer Volume 4: Age of Doom Part Two', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RIWODwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Jeff Lemire', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506708560', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-12-31', NULL, 'The Eisner Award-winning superhero saga continues with this two-part mystery that will change the world forever! After learning how they got trapped on the farmworld, our heroes find themselves with everything they thought they wanted. Yet not everything is right just yet and it takes the strong resolve of the new Black Hammer to get the team back together, as shocking revelations change their world at every turn! Collects Black Hammer: Age of Doom #6-12 from the Eisner Award winning team of Jeff Lemire and Dean Ormston, with a special guest artist appearance from superstar creator Rich Tommaso!', 192);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(594, 'Solomon Kane Volume 2: Death\'s Black Riders', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6I4nJQjPXTEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Scott Allie', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781621154716', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2010-10-12', NULL, 'Taking place after the events in Solomon Kane: The Castle of the Devilâ€”but written to stand on its ownâ€”this new tale delves deep into the horrors scattered throughout Germany\'s Black Forest and adapts two of Robert E. Howard\'s most beloved Solomon Kane pieces. When Kane comes across gypsies being terrorized by roving bandits, he\'s not sure what\'s worseâ€”the bandits who wish to rob and rape innocent travelers or the evils that spew forth from the forest, intent on killing every man and woman around! This book also features the \"All the Damned Souls at Sea\" Kane comic by Scott Allie, Guy Davis, and Dave Stewart; creature designs by Eisner Award-winning artist Guy Davis; and a new cover by Hellboy creator Mike Mignola. â€¢ \"Solomon Kane is a welcome addition to the other excellent Howard properties produced by Dark Horse.\"â€”ComicsBulletin.com', 136),
(595, 'Dear Creature', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nG67DAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=nG67DAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-nG67DAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630087043', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-10-11', NULL, 'A monstrous love ballad Deep beneath the waves Grue discovers love after finding Shakespeareâ€™s plays in cola bottles. When his first attempt at companionship in the world above ends . . . poorly, Grue searches for the person who cast the plays into the sea. What he finds is love in the arms of Giuliettabut with his wicked past catching up to him, Grue must decide if becoming a new man means ignoring the monster he was. * Brand-new hardcover edition of Jonathan Caseâ€™s debut graphic novel!', 192),
(596, 'Blade of the Immortal: On silent wings', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=X8s3AQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Hiroaki Samura', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569714126', NULL, NULL, '1999-08-25', NULL, 'Condemned to a life of warfare until he kills a thousand evil men, Manji, a skilled samurai swordsman, labors as the bodyguard for Rin, a woman who has vowed revenge for her father\'s murder. Original.', 176),
(597, 'Aliens 30th Anniversary: The Original Comics Series', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=b-OaCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Verheiden', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=b-OaCwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-b-OaCwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630086916', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-04-26', NULL, 'The original sequel to Aliens! For the thirtieth anniversary of Aliens, Dark Horse is releasing an oversized edition of the unabridged and unadulterated series! In 1988, Dark Horseâ€™s Aliens, with stunning art by Mark A. Nelson and a script by Mark Verheiden, took the comics market by storm . . . until the release of Alien3 forced the story to change. * First major comics work by Mark Verheiden, who went on to write The Mask, Timecop, Battlestar Galactica, Daredevil, and many other films and television shows.', 184),
(598, 'Predator Versus Judge Dredd', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-N9ez3d6030C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'John Wagner', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1569713456', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Dark Horse re-presents the action-filled Predator vs. Judge Dredd miniseries in one package! In a tale of the far-flung future, a rogue Predator comes to Mega-City One looking for the ultimate hunt . . . and the city\'s toughest lawman, Judge Dredd, is its prey!', 117),
(599, 'Traveler', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Gow7HIuYRZ0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1569719861', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'After lonely college student Keiichi dials a wrong number, his wish of having a goddess as a companion is granted, and many adventures ensue involving him, his goddess girlfriend, her older sister, and other unworldly friends.', 256),
(600, 'Sora Unchained', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hjRZAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '159307316X', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'After lonely college student Keiichi dials a wrong number, his wish of having a goddess as a companion is granted, and many adventures ensue involving him, his goddess girlfriend, her older sister, and other unworldly friends.', 312),
(601, 'Death and Consequences', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=R6UBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rebekah Isaacs', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616551650', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'A demon from Giles\'s past has reemerged in London, giving Angel the opportunity he\'s been waiting for: capturing the final piece of the late Watcher\'s soul. For Faith, this is when Angel delivers on his promise - the resurrection of her mentor and friend. This venture draws the attention of Faith\'s Slayer comrades, who also seek to bring back a fallen friend. When the Slayers find themselves in the middle of Angel and Faith\'s quest, they\'re turned into living zombies by the soul-possessing demon Eyghon!', 136),
(602, 'H.P. Lovecraft\'s At the Mountains of Madness Volume 1 (Manga)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=txaZDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gou Tanabe', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=txaZDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-txaZDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506710242', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-07-09', NULL, 'From adapter and illustrator Gou Tanabe, comes H.P Lovecraft\'s At the Mountains of Madness. This manga adaptation of some of Lovecraft\'s best stories is perfect for manga fans and Lovecraft fans alike. With art resembling more of a western comic book, this book lends itself well as a \'gateway\' for those who are looking to get into manga! January 25, 1931: an expedition team arrives at a campsite in Antarctica...to find its crew of men and sled dogs strewn and dead. Some are hideously mangled, as if in rage--some have been dissected in a curious and cold-blooded manner. Some are missing. But a still more horrific sight is the star-shaped mound of snow nearby...for under its five points is a grave--and what lies beneath is not human! At the Mountains of Madness is a journey into the core of Lovecraft\'s mythos--the deep caverns and even deeper time of the inhospitable continent where the secret history of our planet is preserved--amidst the ruins of its first civilization, built by the alien Elder Things with the help of their bioengineered monstrosities, the shoggoths. Since it was first published in Astounding Stories during the classic pulp era, At the Mountains of Madness has influenced both horror and science fiction worldwide!', 298),
(603, 'Fight Club 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7flADAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chuck Palahniuk', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616559458', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Ten years after starting Project Mayhem, our unnamed hero lives a mundane life. A kid, a wife. Pills to keep his destiny at bay. But it won\'t last long, the wife has seen to that. He\'s back where he started, but this go-round he\'s got more at stake than his own life. The time has arrived: \'Rize or Die\'! New York Times bestselling novelist Chuck Palahniuk and acclaimed artist Cameron Stewart have collaborated for one of the most highly anticipated comic book and literary events of 2015 - the return of Tyler Durden.', 276),
(604, 'Spike: Into the Light', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JNliAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'James Marsters', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781621159780', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2014-08-12', NULL, 'He played Spike on the show, and now James Marsters writes a poignant but action-packed story of the vampire who chose to have a soul, and now has to deal with his past while being compelled to play the hero. * Get into Spikeâ€™s head as only James Marsters can! * An original graphic novel set in Buffy Season 7!', 144),
(605, 'Astro Boy 1 & 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iDomZJcj33AC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Osamu Tezuka', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=iDomZJcj33AC&rdid=book-iDomZJcj33AC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621155683', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2008-09-09', NULL, 'Dark Horse proudly presents one of the crown jewels of mangaâ€”Astro Boy! Created by the late Osamu Tezuka, a revered animator and cartoonist (who created over 150,000 pages of comics in his career!) considered the Walt Disney of Japan, Astro Boy was the first manga series to be adapted to animation and became a worldwide phenomenon, making Astro Boy the Mickey Mouse of anime-a jet-powered, super-strong, evil-robot-bashing, alien-invasion-smashing Mickey Mouse, that is! Exciting, whimsical, and touching, Astro Boy hearkens back to the classic era of comics and animation, featuring stories that readers young and old will enjoy. * This special edition combines the first two volumes of the collected Astro Boy, in one value-priced collection!', 432),
(606, 'Hellboy Volume 11: The Bride of Hell and Others', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ggpQZi3OEDoC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Mignola', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ggpQZi3OEDoC&rdid=book-ggpQZi3OEDoC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621150640', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2011-10-04', NULL, 'The world\'s greatest paranormal investigator takes on a carnivorous house, space aliens, a vampire luchador, a vengeful lion demon, and more in this collection featuring the work of comic greats Mike Mignola, Richard Corben, Kevin Nowlan, and Scott Hampton. * Collects Hellboy in Mexico, Hellboy: Double Feature of Evil, Hellboy: The Sleeping and the Dead #1-#2, Hellboy: The Bride of Hell, \"Hellboy: The Whittier Legacy,\" and Hellboy: Buster Oakley Gets His Wish. \"Involves Lucho Libres, vampires, the Devil\'s smell and Hellboy in a demonic wrestling match. How can anybody who loves comics not be excited by something containing all of that?\"-Geek Week', 200),
(607, 'Dust to Dust', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2r6SDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Gabriel Hardman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506707921', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"A mother and son bound by a shared terror--separated by an implacable alien force! A spaceship that should carry them away from the fear becomes a deathtrap from which escape seems impossible.\"--', 96),
(608, 'Sundowners', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7RHaCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Tim Seeley', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616557850', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'This volume collects Sundowners #7-#11.', 128),
(609, 'The Incredible Adventures of Dog Mendonca and PizzaBoy Volume 2: Apocalypse', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tiRMAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Filipe Melo', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=tiRMAgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-tiRMAgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621159131', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2014-03-11', NULL, 'A middle-aged werewolf, a six-thousand-year-old demon, a nervous gargoyle, and an out-of-work pizza delivery boy take a stand against the four horsemen of the apocalypse! A humor-filled romp through Judgment Day, this edition includes a foreword by director George A. Romero, a special \"making of\" section, and all Dog MendonÃ§a stories from the Eisner Awardâ€“winning DHP anthology! * Includes all Dark Horse Presents stories! * Foreword by legendary filmmaker George A. Romero!', 160),
(610, 'The EC Archives: The Vault of Horror', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jiFcDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Gaines', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=jiFcDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-jiFcDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506708812', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-01-08', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics brings even more macabrely majestic stories from the Vault! This terrifying tome has been digitally recolored--using Marie Severin\'s original palette as a guide--and features stories drawn by all-star comic artists Johnny Craig, Graham Ingels, Joe Orlando, Jack Davis, Jack Kamen, Graham Ingels, and George Evans! Collects Vault of Horror issues #36-#40 in full color!', 150),
(611, 'Shadows on the Grave', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=L3JDDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Richard Corben', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=L3JDDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-L3JDDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630089054', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-01-30', NULL, 'Richard Corben follows up 2014\'s Spirits of the Dead with a new collection of original short stories, ranging from gothic tales worthy of Poe, to Twilight Zone-style encounters with the weird, to a full-length fantasy epic featuring a barbarian reminiscent of Corben\'s most notorious creation, Den, immortalized in the 1981 animated film Heavy Metal. Corben rose to prominence with short horror and science fiction stories in the early 1970s in Creepy and Eerie, which were later collected in Creepy Presents Richard Corben. He remains one of the most important voices in horror comics. In 2009 he won the Eisner for Best Miniseries as well as being named Spectrum\'s Grand Master, one of illustration\'s most prominent awards. In 2011 he won the Eisner for Best Oneshot, and the following year he was inducted in the Will Eisner Hall of Fame.', 240),
(612, 'Mystery Girl', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Xx9yDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Tobin', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781616559595', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Trine Hampstead knows everything. Just knows it. Ask her a question like, \"Where are my keys?\" or, \"Is my husband cheating on me?\" or, \"How can there be perfectly preserved mammoths in the ice of Siberia when the ice isn\'t that old?\" and she just knows the answer. She\'s the Mystery Girl. The only thing she doesn\'t know is anything about the last ten years of her own life, including what happened to give her this ability. But that\'s a mystery for later. The mystery for now is about those mammoths. Trine knows why they\'re there but surprises anyone who knows Trine by demanding to leave her London-based sidewalk detective setup to go to Siberia with the archaeological team to see them for herself. And close behind is a vicious killer who is targeting her for reasons even Trine doesn\'t know.', 152),
(613, 'Oreimo Comic Anthology', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KurxDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=KurxDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-KurxDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630087654', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-11-08', NULL, 'Join 21 different artists for manga filled fun! Sakura Ikeda, artist of the regular Oreimo and Oreimo: Kuroneko manga series, joins twenty other artists in this collection of tribute stories to their favorite characters from Oreimo! Contributors include Shakugan no Shanaâ€™s Ayato Sasakura, Spice and Wolfâ€™s Keito Koume, Sword Art Onlineâ€™s abec, Strike Witchesâ€™ Shin Kyogoku, and many more! * Includes seven full-color illustrations. * The Oreimo anime is released in the US through Aniplex USA.', 160),
(614, 'Over the Top', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Lg_aCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Donny Cates', NULL, 'Freight and freightage', NULL, '9781616557119', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'When you need to transport the world\'s most valuable, dangerous or secretive cargo, you don\'t call just any trucking service. you call The Ghost Fleet. But when one of the world\'s most elite, combat-trained truckers takes a forbidden peek at his payload, he uncovers a vast conspiracy that threatens not just him but possibly the entire planet! It\'s badass, supernatural action on the open road in this new thriller from Donny Cates (Buzzkill; also available from Turnaround) and Daniel Warren Johnson. Collects issues #5 - #8 of the Dark Horse thriller series.', 96),
(615, 'Harrow County Volume 7: Dark Times A\'Coming', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eXJDDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Cullen Bunn', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eXJDDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-eXJDDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630089177', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-04-03', NULL, 'Things are heating up in this supernatural fantasy as young heroine Emmy Crawford prepares to face off against old foes in the horror-plagued town of Harrow County Something evil has returned from the grave and joins forces with Emmy\'s wicked family for a brewing monster war! Will she be able to protect her home and herself alone, or will Emmy need to gather some allies in order to defeat this evil once and for all in this coming of age tale? Collects issues #25-#28 from Eisner-nominated series which was recently optioned for TV by SyFy Channel.', 136),
(616, 'The Order of the Forge', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Q6raCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Victor Gischler', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616558291', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"This volume collects The Order of the Forge #1-#3\"--Title page verso.', 74),
(617, 'Will Eisner', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Rwo2DgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Will Eisner', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '9781506703558', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-01-26', NULL, '\"Based on exhibitions at Le Musaee de la Bande Dessinaee; curated by Denis Kitchen and the Society of Illustrators; co-curated by Denis Kitchen and John Lind.\"', 176),
(618, 'The Rook', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=psR7DQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Steven Grant', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506701004', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'The Rook is a time-traveling comic book hero created by Bill DuBay and Budd Lewis for Warren Magazines. First appearing in March 1977, The Rook was published in the pages of Eerie, Vampirella, & Warren Presents. In the 1980s, The Rook gained his own book, The Rook Magazine. In 2014 the original The Rook comics were introduced to a new generation in Eerie Archives 17, and then all-new material written by Steven Grant and illustrated by Paul Gulacy appeared in Dark Horse Presents and a Dark Horse comic book series in 2015. This book collects those all-new stories!', 104),
(619, 'The Adventures of Dr. McNinja Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=eVx1AQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Christopher Hastings', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=eVx1AQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-eVx1AQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621158899', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2013-07-16', NULL, 'Heâ€™s a doctor! Heâ€™s a ninja! And now, his earliest exploits are collected in one mighty omnibus volume! Featuring stories from the very beginnings of the Dr. McNinja webcomic, prepare for a hefty dose of science, action, and outrageous comedy. This omnibus presents more than five-hundred pages of hilarious strips, some of them long out of print.', 390),
(620, 'The Pencil Art of Geof Darrow', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3H4pDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Geoff Darrow', NULL, 'ART', NULL, '9781506703640', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"Featuring the pencils behind well-known covers and never-before-seen drawings, Lead Poisoning reveals Geof Darrow\'s perfectionism at its best, showing how clean the initial drawings can be, as well as the bizarre alterations that appear to happen on the fly\"--', 184),
(621, 'Minecraft: Stories from the Overworld (Graphic Novel)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=m4qMDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mojang Ab', NULL, 'Juvenile Nonfiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=m4qMDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-m4qMDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506708621', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-10-15', NULL, 'From blocks to panels! Minecraft returns to comics in this stand-alone anthology collection of officially licensed, original comic stories! With tales of witch and pillager rivals finding common ground, a heartless griefer who bit off more than they could chew, and valiant heroes new (or not!) to the Overworld, this anthology tells tales that span the world of Minecraft. Featuring stories from star writers Hope Larson (Batgirl), Kevin Panetta (Zodiac Starforce, Bloom), Rafer Roberts (Modern Fantasy, Grumble), and Ian Flynn (Sonic, Mega Man) and exciting artists Meredith Gran (Octopus Pie) and more, this collection brings together stories from all realms, leaving no block unturned!', 88),
(622, 'Empowered & Sistah Spooky\'s High School Hell', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9B5cDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=9B5cDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-9B5cDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506706849', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-02-12', NULL, 'Adam Warren teams with Eisner award winner Carla Speed McNeil, creator of Finder, in a hellishly funny superhero smackdown! Empowered and \"frenemy\" Sistah Spooky are trapped in a twisted high-school hellscape, with Spooky\'s blonde, sold-their-souls-for-hotness, ex-classmates plotting ritual murder to claim her magic for themselves! Beset by giant biology-class frogs, deadly emoji, and a monstrous junk-food elemental, Emp and Spooky fight for their lives against straight-fire blonde ambition! Hell is for heroines!', 144),
(623, 'Crone #1', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=o3OzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dennis Culver', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=o3OzDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-o3OzDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3006119', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-11-06', NULL, 'One more battle for Bloody Bliss! The Sword Saviour and Champion of Men once known as BLOODY BLISS is now nothing more than a reclusive old CRONE. Does she have the strength to answer the call for one last adventure? Only Dennis Culver (Burnouts, E is for Extinction) and Justin Greenwood (Stumptown, The Last Siege) know for sure in this story that is equal parts Unforgiven and Xena: Warrior Princess. From Burnouts creator Dennis Culver and acclaimed artist Justin Greenwood!', 32),
(624, 'Reset', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=o9eghNWS6wwC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Peter Bagge', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=o9eghNWS6wwC&rdid=book-o9eghNWS6wwC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621156338', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2013-01-22', NULL, 'If you could relive major events in your life, would you take a stab at making things betterâ€”and would your best attempts only make things worse? Or would you use your second chance to put your most twisted, perverted fantasies in motion? These are questions washed up actor and comedian Guy Krause asks himself after he signs up to be the main research subject for a virtual reality experiment! This new hardcover graphic novel from Harvey Award-winning writer/artist Peter Baggeâ€”creator of Hate and Apocalypse Nerdâ€”collects the hilarious, offbeat Reset comic-book series in its entirety. * Multiple Harvey Award-winner Peter Bagge!', 128),
(625, 'Dream Thief', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0jYCDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jai Nitz', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616552831', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Collects issues #1-#5 of Dark Horse Comics\' series Dream Thief.', 152),
(626, 'Aliens vs. Predator: Three World War', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8PiCDqrgk_kC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Randy Stradley', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=8PiCDqrgk_kC&rdid=book-8PiCDqrgk_kC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621155539', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2012-10-09', NULL, 'A long-lost Predator clan stakes its claim for galactic dominance, intent on exterminating its rival clan, the self-same trophy hunters who have plagued Earth\'s history. And if the advanced technology and military precision of this new threat weren\'t enough, they have an even more terrifying weaponâ€”a horde of Aliens under their malefic control. Earthmen must now side with the warriors who have relentlessly hunted them, but is the enemy of my enemy my friend or just another enemy waiting for its turn to strike? * One of the most popular science-fiction/action franchises, spawning countless films, games, comics, and toys over three decades. * Aliens vs. Predator: Three World War is the biggest action blowout yet, written by original AvP scribe Randy Stradley and illustrated by Rick Leonardi and Mark Pennington. * Collects issues #1-#6 of the miniseries.', 144),
(627, 'At Death\'s Door', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=B5wBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Braun', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781595829511', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2013-01-08', NULL, 'What\'s that huge, terrifying thing clawing its way onto your bookshelf? It\'s the biggest, bloodiest, most creepy collection of new terror tales you\'ll find this year!', 176),
(628, 'The Dark Horse Book of Horror', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=CbwvDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Mignola', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506703725', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Mike Mignola, Hellboy,and a roster of great creators and characters explore the dark corners of the horror genre in 35 stories of witchcraft, ghosts, and the risen dead. Originally published in four award-winning anthologies, these stories featured the debut of Evan Dorkin and Jill Thompson\'s Beasts of Burden series, and standalone stories by Kelley Jones, Kurt Busiek, and many others. In addition to the comics, Gary Gianni (Hellboy- Into the Silent Sea) illustrates stories by legendary authors such as Robert E Howard (Conan) and William Hope Hodgson (The House on the Borderland), and Scott Allie interviews experts in the occult fields, including a seance medium, and witch who specializes in love spells. Collects- Dark Horse Book of Monsters, the Dark Horse Book of Witchcraft, the Dark Horse Book of Hauntings, andthe Dark Horse Book of the Dead', 368),
(629, 'House of the Green Mask', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=w9IiDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Tobin', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506702193', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"The world\'s greatest thief is a costumed teen burglar by the nome d\'arte of Bandette! Gleefully plying her skills on either side of the law alongside her network of street urchins, Bandette is a thorn in the sides of both Police Inspector Belgique and the criminal underworld. But it\'s not all breaking hearts and purloining masterpieces when a rival thief makes a startling discovery. Can even Bandette laugh off a plot against her life?\"--Page 4 of cover, volume 1.', 128),
(630, 'Bet Your Life', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mzv5MMDv89cC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '156971617X', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'High school student Alex Fleming\'s normal life of homework, dating, and bullies is turned upside-down when his latent martial arts and technological abilities start to develop, making him the unwitting target of evil-doers.', 80),
(631, 'Predator: Rite of Passage/Pride at Nghasa', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=u4CjCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Charles Dixon', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=u4CjCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-u4CjCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:23314', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', NULL, NULL, 'In Rite of Passage,Â a ritual lion hunt intended as a tribal test of manhood turns into a deadly encounter with a visitor from the stars as the young hunter becomes the hunted. In Pride of Nghasa,Â the once-in-a-lifetime appearance of the hunting starÂ brings with it a murderous curse that besets a British railway crew. But while this curse is worse than rogue animals or men, Earth is not its home. And a hunting ground may be even more merciless than the most heartless hunter.', NULL),
(632, 'Cravan', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=A4tQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Richardson', NULL, 'Biography & Autobiography', NULL, '1593072910', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Chronicles the life of the poet, pugilist, and self-professed con artist whose mysterious disappearance at age thirty-one aroused suspicions that he had gone into hiding to reemerge as reclusive novelist B. Traven.', 72),
(633, 'The Witcher Volume 4: Of Flesh and Flame', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_E6FDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Aleksandra Motyka', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=_E6FDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-_E6FDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506711133', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-07-30', NULL, 'Based on the hit games by CD Projekt Red! Geralt is summoned by an old acquaintance to help solve a mystery involving his daughter. Upon arriving to investigate the situation, however, Geralt is surprised to find Dandelion, and the duo unexpectedly find themselves transported to regions beyond. After arriving in a dangerous and enigmatic location by mistake, they are forced to hide their identities while faced with an impossible task. Geralt works side by side with a local woman to defeat the dark forces plaguing the land but soon discovers that the situation at hand, in which he believes to be helping with, only leads to more trouble for the witcher and results in all signs pointing towards him as the prime suspect. Featuring the debut of creative team Aleksandra Motyka and Marianna Strychowska, and created in close collaboration with the studio behind the games! Collects issues #1-#4 of the Dark Horse Comics series The Witcher: Of Flesh and Flame.', 104),
(634, 'Bottom of the Dark', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GHkEDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Yasuhiro Nightow', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781593073145', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Nice-guy gunslinger Vash the Stampede has a dangerous past and a huge bounty on his head, but none of his enemies can stop him as he fights for justice on his planet.', 204),
(635, 'One Gamble at a Time', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Yq4BDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Daniel Warren Johnson', NULL, 'Adventure and adventureers', NULL, '9781616559120', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"This volume collects chapters 1 through 4 of the comic Space-Mullet!, serialized online between 2012 and 2014.\"', 210),
(636, 'The Witcher Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=aXeeDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Tobin', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506713953', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-12-03', NULL, 'Multi-Eisner award-winning writer Paul Tobin pens a fantasy epic of the adventures of Geralt of Rivia, a witcher--one of the few remaining monster hunters from the critically acclaimed video game fantasy The Witcher by CD Projekt Red! Featuring story art by Joe Querio, Piotr Kowalski, Max Bertolini, with a bonus sketchbook section and additional art by Dave Johnson (100 Bullets), Dan Panosian (Slots), Stan Sakai (Usagi Yojimbo), Duncan Fegredo (MPH), Simon Bisley (Lobo), and a cover by Mike Mignola (Hellboy). Collects issues #1-#5 of The Witcher comic series House of Glass, Fox Children, Curse of Crows, and the Killing Monsters one-shot--and features annotations from the creators of the comics, as well as a sketchbook section.', 440),
(637, 'Rasputin: The Voice of the Dragon', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GjhcDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Mignola', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=GjhcDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-GjhcDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630089870', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-08-07', NULL, 'With the World War II raging, Hellboy\'s future guardian Trevor Bruttenholm enlists with Britain\'s Military Intelligence, where he uncovers a collection of strange messages. Believing it to be an occult language, he follows his hunch and is thrown into a world of animated corpses, deadly mystics, and Nazi agents. The treacherous journey leads him face to face with the man who will bring Hellboy to Earth--Rasputin! The two men responsible for Hellboy face off!', 135),
(638, 'Disney Frozen: The Hero Within (Graphic Novel)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OGGXDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Caramagna', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '9781506712864', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-11-19', NULL, 'Build strength and heroism with Anna, Elsa, Kristoff, Sven, Olaf, and their friend Hedda, as they deal with bullies, and the harsh environment of the Forbidden Land! Olaf\'s friend at the orphanage in Arendelle village is a spunky girl named Hedda with a big imagination and dreams of adventure. When Kristoff passes through the village and witnesses two kids bullying Hedda, he is drawn to help. He recalls his own experience with bullying during his childhood and assures her that there is hope on the horizon. Things start to look up when Hedda is invited to dinner at Arendelle Castle! Ecstatic, Hedda shares the news with the orphanage and is prepared for the best night ever. But as she makes her way to the castle, the two bullies return, and turn Hedda\'s joyous day into one of sadness. Feeling alone and unwanted, Hedda runs away on a journey to the Forbidden Land, to prove herself . . . on her own. Facing dangerous heights and treacherous elements, Anna, Elsa, Kristoff, Sven, and Olaf must find Hedda before it\'s too late. Along the way, Kristoff confronts his past and everyone learns valuable lessons about differences and understanding--even the two bullies! Joe Caramagna (Zootopia, Avengers Assemble) and Kawaii Creative Studio, the original team behind Frozen: Breaking Boundaries, returns for a story of adventure, friendship, and celebration of diversity.', 72),
(639, 'Evelyn Evelyn', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=75MBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Amanda Palmer', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781595825780', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Conjoined twins Evelyn and Evelyn experience many triumphs and tragedies after their mother\'s death during their birth, including a childhood in a chicken coop, time traveling with the circus, and sudden superstardom through a hit song on the Internet.', 80),
(640, 'Predator: Fire and Stone', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZuZxCQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joshua Williamson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ZuZxCQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-ZuZxCQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630082369', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-07-28', NULL, 'After the terror of Weyland-Yutani\'s disastrous mission to the site of the fallen Prometheus, the Perses begins her long journey home, but an invisible stowaway forces the crew into a deadly conflict! While the crew defend themselves against this unseen predator, the hunter itself stalks a much more substantial game! Collects Predator: Fire and Stone #1-#4!', 104),
(641, 'Inferno', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=mGeBDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jackson Lanzing', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506705033', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '2019-01-22', NULL, 'Writers Jackson Lanzing and Collin Kelly (Joyride, Hacktivist) continue Lara\'s story after Rise of the Tomb Raider and where Dark Horse series Survivor\'s Crusade left off! This volume collects issues #1-#4 of the 2018 Dark Horse Comics series Tomb Raider: Inferno. Lara succeeds in hunting down Trinity to a remote outpost in Antarctica amidst the cold and darkness of the seemingly isolated land. Seeking to discover the mystery within the icy tomb before Trinity can exploit it, Lara faces a new adversary who is more cunning and more prepared than Lara has encountered in the past. In order to stop the terror Trinity is about to release, Lara must face the conflict residing within herself and decide once and for all how far she\'s willing to go, and what she\'s willing to let go of in the process.', 104),
(642, 'Disney Frozen: Breaking Boundaries (Graphic Novel)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AaZgDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Caramagna', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '9781506710587', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-01-29', NULL, 'In a comics follow-up to the Disney film, Elsa and Anna resolve problems in their beloved kingdom and make new friends along the way. Elsa and Anna are ready to get to the bottom of things when the peace of the kingdom of Arendelle is threatened. A wild animal loose in the village and destruction in the nearby Arendelle woods causes Queen Elsa to miss an important meeting with a neighboring monarch and she sends Princess Anna in her place. When Anna learns that this particular king will only speak to her sister, she begins to question her role in the kingdom. But when she learns that the king\'s daughter, the adventurous Princess Mari, is frustrated--with her father\'s overprotective ways--and would dearly love to find something purposeful to do, Anna is incredibly keen to help Mari to find a job that fits her perfectly! So as both princesses explore the variety of occupations that the kingdom has to offer, Elsa must address the problem in Arendelle\'s forest with Mari\'s father--who happens to be the unknowing source of the trouble! Elsa, Anna, and Mari will join together to resolve the confusion over the woodland and to find a purpose for Mari that she will love and her father will find fitting for his cherished daughter. The continuing story of Arendelle\'s sister rulers, Elsa and Anna, is chock full of snow flurries of fun and unfrosted heart with writer Joe Caramagna (DuckTales, Zootopia, Avengers Assemble) and art by Kawaii Creative Studio from the Frozen film graphic novel adaptation.', 80),
(643, 'The Incredible Adventures of Dog Mendonca and PizzaBoy Volume 3: Requiem', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6XrqCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Filipe Melo', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=6XrqCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-6XrqCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630084929', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-02-02', NULL, 'Civil war brews in the secret realm of monsters, threatening to spill over into the human world! Dog MendonÃ§a and PizzaBoy must get their strange band of adventurers together one final time! A world-weary werewolf, a six thousand-year-old demon trapped in the body of a little girl, a nervous gargoyle, and a former pizza delivery boy take a stand against a seemingly endless horde of angry creatures, led by an evil genius from Dog\'s past! A hit sensation in its home country of Portugal, this English-language edition includes a special \"making of\" section and a foreword by legendary horror director and writer Tobe Hooper! \"There\'s real wit on every page.\"-George A. Romero (Director of The Night of the Living Dead series)', 128),
(644, 'Extraordinary: A Story of an Ordinary Princess', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=T16IDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Cassie Anderson', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=T16IDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-T16IDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506710280', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-08-06', NULL, 'While her sisters were blessed at birth with exceptional skills, Princess Basil\'s \"gift\" is to be ordinary. But can a princess be ordinary? After escaping an unconventional kidnapping, Princess Basil finds herself far from her castle and must take fate into her own hands. She tracks down the fairy godmother who \"blessed\" her, and learns the solution to her ordinariness might be as simple as finding a magic ring. With an unlikely ally in tow, she takes on gnomes, a badger, and a couple of snarky foxes in her quest for a less ordinary life. Portland comics artist Cassie Anderson (Lifeformed) takes her webcomic to print in this tale of magical adventure, full of soul and humor for readers of all ages.', 199),
(645, 'Milk and Cheese: Dairy Products Gone Bad', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nyxGlKPdfikC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Evan Dorkin', NULL, 'Humor', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=nyxGlKPdfikC&rdid=book-nyxGlKPdfikC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621152460', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2007-11-20', NULL, 'A carton of hate. A wedge of spite. A comic book of idiotic genius. The Eisner Award-winning dairy duo returns in this deluxe hardcover collecting every single stupid Milk and Cheese comic ever made from 1989 to 2010, along with a sh*t ton of supplemental awesomeness. This has everything you need! Don\'t judge itâ€”love it! Or else! â€¢ Look for brand-new stories by Evan Dorkin in upcoming Dark Horse Presents issues! â€¢ \"Evan\'s calcium-rich creations are guaranteed to spread lactose intolerance everywhere.\"â€”David Mazzucchelli (Asterios Polyp, Batman: Year One)', 240),
(646, 'Harrow County Library Edition', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=pE-FDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Cullen Bunn', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=pE-FDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-pE-FDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506710709', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-08-06', NULL, 'The next chapter of the highly acclaimed, Eisner-nominated horror fantasy. While Emmy has been focused on dealing with supernatural threats from the outside world, a much bigger problem has been brewing at home. Collects the volumes five and six of Harrow County with a new cover, sketchbook material, essays, and \"Tales from Harrow County\" bonus stories by guest creators, and more! Collects Harrow County issues #17-#24.', 241),
(647, 'B. P. R. D. Hell on Earth', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MqoBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Mignola', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616554712', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Mike Mignola was born September 16, 1960 in Berkeley, California and grew up in nearby Oakland. His fascination with ghosts and monsters began at an early age (he doesn\'t remember why) and reading Draculaat age 13 introduced him to Victorian literature and folklore from which he has never recovered. In 1993 Mike moved to Dark Horse comics and created Hellboy-A half-demon occult detective who may or may not be the Beast of the Apocalypse. While the first story line (Seed of Destruction, 1994) was co-written by John Byrne, Mike has continued writing the series himself. There are, at this moment, 13 Hellboy graphic novel collections with more on the way, several spin-off titles (BPRD, Lobster Johnson, Abe Sapienand Witchfinder), three anthologies of prose stories, several novels, two animated films, and two live action films staring Ron Perlman. Hellboyhas earns numerous comic industry awards and is published in a great many countries.', 144),
(648, 'Lone Wolf and Cub', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=q40qAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'å°æ± ä¸€é›„', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569715076', NULL, NULL, '2001-02-28', NULL, 'Lone Wolf and Cub Vol. 6', 288),
(649, 'Buffy - Season Nine', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=uF_ZCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joss Whedon', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616557171', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Reprints issues from the Dark Horse comic book series Buffy the Vampire Slayer Season Nine.', 276),
(650, 'Cuphead', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2JyyDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Zack Keller', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506712970', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2020-06-23', NULL, 'Revisit the colorful characters of the Inkwell Isles in this collection of brand new Cuphead and Mugman tales! Prone to unexpected predicaments and thrilling adventures, Cuphead and Mugman feature front and center in a series of short but sweet side stories that reimagine the world of the all-cartoon magical wondergame. This original graphic novel features all-new original tales, authentically drawn to match the glorious, award-winning vintage animation style of Cuphead! Don\'t miss Cuphead and Mugman\'s graphic novel debut in written by Zack Keller and illustrated to 1930s perfection by Shawn Dickinson!', 72),
(651, 'Hellboy Journal', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JsvZwQEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Deluxe', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1506712304', NULL, NULL, '2019-03-20', NULL, '192 pages, includes bookmark, and pocket in back cover.', NULL),
(652, 'Stranger Things: SIX (Graphic Novel)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KYiODwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jody Houser', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=KYiODwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-KYiODwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506712949', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-11-26', NULL, 'A prequel comic from Netflix\' award-winning series, delving into the mysterious workings of Project MKUltra and the weird science that opened the door to the Upside Down. Francine, a teenage girl with precognition, has struggled through a lifetime of exploitation: first by her parents, then by Dr. Brenner of Hawkins Laboratory. Dr. Brenner wants to harness her powers as well as those of the other gifted children that they hold captive at the lab. Wracked by increasingly disturbing visions, she sees an opportunity for her and all the children to escape. But at what cost? From the pen of Jody Houser (Faith, CMYK: Magenta, Max Ride: Ultimate Flight) and featuring art from Edgar Salazar and Keith Champagne (Black Panther), Stranger Things comics is essential reading for fans of the hit Netflix series as well as fans of the urban fantasy and horror genres in general. Collects Stranger Things II issues #1-4.', 96),
(653, 'Black Hammer/Justice League: Hammer of Justice! #5', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=B3GzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jeff Lemire', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=B3GzDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-B3GzDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3004087', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-11-13', NULL, 'The Ultimate superhero crossover of the year! Colonel Weird and the Green Lantern must convince the Black Hammer crew to go back to their own dimension to save the multiverseâ€”which means giving up more than some may be willing to give.', 32),
(654, 'Hedge Magic', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PBg3DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Cullen Bunn', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506702087', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"This volume collects Harrow County #21-#24\"', 136);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(655, 'Hellboy in Hell Volume 1: The Descent', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=KefzAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Mignola', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=KefzAgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-KefzAgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621159445', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2014-05-14', NULL, 'Hellboy creator and comics superstar Mike Mignola returns to draw Hellboy\'s ongoing story for the first time since Hellboy: The Conqueror Worm. It\'s a story only Mignola could tell, as more of Hellboy\'s secrets are at last revealed, in the most bizarre depiction of Hell you\'ve ever seen! Comic Book Resources said, \"Hellboy in Hell shows a master returning to his craft and exceeding reader expectations. This is a horror comic that reminds just how good both the genre and the medium can be.\"', 128),
(656, 'Flaming Carrot Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=xnaNDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bob Burden', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=xnaNDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-xnaNDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506714189', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-10-01', NULL, 'The Eisner award-winning, surreal superhero series, The Flaming Carrot, returns with a new omnibus collection! Before there ever was a Deadpool, Twin Peaks, or Lady Gaga; the Flaming Carrot\'s madcap madness, manic mayhem, and impish mischief exploded from the vanguard of the 80s\' New Wave comic revolution, taking us right down the rabbit hole of creativity-gone-off-the-tracks, and over the rainbow. Propagating dreamlike surrealism, disturbing violence, sexual adventurism, bar-hopping, and a bizarre and nightmarish costume, the world\'s first postmodern super man battled Road Hogs From Outer Space, went on drinking binges with Death, bounced around on a nuclear powered pogo stick, and ordered some of that new Brussels sprout flavored ice cream that wasn\'t even on the menu yet. Check out a comic book series that for many years most people believed to be nothing more than a ridiculous legend or an amusing joke. Doctor recommended. Maximum strength formula. New hope for a nation suffocating in the swill of its own mediocrity. Collects Flaming Carrot #1-2, 4-11, 25-27.', 408),
(657, 'Call of Duty', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OCw8DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Justin Jordan', NULL, 'ART', NULL, '9781506703053', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'This volume collects issues #1-#6 of the Dark Horse Comics series Call of Duty: Zombies.\"', 144),
(658, 'God of War', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=41mYDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Chris Roberson', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506707464', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'v. 1 \"collects issues #0 through #4 of the Dark Horse comic-book series God of war.\"', 120),
(659, 'The Massive Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Bk-FDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Wood', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=Bk-FDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-Bk-FDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506713342', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-07-16', NULL, 'In a post-war, post-crash, post-disaster, post-everything world, the environmental-action trawler Kapital scours the earth\'s oceans for its mysteriously missing sistership, The Massive. Captain Callum Israel, a man who has dedicated his life to the ocean, now must ask himself--as our planet dies--what it means to be an environmentalist after the world\'s ended. This omnibus collects issues #0-#15 of acclaimed writer Brian Wood\'s sprawling, post-apocalyptic epic at a must-own value rate. Collects issues #0-#15 of The Massive.', 392),
(660, 'H.P. Lovecraft\'s The Hound and Other Stories (Manga)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8Q92DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=8Q92DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-8Q92DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506713366', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-12-18', NULL, 'From adapter and illustrator Gou Tanabe, comes H.P Lovecraft\'s The Hound and Other Stories. This manga adaptation of some of Lovecraft\'s best stories is perfect for manga fans and Lovecraft fans alike. With art resembling more of a western comic book, this book lends itself well as a \'gateway\' for those who are looking to get into manga! A pair of decadent young men pursue the abhorrent thrill of grave robbing...a German submarine\'s crew is driven mad by the call of an underwater temple...an explorer in the Arabian desert discovers a hideous city older than mankind. This moody and evocative manga gets back to the dark foundations of the Cthulhu Mythos, adapting three of H.P. Lovecraft\'s original stories that first shaped the outlines of cosmic horror!', 166),
(661, 'Jack the Ripper', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-NTYCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'FranÃ§ois Debois', NULL, 'Graphic novels', NULL, '9781616558192', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Dark Horse continues its reissues of classic French graphic novels with this timeless tale of grisly London murders. Spring, 1889. Months have passed since Whitechapel was covered in blood, and while the mystery surrounding Jack The Ripper goes cold, Inspector Frederick Abberline is still a man obsessed. But when a series of killings identical to the Ripper\'s occur in Paris, Abberline must risk everything to close history\'s most famous murder case once and for all! Francois Debois and Jean-Charles Poupard\'s Soleil edition of this classic graphic novel is now available in English.', 104),
(662, 'Captain Midnight', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=izcCDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jemiah Jefferson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616552428', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2013-12-10', NULL, 'From the glory days of World War II comes the unstoppable patriotic superhero Captain Midnight! Volume 1 features selected tales compiled from the original 1940s-era comic book featuring the adventures of the Captain and his sidekick, Sergeant Twilight, as they battle bad guys from the Axis of Evil with art by comics greats Jack Binder, Mac Raboy, Dan Gormley, and others! Collecting selected stories from The Funnies, Popular Comics, and Captain Midnight issues. * Reprints one of the greatest military superhero comics of the 1940s! * Complements new Captain Midnight stories coming from Dark Horse!', 230),
(663, 'Disney Mulan: The Story of the Movie in Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=8dW1DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Disney', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '9781506717494', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2020-06-30', NULL, 'Venture to the Great Wall of China in a remarkable tale of bravery in this retelling of the animated film, Disney Mulan. The Huns have invaded China. One man from every family must serve in the Imperial Army. Mulan, a strong-willed teenage girl, volunteers to fight among the soldiers in her father\'s stead. With women forbidden to join the army, Mulan risks death and dishonor as she goes undercover as a man to defend her land and protect her father. With the help of the General\'s son, a sassy guardian dragon, and a lucky cricket, Mulan pursues her passion of bringing honor to her country, her family, and herself--she is a girl bound by no limits! With wit, strength, and determination, Mulan fearlessly enters the battlefield and goes head to head to the vicious leader of the Huns! Pave your own destiny with Mulan as she fights for family, peace, and the right to be yourself!', 56),
(664, 'Aliens: Defiance', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-LsmDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Wood', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-LsmDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book--LsmDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630087869', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-02-06', NULL, 'Colonial Marine Private First Class Zula Hendricks is on an AWOL mission to prove her mettle by eradicating the alien species before they can be exploited as weapons on Earth. She must battle with aliens, fend off space pirates, and elude the insidious Weyland-Yutani corporation that wants their freighter back, all while facing rehabilitation from an old war injury. New York Times best-selling comics writer Brian Wood gives us a gripping story of strength going up against staggering fears. The talented artist Tristan Jones brings these fears to life.', 152),
(665, 'Muhammad Ali', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4-rxDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=4-rxDAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-4-rxDAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630088996', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-11-15', NULL, 'The story of boxing icon Muhammad Ali! An original graphic novel celebrating the life of the glorious athlete who metamorphosed from Cassius Clay to become a three-time heavyweight boxing legend, activist, and provocateur: Muhammad Ali. Not only a titan in the world of sports but in the world itself, he dared to be different and to challenge and defy through his refusal to be drafted to fight in Vietnam, his rejection of his â€œslaveâ€ name, and ultimately his final fight with his body itself through a thirty-year battle with Parkinsonâ€™s disease. Witness what made Ali different, what made him cool, what made him the Greatest. * The critically acclaimed French graphic novel, now available for the first time in English. * Focuses on key figures in the Civil Rights movement.', 128),
(666, 'The Goon Volume 15: Once Upon a Hard Time', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kIwBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '9781506700984', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'This book collects The Goon: once upon a hard time #1-4 and \"Colonel Nosferatu\'s underground soiree previously published in Free Comic Book Day 2015.', 136),
(667, 'The Goon Volume 14: Occasion of Revenge', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0N_yBgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Eric Powell', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781630081362', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2015-04-14', NULL, 'Eric Powell\'s biggest story since 2008! What\'s left of the Zombie Priest\'s race of witches comes after the Goon, forcing him to face his nightmares or lose his town! This volume collects The Occasion of Revenge #1-#4.', 120),
(668, 'Alena', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=oWjNDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kim W. Andersson', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506702155', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"Alena\'s life is a living hell. Since starting at boarding school Alena\'s been harassed every day by Philippa and the lacrosse team. But Alena\'s friend Josephine is not going to accept that anymore. If Alena does not fight back then Josephine will take matters into her own hands. There\'s just one problem--Josephine has been dead for a year\"--Provided by publisher.', NULL),
(669, 'Fray: Future Slayer', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=wsckub9f0kYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joss Whedon', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=wsckub9f0kYC&rdid=book-wsckub9f0kYC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621150527', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '1999-11-16', NULL, 'Hundreds of years in the future, Manhattan has become a deadly slum, run by mutant crime-lords and disinterested cops. Stuck in the middle is a young girl who thought she had no future, but learns she has a great destiny. In a world so poisoned that it doesn\'t notice the monsters on its streets, how can a street kid like Fray unite a fallen city against a demonic plot to consume mankind? Joss Whedon, the celebrated creator of Buffy the Vampire Slayer, brings his vision to the future in this unique tale. As inventive in the comics medium as in that of television or film, Whedon spins a complex tale of a skilled thief coming of age without the help of friends or family, guided only by a demonic Watcher. * Joss Whedon, creator of Fray and Buffy the Vampire Slayer, has been nominated for Nebula, Hugo and Emmy Awards as well as an Oscar!', 200),
(670, 'Avatar: The Last Airbender - The Lost Adventures', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=HcY6DbenGBQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Various', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=HcY6DbenGBQC&rdid=book-HcY6DbenGBQC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621157991', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2013-07-02', NULL, 'For three years, millions of eager fans tuned in to watch new episodes of Nickelodeon\'s hit animated series Avatar: The Last Airbender. Ever since, fans have been hungry for moreâ€”and now their wait is finally over! This volume collects the long-out-of-print, fan-favorite comics previously published in Nickelodeon Magazine and with the Airbender DVDs, plus over seventy brand-new comics pages. That\'s twenty-six stories set in Airbender continuity, by a host of top-notch talent, many of whom worked on the original animated series! * A must-have for any Airbender fan! * Twenty-six in-continuity stories, plus bonus content! * The latest release in an ongoing partnership between Nickelodeon and Dark Horse, to bring you the very best in Airbender books!', 240),
(671, 'Ghost', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nakBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kelly Sue DeConnick', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616554200', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Ghost is only one who can save Chicago from the demons and the murderer lurking in its dark alleys, but her alter ego Elisa Cameron struggles to balance her role as spectral protector with her desire to learn more about her mysterious past.', 96),
(672, 'The Mask Strikes Back', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=bkYEAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'John Arcudi', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1569711682', NULL, NULL, '1996-06-01', NULL, 'Rick, Ben, Hugo, and Archie are four teens with a fixation on that melon-headed menace, The Mask. When they each get a shot at wearing the empowering emerald artifact, they figure it\'s a dream come true! And it is! Power, fame, and ultimate wish fulfillment are at arm\'s reach! But so is the mute man-monster, Walter, and arm\'s reach is far too close when he\'s involved!', 117),
(673, 'Bad Blood #2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cTOiCgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jonathan Maberry', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=cTOiCgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-cTOiCgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:24054', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2014-01-01', NULL, 'An unlikely ally aids our hero in his hunt for vampires. Using her expertise in the seedy underground, they travel to back alleys and dungeon haunts. But when the real vampires attack, will she become another casualty? * Bram Stoker Award winner Jonathan Maberry (_Ghost Road Blues_)! * Eisner Award winner Tyler Crook (_B.P.R.D._, _The Sixth Gun_).', 24),
(674, 'Black Hammer: Streets of Spiral', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=d-eTDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jeff Lemire', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=d-eTDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-d-eTDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506709512', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-09-24', NULL, 'From the Eisner-award winning Black Hammer superhero fantasy comes this collection of three stories and a universe guide tied to the world of Jeff Lemire and Dean Ormston\'s hit comic book series. A Lovecraftian teen decides she will do anything to make herself \'\'normal\'\', a bizarre witch guides her guests through her house of horrors, and an all-star slate of guest artists illustrate a bizarre adventure with Colonial Weird on the farm. Also featuring a complete world guide to the Black Hammer universe and its characters. Collects: Black Hammer: Giant Sized Annual, Black Hammer: Cthu-Louise, World of Black Hammer, and material from Free Comic Book Day 2019.', 128),
(675, 'Mask', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=er8yDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Arcudi', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781630089443', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Between 1991 and 2007 Dark Horse Comics and DC Comics collaborated on an unprecedented level, pitting their top franchises against one another in no-holds-barred throwdowns! In this collection of DC Comics crossovers, Dark Horse brings never republished material featuring a host of heroes back to fans in a single volume. This volume features The Mask, The Grifter, and The Joker in crossover action!', 256),
(676, '3 Story: The Secret History of the Giant Man (Expanded Edition)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=YB5cDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Kindt', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=YB5cDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-YB5cDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506706238', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-08-14', NULL, 'From New York Times bestselling and Harvey award-winning Mind MGMT graphic novelist Matt Kindt comes a decades-spanning tale of love, secrets, aging, espionage, and family. Craig Pressgang\'s life is well documented in his official CIA biography, Giant Man: Pillar of America, but the heroic picture it paints is only half the story. The continuous growth caused by Craig\'s strange gigantism brings a variety of problems as he becomes more isolated and unknowable. Told during three eras by three different women with unique relationships with nearly three story tall Craig, 3 Story follows his sad life from his birth to the present.', 224),
(677, 'Heart in a Box', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=UA7aCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Kelly Thompson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616556945', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'When the Man with No Name breaks Emma\'s heart, she wants to die. But you never die from these things; you just want to. In a moment of weakness, she wishes her broken heart away and a mysterious stranger--who may or may not be totally evil--obliges. But emptiness is even worse than grief, and Emma sets out to collect the seven pieces of her heart spread across the country, a journey that forces her to face her own history and the cost of recapturing it, and leads inevitably to a confrontation with the Man with No Name himself! Reviews: Heart in a Box serves up a complete story of heartbreak, recovery and the effects those have on the world. Like the butterfly wings of the chaos theory, one person\'s acts -- random, violent, kind, insincere or hearty -- impact others and multiply in ways and directions that frequently defy description.\" - Comic Book Resources (CBR) \"This book is magical. It reminds me of so many stories and yet manages to be wholly original. Be good to your heart and grab this comic with both hands.\" - Big Comic Page \"A slice of life story with magical realism, Heart in a Box is smart storytelling, but it\'s also just so very raw. Like real raw.\" - Women Write About Comics \"With Heart In A Box, Thompson & McClaren pull off the kind of smart story telling and allegory that transcends the genre and medium with a comic that almost anybody could enjoy...Heart In a Box in one of the best comics of 2015 which feels like nothing else in the medium, but is still warm and familiar. It has a casual complexity that is as inviting as it is engaging and emotionally affecting.\" - Nothing But Comics \"It\'s brilliant - so far, it\'s one of the two or three best comics I\'ve read this year.\" - Comics Should Be Good', 160),
(678, 'Hatsune Miku: Mikubon', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=V9MiDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Ontama', NULL, 'Friendship', NULL, '9781506702315', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'First punlished in Japan in 2013 by Kadokawa Corporation, Tokyo.', 163),
(679, 'Playboy\'s Little Annie Fanny', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=XOwhuqmCVN4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Hugh Marston Hefner', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569715203', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Dark Horse concludes its complete reprinting of Playboy\'s legendary Little Annie Fanny strip, with an even bigger second volume, at the same price as the first. Picking up where the first volume left off, this collection follows the strip through to its end in 1988. Ralph Nader, the women\'s movement, Star Wars, and Arnold Schwarzenegger all fall victim to the merciless and masterful satire of Kurtzman and Elder. The first volume was a smash hit, and the second includes all the same goodies, with never-before-seen production art and behind-the-scenes info about Hefner, Kurtzman, Elder, and the host of cartoonists who contributed to this revolutionary comic.', 240),
(680, 'Ether Volume 2: Copper Golems', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zKhkDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Kindt', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=zKhkDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-zKhkDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506705088', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-02-19', NULL, 'From New York Times bestselling Mind MGMT creator MATT KINDT and Black Hammer\'s DAVID RUBÃN comes this fantasy adventure about a science-minded hero intent on keeping the balance between Earth and a magic world! Portals between Earth and the Ether begin to crack open unleashing devastating magical fury on our planet and only adventurer Boone Dias can seal the breaches. In order to put an end to this chaos, Boone recruits a powerful team of mystical beings including a grumpy, spell-writing fairy; a bickering, lavender gorilla; and a bull-headed, motorcycling, spell-hacker. These heroes set off on a journey taking the reader through the center of volcanoes, deserts full of living mummies and sphinxes, and a bizarre fairy forest in an effort to save both worlds from complete destruction! Collecting issues #1-5 of Ether series II and featuring a sketchbook section with bonus art from PAUL POPE, MIKE ALLRED, BILL SIENKIEWICZ, MARCOS MARTÃN and JEN BARTEL!', 144),
(681, 'Hellboy: 25 Years of Covers', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9H6WDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Mignola', NULL, 'Art', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=9H6WDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-9H6WDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506715902', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-07-16', NULL, 'To commemorate the 25th anniversary of the first issue of Hellboy, this deluxe art collection includes more than 150 full-page cover pieces from Mike Mignola, Richard Corben, Duncan Fegredo, and more! This oversized 8x12\" hardcover is sure to appeal to Mignola fans and comics enthusiasts alike, featuring an introduction by colorist Dave Stewart and a foreword by Mignola himself.', 200),
(682, 'Prometheus: Life and Death', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=TZHCDQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Abnett', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=TZHCDQAAQBAJ&rdid=book-TZHCDQAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630086565', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-01-24', NULL, 'Colonial Marines have taken possession of an \"abandoned\" alien spacecraft-only to discover its owner is still onboard! Instead of heading to Earth as expected, the humans end up on LV-223 (the planet where the events in the film Prometheus took place). There they must contend with hostile alien life forms, as well as the mysterious \"Engineers\" who are determined to wipe out not just them, but possibly all of humanity! This is the second chapter in the Life and Death story cycle-the follow-up to 2015\'s epic Fire and Stone crossover event. Before this tale is complete, the story lines of Predator, Prometheus, Aliens, and Aliens vs. Predator will all converge!', 96),
(683, 'The EC Archives: Frontline Combat', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5IWODwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Harvey Kurtzman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=5IWODwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-5IWODwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506709659', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-10-22', NULL, 'Legendary Writer/Artist/Editor Harvey Kurtzman collaborates with some of the greatest artists of all time in Wally Wood, John Severin, Alex Toth, and many others to create some of the most essential War stories ever told! In these classic EC tales, we are taken to War in the true grueling and horrific light that few comics of the time dared to show! Collecting Frontline Combat #7-12, this volume features--in fully remastered digital color--the work of comic book greats Harvey Kurtzman, Wally Wood, John Severin, Bill Elder, George Evans, and Alex Toth! Collects Frontline Combat issues #7-#12.', 184),
(684, 'Future in the Wind', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vPE0DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'YOUNG ADULT FICTION', NULL, '9781616557492', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2017-10-10', NULL, 'Four modern-day misfit teens are reluctant recruits to save the mystical isle of Avalon. Magically empowered (and chained to the task) by a set of rings, and directed in their mission by a tight-lipped talking dog, they must stop the rise of King Arthur. But as they struggle to get used to their powers and each other, they\'re faced with an even greater challenge: the discovery that they may not be the good guys in this story. But does that really matter, anyway?', 216),
(685, 'Predator Versus Judge Dredd Versus Aliens', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=34naBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'John Wagner', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=34naBAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-34naBAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630081287', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2014-10-28', NULL, 'Dredd is the most lethal of the highly-trained and obscenely well-armed law enforcement agency known as the Judges, tasked with keeping the sprawling metropolis of Mega-City One from descending into chaos and anarchy. But now Dredd and the other Judges are all that stand between the universe\'s most efficient killing machines and the annihilation of every living being in the city--criminal or innocent. Dark Horse Comics and 2000 AD team up to bring you a collection of the classic stories Predator versus Judge Dredd and Judge Dredd versus Aliens in one handsome hardcover.', 184),
(686, 'Deception', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=49GMDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nunzio DeFilippis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781506707457', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Olivia Pryde hasn\'t worked an honest day in years. Once an actress, she now lives by the con, and has come to Tevinter with a new target: Calix Qintara, the heir to a wealthy house. Once she approaches the young man, she quickly realises that he is not exactly who he says he is - and she may be in too deep.', 72),
(687, 'Fear Agent', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NKsBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Rick Remender', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616554514', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Trapped in the past with the Feeders advancing on Earth, alien exterminator Heath Huston must stop the automaton regime responsible for robbing him of all he loves before the alien infestation arrives on his home planet.', 136),
(688, 'Creepy Presents Richard Corben', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MzwBJQlsbbAC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Richard Corben', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=MzwBJQlsbbAC&rdid=book-MzwBJQlsbbAC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621155973', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2012-07-10', NULL, 'Over 300 pages of timeless terror from a master storyteller! Horror comics visionary and coloring pioneer Richard Corben has been a voice of creativity and change for over four decades. For the first time ever, Corben\'s legendary Creepy and Eerie short stories and cover illustrations are being collected into one deluxe hardcover! With an informative foreword by artist and comic book colorist JosÃ© Villarrubiaâ€”who also provides color restorationâ€”this volume features Richard Corben\'s original stories, Edgar Allan Poe adaptations, and collaborations with cast of comic-book writers.', 320),
(689, 'Megatokyo Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ba4zDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Fred Gallagher', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781506701882', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2016-10-20', NULL, '\"Largo, a hardcore American gamer and l33t h4x0rm4573r, has classes to teach, PH33Rbots to build, and a retired, weapon-grade idol to aid. Piro-an obsessed anime and manga fan-tries to help an emerging idol with her rise to fame, teach a young schoolgirl how to draw, and make a mysterious but darkly cute girl go away\"--Provided by publisher.', 720),
(690, 'Edgar Rice Burroughs\' Tarzan', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=O6WvDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Joe Kubert', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '9781616559823', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"This volume collects Joe Kubert\'s Tarzan stories from Tarzan #207-#225 and #227-#235 and Joe Kubert\'s cover for Tarzan #226, originally published in 1972, 1973, 1974, and 1975 by National Periodical Publications, Inc. These stories were previously collected in Tarzan: The Joe Kubert Years Volumes 1-3, published in 2005 and 2006 by Dark Horse Comics\"--Colophon.', 616),
(691, 'Star Wars Episode IV, a New Hope Photo Comic', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=N7zVQgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'George Lucas', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1593078749', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Two robots sent to find help by Princess Leia contact Luke Skywalker and Obi-Wan Kenobi, and provide the Rebel forces with important information about the Empire\'s death star.', 96),
(692, 'Creepy Archives', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-CoCDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Archie Goodwin', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781595827722', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Gather up your wooden stakes, your blood-covered hatchets, and all the skeletons in the darkest depths of your closet, and prepare for a horrifying adventure into the darkest corners of comics history. Dark Horse Comics further corners the market on high-quality horror storytelling with one of the most anticipated releases of the decade - a hardcover archive collection of the legendary Creepy Magazine!', 272),
(693, 'Flash Gordon Comic Book Archives', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=B9HUSAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Paul Norris', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1595825592', NULL, NULL, '2010-08-24', NULL, 'Flash Gordon\'s classic era in comic books returns in a new archival collection from Dark Horse! Join the handsome and fearless Flash, his clever and capable companion Dale Arden, and eccentric scientist Dr. Zarkov as they face peril and danger in the wild landscapes of the planet Mongo and go head-to-head with the villainous despot Ming the Merciless! This archival collection, reprinting seven complete comics originally published from 1947 through 1953, makes a fine addition to any comics library. Ray guns, spaceships, and Silver Age storytelling â€” it\'s all here and it\'s all action!', 312),
(694, 'Buffy, the Vampire Slayer', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=27jS7HK38scC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Christopher Golden', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1569716021', NULL, 'Dark Horse Books', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Collects eight stories in which Buffy, Willow, Xander, Oz and their friends battle an assortment of monsters including vampires, demons, and ghosts.', 170),
(695, 'Star Wars', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Lwm0TKjJEc4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1569716234', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Jago Fett is hired by a mysterious employer to retieve an ancient alien artifact and finds himself being played against the beautiful, deadly Zam Wesell, who has also been hired for the job.', 70),
(696, 'Bride of Blood', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vKcBDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Alex De Campi', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781616553784', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"A comic-book double feature mining the exploitation genres of the 1970s for stories of Medieval-era revenge and Puritan-era curses, filled with sex and violence\"--', 112),
(697, 'The Comics', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EJJIewAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Jerry Robinson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1595826572', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Revised and updated edition. Originally published: New York: Putnam, 1974.', 394),
(698, 'Dark Horse Heroes Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OfAHDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mike Richardson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781593077341', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'In the not-too-distant past, the first nuclear weapon test changed the world forever . . . but not in the way we expected. Unleashed upon the planet was a microscopic technological virus of unknown origin that infected millions â€” some to no effect, some to horrifying agonies and disfigurement, others with the gift of incredible and sometimes terrifying power. But would a world populated by supermen become a battleground for good against bad . . . or bad against worse? Is it true that with great power comes great responsibility . . . or does it truly come with great license?', 485),
(699, 'The Guns of Shadow Valley', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E4QRBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dave Wachter', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=E4QRBAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-E4QRBAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781630080631', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2014-08-13', NULL, 'Somewhere in Shadow Valley lies a secret that could forever change the frontier. Only a posse of gunmen with special abilities can defend that secret from a tribe of ghostly warriors, an advancing army led by a deranged Colonel, and the perils of the valley itself. Nominated for the Eisner Award for \'Best Digital Comic\' in 2010, and for the Harvey Award for \'Best Online Comics Work\' in 2011, Dark Horse collects the supernatural webcomic into a 200+ page graphic novel!', 240),
(700, 'The Art of Bravest Warriors', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=S9uJDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Frederator Studios', NULL, 'Art', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=S9uJDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-S9uJDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506712956', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-08-27', NULL, 'Explore the cosmos with zany teenage heroes-for-hire, the Bravest Warriors! Reminisce on the super-powered team\'s greatest adventures from Cartoon Hangover\'s hit animated series, Bravest Warriors! Warp through informative chapters of the show\'s main characters, beloved environments, and unique alien species that the team\'s encountered before. This exclusive collection of beautiful art from the creative mind of Pendleton Ward includes storyboards and scripts from early stages of the show\'s production as well as comics and fan art for the most impassioned fans of the series. Enjoy this comprehensive collection of illustrations and dive into the development and production materials of the Bravest Warriors--all available in this exclusive art book! This exploration of the hit series Bravest Warriors features hundreds of marvelous art pieces that make this an impeccable volume that can\'t be missed!', 199),
(701, 'Usagi Yojimbo: Yokai', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=PaNeDRj_3fUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Stan Sakai', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=PaNeDRj_3fUC&rdid=book-PaNeDRj_3fUC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781621155485', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2009-11-17', NULL, 'Yokai are the monsters, demons, and spirits of Japanese folklore, such as the shape-changing kitsune, the obakeneko demon cats, and the evil oni ogres. Usagi faces all these and more when a desperate woman begs for his help in finding her kidnapped daughter. Tracing the abducted girl deep into the forest, Usagi finds it haunted by creatures of Japanese legend and discovers that they are amassing for a great raid on the countryside! Fortunately, Usagi is joined by Sasuke the Demon Queller, who is also fighting to prevent the invasion, but things aren\'t always as they seem â€” especially when dealing with the supernatural! * The rabbit ronin turned twenty-five, and Dark Horse celebrated with the first-ever Usagi Yojimbo original graphic novel, fully hand-painted, written, and lettered by creator Stan Sakai! * Completely self-contained story. * Usagi Yojimbo is a 2009 Eisner Award nominee for Best Continuing Series. First ever, full color, original story!', 64),
(702, 'Trout Volume 1: Bits & Bobs', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=CGeEDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Troy Nixey', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=CGeEDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-CGeEDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781506712611', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2019-03-26', NULL, 'When a mysterious and evil puppet show passes by, Trout finds himself as the only one able to save the town from the puppeteer\'s nefarious grasp! Living above a Turnip Factory, Trout is not like other kids. After many bizarre adventures, Trout has seen more than most adults in his short lifetime. Trout must grapple with the ferocious appetite of a monstrous repressed memory come to life, hell-bent on eating the town. And if that wasn\'t enough, when a mysterious and evil puppet show passes through, Trout is the only one able to save the town\'s children from the puppeteer\'s insidious grasp! This Hardcover volume collects Trout #1-2 previously published by Oni Press in 2001, as well as Trout\'s first appearance in Dark Horse Presents #119-123 from 1997 along with a wonderfully weird assortment of never before seen material!', 104),
(703, 'DisneyÂ·PIXAR The Incredibles 2: Heroes at Home (Younger Readers Graphic Novel)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cwRSDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Liz Marsham', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '9781506709734', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '2018-06-12', NULL, 'Interwoven with the events of the film, the kids of The Incredibles super family, Violet, Dash, and Jack-Jack, have adventures of their own in two tales where they balance their everyday lives with being secret Superheroes. While their mom and dad--Mr. Incredible and Elastigirl--are both taking on new and very different jobs, Dash and Violet are doing their best to help out! First, Dash and Violet become sudden and secret superheroes when they interrupt criminal activity on a routine grocery trip to pick up some essentials! Then, helping out at home, their efforts to keep up on their chores are unknowingly obstructed by the innocent mischief of their little brother, Jack-Jack! This comics collection, written by Liz Marsham (Batgirl Classic, Wonder Woman Classic, Disney Princess Beginnings, Harley Quinn: Wild Card), and illustrated by Nicoletta Baldari (Star Wars Adventures: Forces of Destiny, The Powerpuff Girls), features stories that are accessible for the young reader--but enjoyable for everyone! Also included in this volume are a variety of story-related activities and a special feature on how comic books come to life!', 48),
(704, 'Aliens Omnibus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Z_MHDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Mark Verheiden', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '9781593079260', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Presents a series of episodes in which scientists, military personnel, corporate officials, and hapless civilians encounter the deadly and mysterious Aliens, leading to adventures on Earth and other planets.', 374),
(705, 'Too Much Coffee Man Omnibus Plus', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=2nskDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Shannon Wheeler', NULL, 'Antiheroes', NULL, '9781506704029', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"This volume collects Too Much Coffee Man\'s Guide for the Perplexed, published in 1998; Too Much Coffee Man\'s Parade of Tirade, published in 1999; Too Much Coffee Man\'s Amusing Musings, published in 2001; Too Much Coffee Man: How to be Happy, published in 2005; Screw Heaven, When I Die I\'m Going to Mars, published in 2007; Too Much Coffee Man Omnibus, published in 2011; the Dark Horse Presents Volume 3 #33 cover, featuring Too Much Coffee Man; and \"Too Much Coffee Man vs. The Squirrel..\"\"', 600),
(706, 'Tales from the Crypt', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EsGcDAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Albert B. Feldstein', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '9781506700540', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'EC Comics are widely credited for causing the dissolution of the morals of kids and teens in the 1950s, thus playing a large part in the public outcry over comics that led to Senate hearings condemning the sex and violence within their pages. Dark Horse brings their usual high quality design and production to the creation of collector\'s editions of these seminal comics.', 216),
(707, 'Screw Heaven, When I Die I\'m Going to Mars', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ilZQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Shannon Wheeler', NULL, 'Humor', NULL, 'UOM:39015068786683', NULL, NULL, '2007-07-04', NULL, 'For longer than a decade Shannon Wheeler\'s flagship character Too Much Coffee Man has cast his tender, cynical gaze on lots of stuff that deserves to be made fun of, from the insipidity of coffee consumer culture to the horrendous reality of dating. This latest collection of short cartoons takes a step back from the cartoonist\'s usual scrutiny of mundane pettiness and takes a somewhat sweeter look at life\'s bigger issues. The result is the funniest, most sharply executed collection of Wheeler\'s comics ever.', 141),
(708, 'Al Capp\'s Complete Shmoo', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Eo8CHwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Al Capp', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '159307901X', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'First appearing in Al Cappâ€™s \"Liâ€™l Abner\" comic strip in 1948, the oddly shaped (and happily edible) Shmoo became an overnight phenomenon, spawning an unprecedented merchandising frenzy in the late â€™40s and 50s. As part of the Dark Horse Archives series, ALL Shmoo comic book appearances are being collected for the first time ever in a deluxe hardcover edition! In addition to every issue of Shmoo Comics from 1949 and 1950, rare bonus stories, and Shmoo-centric advertisements from yesteryear, Al Capp\'s Complete Shmoo: The Comic Books features an introduction and annotations by certified Shmoo-ologist Denis Kitchen. A persistent presence in pop culture, the selfless Shmoo has served humanity for decades â€” mostly by offering itself as food â€” but also by entertaining and tickling our funny bones like no other creature can. Treat yourself to these hilarious adventures, featuring Washable Jones, Super Shmoo, Frankenshmoo, Fu Manshmoo and truly a cast of thousands! This archival collection sports a new cover by Peter Poplaski.', 173),
(709, 'Invisible Kingdom #7', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=DXOzDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'G. Willow Wilson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=DXOzDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-DXOzDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3005594', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-11-27', NULL, 'The Sundog has been captured by pirates, with Grix and the crew at the mercy of its black-hearted captain Turo. When a disabled Lux ship is found stranded in the junk rings, it becomes the Riveters\' next target . . . and the Sundog is dragged along for the increasingly treacherous ride.', 32),
(710, 'Invisible Kingdom #6', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=X7GqDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'G. Willow Wilson', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=X7GqDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-X7GqDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', 'PKEY:3005593', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics (Single Issues)', '2019-10-30', NULL, 'A fierce beginning to arc two of the astronomical hit series! Desperate after a devastating battle, the Sundog is stranded and running out of fuelâ€”and they turn to Vess\' breathtaking home planet of Rool for help. But just as unexpected bonds and newfound strength begin to reveal themselves . . . so does a new and terrifying gang of spacefaring renegades.', 32),
(711, 'Blade of the Immortal: Dark shadows', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3ss3AQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Hiroaki Samura', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '156971469X', NULL, 'Dark Horse Manga', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Manji, a ronin warrior of feudal Japan, has been cursed with immortality and to rid his eternal suffering and lift the curse, he must slay one thousand enemies, and his quest begins with a young girl who seeks revenge on her parents\' killers.', 117),
(712, 'Digital Monsters', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=aJ4S2rcKl9kC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Daniel HDR', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1569715165', NULL, NULL, '2000-12-05', NULL, 'Seven children at summer camp discover mysterious devices that transport them to the Digiworld--a strange land populated by fantastic digital monsters, or Digimon. The kids are befriended by seven small Digimon who have the ability to evolve into more powerful forms to help protect their human pals. This graphic novel is based on the Fox Kids! series. Illustrations.', 117),
(713, 'What\'s Michael?', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vGJQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Makoto Kobayashi', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569719144', NULL, NULL, '2003-02-19', NULL, 'Everyday cat and human interactions mingle with fantasy stories featuring the fat cat Michael and other felines.', 86),
(714, 'Olivia', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=S_PNAAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Dark Horse Comics', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1596174323', NULL, NULL, '2006-02-01', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(715, 'Dreamsong', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Wss3AQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Wayne Truman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '156971357X', NULL, 'Dark Horse Manga', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Manji, a ronin warrior of feudal Japan, has been cursed with immortality and to rid his eternal suffering and lift the curse, he must slay one thousand enemies, and his quest begins with a young girl who seeks revenge on her parents\' killers.', 208),
(716, 'Spyboy', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=MrTGV00ipQIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Peter David', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569719845', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'When SpyGirl finds an old photograph of her with Japan\'s Minister of Defense that she does not remember being taken, she tries to figure out what is going on, and what it has to do with Spyboy.', 80);
INSERT INTO `comic` (`idCom`, `nombre`, `imagen`, `autor`, `artista`, `categoria`, `compra`, `isbn`, `genero`, `editorial`, `fec_publi`, `nacionalidad`, `descripcion`, `paginas`) VALUES
(717, 'El Zombo Fantasma', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=U2FtP5fG4MgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Kevin Munroe', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1593072848', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'After being murdered, Mexican wrestler El Zombo finds himself in purgatory and in order to avoid fiery damnation he must become a bodyguard for ten-year-old Belisa Montoya, which gives him the opportunity to track down his killer.', 88),
(718, 'Museum of Terror', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=9XRQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1593075421', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Dark Horse Comics is very proud to present Museum of Terror, a series of horror stories by Japan\'s foremost creator of horror manga. Full of compelling and charming characters and relationships, and featuring some of the finest comics art available, Junji Ito has seen his works translated into successful films in Japan. Ito\'s Uzumaki, the thrilling and grotesque manga and film, has already found success in America, and now we present \"Tomie,\" the first story in this fantastic series. \"Tomie\" is the story of an eternally youthful and beautiful high school girl, whose admirers are obsessed to the point of murdering her. But to their horror, she is reincarnated over and over. \"Tomie\" also became a popular film in Japan, and now it launches Dark Horse\'s series of Ito\'s horrific works, Museum of Terror.', 370),
(719, 'The Devil Inside', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=E4i6bw5V0jgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Kosuke Fujishima', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '1593073348', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(720, 'Blade of the Immortal: The gathering II', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iMY3AQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Hiroaki Samura', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569715602', NULL, NULL, '2002-01-02', NULL, 'Manji, a ronin warrior of feudal Japan, has been cursed with immortality and to rid his eternal suffering and lift the curse, he must slay one thousand enemies, and his quest begins with a young girl who seeks revenge on her parents\' killers.', 216),
(721, 'Blade of the Immortal', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Pc03AQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Hiroaki Samura', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569715467', NULL, 'Dark Horse Manga', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Blade of the Immortal', 208),
(722, 'Shockrockets', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QAGS7oXQhToC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Kurt Busiek', NULL, 'Juvenile Fiction', NULL, '1593071299', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Alejandro Cruz find his bleak 2087 postwar world changing for the better after he accidentally becomes the newest pilot for the Shockrockets, an elite, high-tech fighter squadron.', 160),
(723, 'Caravan Kidd', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zck3AQAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Johji Manabe', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1569713383', NULL, NULL, '1999-01-27', NULL, 'Acclaimed manga-master Johji Manabe, creator of Outlanders and Drakuun, completes his epic Caravan Kidd saga in this massive 296-page volume. The beautiful warrior Mian Toris confronts her arch-nemesis, Empress Shion, on the homeworld of the Helgebard Empire. If Mian prevails, the Empire will be brought to its knees -- and the homeworld of her conscripted sidekick Wataru (who just happens to be in love with Mian) will be destroyed by an even greater stellar menace!', 292),
(724, 'DMZ', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=IMecxAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Wood', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '0857680641', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'AmericaÂ¿s worst nightmare has come true. With military adventurism overseas bogging down the Army and National Guard, the US government neglects the very real threat of anti-establishment militias scattered across the 50 states. Middle America rises up and violently pushes its way to the seas, coming to a standstill at Manhattan or, as the world now knows it, the DMZ.', 128),
(725, 'Transmetropolitan: Lonely city', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=1X9kRQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Warren Ellis', NULL, 'Antiheroes', NULL, '1563897229', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'The City can be a lonely place - especially for famed journalist Spider Jerusalem, despised and loved in equal measure (and with equal ferocity) by The City\'s wealthy elite and its downtrodden rabble. But in a town where anything can bought, stolen, or manufactured, the truth is still in short supply, and Jerusalem is the one man determined to keep it on the market - no matter what the price.', 134),
(726, 'Demo', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hE2gSgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Wood', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1401229956', NULL, 'Vertigo', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Six vignettes feature disaffected young people with latent abilities and fantastic situations.', 152),
(727, 'The Reformed Citizen', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-Cq0PQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Jesse Gordon', NULL, 'Fiction', NULL, '061514182X', NULL, NULL, '2007-03-01', NULL, 'While 2005\'s The Midnight Recollections served as an introductory sampling of Gordon\'s short story work, this new collection of mostly novellas and novelettes delves specifically into the dark, the introspective, and the surreal. Most of the material presented herein comes in the form of rare and unpublished gems sharing similar themes of societal idiosyncrasies. The Reformed Citizen could be classified as \"social science fiction\" - with a devious twist. As usual, Gordon\'s ideas are potent and varied, unabashedly frank, his characters well-developed. Included in this volume: Distributed Logic; Line 43; The Ninth Life of Vincent Nguyen; A Whisper from the Mirror; Fogy; The Path Between; Arrival. NOTE: For mature readers; contains sexual/violent content.', 336),
(728, 'One Hundred Bullets', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=7wl4wgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Azzarello', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '1401204902', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 222),
(729, 'Wish You Were Here', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=T4DnwAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Simon Oliver', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '140125067X', NULL, 'Vertigo', '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"Quantum tornadoes. Localized gravity failures. Bubble dimensions. Inescapable vortexes. The fabric of the universe is weakening, and the brave men and women who risk their lives to repair it work for the Federal Bureau of Physics.\"--Back cover of Volume 1.', 144),
(730, 'CMYK', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gewCogEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Fabio Moon', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1401253369', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2015-07-15', NULL, '[C]yan. [M]agenta. [Y]ellow. Blac[K]. From these basic building blocks, the entire spectrum of comic book coloring is formed. Now the medium is returning the favor. Building on the innovative tradition that has made it one of comics\' most cutting-edge imprints, VERTIGO is proud to present CMYK -- a bold new anthology of original stories from dozens of the art form\'s greatest creators. The short graphic fiction collected here all originates with the four process colors of comics printing, but where they go from there is as unbounded as imagination itself. In these pages, the glacial glow of cyan bathes alien worlds and wintry city streets; the vivid splash of magenta highlights the hair of outcasts and the evil of demons; the bright light of yellow shines on old worlds ending and new lives beginning; and the enveloping void of black offers both despair and liberation. The stunning stories and breathtaking visions of CMYK will forever color your perception of what comics can do! Featuring work by Gene Luen Yang, Jeff Lemire, Gerard Way, Amy Chu, Jock, Fabio Moon, Francesco Francavilla, Bill Sienkiewicz and many more! Collects VERTIGO QUARTERLY: CYAN #1, VERTIGO QUARTERLY: MAGENTA #1, VERTIGO QUARTERLY: YELLOW #1 and VERTIGO QUARTERLY: BLACK #1.', 296),
(731, 'Army@love', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nH8bMQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Rick Veitch', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1401218326', NULL, 'Vertigo', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Hegemony in the new millenium can\'t be maintained with the kind of lumbering, out-of-date combat styles that we rocked in the 20th century - leave that nostalgia trip to the codgers watching the Hitler channel! This is the new military, and we\'ve got a new paradigm: Ground Zero in Afbaghistan as the ultimate wi-fi hotspot, live and streaming! We\'ve also ditched those tired nation-state crutches of sovereignty and diplomacy - so mid nineties, so brick and mortar! -- and the result is a vast new market thirsting for consumer satisfaction!', 166),
(732, 'Greek Street', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EqtRXwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Peter Milligan', NULL, 'Fantasy comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '0857688901', NULL, 'Titan Publishing Company', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'The turf war between the Fureys and the Limms comes to a violent conclusion and a poor, half-blinded Eddie is caught in the middle. Will his last act bring order to the chaos on Greek Street? Or will his life end in tragedy?', 128),
(733, 'Preacher Book Six', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=JvyqBAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Garth Ennis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=JvyqBAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-JvyqBAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401256609', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2014-11-04', NULL, 'In this final PREACHER volume, Jesse Custer makes amends with his girlfriend, Tulip, then seeks revenge against his formerfriend and compatriot Cassidy for the things the Irish vampire did to her when they both believed the Preacher to be dead. The final chapter in the Preacher storyline and the conclusion of Jesse Custer\'s quest to literally find God and take Him to taskfor the world\'s injustices. As the Preacher\'s crusade draws to an end, all of the players converge at the Alamo for a final show-down. With the love of his life, Tulip, by his side, Jesse makes his last stand against all of his enemies, including the Irish vampireknown as Cassidy, whom he used to call friend. But as the dust settles in the Texas desert, you won\'t believe how this epic battleof good versus evil will end.', 380),
(734, 'American Vampire', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lvDZtwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Scott Snyder', NULL, 'Vampires', NULL, '1401267157', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Scott Snyder and Rafael Albuquerque\'s award-winning series continues! Welcome to the \'60s. It\'s a turbulent time to be an American-especially an American Vampire. While the rest of the nation uneasily watches the spread of communism across the world stage, the three surviving Abominus Americana-Pearl Jones, Skinner Sweet and Calvin Poole-are fighting a battle much closer to home. An evil right underneath their feet. The Gray Trader, the nearest thing to the devil this world has ever seen, is summoning an ancient beast from the depths of the earth. The original and oldest evil, this abomination would devour the world if freed. To prevent it, the American Vampires will have to fight the Gray Trader on two fronts, with one team targeting a top-secret government stronghold known as Area 51 and the other heading up-way up-into the final frontier! But can such an ambitious plan succeed when one of their own has already been compromised by the Beast?', NULL),
(735, 'Letters from Lost Countries', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tmNFbwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'G. Willow Wilson', NULL, 'Blythe (Fictitious character : Wilson)', NULL, '1848568819', NULL, 'Titan Publishing Company', '2010-09-01', NULL, 'Blythe knew it was a risky time to be an airline stewardess. She\'s just learned of the Etesian Front - vigilantes dedicated to take the skies back from terrorism. They\'re after a mysterious man she\'s just met.', 144),
(736, 'Motel California', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ahaoswEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Michael Carlon', NULL, 'Fiction', NULL, '0997983973', NULL, 'Uncorking a Story', '2017-12-22', NULL, 'Sex, drugs, and rock & roll, LAÂ¿s Hotel Palomino (aka The Motel California) has them all, but it never had a murder on its hands, until now.Farrah Graham and Jimmy Doubts, hosts of the popular Uncorking a Murder podcast, are in Los Angeles promoting season three of their show. As part of their media tour, they appear on a late-night talk show where Bernie Deville, a singer intent on distancing himself from his past, performs as the showÂ¿s musical guest.After the show, Jimmy has a physical altercation with the singer. Later that evening, the singerÂ¿s life meets an untimely end when heÂ¿s thrown off the balcony of his hotel room at the seedy Hotel Palomino. After a video clip of JimmyÂ¿s fight with the singer goes viral, Doubts becomes a prime suspect in the murder of Bernie Deville.Farrah, meanwhile, is distracted by another matter; Interpersonal Audio Inc, a patent holding company, is coming after Uncorking a Murder and other successful podcasts claiming content infringement. If this patent troll wins, it would mean the end of Uncorking a Murder. The stakes couldnÂ¿t be higher as Farrah and Jimmy fight for their futures.Twin Detectives who argue about Heavy Metal music, a sociopathic killer dressed like a cowboy, and a mob boss addicted to home improvement television round out the cast of Motel California, a story that could only be told in the backdrop of a town as unique as LA.', 314),
(737, 'Clean Room', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zoiavwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Gail Simone', NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '1401275842', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, '\"Journalist Chloe Pierce had no idea that her fiance Philip\'s decision to pick up a book by enigmatic and compelling self-help guru Astrid Mueller would change her life forever--by ending his! Three months after reading Mueller\'s book, Philip had blown his brains out all over Chloe\'s new kitchen and something in that book made him do it. Now, Chloe will stop at nothing as she attempts to infiltrate Mueller\'s clandestine organization to find the truth behind Philip\'s suicide and a \"Clean Room\" that she\'s heard whispers of--a place where your deepest fears are exposed and your worst moments revealed. This volume features a spectacularly disturbing standalone issue that delves into the depths of Astrid\'s terrifying personal history and explains why demons have haunted her since birth\"--', NULL),
(738, 'Little Apple', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3K9rjgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Leo Perutz', NULL, 'Europe', NULL, '1782271678', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Vittorin, a young Austrian officer, has just been released from a Russian POW camp toward the end of the Great War. In Vienna his family, his girlfriend, and his old job await him, but Vittorin can\'t think of settling down until he has settled the score with the sadistic camp commander, Staff Captain Selukov. Private obsession and political turmoil mix as Perutz leads his hero on a manhunt into the thick of the Russian civil war. In and out of prison, starving in the gutters of Moscow, thrown into revolutionary battle, Vittorin pursues his elusive quarry across postwar Europe. At each turn, he encounters only Fate\'s joker, until, back in Vienna, Fate plays him the biggest joke of all.', 200),
(739, 'The Executioner Weeps', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=hBRDDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Ã©dÃ©ric Dard', NULL, 'Barcelona (Spain)', NULL, '9781782272564', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'On a quiet mountain road near Barcelona, a woman steps out in front of a car. When the driver, a well-known artist, stops to come to her aid, he finds she is alive, but without any memory of who she is or where she has come from. The only clue to her identity is the broken violin lying at her side. The artist tries to help her remember her past, and finds himself falling in love, but as secrets from the woman\'s forgotten life start to come to light, he finds his new romance turning into a nightmare.', 157),
(740, 'Return to Casa Grande', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kQ6UjgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Michael Carlon', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0692562192', NULL, NULL, '2015-10-21', NULL, 'A washed up 80s soap star is thrust back into the spotlight after an accidental appearance on a hit reality show. Blaze Hazelwood is a former \"household name\" actor searching for relevance in an entertainment environment that is remarkably different from what it was in his heyday. Blaze was the breakout star of Casa Grande, a 1980s primetime soap beloved by millions. Twenty-five years after the show\'s finale, the rest of the cast is struggling to get by but Blaze manages to stay busy doing voiceover work as well as participating in marketing focus groups taking on different personas to continually \"build his chops.\" Blaze loathes reality TV; for he truly believes that it represents everything wrong with the entertainment industry - and quite possibly the world - today. Harvard educated Allison Hart, meanwhile, has a hit on her hands with Bling it on Featuring T-Bang - a \"celebreality\" show crafted around Hollywood \"bad-boy\" Thaddeus Stevens. The show\'s popularity doubled the sales of a sponsor\'s product and she has been approached to repeat its success for a product line geared towards women in an age group who still romance over Blaze Hazelwood and Casa Grande. When Blaze unknowingly appears on an episode of Bling it On, the US goes with Blaze Fever - an affliction that many suffered in the 80s. This puts Blaze, Allison, and the former cast of Casa Grande on a collision course filled with hilarity, over the top revelations, and twists and turns that can only be true in a story featuring aging soap opera stars.', 192),
(741, 'Air: Flying machine', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=I1SnbwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'G. Willow Wilson', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '1848568827', NULL, 'Titan Publishing Company', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Blythe\'s mysterious rescuer reveals the truth behind one of the most shocking disappearances in aviation history - a secret tied to the origin of hyperprax flight. Then, as the race to find a mysterious device begins, Blythe must master her skills as a hyperpract - regardless of her own acrophobia.', 128),
(742, 'Uncorking a Murder', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=OgJYvgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Michael Carlon', NULL, 'Fiction', NULL, '069276075X', NULL, 'Uncorking a Story', '2016-08-17', NULL, 'A retired detective short on time is looking to right a wrong in this \"Serial meets Gone Girl\" thriller. The Uncorking a Murder podcast took the nation by storm. Farrah Graham, the creator and host, struck a nerve with listeners through a ten-episode serial that combined investigative journalism, old fashioned radio drama, and compelling storytelling. Farrah\'s loyal listeners and advertisers are hungry for season two! While Farrah and her partner Melody struggle to agree on a topic for the second season of the podcast, their intern takes a call from a retired detective in Ft. Lauderdale pitching his request to focus on a case he was involved with five years earlier. Interested to hear why a retired detective is driven to have a conviction overturned, Farrah follows her curiosity down to Ft. Lauderdale where she uncovers a conspiracy involving a narcissistic CEO fueled by greed, a US Senator, and a wrongly imprisoned man; but will she live long enough to uncork the story?', 348),
(743, 'The Murdered Banker', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LOTPCwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Augusto De Angelis', NULL, 'Detective and mystery stories', NULL, '9781782271703', NULL, 'Pushkin Vertigo', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'A body is discovered in a Milan apartment, and Inspector De Vincenzi investigates. The apartment happens to belong to and old university friend of his, Aurigi. When the body turns out to be that of Aurigi\'s banker, and a phial of prussic acid is discovered in the bathroom, suspicion falls on the apartment\'s owner, and De Vincenzi is agonisingly torn between his sense of duty and his loyalty to an old comrade... This intensely dramatic mystery from the father of the Italian crime novel, Augusto de Angelis, is the first to feature his most famous creation--Inspector De Vincenzi.', 160),
(744, 'Room and Boredom', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Z6OqNwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Matthew Sturges', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1401220797', NULL, 'Vertigo', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Meet the five lost souls who unwillingly make the House of mystery their home.', 122),
(745, 'Sweet Tooth', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=vroSTwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Jeff Lemire', NULL, 'Animal mutation', NULL, '0857680447', NULL, 'Titan Books', '2011-03-01', NULL, 'Lemire explores the heartbreaking story of Jeppard and how he went from devoted husband to ruthless mercenary. Meanwhile, Gus is captive with other hybrid creatures in a camp where he meets a scientist studying the plague that\'s wiped out so much of the world.', 144),
(746, 'Architecture Degree Zero', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Roger Connah', NULL, 'Architecture', NULL, 'OCLC:747408550', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 71),
(747, 'Scalped Vol. 2: Casino Boogie', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ISIWAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jason Aaron', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=ISIWAgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-ISIWAgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401241520', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2008-02-06', NULL, 'This volume, collecting issues #6-11 of the acclaimed new series by Jason Aaron (THE OTHER SIDE), explores Dash Bad Horse\'s troubled origin and chronicles his day-to-day life on The Rez working for Chief Red Crow. - See more at: http://www.vertigocomics.com/graphic-novels/scalped-vol-2-casino-boogie#sthash.Eg03FKxq.dpuf', NULL),
(748, 'Y', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fRRhPgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Brian K. Vaughan', NULL, 'Brown, Yorick (Fictitious character)', NULL, '1401219217', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Yorick Brown, an unemployed and unmotivated slacker, discovers that he is the only male left in the world after a plague of unknown origin instantly kills every mammal with a Y chromosome.', 246),
(749, 'The Kindly Ones', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ftP6QgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1563892057', NULL, 'Vertigo', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Dream of the Endless finds himself caught up in a mission of vengeance by the Kindly Ones.', 352),
(750, 'Ex Machina Book One', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=3I9bAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian K. Vaughan', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=3I9bAgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-3I9bAgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401249830', NULL, 'DC', '2014-01-21', NULL, 'Award-winning writer Brian K. Vaughan (PRIDE OF BAGHDAD, Y: THE LAST MAN) uniquely combines big city politics and superheroes in this criticially acclaimed series. Set in our modern-day world, EX MACHINA tells the story of civil engineer Mitchell Hundred, who becomes America\'s first living, breathing super-hero after a strange accident gives him the power to communicate with machines. Eventually Mitchell tires of risking his life merely to maintain the status quo, retires from masked crime fighting and runs for mayor of New York City, winning by a landslide after the events of 9/11. Illustrated by Tony Harris, EX MACHINA BOOK ONE is the first chapter of one of the finest series ever from Vertigo. Collects issues #1-11.', NULL),
(751, 'Army at Love', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rMWMGQAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Rick Veitch', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1401214746', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'When a New Jersey National Guard unit is deployed indefinitely to a never-ending series of wars in the Middle East, the citizen soldiers--ranging from kids fresh out of high school to middle-aged corporate managers--are motivated by the modernized military, who has gone into take-no-prisoners marketing mode.', 128),
(752, 'Whys and wherefores, #55-60', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ljpfxAEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Brian K. Vaughan', NULL, 'Heroes', NULL, '140121813X', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(753, 'Scalped', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4BVOwgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Jason Aaron', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1401232884', NULL, 'Vertigo', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'While Red Crow takes on a challenger for tribal leadership, Dash pursues his mother\'s killer, and Officer Falls Down is held captive.', 160),
(754, 'John Constantine, Hellblazer', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QHKcuAAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Si Spencer', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '0857685147', NULL, 'Titan Publishing Company', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'When John Constantine is run over by a truck, it takes him a little while to realise that he\'s perched between life and death. After a few weeks of hospital rehab, Constantine finds the London streets very different from when he left as a series of occult murders and mutilations demands his attention.', 128),
(755, 'Transmetropolitan Vol. 10: One More Time (New Edition)', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=sPkPAwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Warren Ellis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=sPkPAwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-sPkPAwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781401251970', NULL, 'DC', '2011-08-23', NULL, 'The final volume in the saga of outlaw journalist Spider Jerusalem written by comics superstar Warren Ellis. At last, it\'s the final showdown between Spider and the absolutely corrupt President of the United States in this new edition of the finale to the classic dystopian saga from Vertigo.', NULL),
(756, 'The Losers', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Fu96QgAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Andy Diggle', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1401227333', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'The Losers, a squad of former special forces soldiers believed killed in the line of duty on a mission for the CIA, journey to the Caribbean to try to track down Max, the mysterious CIA agent who is not supposed to exist.', 304),
(757, 'Air', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5Uk8bwAACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'G. Willow Wilson', NULL, 'Blythe (Fictitious character : Wilson)', NULL, '1848568835', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Blythe makes a dangerous journey to the Northwest Frontier province of Pakistan, where she\'s drawn into a holy war with a bizarre twist.', 162),
(758, 'John Constantine, Hellblazer: Dangerous habits', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=iVtCwgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', NULL, NULL, 'COMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS', NULL, '1401238025', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'John Constantine is an unconcerned, somewhat amoral occultist with a British working-class background. He\'s a hero, of sorts, who manages to come out on top through a combination of luck, trickery, and genuine magical skill.', NULL),
(759, 'Aalto-ego', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Roger Connah', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'OCLC:747408554', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 209),
(760, 'Fables', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Graphic novels', NULL, '1401236022', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'When a savage creature known only as the Adversary conquered the fabled lands of legends and fairy tales, all of the infamous inhabitants of folklore were forced into exile. Disguised among the normal citizens of modern-day New York, these magical characters have created their own peaceful and secret society within an exclusive luxury apartment building called Fabletown. But when Snow White\'s party-girl sister, Rose Red, is apparently murdered, it is up to Fabletown\'s sheriff, a reformed and pardoned Big Bad Wolf, to determine if the killer is Bluebeard, Rose\'s ex-lover and notorious wife killer, or Jack, her current live-in boyfriend and former beanstalk-climber.', NULL),
(761, 'Black Orchid', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Adam Beechen', NULL, NULL, NULL, '140124663X', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'A NEW YORK TIMES Bestseller Before introducing the modern version of The Sandman, Neil Gaiman wrote this dark tale that reinvented a strange DC Comics super hero in the Vertigo mold. Featuring spectacular art by Gaiman\'s frequent collaborator, DaveMcKean, BLACK ORCHID. After being viciously murdered, Susan Linden is reborn fully grown as the Black Orchid, a hybrid of plant and human, destined to avenge her own death. Now, as this demigoddessattempts to reconcile human memory and botanical origins, she must untangle the webs of deception and secrets that led to her death. Beginning in the cold streets of a heartless metropolis and ending in the Amazon rainforest, this book takes thereader on a journey through secrets, suffering and self-rediscovery.', NULL),
(762, 'Pulp Surrealism and Other Visions', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Beric Henderson', NULL, 'Art, Australian', NULL, '0975814702', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, 24),
(763, 'DMZ: On the ground', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Brian Wood', NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, '1401210627', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'While the U.S. Army and National Guard are fighting overseas, an anti-establishment militia rises up and begins a second civil war.', 126),
(764, 'Doom Patrol', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Grant Morrison', NULL, 'Doom Patrol (Fictitious characters)', NULL, 'OCLC:1090300527', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'This new edition of the first collection of Grant Morrison\'s DOOM PATROL run includes issues #19 - 25 of the series, including the restoration of three story pages omitted from the original printing. Plus, a new cover by Bolland.', NULL),
(765, 'Ottawa You\'re So Vanier!', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', 'Carleton University. Azrieli School of Architecture and Urbanism', NULL, 'Architecture', NULL, '1987899024', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(766, 'The Sandman: Overture 30th Anniversary Edition', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EBO2DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Neil Gaiman', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=EBO2DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-EBO2DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781779504173', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-10-15', NULL, 'From the birth of a galaxy to the moment that Morpheus is captured, THE SANDMAN: OVERTURE features cameo appearances by fan-favorite characters such as the Corinthian, Merv Pumpkinhead and, of course, the Dream Kingâ€™s siblings: Death, Desire, Despair, Delirium, Destruction and Destiny. This volume collects THE SANDMAN: OVERTURE #1-6, plus bonus material.', 172),
(767, 'Vamps: The Complete Collection', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=w5-8DwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Elaine Lee', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=w5-8DwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-w5-8DwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781779503909', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-11-05', NULL, 'Meet Howler, Screech, Whipsnake, Skeeter, and Mink-five dangerously alluring female vampires thundering down Americaâ€™s highways on Harleys, drunk on freedom and high octane. After killing their male master, the Vamps set out on the open road in search of a new life. But Howler, their leader, is driven by a demon from her past...one that she must vanquish before she can truly enjoy the pleasures of an undead existence. Then, the Vamps go Hollywood as Mink tries to kickstart her movie career-but they soon run afoul of Screechâ€™s old flame, a movie mogul with a nasty secret. This new book collects both VAMPS #1-6 and the never-before-collected VAMPS: HOLLYWOOD AND VEIN #1-6 and VAMPS: PUMPKIN TIME #1-3 in a single volume for the first time, along with a treasure trove of bonus and behind-the-scenes material and a brand-new cover by original series artist Will Simpson!', 360),
(768, 'Flinch', 'assets/images/image_not_found.png', NULL, NULL, 'Comic books, strips, etc', NULL, 'UOM:39015069225236', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(769, 'IZombie', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EyagvgEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Chris Roberson', NULL, 'Vampires', NULL, '1401236979', NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', NULL, 'Every time Gwen, a zombie, eats someone\'s brains she also inherits some of their memories and the latest morsel she devoured gives her memories of a murder she and her friends need to solve.', NULL),
(770, 'Books of Magic (2018-) #14', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=6FHADwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Kat Howard', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, 'PKEY:T1853500145001', NULL, 'Vertigo', '2019-11-27', NULL, 'In the wake of Octoberâ€™s The Sandman Universe Presents: Hellblazer #1, John Constantine is loose in our world again- and unfortunately for Tim Hunter, heâ€™s convinced the only way for the human race to survive is if Tim is taken off the board. But from where Timâ€™s standing, heâ€™s the only one with the power to save us all. Whoâ€™s right? Whoâ€™s wrong? And is there room in London for the both of them? The scribes of Books of Magic and John Constantine, Hellblazer square off to tell both sides of the tale in a unique, innovative issue!', 22),
(771, 'Snow White', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=b6SOmwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'Bill Willingham', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', NULL, '1401242480', NULL, 'Vertigo', '0000-00-00', NULL, 'With Castle Dark now back in the hands of the Fables, mysteries both young and old begin to challenge the residents of Fabletown. Bigsby and Stinky set off from Fabletown in Rose Red\'s blood-fueled sports car to track down the two abducted cubs. Unfortunately for Snow White, besides suffering the trauma of having two of her cubs go missing, a long forgotten secret uncovered in Castle Dark threatens to sabatoge her and Bigsby\'s marriage. This volume also collects the backup adventures of Bufkin and Lily from issues #114-121, as well as their full length adventures found in issue #124. Collected here are Fables issues #114-123 (back-up stories only) and issues #124-129.', 165),
