(778, 'Avengers Epic Collection', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LAWFDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Bob Harras', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LAWFDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-LAWFDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302510558', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-04-10', NULL, 'Collects Avengers (1963) #348-359 and Annual #21 and material from Captain America Annual #11, Thor Annual#17 and Fantastic Four Annual #25. When come the Gatherers! First, the machinations of Hera and Ares pit Hercules against Thor! A visit from the Starjammers and the X-Men proves painful for the Black Knight Â— and so do his feelings for Crystal and Sersi! And the demonic return of a classic villain teaches the Avengers to fear the Grim Reaper Â— not to mention his shambling Legion of the Unliving! Then, the Gatherers Â— Proctor, Magdalene and the Swordsman, plus Sloth and Cassandra Â— attack at last! But what is the secret behind their dastardly plan Â— and why is their next target the Black Panther? Plus: The Avengers aid Arkon! And Captain America, Thor and the Fantastic Four are drawn into the time-travel saga of Citizen Kang!', 480),
(779, 'Spider-Man', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RJaTDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Eleni Roussos', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=RJaTDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-RJaTDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302507893', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-04-24', NULL, 'Fresh off the heels of his first adventure with the Avengers in Marvel\'s Captain America: Civil War, Peter Parker is back in action! With a mentor like Tony Stark - a.k.a. Iron Man - it looks like Spider-Man\'s about to hit the big time. But New York\'s newest villain has other plans. Go behind the scenes in this new keepsake volume continuing Marvel\'s popular ART OF THE MOVIE collection! Discover exclusive concept art, production stills and commentary from cast and crew as Marvel Studios and Sony team up to bring Spider-Man into the ever-expanding Marvel Cinematic Universe!', 256),
(780, 'The Superior Foes Of Spider-Man Vol. 2', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AvlvCAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Nick Spencer', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=AvlvCAAAQBAJ&rdid=book-AvlvCAAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302380991', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'The Superior Foes of Spider-Man 7-11', NULL),
(781, 'The Unworthy Thor', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=M07CDgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Jason Aaron', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=M07CDgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-M07CDgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302497897', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2017-05-24', NULL, 'Collecting The Unworthy Thor #1-5. Unfit to lift his hammer, with another now wielding the power of Thor, the Odinson\'s desperate quest to regain his worthiness takes him out into the cosmos - where he\'s learned of the existence of a mysterious other Mjolnir! This weapon of ultimate power, a relic from a dead universe, is the key to the Odinson\'s redemption - but some of the greatest villains of the Marvel Universe are anxious to get their hands on it as well. And when the Realm of Old Asgard vanishes, the Odinson\'s hopes might go with it - unless good tidings from Beta Ray Bill offer fresh hope! Can the Odinson reclaim his honor, or will the power of thunder be wielded for evil? Let the battle for the hammer commence!', 112),
(782, 'Avengers By Brian Michael Bendis', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=m3yPDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=m3yPDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-m3yPDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302513894', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-05-23', NULL, 'Collects New Avengers (2010) #1-16. The order changeth! But as the Marvel Universe enters a Heroic Age, who will assemble as the newest New Avengers? Where will they call home? And which Dark Avenger is sticking around for the ride? The latest roster has come together to take on the perils too dangerous and bizarre for any other heroes Â— beginning with an interdimensional demonic threat to all existence! Then, a deep and deadly secret Nick Fury has kept buried for decades comes back to haunt the team Â— but who were their predecessors in the 1950s? And when the madness of FEAR ITSELF hits home, the New Avengers battle alongside the Avengers, super-hero nanny Squirrel Girl fights alone and the status quo gets shaken up once again. The time has finally come for Daredevil: Avenger!', 456),
(783, 'Decades', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=tv6dDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Brian Michael Bendis', NULL, NULL, 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=tv6dDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-tv6dDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302515034', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2019-07-10', NULL, 'Collects Ultimate Comics Spider-Man (2011) #7, Captain Marvel (2012) #1, Iron Man (2012) #1, Guardians Of The Galaxy (2013) #4, Edge Of Spider-Verse #2, Ms. Marvel (2014) #12, Amazing Spider-Man (2015) #3, Mighty Thor (2015) #5, Black Panther (2016) #1, Unbeatable Squirrel Girl (2015b) #7 And Thanos (2016) #1. Celebrate 80 years of Marvel Comics, decade by decade. The blockbuster icons and bold new generation of the trailblazing 2010s! As iconic heroes enjoyed worldwide cinematic success, a diverse array of young champions stole the spotlight! Find your favorite movie stars in outstanding adventures by the best modern creators â€” from Iron Man, Black Panther, Spider-Man and Captain Marvelâ€¦to Thanos! And get to know the new kids on the block â€” Miles Morales; Spider-Gwen; Thor, Goddess of Thunder; the Unbeatable Squirrel Girl; and Kamala Khan, the incomparable Ms. Marvel!', 232),
(784, 'Secret Invasion', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=-rFbDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Stan Lee, John Byrne, Roy Thomas, Roger Stern, Steve Englehart, Brian Reed, Justin Gray, Jimmy Palmiotti, More', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=-rFbDwAAQBAJ&rdid=book--rFbDwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302505288', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-07-25', NULL, 'Collects Fantastic Four (1961) #2, #18 And Annual #19; Avengers (1963) #97 And Annual #14; Silver Surfer (1987) #25; Marvel: The Lost Generation #11; Captain Marvel (2007) #1-5; Ms. Marvel (2006) #25-27; And Material From Fantastic Four (1961) #257; Marvel Westerns: Kid Colt And The Arizona Girl; Avengers: The Initiative Annual #1; And Secret Invasion: Who Do You Trust? Chart the history of the Skrulls Â— from their first visits to Earth to their devastating Secret Invasion! Meet the Super-Skrull who wields all the Fantastic FourÂ’s powers! Witness the Kree/Skrull WarÂ’s cataclysmic climax alongside the Avengers! The legendary Mar-Vell returns from the dead Â— or does he? And Carol Danvers is swept up in the alien intrigue as the SECRET INVASION begins! Plus: 1800s and 1950s infiltration attempts! Galactus targets the Skrull throneworld! The Skrulls lose their shape-shifting powers! And more!', 496),
(785, 'Deadpool Vol. 4', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LRAwiz0TRLIC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Daniel Way', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=LRAwiz0TRLIC&rdid=book-LRAwiz0TRLIC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785179399', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', NULL, NULL, 'Collects Deadpool (2008) #19-22 & Hit-Monkey. Not many people - hero, villain, mercenary or otherwise - are going to upstage the Amazing Spider-Man in a team-up. But Deadpool will have to if he\'ll survive the most dangerous threat he\'s ever faced - Hit-Monkey! Plus: The origin of Hit-Monkey revealed!', 120),
(786, 'Spider-Man Noir', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QiVRAgAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'David Hine', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=QiVRAgAAQBAJ&rdid=book-QiVRAgAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785179474', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2014-01-22', NULL, 'Collects Spider-Man Noir #1-4. It was 1933 and the Great Depression was just getting started. And so was the corrupt mob boss the Goblin. When embittered, angry Peter Parker meets a spider and its life-changing bite, he may have just inherited the force to honor the phrase, \"If those in power can\'t be trusted, it\'s the responsibility of the people to remove them.\"', 112),
(787, 'Thor', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=b-m8WFspskUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Dan Jurgens', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=b-m8WFspskUC&rdid=book-b-m8WFspskUC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785178552', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2011-07-27', NULL, 'For years, Thor lived on Earth as protector, champion and Avenger - endearing himself to the entire world. Having lived a mortal\'s life, Earth\'s well-being was of paramount importance to the Asgardian God of Thunder. His ascension to the throne interfered with that mission. Asgard\'s interests forced Thor to ignore Earth. So wielding a power only the greatest of gods might possess, Asgard\'s liege transported his realm to the skies above Manhattan, the better to guide and protect the whole of humanity. Now, see how the Thunder God\'s presence on Earth affects the lives of people both ordinary and extraordinary and not for the better. Collecting THOR (1998) #59-67 and material from MARVEL DOUBLE-SHOT #1.', 216),
(788, 'The Mighty Captain Marvel Vol. 3', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kKFODwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Margaret Stohl', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=kKFODwAAQBAJ&rdid=book-kKFODwAAQBAJ&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9781302504366', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2018-05-23', NULL, 'Collects Captain Marvel (2017) #125-129. As Captain Marvel, Carol Danvers has traveled to almost every inch of the planet Â— and beyond! Now sheÂ’s heading somewhere uncharted! Join Carol on her new cosmic journey through a realm where up is down...and good is evil! As Carol chases down the the truth about her Kree friend Bean, sheÂ’ll come face to face with the darkest being in this or any galaxy. YouÂ’d think a familiar face would be comforting, but this Peter Quill doesnÂ’t seem to be in a friendly mood. ItÂ’s Carol vs. Peter, and the prize is Â— the Reality Stone! But will the unmatched power of this unearthed artifact be enough to pull Carol back to reality, or is this merely the first step in a much larger quest?', 136),
(789, 'Invincible Iron Man Vol.8', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=pO3V_Uyn7wsC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'Matt Fraction', NULL, 'Comics & Graphic Novels', 'https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=pO3V_Uyn7wsC&rdid=book-pO3V_Uyn7wsC&rdot=1&source=gbs_api', '9780785182771', NULL, 'Marvel Entertainment', '2011-09-14', NULL, 'Why should Tony Stark be the one to benefit from all of his technology? What right does Stark have to keep his miracles to himself? A familiar threat in other corners of the Marvel Universe comes demanding answers - and salvation - from Iron Man. And because it\'s not enough to remake the world with free and limitless energy, Stark Resilient takes on the challenge of remaking another world: Asgard! Plus: Witness Rescue in action, as Pepper Potts lets loose with her bleeding-edge suit and astonishing power! And Iron Man and Thor find themselves facing an enemy unlike any they\'ve fought before! Collecting INVINCIBLE IRON MAN #501-502, FREE COMIC BOOK DAY 2010: IRON MAN/THOR, RESCUE #1 and material from INVINCIBLE IRON MAN #503.', 120);
